mask setting details of the current user, run the \'umask\" command at the command prompt The umask value should be set to \"027\" or \"022\". If the umask value is set to \"027\" , a file is created with the access rights of \"rW-r-- and if the umask value is set to \"022\" , a file is created with the access rights of \"rw-r--r- Therefore, the umask value should be set to \"022 So as not to allow unnecessary access: In SUN, uncomment the UMASK option in the /etc/default/login file and set it to 022. For other UNIX operating systems, add \"Umask 022\" in the .profile','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-18 22:31:02','2025-02-18 22:31:02'),(352,'85','App\\Models\\Section','Text','Setting privileges to the users default configuration file','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-18 22:31:02','2025-02-18 22:31:02'),(353,'168','App\\Models\\Subsection','Tables',NULL,'',5,'67b50a3c8e1ab.png','/storage/tables/67b50a3c8e1ab.png','2025-02-18 22:31:02','2025-02-18 22:31:24'),(354,'168','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','If unnecessary service ports are open, it can cause security vulnerability: Therefore, unused services should be removed. <Table 34  shows a list of daemon services and service ports that should be checked for stopping:','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-18 22:31:02','2025-02-18 22:31:02'),(355,'169','App\\Models\\Subsection','Code',NULL,'',2,'67b50a3c9ea17.png','/storage/code/67b50a3c9ea17.png','2025-02-18 22:31:02','2025-02-18 22:31:24'),(356,'169','App\\Models\\Subsection','Code',NULL,'',2,'67b50a3ca8edc.png','/storage/code/67b50a3ca8edc.png','2025-02-18 22:31:02','2025-02-18 22:31:24'),(357,'169','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','Anonymous FTP allows a malicious user to obtain information about the system: Since various attacks can be made if writing permission is set in the directory, the use of anonymous FTP should be restricted by setting it in such a way that only necessary users can access. Also, secure FTP should be used, rather than FTP with weak security: gain When general FTP by anon