re is a user who processes it, a language that can manipulate and read data in the database, and DBMS software that enables the processing of all data That is, a database system is composed of four attributes: database, database language, user, and database management system (DBMS):','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-18 22:31:04','2025-02-18 22:31:04'),(449,'206','App\\Models\\Subsection','Figures',NULL,'[Figure 2] 3-level database architecture',2,'67b50a3ddcdad.png','/storage/figures/67b50a3ddcdad.png','2025-02-18 22:31:04','2025-02-18 22:31:25'),(450,'206','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','To understand data independence, it is helpful to understand the background to the introduction of the concer of data independence. The opposite of data independence can be defined as data dependency: Here, the subjec of dependency generally refers to an application program. An application is the interface object which interact with users and handles the user requirements. It can be said that data dependency has the purpose of reducin continuously increasing maintenance costs, data complexity, and the number of duplicated data. The concept data independence was also introduced to maintain independence between the screen and the database against th users\' constantly evolving requirements It can be said that data independence is a three-schema architecture, which was proposed by the speciz subcommittee of the X3 committee under the American Standards Institute (ANSI) for the DBMS and its interfaces: The main purpose of this three-schema architecture was to reduce interference in changes by separating th users view of the database from the view by which the database is actually expressed When data independence secured, the independence of each view can be maintained, data can be changed without affecting the view by and different DDL (data definition language) and DML (data manipulation language) can be provided according to th schema by phase laye','',3,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-18 22:31:04','2025-02-18 22:31:04'),(451,'207','App\\Models\\Subsection','Tables',NULL,'',2,'67b50a3dea7aa.png','/storage/tables/67b50a3dea7aa.png','2025-02-18 22:31:04','2025-02-18 22:31:25'),(452,'207','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','The data independence model, which is based on the 3-level database architecture proposed by ANSIJSPARC, presents a model composed of an external phase, a conceptual phase, and an internal phase, none of which interferes with the others','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-18 22:31:04','2025-02-18 22:31:04'),(453,'208','App\\Models\\Subsection','Tables',NULL,'<Table 6  Types of independence',2,'67b50a3e03169.png','/storage/tables/67b50a3e03169.png','2025-02-18 22:31:04','2025-02-18 22:31:26'),(454,'208','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','As the concept of data independence can be separated into these three phases, there are two terms that spec the independence of each area, namely \'logical independence\' and \'physical independence.','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-18 22:31:04','2025-02-18 22:31:04'),(455,'209','App\\Models\\Subsection','Tables',NULL,'<Table 7  Types of mapping',2,'67b50a3e0e021.png','/storage/tables/67b50a3e0e021.png','2025-02-18 22:31:04','2025-02-18 22:31:26'),(456,'209','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','The English word \"mapping\" can be translated into \"sasang\" in Korean, which can be defined as a \"bridge that connects independent concepts\" Broadly speaking, there are two types of mapping in data independence.','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-18 22:31:04','2025-02-18 22:31:04'),(457,'210','App\\Models\\Subsection','Tables',NULL,'',3,'67b50a3e1cb8e.png','/storage/tables/67b50a3e1cb8e.png','2025-02-18 22:31:04','2025-02-18 22:31:26'),(458,'210','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','The DBA takes responsibility for the configuration and overall administration of the database to ensure that the functions of the database system are performed properly:','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-18 22:31:04','2025-02-18 22:31:04'),(459,'211','App\\Models\\Subsection','Tables',NU