and comprises a series of tasks aimed at correcting software errors and improving its functions and performance by modifying the original requirements. Software maintenance is a series of software engineering works that eliminate defects, improve performance, and adapt software to the changed environment after its initial delivery to the customer','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-18 22:31:18','2025-02-18 22:31:18'),(1245,'410','App\\Models\\Section','Text','Software is mainly maintained to improve software performance, repair defects, port software to enable it to run in a new environment,, and consists of a series of preventive measures including correction. As mentioned above, software maintenance is a very important phase in securing the efficiency of the software life cycle for the following reasons. Noticeable increase of maintenance costs that are higher than the existing development costs among the entire software development and maintenance costs. Increased administrative tasks such as documentation due to the complexity of the software Emphasis is placed on the importance of management due to the use period being longer than the development period: Increased maintenance works due to the spread of package development, rather than outsourced development','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-18 22:31:18','2025-02-18 22:31:18'),(1246,'411','App\\Models\\Section','Tables',NULL,'<Table 44  Classification of software maintenance',2,'67b50a48c6c1b.png','/storage/tables/67b50a48c6c1b.png','2025-02-18 22:31:18','2025-02-18 22:31:36'),(1247,'411','App\\Models\\Section','Text','oftware maintenance can be classified according to reason, time, ad target. Sometimes, a contract is signe ccording to these classification criteria.','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-18 22:31:18','2025-02-18 22:31:18'),(1248,'412','App\\Models\\Section','Tables',NULL,'<Table 45  Maintenance procedure',2,'67b50a48d28b1.png','/storage/tables/67b50a48d28b1.png','2025-02-18 22:31:18','2025-02-18 22:31:36'),(1249,'412','App\\Models\\Section','Text','Software is generally maintained in the following order:','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-18 22:31:18','2025-02-18 22:31:18'),(1250,'412','App\\Models\\Section','Text','\"Requirements analysis\" , which is an important activity in the above maintenance sequence, aims to quickly understand how a maintenance request affects the current system  \"Identifying the scope of impact\" may be easy or require tremendous efforts, as described in the example, depending on how easy it is to maintain the software in the existing system: Ease of maintenance is a characteristic that indicates the level of difficulty in maintaining software, and there are the following types. Ease of use: A characteristic that indicates how easy it is to understand an application or program Ease of modification: A characteristic that indicates how easy it is to modify an application or program: Ease of testing: A characteristic that indicates how easy the process is to show the accuracy of an application or program. Therefore, if systematic activities are performed to improve ease of maintenance while developing software, as shown in the following, the requirements of users or customers can be continuously satisfied, and rapidly increasing maintenance costs can be handled economically even in the event of changes in the environment in the future Analysis activities: Determining the customer\'s requirements and constraints, and proving the validity of the product to be developed. Standards and guidelines: Establishing various kinds of standards and guidelines to facilitate software maintenance: Design activities: Emphasizing and making use of clarity, modularity and ease of change Implementation activities: A standard structure and coding style should be applied. Supporting documents: The and test manual required for maintenance activities. guide','',3,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-18 22:31:18','2025-02-18 22:31:18'),(1251,'413','App\\Models\\Section','Tables',NULL,'<Table 47  Types of software maintenance organizations',7,'67b50a48e1fa1.png','/storage/tables/67b50a48e1fa1.png','2025-02-18 22:31:18','2025-02-18 22:31:36'),(1252,'413','App\\Models\\Section','Text','EEEJEIA 12207 defines maintenance personnel as an organization that performs maintenance activities\". The term','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-18 22:31:18','2025-02-18 22:31:18'),(1253,'413','App\\Models\\Section','Text','\"maintenance personnel\" often refers to each individual who performs maintenance activities, so as to distinguish them from developers Maintenance personnel can learn much from developers who have a deep knowledge of the software concerned. If maintenance personnel meet developers or participate in development from the beginning, maintenance can be reduced Sometimes maintenance personnel become perplexed because the software engineer in charge has moved to another job or is out of contact. Maintenance personnel should take over and immediately support the developed product code or document) , and evolve and maintain the developed product throughout the entire software life The table below shows the various subjects for each activity in the general maintenance phase. Each activity subject perform and bears the responsibility for the maintenance activity concerned. The maintenance management committee approves or reiects the maintenance of changes, and finally reviews and approves the applied change (e.g cycle','',4,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-18 22:31:18','2025-02-18 22:31:18'),(1254,'413','App\\Models\\Section','Text','The table below describes the types of software maintenance organizations The \"organization by application field\" is the most frequently type mainly to fields requiring knowledge about the application business applied','',6,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-18 22:31:18','2025-02-18 22:31:18'),(1255,'414','App\\Models\\Section','Text','Open-source software is free software that can be used, copied, and modified by anyone while protecting the rights of the creator As the software industry began to develop, a move was made to impose restrictions on the use and modification of software based on the intellectual property rights and license agreement in 1980. To oppose to this move and protect the rights of free software use, Richard Stallman founded the Free Software Foundation (FSF) and launched the free software movement, which ultimately became the origin of open-source software: Open-source software includes FSF free software in Korea. However, free software pursues the meaning of emphasizing users\' freedom, while open-source software pursues the idea that the source code must be shared for joint research to make software \"better\". The term open-source software was widely used at the time the Open Source Initiative (OSI) was formed in 1998. The OSI manages the promotion and certification of open-source software. The OSI has defined the minimum standard with which the license should comply (Open Source Definition, OSD), and awards an OSI certification mark to open-source software certified by the OSL Server software such as the Apache web server, PHP, MySQL, Hadoop, and Openstack, development tools such as Eclipse and gdb, and operating systems such as Linux are representative types of open-source software. ver software such as the Apache web server, PHP, MySQL, Hadoop, and Openstack, development tools such Eclipse and gdb, and operating systems such as Linux are representative types of open-source software.','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-18 22:31:19','2025-02-18 22:31:19'),(1256,'415','App\\Models\\Section','Text','An open-source software license reters to an agreement made between an open-source developer and a user on the method of use and the scope of the conditions of use. Open-source software should be used by protecting and preserving the rights of the creator and complying with the conditions set by the open-source developer: If the user violates these conditions, the user must assume legal responsibility for violation of the license and infringement of the copyright. Representative licenses include the General Public License (GPL), Lesser General Public License (LGPL) , Berkeley Software Distribution (BSD) , and Mozilla Public License (MPL): These open-source licenses have been created and imposed to force disclosure of the source code within the legal boundaries:','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-18 22:31:19','2025-02-18 22:31:19'),(1257,'416','App\\Models\\Section','Figures',NULL,'[Figure 27] Obligations of the open-source software license',4,'67b50a48ed35b.png','/storage/figures/67b50a48ed35b.png','2025-02-18 22:31:19','2025-02-18 22:31:36'),(1258,'416','App\\Models\\Section','Text','We need to understand the scope of using open-source software before understanding the license classification. Obligations are not imposed when open-source software is used internally, rather, they ar applied only when open-source software is distributed and sold outside:','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-18 22:31:19','2025-02-18 22:31:19'),(1259,'592','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','GPL 2.0 is the license most frequently adopted for open-source software. It was created and distributed by Free Software Foundation (FSF) and is very strict compared to other open-source software licenses The ma matters to be observed are as follows. When distributing software, the distributor should specify the copyright notice, distribution under the GPL, and the absence of warranty liability for GPL software When modifying software or new software (both static and dynamic linking), the source code must be opened in accordance with the GPL. When distributing its own patented program,, a distributor cannot receive royalties from users Who use the program under the GPL. linking','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-18 22:31:19','2025-02-18 22:31:19'),(1260,'593','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','The basic contents of GPL 3.0 are similar to those of GPL 2.0, but it has been supplemented with matters related to DRM (Digital Rights Management, technology and service to protect copyrights)  software patent issues, and compatibility issues. The main matters to comply with are as follows. When including the source code under GPL 3.0 in the users product or distributing it with the users product, installation information should be provided with the source code The interests related to DRM, which are protected by the laws of each country, should be waived. If a contributor has improved the source code, that contributor should provide a license stating that hishher contribution is non-discriminatory and does not require any fee with regard to the patent.','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-18 22:31:19','2025-02-18 22:31:19'),(1261,'594','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','The LGPL enables users to use some libraries in a way that the source code can be used in a more eased form than the GPL. If a strict license such as the GPL is applied, commercial software developers will be reluctant to use the open-source library because have to open the source code of the software that uses the library: In other words, the LGPL is designed to encourage the use of an open-source library from a strategic point of view: The main matters to comply with are as follows they When linking an application program with the LGPL (both static and dynamic linking) , developers do not have to open the source code of the application program concerned. The patent is handled in the same way as the GPL library','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-18 22:31:19','2025-02-18 22:31:19'),(1262,'595','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','The BSD license is a representative open software license that does not require the developer to disclose the software source code. The scope of BSD license permission is wide because projects deployed with the BSD license have been implemented using the financial resources provided by the U.S. government: As the software was for with the taxes of U.S. citizens in advance, people can use or create the software in the way want. The main matters to comply with are as follows. paid they When distributing the software, copyright notice and absence of warranty should be specified: The source code can be used for commercial software without limitations because there is no obligation to disclose the source code of the modified program.','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-18 22:31:19','2025-02-18 22:31:19'),(1263,'596','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','The Apache license is applicable to all software of the Apache Software Foundation (ASF)  including the Apache web server: Like the BSD license, it does not require disclosure of the source code. The main matters to comply with are as follows. The trademark right for the name \"Apache\" should not be violated When distributing the software, copyright notice and absence of warranty should be specified. The code distributed under the Apache license can be combined with the code distributed under the GPL 3.0. The source code can be used for commercial software without limitations because there is no obligation to disclose the source code of the modified program.','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-18 22:31:19','2025-02-18 22:31:19'),(1264,'597','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','The MPL was developed to disclose the source code of the Netscape browser It defines the scope of the source code to be disclosed more clearly: The modified part of the MPL code itself should be distributed under the MBL again, but there is no obligation of disclosure if the modified part is combined with other codes or if new codes are written The main matters to comply with are as follows When distributing the software, copyrights, no warranty, and distribution under the MPL should be specified. The part that modified the MPL code should be distributed under the MPL again. When the MPL code and another code are combined, the source code for the combined program excluding the MPL code does not have to be disclosed.','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-18 22:31:19','2025-02-18 22:31:19'),(1265,'417','App\\Models\\Section','Text','Open-source software licenses have common characteristics such as free use, distribution without restrictions, source code acquisition, and source code modification However, there are some differences with each license regarding the obligation to disclose secondary works and the combination of open source with proprietary software. The GPL is the most stringent license, which specifies the condition that combining GPL code with proprietary software is not allowed, When a program is distributed under the GPL, which combines proprietary software code and the GPL code, the proprietary software code must also be opened. again,','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-18 22:31:19','2025-02-18 22:31:19'),(1266,'418','App\\Models\\Section','Text','lividual enterprises should clearly understand the advantages and disadvantages of using open-sourc tware before an open-source software license. using The major advantages are as tollows: The initial development cost is low because the source code can be downloaded from the web, and modified and redistributed free of Technology can be developed quickly and flexibly as the latest technical information, problems, and solutions are shared between communities Interoperability between different software is guaranteed because the open format or protocol are mainly used. Open source programs are relatively stable compare to proprietary programs because many outstanding developers are participating in development charge: The major disadvantages are as follows: Documents are not as systematic as those of commercial programs. The development roadmap is not systematic because the source code is developed on the web freely basec on voluntary participation. To utilize open-source software, the future development plan of the software concerned needs to be considered. Generally, it is required that open-source software should be distributed without a patent royalty:','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-18 22:31:19','2025-02-18 22:31:19'),(1267,'598','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','Integrated development environment software supports all tasks related to programs and development, such as coding, debugging, compilation, and deployment, in one unified program development environment: It has been highlighted as a development tool capable of meeting the calls of open source and global IT companies for rapid development This environment is evolving into a cloud-based one, such as Codenvy, GoormIDE, and Cloud9, which enables development regardless of the location and does not require the installation of an integrated development program:','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-18 22:31:19','2025-02-18 22:31:19'),(1268,'599','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','Performance management tools, requirements management tools, issue management tools, etc. that support development were designed to manage specific purposes and specific steps. Since the introduction of the cloud, it has been evolving into a tool that encompasses development/test/operation due to the complexity of the infrastructure and the market environment, which demands ever faster IT services. The main purpose of the performance management tool was to prevent application delays and improve performance Recently, such tools have been integrated with ALM, which detects changed codes and manages the changes, and supports build/distribution comprehensively:','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-18 22:31:19','2025-02-18 22:31:19'),(1269,'600','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','JavaScript is one of the most popular and powerful programming languages in the world. It is often used to make an interactive web page by adding some effects to a web page, creating a game, animation, or down menu, ad effectively controlling the web interface This programming language is basically useful for front-end development and is used by 88% of all websites drop- Recently, TypeScript has been highlighted as an extended version of JavaScript TypeScript is an open source project created by Microsoft in 2012, and is used as the base language of Angular features of TypeScript Key _ \'Jp~- \'Pt It includes the functions of JavaScript as it is based on JavaScript: It is a  static type\" language that checks types at the time of compilation It offers ease of compilation in all browsers and environments, making it highly useful. It enables easy coding and learning because everything is a class or component. It is applicable to large-size application programs','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-18 22:31:19','2025-02-18 22:31:19'),(1270,'601','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','Java is an object-oriented programming language and has become the most widely used language in web development. The newly released Java 9 includes about 90 new features. features of Java 9 Increased modularization enables optimization in small devices, and the scalability and performance of Java have been improved. The Ahead of Time (AOT) compilation function,, which compiles the code before execution in a virtual system, reduces the startup time of the application program. REPL (Real Eval Print Loop) is supported, which enables the reception of feedback on the program before compilation Key','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-18 22:31:19','2025-02-18 22:31:19'),(1271,'602','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','Kotlin is a functional programming language developed by JetBrain, the creator of Android Studio. It quickly gained in popularity after Google adopted it as the official programming language for Android in 2017. Kotlin provides a optimal environment for application development based on Android, as it is simple offers excellent performance yet Key features of Kotlin Key Tcaluicd Ui ioc| Compatible with the existing Android APIs, and an app can be developed using concise syntax Very similar to Java, thus allowing Java developers to use Kotlin quickly and easily:','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-18 22:31:19','2025-02-18 22:31:19'),(1272,'603','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','Swift was developed by Apple to support application development for its products such as iOS, macOS watchOS, and tvOS. It was designed to support easier and faster development on its platform. Aey \'culuics i O Easy to develop an app owing to the simple coding process, while providing excellent performance Interactive and easy to understand:','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-18 22:31:19','2025-02-18 22:31:19'),(1273,'604','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','Angular4 was developed by Google, and uses the JavaScript framework for maintenance. Angular4 is used for single-page application programs and responds to user requests quickly by extending the HTML DOM Angular is a single page application (SPA) framework, which means that a view page can be retrieved and used dynamically without having to change the address of the page when executing the web page. features of Angular4 Created using TypeScript 2.1, which is helpful when making a small application. Key - Supports program logic and the backend binding function, and is not a simple static web page','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-18 22:31:19','2025-02-18 22:31:19'),(1274,'605','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','React is a JavaScript library created by Facebook to develop the Facebook web Like Backbonejs and Angula React provides a web front framework needed for developing a app. React is useful when building a large scale application that changes web pages frequently: Key features of React Supports the writing of the markup code in JavaScript using extended JavaScript syntax, which enables the existing XML called JSX (JavaScript XML): Supports components in individual view units that constitute the user interface Allows data processing using the Virtual DOM','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-18 22:31:19','2025-02-18 22:31:19'),(1275,'606','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','Express is the web application framework of Nodejs, which is small and flexible and provides optimal features needed to develop a web or application: Express supports fast web development for Nodejs Nodejs is back-end server development language based on events, which uses the JavaScript engine of Google s Chrome V8. ~J A CApC Enables processing of the dynamic view of HTML pages depending on the parameters passed to the template Combines necessary functions only by supporting a middleware structure written in JavaScript code','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-18 22:31:19','2025-02-18 22:31:19'),(1276,'607','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','The microservice architecture allows independent development, build, test, deployment, monitoring, routing and extension for each service, by dividing one large application into several small services and creating an individual data repository, and by creating an independent execution environment: Prompt response to rapid business changes, deployment within a short period of time, easy improvement and modification are all possible features of the microservice architecture Development productivity is high as a service is divided into small units and developed independently: Flexible deployment in units rather than deployment of the whole set. A system can be expanded elaborately by expanding the units independently: Key -','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-18 22:31:19','2025-02-18 22:31:19'),(1277,'608','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','Docker is an open-source platform that automates the Linux container (LXC) technology, which provides an independent and isolated space like a virtual machine, for ease of use A company called Dot Cloud (now Docker) has started providing technical support for the first time, while Google is preparing Docker configuration for enterprises by implementing an open source project called \"Kubernetes\" . Docker can create a virtualization environment that is much lighter than hypervisor-based virtualization, supports server virtualization, and enables the user to develop an application regardless of the development language or tool. Key features of Docker Makes it easy to package, distribute, and manage an application developed using a container: Files and set values needed for container execution are included using an image. Allows simple and fast development configuration regardless of the infrastructure requirements Supports multiple cloud platforms.','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-18 22:31:19','2025-02-18 22:31:19'),(1278,'423','App\\Models\\Section','Text','the words of six senior US intelligence officials on the Ath (local time) , Bloomberg reported tha hacking microchip, that was not in the design, was found on the server mainboard of a well-known ser manufacturer, Super micro, and that the Chinese Government was allegedly involved (Courca httn\" Ilit chocun com Icite IdataIhtml dir/2018/10/05/2018100502710 Citing There is not a moment in our daily lives when we do not use the services provided by computer systems. With the wide-spread use of smartphones, we are spending even more time with computer systems. In such an environment, Chinese hacking chips can expose our lives to hackers This hacking chip was found on a computer system\'s board. It contains stolen key US information through hardware hacking, which is more threatening than software hacking: This chip has the capability to steal information a computer over a network How can such a small chip contain this function? While the early computer, ENIAC, was the size of a building, computers have become drastically smaller since then, and the computing power of smartphones that we carry in our hand is so high, that it is not even comparable to that of ENIAC. It is necessary to learn the system architecture to understand the concept of a computer system: from tiny','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 13:46:11','2025-02-19 13:46:11'),(1279,'609','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','An information is a that uses information technology (IT): The information system provides services a computer, and a computer operates with combination of hardware and software. Implementing an information system used inside an enterprise, or provided as a service to users, requires the design and construction of IT infrastructures, such as hardware and software design and development, Software designs the software components and operations, such as the connection of the software components and constraints based on software architecture Hardware, like software, designs and develops the hardware architecture System architecture refers to the architecture for a to provide services, based on hardware and software architecture In a broader definition, it refers to all architecture, including the application architecture (AA), data architecture (DA), and technical architecture (TA), for constructing an information system A narrow definition refers to the document that defines the configuration and relationship of hardware, such as a server, storage, network and security, and certain software parts, such as OS and middleware system system using system','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 13:46:11','2025-02-19 13:46:11'),(1280,'610','App\\Models\\Subsection','Tables',NULL,'',4,'67b5e0b219490.png','/storage/tables/67b5e0b219490.png','2025-02-19 13:46:11','2025-02-19 13:46:27'),(1281,'610','App\\Models\\Subsection','Figures',NULL,'[Figure 1] Definition of System Architecture',2,'67b5e0b36d87a.png','/storage/figures/67b5e0b36d87a.png','2025-02-19 13:46:11','2025-02-19 13:46:27'),(1282,'610','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','Definition as defined by the International Council on Systems Engineering (INCOSE) The fundamental and unifying system structure defined in terms of system elements, interfaces, processes, constraints, and behaviors.','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 13:46:11','2025-02-19 13:46:11'),(1283,'610','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','DIUau uemii itui ui syslemii aiciilecluie A system architecture is a document that defines the structure of an information system provided to support the business process required to achieve the objective of an enterprise. A system architecture is divided into TA which defines the structure of hardware, such as a server, network, ad security, as well as the distributed structure of middleware operating on the hardware, DA, which defines the data structure to assure data integrity, and AA, which defines the software components and the relationship and constraints of said defined components Narrow detinition of system architecture A system architecture refers to the structure of an information system, which includes principles and guidelines that define the components, such as hardware, software, security, interactions, and constraints. In other words, it refers to TA and defines the layout and connection mode of the middleware, such as the DB server and WAS, to distribute the application programs of the developed and hardware, such as a server, storage, and network The following table shows the types of detailed architecture defined in system architecture system','',3,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 13:46:11','2025-02-19 13:46:11'),(1284,'611','App\\Models\\Subsection','Figures',NULL,'[Figure 2] Information System Components',2,'67b5e0b37abcf.png','/storage/figures/67b5e0b37abcf.png','2025-02-19 13:46:11','2025-02-19 13:46:27'),(1285,'611','App\\Models\\Subsection','Figures',NULL,'[Figure 3] Storage Type According to Connection Method',4,'67b5e0b3888ad.png','/storage/figures/67b5e0b3888ad.png','2025-02-19 13:46:11','2025-02-19 13:46:27'),(1286,'611','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','System components are a configuration of items to provide the functions of information system services include a server that provides the computing power of an information system, storage that stores the data, a network that provides communication between each component, such as a server and storage, and security to provide confidentiality, integrity, and availability of the information system: The detailed components include computer hardware, OS, and middleware operating on physical server The following diagram shows the details of each component They','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 13:46:11','2025-02-19 13:46:11'),(1287,'611','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','A server provides the computing power of an information system. The information system uses this computing power to process the business logic and data by running the application programs. Server components include the stacked structures of the computer\'s hardware, OS, middleware, and application programs.  The system architecture design defines the server capacity, count, layout, and role, and the network facilitates communication between the servers. Mainframes, Unix servers, and x86 servers are the most commonly used server types, and the x86 servers using Intel CPUs have been used more often as the cloud services expand For example, the servers of an information system providing web services include a webserver that responds to user requests through a web browser organizes web pages, ad provides a screen to display the contents to users, web application server (WAS) that processes business logic, according to the user request ad delivers the results to a database server for storage, or to a WAS for display, ad a database server that creates, requests, modifies, and deletes data. A network connects the information system components for communication Network devices process communication between servers, between servers and storage units ad between the enterprise\'s internal and external networks. A networks devices ad roles vary, based on the OSI layer 7 standard. Network devices include switches, routers, load balancers (L4/L7 load balancers) , and bridges. Additionally, AP (access point) is used in wireless networks There is an overlap between the network domain and the security domain: Since most of the hacking attacks intrude through the network the internal network (LAN) connected to the external network (WAN) , is protected by a security device. gate, A storage system holds the data of an information system. It is categorized into three types according to how it stores data. Block storage saves data in fixed block units, like 16KB and 64KB. It stores the OS, such as MS Windows, Linux, and Unix File storage saves data in file units, instead of in fixed blocks. Network attached storage (NAS), widely used as the shared file repository, is a type of file storage Object storage saves data in object units, instead of in fixed blocks or files. It is mostly used in cloud storage Storage types can also be categorized by their connection method. Direct access storage (DAS) is mounted in each server, NAS is connected through a network and storage area network (SAN) is connected through the network used exclusively for storage DAS can only be used with a filesystem and includes IDE, SATA, and SAS. SAN is provided to the OS through an SAN network ad it requires the creation of a filesystem before it can be used as DAS. It includes SAN, iSCSI, and FCoE. NAS becomes usable after it is mounted to the OS.It includes NFS, CIFS, and AFS.','',3,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 13:46:11','2025-02-19 13:46:11'),(1288,'611','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','Occunily Information security is configured through the network connection. Some security hardware is installed between the external Internet section and the internal network to protect the internal systems while some are installed in the internal network It includes the DDoS defense system to defend against DDoS attacks, firewalls to protect the system through monitoring logging, ad blocking network traffic, and IPSJIDS to prevent abnormal traffic or abuse. It also includes web firewalls protect webservers by logging, monitoring, blocking web service traffic, and access control solutions to provide management functions that allow or to deny access to servers','',5,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 13:46:11','2025-02-19 13:46:11'),(1289,'426','App\\Models\\Section','Text','Various ways of configuring a system are provided. System configuration is changing in various ways, according to the changes in hardware ad software technology, &d the changes to the user environment: As the use of mobile devices, such as smartphones, has recently increased, most systems provide services based on the system architecture centered around a web service: Moreover, the system layout is also changing into a centralized structure, as the cloud services have expanded','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 13:46:11','2025-02-19 13:46:11'),(1290,'612','App\\Models\\Subsection','Figures',NULL,'[Figure 4] Centralized Architecture',2,'67b5e0b3940b9.png','/storage/figures/67b5e0b3940b9.png','2025-02-19 13:46:11','2025-02-19 13:46:27'),(1291,'612','App\\Models\\Subsection','Figures',NULL,'[Figure 5] Multi-region Distributed System Architecture',4,'67b5e0b3a3363.png','/storage/figures/67b5e0b3a3363.png','2025-02-19 13:46:11','2025-02-19 13:46:27'),(1292,'612','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','A centralized architecture stores and operates the system ad data from an integrated center It configures an integrated database on a large-capacity server and it has a relatively simple configuration. Having an integrated database makes it easy to assure data integrity, and having all components in one place makes them convenient to manage and operate. It can also quickly respond to system failures. However all business services are terminated if the integrated center fails. Moreover, the load is concentrated during time system peak','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 13:46:11','2025-02-19 13:46:11'),(1293,'612','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','Multi-region distributed system architecture The multi-region distributed architecture operates the systems, and the application systems are distributed regionally: Each region manages the distributed data using small or medium-sized servers. This structure can reduce the load of each server, since it distributes the user load. When there is a failure, only the regional business services are terminated. However the distributed databases make it difficult to manage the data integrity, and both the svstem configuration and management become complex','',3,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 13:46:11','2025-02-19 13:46:11'),(1294,'427','App\\Models\\Section','Text','Architecture types can be classified according to the information system layout The centralized architecture arranges all the systems in a centralized place. Multi-region distributed architecture operates the system by distributing regional and application systems regionally:','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 13:46:11','2025-02-19 13:46:11'),(1295,'613','App\\Models\\Subsection','Figures',NULL,'[Figure 6] Client-Server Architecture',2,'67b5e0b3b10de.png','/storage/figures/67b5e0b3b10de.png','2025-02-19 13:46:11','2025-02-19 13:46:27'),(1296,'613','App\\Models\\Subsection','Figures',NULL,'[Figure 7] Web System Architecture',4,'67b5e0b3bdfd4.png','/storage/figures/67b5e0b3bdfd4.png','2025-02-19 13:46:11','2025-02-19 13:46:27'),(1297,'613','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','The architecture places system functions in the servers and clients ad configures them to use the service, depending on the business size or environment: The server and client\'s role differs, depending on where the system functions, such as data management, business processes, and presentation, are located. It can provide the convenience of a graphical user interface by running the application program from the client side: However, the configuration is complex ad the development and management are difficult because the architecture is separated into servers and clients Service types include games chatting, messenger FTP servers, and terminal servers','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 13:46:11','2025-02-19 13:46:11'),(1298,'613','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','WVCd syslemn aici iecluie The architecture runs the server s application programs, and the client uses the service with a web browser: It generally consists of a webserver, a web application server, and a database server The middleware assures stable performance,, and the program reusability is high. Although the web system architecture was limited by only providing web services with a static display, the introduction of HTML5, and the performance enhancement of PC environments, have enabled them to provide services in an impressive GUI environment: Most recent information systems use web system architecture The client can use all the services with a PC or mobile device, if the environment runs a web browser','',3,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 13:46:11','2025-02-19 13:46:11'),(1299,'429','App\\Models\\Section','Tables',NULL,'',2,'67b5e0b3d3a41.png','/storage/tables/67b5e0b3d3a41.png','2025-02-19 13:46:11','2025-02-19 13:46:27'),(1300,'429','App\\Models\\Section','Figures',NULL,'[Figure 8] Types of Information System Architectures Tier',4,'67b5e0b3efffc.png','/storage/figures/67b5e0b3efffc.png','2025-02-19 13:46:11','2025-02-19 13:46:27'),(1301,'429','App\\Models\\Section','Text','The function and role of each system component are classified by tier or layer The most widely known layer is the OSI 7 \'layer which shows the network structure: Layers and tiers are considered similar concepts because they both represent functions and rules in a tiered structure. The most common difference is that layers refer to structures from a logical point of view, and tiers refer to structures from a physical perspective An information system is divided into a presentation layer, a business logic layer, and a data layer This logical layer architecture can be divided into an N-tier structure as a physical system architecture The typical N-tier structures are a two-tier structure and a three- tior ctri','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 13:46:11','2025-02-19 13:46:11'),(1302,'429','App\\Models\\Section','Text','WO-ter arcnitecture Two-tier architecture stores and processes data in the server and processes business logic and presentation for the Two-tier architecture stores and processes data in the server and processes business logic and presentation for the client It is generally the same structure as the client-server architecture Since the client processes most logic, it can be fast ad easily implemented when the number of users is small However, the performance becomes poor as the number of users increases, and the architecture is disadvantageous in terms of scalability, reusability, and resource use. Actual cases include application implemented with 4GL tools, such as PowerBuilder Visual Basic, and Delphi:','',3,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 13:46:11','2025-02-19 13:46:11'),(1303,'429','App\\Models\\Section','Text','ee-lel aiclileclule Three-tier architecture is a structure created to overcome the limitations of two-tier architecture, and it is also called multi-tier architecture This structure has an additional tier between the presentation tier and the data tier, in order to process business logic to be flexible ad scalable The problems of two-tier structures include security problems due to the clients\' ability to access the database through the network, the difficulty of user authority management, and the difficulty of changing programs: In three-tier architecture, the client does not have database access information. It is easy to manage the database object reference authority through the application server The distribution of the separate presentation tier becomes flexible: However, the development environment is complex, and the cost increases because of the need to procure middleware and additional hardware','',5,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 13:46:11','2025-02-19 13:46:11'),(1304,'430','App\\Models\\Section','Figures',NULL,'[Figure 9] Information System Server\'s Stack Structure',2,'67b5e0b40bf1d.png','/storage/figures/67b5e0b40bf1d.png','2025-02-19 13:46:11','2025-02-19 13:46:28'),(1305,'430','App\\Models\\Section','Text','\"Server\" refers to a computer or program that provides information or services to users through a network It provides the computer power needed for the information system services. The concept of the server was created when IBM started making a server called the mainframe: The term mainframe refers to a steel enclosure, like a cabinet, large that houses the CPU ad the main memory: The mainframe features excellent stability and performance, but it is very expensive because a enterprise made all the elements from the CPU to OS, the development language, and the application programs. The mainframe began downsizing gradually in 1997 when the attention to super Unix servers, such as HP, Sun, and Silicon Graphics, increased. Downsizing refers to replacing a mainframe server with a super Unix server While Unix servers were generally equipped with a Power CPU, it is worth noting that more mid- to large-sized servers began featuring Pentium CPU in the server market in 1997. It was around this time that Windows NT servers, using Intel CPU, were on the sharp rise: Twenty years later, in 2017,x86 servers, featuring Intel CPU, are dominating the Unix server market  Currently, the server market is divided into x86 servers ad non-x86 servers Although the market is divided into two major server types in terms of sales,x86 servers account for more than 70% when comparing the number of server units sold. This server has a stack structure The computer hardware, consisting of a CPU, main memory, and auxiliary memory is at the bottom An OS that abstracts computer hardware and provides services to software is located above it On top of the OS, middleware, such as a webserver, WAS, and DBMS server to support the flexibility of convenient expansion, as well as the reduction of application programs ad independence of computer hardware, is located. Application programs provide services to users this middleware using','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 13:46:11','2025-02-19 13:46:11'),(1306,'431','App\\Models\\Section','Tables',NULL,'',2,'67b5e0b418756.png','/storage/tables/67b5e0b418756.png','2025-02-19 13:46:11','2025-02-19 13:46:28'),(1307,'431','App\\Models\\Section','Figures',NULL,'[Figure 10] ENIAC, the First Electronic Vacuum Tube Computer',4,'67b5e0b44dc1b.png','/storage/figures/67b5e0b44dc1b.png','2025-02-19 13:46:11','2025-02-19 13:46:28'),(1308,'431','App\\Models\\Section','Text','While some argue that an abacus used in calculations in ancient times is the origin of computers, the Machine, devised by the English mathematician Allen Turing in 1936, is generally regarded as the beginning of modern computers  This Machine proved the mathematical concepts and calculation processes. Afterward, ENIAC, created in 1946, is known as the first programmable general-purpose computer Using 18,000 vacuum tubes, it weighed 30 tons and was literally as large as a house. Later, EDSAC, the first computer that embedded the program Turing Turing','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 13:46:11','2025-02-19 13:46:11'),(1309,'431','App\\Models\\Section','Text','in a memory unit, as proposed by John von Neumann, was developed in 1949. While computers were mostly usec for military purposes in the past,, the popularization of computers began in the 1980s when a PC, developed by IBM_ and the Windows operating system, developed by MS, were successful: In recent years, mobile computers installed smartphones have become popular and opened the era of handheld computers','',3,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 13:46:11','2025-02-19 13:46:11'),(1310,'614','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','Application programs, such as web (HTTP) , DNS, telnet, FTP, and email sendinglreceiving (SMTPIPOPBJIMAP4) , allow access to services on other layers In the OSI reference model, this layer\'s concept includes the presentation layer and the session layer','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 13:46:12','2025-02-19 13:46:12'),(1311,'615','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','Also called the host-to-host transport layer the transport layer is responsible for data exchange between abstract ports, managed by application programs such as TCP, UDP and SCTP protocols It is equivalent to the transport layer in the OSI reference layer','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 13:46:12','2025-02-19 13:46:12'),(1312,'616','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','Also called the network layer, it is responsible for addressing ad routing functions. It is equivalent to the network layer in the OSI reference layer','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 13:46:12','2025-02-19 13:46:12'),(1313,'617','App\\Models\\Subsection','Figures',NULL,'[Figure 14] TCPIIP Protocol Layers: Based on the ARPANET Reference Model [10]',2,'67b5e0b474a74.png','/storage/figures/67b5e0b474a74.png','2025-02-19 13:46:12','2025-02-19 13:46:28'),(1314,'617','App\\Models\\Subsection','Figures',NULL,'[Figure 15] Example of Network Protocol Header and Data Configuration',4,'67b5e0b487ffc.png','/storage/figures/67b5e0b487ffc.png','2025-02-19 13:46:12','2025-02-19 13:46:28'),(1315,'617','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','Also called the network access layer, the network interface layer has the role of actually sending and receiving TCPIIF packets through physical media, such as IEEE 802.3 and IEEE 802.11 WiFi. It includes the data link layer responsible fo the MAC function in the OSI reference model, as well as the physical layer that defines electric signals','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 13:46:12','2025-02-19 13:46:12'),(1316,'617','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','As shown in [Figure 13], these protocols specify communication with the same protocol layers of other hosts connected through a network For communication, a header for the exchanging of data between protocols of the same layer with data downloaded the layer immediately above are generally required. As shown in [Figure 15], an application layer can transmit the user data through a transport protocol TCP (or UDP), which is an end-to-end protocol connected to the other host: It requires a TCP header (or UDP header): The transmission of user data, including a TCP header, uses IP which is a network layer protocol that has routing information to the network of the other host, and the IP head has the information The network considers both the TCP header and the user data received from the transport layer as data. The data link protocol, which has the necessary information for physical delivery to other hosts in the same network mostly uses Ethemet: In that case, both the TCP header ad the user data, including the Etheret header with the necessary information and the IP header downloaded from the network layer, are regarded as data. It should be noted that laver uces Onlv the header that correcnonds to the oiven fiinction from layer each','',3,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 13:46:12','2025-02-19 13:46:12'),(1317,'618','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','IP address: The IP address is the address system of the network layer to transfer datagram between two hosts/ routers It facilitates data to be transferred from the source node to the destination node, through multiple Internet networks While the MAC address is a physical address, the IP address is a logical address. Existing IP addresses, or','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 13:46:12','2025-02-19 13:46:12'),(1318,'619','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','Pv4 addresses based on the 32-bit address system, faced exhaustion as Internet use increased rapidly worldwide Ilthough the IPv6 address system based on 128 bits was introduced to solve the problem, IPv4 addresses are nainly used Although the IANA (Internet Assigned Numbers Authority) was responsible for IP address allocation in the ast, the ICANN (International Corporation for Assigned Names and Numbers) is currently in charge still','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 13:46:12','2025-02-19 13:46:12'),(1319,'620','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','Port number: The port number used to transfer messages between two processes (running applications) is responsible for the connection between the web browser on user As computer, shown in [Figure 10], and the webserver program on my.servercom: The 16-bit number system can identify up to 65,535 application programs. The port numbers from 0 to 1023 are called well-known ports and are allocated by the IANA Application programs, such as telnet and email, use it for sending and receiving data: The port numbers 1024 to 49,151 are called registration and, like well- known ports, are mostly used by servers. The Internet chatting protocol, IRC (TCP port number 6667), and Git version control system (TCP port number 9418) are examples The port numbers from 49,152 to 65,535 are mostly used as a temporary number by clients, and are called dynamic ports or temporary ports. from ports','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 13:46:12','2025-02-19 13:46:12'),(1320,'434','App\\Models\\Section','Text','S is a system software that provides a computer resource interface to users or application programs by efficiently nanaging the limited resources of computer hardware \"he first computers were set to operate single-purpose programs, as did not have an OS. The programs they ran slowly and were difficult to develop in this torm, since the developer needed to implement every intertace tor accessing the computers resources and allocating and recovering resources: OS implements input, control, memory, operation, and output functions to provide services in order to use computer resources efficiently: In other words, an OS controls the computers resources ad implements usage policies to allocate resources to users through scheduling: It exchanges data through inputfoutput devices, or outputs exceptions or errors. The purposes of using the operating system are as follows Abstraction: Provides standardized API to application programs by abstracting the complexity of the computers hardware. Virtualization: Provides a virtualization function to enable application programs and users to share computer resources, and to use a single virtual computer hardware Management: Maximizes computer resource performances and provides them to application programs, while','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 13:46:13','2025-02-19 13:46:13'),(1321,'622','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','In simple terms, a process is a running program: However it is actually more than just a program, as a process is & system work unit that allocates, uses, and recovers various resources, such as the CPU, storage unit, and input/ output units to perform its tasks An OS manages processes and performs the following tasks: Creating and disposing of user and svstem processes files, In Simpie lerms, & process IS & runniing progrram, hiowevel, Il IS aclually More lan just & PIe system work unit that allocates, uses, and recovers various resources, such as the CPU, stora output units to perform its tasks An OS manages processes and performs the following task Creating and disposing of user and system processes Terminating and re-running processes Providing a technique for process communication and synchronization Providing techniaues to prevent deadlock','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 13:46:13','2025-02-19 13:46:13'),(1322,'623','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','A hard disk (HDD) is the hardware that most people think of when consider a storage unit. However the main memory is a different type of storage. The main memory is a depository that allows the CPU to fetch commands and data to use the instructions, The addresses that the CPU uses to access data are only available in the main memory: Even if the CPU intends to retrieve data in an HDD, it cannot read the data if it is not stored in the main memory The main memory must handle the following management functions to provide data to the CPU: Tracking and managing the space and the users that use the storage device they from','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 13:46:13','2025-02-19 13:46:13'),(1323,'624','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','OS can store data through various physical devices. It is necessary to abstract media with different physical characteristics such as magnetic tape, magnetic disks optical disks, and flash memory, for the OS to use them: File management provides the function of abstracting these physical characteristics into files, the logical storage units It handles the following tasks: Creating and disposing of files Creating and disposing of the directory Providing primitive files and directory management Mapping for the OS to use the file in the auxiliary memory unit Storing the file in a nonvolatile storage medium','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 13:46:13','2025-02-19 13:46:13'),(1324,'625','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','The OS helps users use a device, even if do not know its characteristics Here, a device refers to an input/output device and includes a mouse, keyboard, printer, and speaker Users can easily use these devices with the functions provided by the OS. they \'','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 13:46:13','2025-02-19 13:46:13'),(1325,'626','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','The volume of data used by a computer system is growing larger, from gigabytes and even to terabytes However the data used by a computer\'s CPU is that which is in the main memory unit: The main memory does not provide the capacity at the terabyte level. The OS hands the following auxiliary memory unit management function to store the managed data: Empty space management The volume of data used by a comput the data used by a computer\'s CPU is capacity at the terabyte level. The OS managed data: Empty space management Storage allocation Disk scheduling','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 13:46:13','2025-02-19 13:46:13'),(1326,'627','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','distributed system is a set of memory units or separate processors Each processor communicates at a high spee rough the network The network integrates scattered computer resources into a system to improve the calculatic eed, share data, and to enhance reliability:','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 13:46:13','2025-02-19 13:46:13'),(1327,'628','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','command-interpreter is one of the programs that enables users to access the main OS function MS-DOS of UNIX shell, a user can enter a command with a keyboard in order to run an OS function system system','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 13:46:13','2025-02-19 13:46:13'),(1328,'435','App\\Models\\Section','Text','OS abstracts and virtualizes computer hardware to provide resources to application programs, or to manage ther efficiently: Therefore, OS can be understood by the functions of managing main hardware components. The mair functions of OS are described as follows','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 13:46:13','2025-02-19 13:46:13'),(1329,'436','App\\Models\\Section','Tables',NULL,'',2,'67b5e0b4a0d6b.png','/storage/tables/67b5e0b4a0d6b.png','2025-02-19 13:46:13','2025-02-19 13:46:28'),(1330,'629','App\\Models\\Subsection','Figures',NULL,'[Figure 16] Process Status Change',2,'67b5e0b4b7a47.png','/storage/figures/67b5e0b4b7a47.png','2025-02-19 13:46:13','2025-02-19 13:46:28'),(1331,'629','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','A process has a distinct process status during its lifecycle, as shown in [Figure 16]','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 13:46:13','2025-02-19 13:46:13'),(1332,'629','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','Created: A process is created but is not running by the OS. Preparing: The process is waiting for the CPU allocation to run:','',3,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 13:46:13','2025-02-19 13:46:13'),(1333,'632','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','Kunning: ine process nas tne CPU allocaion: Finished: The process has completed its running, and the CPU allocation is released Standby: The process ran after getting the CPU allocation, and is waiting for an event, such as the completion of input or output.','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 13:46:13','2025-02-19 13:46:13'),(1334,'635','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','PCB stores information necessary for process management. A unique PCB is generated when a process is createc and the PCB is removed from the process completion A PCB includes a process identification number (PIC) , a proces status, program counter (the value that indicates the instruction to run next) , a scheduling priority, registere information, and main memory unit information','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 13:46:13','2025-02-19 13:46:13'),(1335,'437','App\\Models\\Section','Text','Early computer systems could only execute one application program at a time. In other words, one program occupied all the system\'s resources. However modern computer systems run multiple programs concurrently: The OS must manage computer resources so that multiple programs share resources and operate in stable condition at the same time: A process refers to a running program, and in todays concurrent multi-process environment, it is a work unit of a time-sharing system.','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 13:46:13','2025-02-19 13:46:13'),(1336,'636','App\\Models\\Subsection','Figures',NULL,'',2,'67b5e0b4c8a08.png','/storage/figures/67b5e0b4c8a08.png','2025-02-19 13:46:13','2025-02-19 13:46:28'),(1337,'636','App\\Models\\Subsection','Code',NULL,'[Figure 17] Process Tree Structure in the UNIX OS (Example)',3,'67b5e0b4d775e.png','/storage/code/67b5e0b4d775e.png','2025-02-19 13:46:13','2025-02-19 13:46:28'),(1338,'636','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','Processes must be able to run in parallel, and also be created and removed dynamically: A process can create other new processes through the \"fork()\" system call while it runs. The process that creates other processes is called a parent process, and a newly created process is called a child process. A child process can create another child process, and this relationship is formed in a tree structure, as shown in [Figure 17].','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 13:46:13','2025-02-19 13:46:13'),(1339,'637','App\\Models\\Subsection','Figures',NULL,'[Figure 18] Process Creation and Termination in the UNIX OS',2,'67b5e0b4e5c2f.png','/storage/figures/67b5e0b4e5c2f.png','2025-02-19 13:46:13','2025-02-19 13:46:28'),(1340,'637','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','After completing the last code of the program, the process requests the to delete the process with the \"exit()\" system call, as shown in [Figure 18]. At that point, the child process returs data to the parent process with the \'wait()\" system call, and the OS recollects all the resources allocated to the deleted process OS','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 13:46:13','2025-02-19 13:46:13'),(1341,'638','App\\Models\\Subsection','Figures',NULL,'[Figure 19] Relationship between Thread and Process',2,'67b5e0b501171.png','/storage/figures/67b5e0b501171.png','2025-02-19 13:46:13','2025-02-19 13:46:29'),(1342,'638','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','A thread is a basic unit for using a CPU and is all called a lightweight process As shown in [Figure 19], a proces generally has one or more threads. A thread shares the memory unit, such as codes, data, and files, and create its own register and stack While processes use more CPU time than threads for context exchange, threads ca exchange context more economically because threads share the memory unit','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 13:46:13','2025-02-19 13:46:13'),(1343,'639','App\\Models\\Subsection','Figures',NULL,'[Figure 20] Single Thread and Multi-thread',2,'67b5e0b511a3c.png','/storage/figures/67b5e0b511a3c.png','2025-02-19 13:46:13','2025-02-19 13:46:29'),(1344,'639','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','As shown in [Figure 20], a single-thread process is a case in which a thread exists for a process, and a process, having multiple threads, is called a multi-threaded process A thread operates with the status of \"ready\" , \'blocked\" , \"running\" , and \"terminated\". A CPU can occupy only one thread at a time: In other words, only one thread runs at a time, and the status of the other threads is \"blocked \" When a thread is blocked, other threads can run There are certain benefits to using multi-threads The memory occupied by a process can be shared, and another thread can access the same memory addres multi-thread system: The cost of thread creation and context exchange is more economical than the process Threads increase the parallel attributes of the process and enable the utilization of multiprocessors.','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 13:46:13','2025-02-19 13:46:13'),(1345,'440','App\\Models\\Section','Text','A race condition refers to two or more parallel processes simultaneously accessing and changing the same dat or the order of manipulating the data affecting the execution result: In a race condition, only one process must protected to manipulate data, and process synchronization is necessary for its protection','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 13:46:13','2025-02-19 13:46:13'),(1346,'441','App\\Models\\Section','Code',NULL,'[Figure 21] Critical Section Structure in a Process Code',2,'67b5e0b51f2a6.png','/storage/code/67b5e0b51f2a6.png','2025-02-19 13:46:13','2025-02-19 13:46:29'),(1347,'441','App\\Models\\Section','Text','For process synchronization, each process defines a critical section in a part of the code and performs the task of changing the data that is shared with other critical section processes. Two or more processes that are mutually exclusive cannot run in the critical section at the same time. [Figure 21] shows the structure of the critical and remainder sections.','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 13:46:13','2025-02-19 13:46:13'),(1348,'441','App\\Models\\Section','Text','The critical area problem is to establish rules so that the processes cooperate with each other Each process must request permission to enter, even if it enters its critical section The part of the code that implements such a request is called the entry section The exit section is after the critical section, and the rest of the code is collectively called the remainder section, Solving the critical section problem requires satisfying the following conditions: Mutual exclusion: If a process runs in its critical section, the other processes cannot run their own critical section Progress: Only processes that are not running in the remainder section can enter a critical section without a running process Bounded waiting: After a process makes a request to enter its critical section, the time allowed for other processes to enter the critical section should be limited until the process enters the critical section','',3,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 13:46:13','2025-02-19 13:46:13'),(1349,'442','App\\Models\\Section','Text','One of the ways to solve the critical section problem is to configure the synchronization hardware, not to allow the interruption of generation while the shared data in the critical section is changed. However, the hardware method is not feasible, since it deteriorates the system efficiency in a multiprocessor environment Another way is to use a semaphore, which is a synchronization tool. The semaphore, \'S\', is an integer variable, and only the P operation (wait) and V operation (signal) are enabled  If one process modifies the semaphore value, the other processes cannot modify the same semaphore value at the same time. It works by setting the semaphore value to \"wait\" when a process enters the critical section and changing the value to \"signal\" when the process exits the critical section: Another process checks the semaphore value and does not enter the critical section if the value isin the \"wait\" state, preventing multiple processes from simultaneously accessing the shared data being','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 13:46:13','2025-02-19 13:46:13'),(1350,'443','App\\Models\\Section','Tables',NULL,'(Table 6) Ways to Solve Deadlock State',4,'67b5e0b5341c8.png','/storage/tables/67b5e0b5341c8.png','2025-02-19 13:46:13','2025-02-19 13:46:29'),(1351,'443','App\\Models\\Section','Text','In a multi-, programming environment, the processes compete with each other to use limited resources. When process requests a resource, it obtains a \"standby\" status if the resource is not available There may be a case Wher the status of a process in \"standby\" is never changed because the requested resource is allocated to other standby processes. This state is called the deadlock The deadlocked processes cannot finish the running program, and the system cannot start other tasks because the resource is tied to other processes <Table 5  shows the conditions that can cause deadlock include mutuz exclusion, hold & wait, non-preemption, and circular wait The deadlock occurs when these four conditions are met They','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 13:46:13','2025-02-19 13:46:13'),(1352,'443','App\\Models\\Section','Text','<Table 6  shows how to solve the deadlock state','',3,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 13:46:13','2025-02-19 13:46:13'),(1353,'444','App\\Models\\Section','Text','A CPU uses scheduling to improve the utilization rate as if multiple programs share it at the same time A CPU can only execute the instruction and read data when are stored in the memory: Therefore, multiple processes must be stored in a memory unit for them to run. Virtual memory is the technique of running processes, even if are not present in the memory unit: This technique allows a user program that is larger than the physical memory unit to run: This section describes various techniques for managing the storage unit: they they','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 13:46:13','2025-02-19 13:46:13'),(1354,'640','App\\Models\\Subsection','Tables',NULL,'(Table 7) Techniques of Allocating Memory Unit',2,'67b5e0b54e81f.png','/storage/tables/67b5e0b54e81f.png','2025-02-19 13:46:13','2025-02-19 13:46:29'),(1355,'640','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','It is the technique of searching for the best way to allocate processes to the available main memory area when process requests the memory unit for a new use. As shown in <Table 7  , the first-fit, best-fit, and worst-fit are the generally used techniques for selecting the available areas a set of available areas. from','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 13:46:13','2025-02-19 13:46:13'),(1356,'641','App\\Models\\Subsection','Figures',NULL,'[Figure 22] Case f External Fragmentation',2,'67b5e0b55f9a0.png','/storage/figures/67b5e0b55f9a0.png','2025-02-19 13:46:13','2025-02-19 13:46:29'),(1357,'641','App\\Models\\Subsection','Figures',NULL,'[Figure 23] Case of Internal Fragmentation',3,'67b5e0b572ab0.png','/storage/figures/67b5e0b572ab0.png','2025-02-19 13:46:13','2025-02-19 13:46:29'),(1358,'641','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','Memory space is allocated when the memory is requested and recollected after use. Repetition of the allocation and recollection can result in memory space that is wasted without being used   Using the first-fit, best-fit, and worst- fit techniques to allocate the memory unit can cause external fragmentation, as shown in [Figure 22]. Let us assume that a process requests 64,450 bytes when there are 64,500 bytes of available space In that case, 50 bytes of available space remains after allocating the requested space: If the memory is partitioned into a fixed size to provide multiple fixed-sized available spaces to processes, it may be slightly larger than the required space The remaining space is called the internal fragmentation as shown in [Figure 231.','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 13:46:13','2025-02-19 13:46:13'),(1359,'642','App\\Models\\Subsection','Figures',NULL,'[Figure 24] Solving Fragmentation Problem through Compaction Technique',2,'67b5e0b5838e4.png','/storage/figures/67b5e0b5838e4.png','2025-02-19 13:46:13','2025-02-19 13:46:29'),(1360,'642','App\\Models\\Subsection','Figures',NULL,'[Figure 25] Solving Fragmentation Problem through Coalescing Technique',4,'67b5e0b5937e3.png','/storage/figures/67b5e0b5937e3.png','2025-02-19 13:46:13','2025-02-19 13:46:29'),(1361,'642','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','compaction lecitique The compaction technique merges small-sized available memory: It is used to remove the exteral fragmentation that generated in a variable-size memory partition system, as shown in [Figure 24]. The technique is not used because it is complex to implement,, and it causes overload as it requires a time widely long','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 13:46:13','2025-02-19 13:46:13'),(1362,'642','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','The coalescing technique merges spaces with adjacent addresses in the unused empty space list in order to create a larger space and to prevent multiple small spaces, as shown in [Figure 25].','',3,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 13:46:13','2025-02-19 13:46:13'),(1363,'446','App\\Models\\Section','Text','Faimess to processes Maximizing throughput per unit time Minimizing response time Predictable execution time Preventing system overload Balanced resource utilization Preventing indefinite process execution Implementing priority schemes','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 13:46:13','2025-02-19 13:46:13'),(1364,'447','App\\Models\\Section','Tables',NULL,'',3,'67b5e0b5bb9e9.png','/storage/tables/67b5e0b5bb9e9.png','2025-02-19 13:46:13','2025-02-19 13:46:29'),(1365,'447','App\\Models\\Section','Text','<Table 8  shows the types and characteristics of scheduling algorithms Preemptive scheduling: A process can take CPU resources while another process is occupying them Non-preemptive scheduling: If a CPU resource is allocated to a process, it cannot be allocated to another process until the task has been completed.','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 13:46:13','2025-02-19 13:46:13'),(1366,'448','App\\Models\\Section','Figures',NULL,'[Figure 26] Comparison of Paging and Segmentation Memory Allocations',2,'67b5e0b5de11b.png','/storage/figures/67b5e0b5de11b.png','2025-02-19 13:46:13','2025-02-19 13:46:29'),(1367,'448','App\\Models\\Section','Text','A virtual memory unit includes the virtual address that processes refer to and the physical address that points to the available main memory: Whenever a process accesses a virtual address, the system must quickly convert it into the physical address through the memory management unit (MMU) It is divided into a paging technique and segmentation technique, according to the block configuration Some systems may use a combination of both techniques (see [Figure 26]). Paging technique: This technique partitions the main memory unit into fixed sizes, called frames, and also partitions the task to the process stored in the virtual memory unit into fixed sizes, called pages, and loads them into the frame to run the task Segmentation technique: This technique partitions the task to the process stored in the virtual memory unit into size segments, which are logical units of various sizes, and then loads them into the main memory unit to run:','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 13:46:14','2025-02-19 13:46:14'),(1368,'449','App\\Models\\Section','Text','f all pages are filled in the paging virtual memory unit, free space must be created before loading new memory page from the auxiliary memory unit The system selects a page to replace the page replacement technique, affecting th svstem efficiencv and performance Optimal technique: This technique replaces a page that is not Iikely to be used for the longest time. Although it is the optimal replacement technique wth the minimum absent page rate, it is not a realistic technique, since it is difficult to predict behavior First In First Out (FIFO) technique: This technique tracks the order of loading in the main memory and replaces the first loaded page Least Recently Used (LRU) technique: This technique replaces the page that has been unused for the longest time: Least Frequently Used (LFU) technique: This technique tracks each page s utilization frequency and replaces the least used or least intensively used page Not Used Recently (NUR) technique: This technique uses the tendency that the page not used recently is less likely to be used in the near future, so it replaces the page','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 13:46:14','2025-02-19 13:46:14'),(1369,'450','App\\Models\\Section','Text','Locality: A tendency to intensively reter to only some pages while & process IS running: It IS divided into temporal locality and spatial locality: Working Set: A set of frequently referred to page lists for a certain period to execute a process efficiently It reduces page absence and page replacement by placing the frequently referred to working sets in the main memory: Thrashing: A phenomenon in which the CPU utilization rate decreases because page replacement takes longer than the processing time The degree of multi-programming is reduced, the CPU utilization rate is increased, or a working set is used to prevent thrashing:','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 13:46:14','2025-02-19 13:46:14'),(1370,'643','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','It is a set of data with & name and stored in an auxiliary memory unit, such as a disk or tape The OS maps files to physical devices. In other words, when the OS writes a program or data to a file, it is permanently stored in a nonvolatile physical device','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 13:46:14','2025-02-19 13:46:14'),(1371,'644','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','Files have several properties to enable the ability to identify and manage them. The most common is the file name, which is expressed as a single string: A process or user can independently create and access files the file name attribute The types of file attributes are described as follows: Name: Should be maintained in a legible form by users. Location: Points to the device and location of the file and includes the directory Size: Includes the current file size (in bytes, words, or blocks) and the maximum allowable size Protection: Controls who can read, write, or run the file Time, date, and user identification: Include the data related to the creation time, recent information, and recent usage using path','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 13:46:14','2025-02-19 13:46:14'),(1372,'451','App\\Models\\Section','Text','A file system stores related data to find and access the OS data and programs quickly: It is a directory structure tha provides information on an aggregation of files and all files in the system:','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 13:46:14','2025-02-19 13:46:14'),(1373,'452','App\\Models\\Section','Text','A directory is a logical structure to manage tens of thousands of files managed by a file system, and can be the t size of gigabytes or terabytes It records the information about all files The following actions are performed directory: File search: A user can search a file from the directory structure File creation: A new file is created and added to the directory: File delete: Unneeded files are removed the file Directory list: Lists files in a directory and shows the directory item: from Renaming file: A file name must be changeable, and a renamed file should exist at a within the directory structure point','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 13:46:14','2025-02-19 13:46:14'),(1374,'453','App\\Models\\Section','Figures',NULL,'[Figure 27] Contiguous Allocation',2,'67b5e0b5f03b1.png','/storage/figures/67b5e0b5f03b1.png','2025-02-19 13:46:14','2025-02-19 13:46:29'),(1375,'453','App\\Models\\Section','Figures',NULL,'[Figure 28] Linked Allocation',4,'67b5e0b60b2d9.png','/storage/figures/67b5e0b60b2d9.png','2025-02-19 13:46:14','2025-02-19 13:46:30'),(1376,'453','App\\Models\\Section','Figures',NULL,'[Figure 29] Indexed Allocation',6,'67b5e0b61b1c1.png','/storage/figures/67b5e0b61b1c1.png','2025-02-19 13:46:14','2025-02-19 13:46:30'),(1377,'453','App\\Models\\Section','Text','file system should consider which space on the disk to use and quickly access the files. An OSs file generally uses the contiguous allocation, linked allocation, or indexed allocation. syster TC \'yslcmmi |iiuulu cun Siuci Wi CI space Un LC UiSn LU USC aru yuickiy GCCC)) CIIC TC). An U5) iC PyslC generally uses the contiguous allocation, linked allocation, or indexed allocation. Contiguous allocation: This method arranges files as a set of contiguous addresses on the physical disk, as shown in [Figure 27] below: disk addresses of stored files are defined linearly This method has the advantage of a relatively high reading spee since the files are stored in contiguous addresses However, it creates an external fragmentation problem','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 13:46:14','2025-02-19 13:46:14'),(1378,'453','App\\Models\\Section','Text','This method stores files in block units and links each block to a list, as shown in [Figure 28] below The directory keeps pointers to the first and last blocks of the files As shown in the figure, the directory contains 9 and 25,which are the first and last block pointers, respectively: Block 9 is linked to blocks 16, 1, .9, 10, and 25 in that order This method can solve the external fragmentation problem of the contiguous allocation method. However, the linked allocation method is slow to read ad requires the area to store the pointers separately, since data blocks are scattered on the physical disk Moreover it can cause data errors if the linked pointer data is lost or corrupt','',3,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 13:46:14','2025-02-19 13:46:14'),(1379,'453','App\\Models\\Section','Text','Utocu The linked allocation cannot support direct access and is difficult to manage the loss, since the block pointer addresses are scattered throughout the disk The indexed allocation solves the problem by managing all pointer data of a file in a index block, as shown in [Figure 29]. The indexed allocation does not create external fragmentation and supports the direct addresses. However, the waste of storage space is larger than the linked allocation method,','',5,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 13:46:14','2025-02-19 13:46:14'),(1380,'454','App\\Models\\Section','Tables',NULL,'',1,'67b5e0b629911.png','/storage/tables/67b5e0b629911.png','2025-02-19 13:46:14','2025-02-19 13:46:30'),(1381,'455','App\\Models\\Section','Tables',NULL,'',3,'67b5e0b63c0ab.png','/storage/tables/67b5e0b63c0ab.png','2025-02-19 13:46:14','2025-02-19 13:46:30'),(1382,'455','App\\Models\\Section','Figures',NULL,'',2,'67b5e0b64e844.png','/storage/figures/67b5e0b64e844.png','2025-02-19 13:46:14','2025-02-19 13:46:30'),(1383,'455','App\\Models\\Section','Text','In a UNIX system, i-node has the role of allocation, application, creation, link, and deleting through the file/directory data','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 13:46:14','2025-02-19 13:46:14'),(1384,'456','App\\Models\\Section','Figures',NULL,'[Figure 30] Computer Structure',2,'67b5e0b65c379.png','/storage/figures/67b5e0b65c379.png','2025-02-19 13:46:14','2025-02-19 13:46:30'),(1385,'456','App\\Models\\Section','Text','he basic function of a computer is to run a program code in the specified sequence. In other words, it reads, rocesses, and stores the needed data: [Figure 30] shows the main components of a computer Central Processing Unit (CPU): Also, commonly known as a processor, it plays a role of the program running and data nrocecsino key aala processing: Memory: Main memory: Closely located to the CPU, it consists of memory semiconductor chips. It can be accessed at a high speed and can be used only as temporary storage because it has no permanent storage capabilities Auxiliary storage device: The secondary storage device can be accessed at a low because it includes mechanical devices. It has a high storage density, and it is moderately priced. Disks and magnetic tapes are some examples speed IO device: consists of an input device and an output device to be used as the tool for interaction between the users and computers.','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 13:46:14','2025-02-19 13:46:14'),(1386,'457','App\\Models\\Section','Figures',NULL,'[Figure 31] Von Neumann Architecture and Harvard Architecture',2,'67b5e0b66d451.png','/storage/figures/67b5e0b66d451.png','2025-02-19 13:46:14','2025-02-19 13:46:30'),(1387,'457','App\\Models\\Section','Figures',NULL,'[Figure 32] Computer Structure Applying Both Architectures',4,'67b5e0b67e061.png','/storage/figures/67b5e0b67e061.png','2025-02-19 13:46:14','2025-02-19 13:46:30'),(1388,'457','App\\Models\\Section','Text','The types of computer architecture include the von Neumann architecture, which is a structure that applies the stored-program design principle\' suggested by von Neumann in 1945,and the Harvard architecturewhich separates instruction memory and data memory: As shown in [Figure 31], these two types have different memory structures, and each has advantages and disadvantages Von Neumann architecture: The CPU can read commands from the memory and can read and write data both from the memory and to the memory: Instructions and data cannot be accessed simultaneously because use the same signal bus and memory: Harvard architecture: It solves computer bottlenecks by storing commands and data in different memories and improves performance by reading and writing commands in parallel However, the bus system design becomes complex they','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 13:46:14','2025-02-19 13:46:14'),(1389,'457','App\\Models\\Section','Text','1 A memory unit is attached next to the CPU, and programs ad data stored in the memory unit are sequentially fetched and processed according to the execution instructions. Since the von Neumann &nd Harvard architectures each has advantages ad disadvantages, the most recent high- performance CPUs apply both architectures in their design. In other words, separate the cache memory for instruction and data, and apply the Harvard architecture inside the CPU (CPU and cache) and the von Neumann architecture outside CPU (CPU and memory), as shown in [Figure 32] they they','',3,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 13:46:14','2025-02-19 13:46:14'),(1390,'458','App\\Models\\Section','Text','The CPU is the most important part of computers, as it interprets instructions and handles arithmetic or logica operations and data processing It plays the key role of running programs and processing data','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 13:46:14','2025-02-19 13:46:14'),(1391,'459','App\\Models\\Section','Tables',NULL,'(Table 9) CPU Execution',2,'67b5e0b693eb2.png','/storage/tables/67b5e0b693eb2.png','2025-02-19 13:46:14','2025-02-19 13:46:30'),(1392,'459','App\\Models\\Section','Text','As shown in <Table 9  , the CPU operation is divided into a function that commonly runs for all instructions, and function that runs only when necessary, according to the instructions','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 13:46:14','2025-02-19 13:46:14'),(1393,'645','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','(instructions) and run them y element of the CPU to execute arithmetic operations? and logical operations','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 13:46:14','2025-02-19 13:46:14'),(1394,'646','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','Register: A temporary storage area that temporarily stores instructions waiting to be processed by the CPU or the intermediate result values of the CPU operation. The register types include, PC (program counter) , IR (instruction register), AC (accumulator), MAR (memory address register), MBR (memory buffer register) , and SP (stack pointer): Bus: A common transmission line that connects the CPU, memory, IO unit, etc, in order to exchange necessary data.','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 13:46:14','2025-02-19 13:46:14'),(1395,'647','App\\Models\\Subsection','Figures',NULL,'[Figure 33] CPU Structure',2,'67b5e0b6a5357.png','/storage/figures/67b5e0b6a5357.png','2025-02-19 13:46:14','2025-02-19 13:46:30'),(1396,'647','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','Duoco Cc Cicooiicc 0o TOo 0 Address bus: A set of signal lines that transmits address data generated by the CPU. Data bus: A set of signal lines that transmits data from the CPU to a memory unit or an IO unit. Control bus: A set of signal lines that are necessary for the CPU to control various elements. system','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 13:46:14','2025-02-19 13:46:14'),(1397,'460','App\\Models\\Section','Text','shown in [Figure 33], a CPU consists of a control unit, an arithmetic logic unit (ALU), registers, and buses that connect them in order to deliver the data. trol unit: A hardware module that sequentially generates control signals to interpret the program codes ructions) and run them','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 13:46:14','2025-02-19 13:46:14'),(1398,'461','App\\Models\\Section','Tables',NULL,'(Table 10} Relationship between Instruction Cycle Types and CPU Components',4,'67b5e0b6bd2b5.png','/storage/tables/67b5e0b6bd2b5.png','2025-02-19 13:46:14','2025-02-19 13:46:30'),(1399,'461','App\\Models\\Section','Figures',NULL,'[Figure 34] Instruction Cycle Conceptual Diagram',2,'67b5e0b6cff57.png','/storage/figures/67b5e0b6cff57.png','2025-02-19 13:46:14','2025-02-19 13:46:30'),(1400,'461','App\\Models\\Section','Text','This is the entire process required for the CPU to execute a instruction: The CPU repeats it from the moment the CPU starts executing the program, until the power is turned off or a irrecoverable error occurs to terminate the execution The instruction cycle from the fetching of the instruction to the completion of the operation consists of a fetch cycle, an indirect an execution and an interrupt cycle, as shown in [Figure 34]. cycle, cycle, 2 Arithmetic operation: Addition, subtraction, multiplication, and division 3 Logic operation: AND, OR, NOT, XOR, etc','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 13:46:15','2025-02-19 13:46:15'),(1401,'461','App\\Models\\Section','Text','[able 10  shows the entire instruction cycle. The CPU components needed in each cycle are different','',3,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 13:46:15','2025-02-19 13:46:15'),(1402,'462','App\\Models\\Section','Tables',NULL,'(Table 11) Comparison of CISC and RISC',2,'67b5e0b6e8473.png','/storage/tables/67b5e0b6e8473.png','2025-02-19 13:46:15','2025-02-19 13:46:30'),(1403,'462','App\\Models\\Section','Text','Instruction set, or instruction set architecture (ISA), refers to the machine language instructions that a microprocessor can recognize, understand its function, and execute The ISA is part of the programming-related computer architecture, and it includes data types, instructions, registers, addressing modes, memory structures interruptions exception handling, ad external inputloutput The ISAs are the complex instruction set computer (CISC) and the Reduced instruction set computer (RISC): <Table 4  shows the concepts and differences in these structures. CISC:A complex instruction-type computer that embeds many complex instructions into the hardware in order to process the complex instructions as a single instruction: RISC: A reduced instruction-type computer that embeds a few simple instructions into the hardware to process complex instructions as a set of simple instructions leading','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 13:46:15','2025-02-19 13:46:15'),(1404,'463','App\\Models\\Section','Figures',NULL,'[Figure 35] Memory Unit s Hierarchical Structure',2,'67b5e0b707fa6.png','/storage/figures/67b5e0b707fa6.png','2025-02-19 13:46:15','2025-02-19 13:46:31'),(1405,'463','App\\Models\\Section','Text','As shown in [Figure 35], the memory unit at a higher level has a higher price per bit, less capacity, a shorter acce: time, ad a higher access frequency by the CPU:','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 13:46:15','2025-02-19 13:46:15'),(1406,'464','App\\Models\\Section','Text','Capacity Access time Cycle time Bandwidth of storage unit Data transportation Cost','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 13:46:15','2025-02-19 13:46:15'),(1407,'465','App\\Models\\Section','Tables',NULL,'(Table 12) Types of Memory Units',2,'67b5e0b72aaaa.png','/storage/tables/67b5e0b72aaaa.png','2025-02-19 13:46:15','2025-02-19 13:46:31'),(1408,'465','App\\Models\\Section','Text','Memory units can be classified according to the use, physical storing method, data retention, and content preservation','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 13:46:15','2025-02-19 13:46:15'),(1409,'466','App\\Models\\Section','Text','address is the location in the main memory where data is stored. Various addressing methods are available tc signate instructions, using limited instruction bits and using the memory unit capacity efficiently An address is the location in the main memory Where data is stored. Various addressing methods are available to designate instructions, using limited instruction bits and using the memory unit capacity efficiently: Direct addressing mode Indirect addressing mode Implied addressing mode MCuialC auuiessinismiuuc Displacement addressing mode: Relative addressing mode, indexed addressing mode, and base-register addressing mode','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 13:46:15','2025-02-19 13:46:15'),(1410,'467','App\\Models\\Section','Text','The locality is a tendency in which programs intensively refer to a area in the moment, rather than uniformly accessing information in the memory device Temporal locality: Recently accessed programs or data are more likely to be accessed in the near future. Spatial locality: Data stored adjacent to the storage device is more likely to be accessed continuously: Sequential locality: Instructions are fetched and executed in the order in which were stored, unless branched (about 20%) specific again they','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 13:46:15','2025-02-19 13:46:15'),(1411,'468','App\\Models\\Section','Text','device is necessary to perform an input operation that stores data to be processed by the CPU in the memory t, as well as an output operation that transfers the processing results from the main memory to a output medium:','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 13:46:15','2025-02-19 13:46:15'),(1412,'469','App\\Models\\Section','Figures',NULL,'[Figure 36] IO Controller Structure',2,'67b5e0b7417b0.png','/storage/figures/67b5e0b7417b0.png','2025-02-19 13:46:15','2025-02-19 13:46:31'),(1413,'469','App\\Models\\Section','Figures',NULL,'[Figure 37] Allocation of Memory Mapped I/O Address',4,'67b5e0b750719.png','/storage/figures/67b5e0b750719.png','2025-02-19 13:46:15','2025-02-19 13:46:31'),(1414,'469','App\\Models\\Section','Figures',NULL,'[Figure 38] Address Allocation by IJO Mapped IO',6,'67b5e0b75c820.png','/storage/figures/67b5e0b75c820.png','2025-02-19 13:46:15','2025-02-19 13:46:31'),(1415,'469','App\\Models\\Section','Text','AnIO controller is necessary to process inputs and outputs, as shown in [Figure 36], and it plays the following roles: VO device control and coordination Communication with the CPU Communication with the IJO device 0 9 ffo timing Gn','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 13:46:15','2025-02-19 13:46:15'),(1416,'469','App\\Models\\Section','Text','Each device needs two addresses (a status/control register address and a data register address) for IO control, anc the same two addresses are required for each device. It is divided into the memory mapped IJO and the IJO mapped O,depending on how the addresses are allocated. Memory mapped IO: It is a method of allocating a part of the address area in the memory to the register addresses in the I/O controller, as shown in [Figure 37]. It has the advantage of easy programming, but the disadvantage 0= reducing the available memory space','',3,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 13:46:15','2025-02-19 13:46:15'),(1417,'469','App\\Models\\Section','Text','IO mapped I/O: It is a method of allocating the I/0 device address space separately from the memory address space, as shown in [Figure 38]. It has the advantage of not reducing the available memory address space, but the disadvantage of making it difficult to program','',5,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 13:46:15','2025-02-19 13:46:15'),(1418,'648','App\\Models\\Subsection','Figures',NULL,'[Figure 39] System Structure Including DMA',2,'67b5e0b76f0a9.png','/storage/figures/67b5e0b76f0a9.png','2025-02-19 13:46:15','2025-02-19 13:46:31'),(1419,'648','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','DMA is a method of the IO device directly accessing the memory without the assistance of the CPU. The DMA controller controls the bus, and the IO device and memory transfer information directly: [Figure 39] shows the system structure that includes the DMA controller: With DMA high-speed IJO devices can increase system efficiency by minimizing the interruption overhead that reduces the CPU\'s actual processing time:','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 13:46:15','2025-02-19 13:46:15'),(1420,'649','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','The IO interface requests a DMA service from the DMA controller: The bus request is transferred to the CPUs HOLD pin,, so that the DMA acquires the control of the bus (Active High): The bus grant is retured the CPUs HLDA (Hold Acknowledge) pin, to the DMAC (Active High): The DMAC loads the contents of the address register into the address bus. The DMAC transfers the DMA acknowledgment to the IJO interface in order to load the data into the data bus. The address bus transfers the data bytes to the identified memory location The IO interface maintains the data transfer (Latch): The DMAC returns the bus grant as the bus request is dropped, and the HOLD becomes a low state The bus grant is dropped, and HLDA becomes a low state. Afterward, the address register increases by increments pf 1, and the byte count decreases by decrements of 1. The process returns to if the byte count is not 0, and otherwise stops. from Step','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 13:46:15','2025-02-19 13:46:15'),(1421,'650','App\\Models\\Subsection','Tables',NULL,'',1,'67b5e0b78463d.png','/storage/tables/67b5e0b78463d.png','2025-02-19 13:46:15','2025-02-19 13:46:31'),(1422,'471','App\\Models\\Section','Figures',NULL,'',2,'67b5e0b796a77.png','/storage/figures/67b5e0b796a77.png','2025-02-19 13:46:15','2025-02-19 13:46:31'),(1423,'471','App\\Models\\Section','Text','Neuromorphic chip, a core technology for neuromorphic computing, is a new semiconductor type that processes information in a way that is similar to human thinking, by implementing brain behavior in silicon as much as possible There are several cores in a semiconductor chip, and electronic devices, such as transistors ad memory, are embedded into the core Some of the devices in the core play the role of neurons and neural cells in the brain, and the memory chip plays synaptic function that links neurons. Since the core, which acts as an artificial neuron,, is configured in parallel like the human brain, it can process a large amount of data with little power and increase the ability to lear and operate like the human brain.','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 13:46:15','2025-02-19 13:46:15'),(1424,'472','App\\Models\\Section','Tables',NULL,'[Figure 40] Comparison of Conventional Semiconductor and Neuromorphic Chip',1,'67b5e0b7a9d79.png','/storage/tables/67b5e0b7a9d79.png','2025-02-19 13:46:15','2025-02-19 13:46:31'),(1425,'472','App\\Models\\Section','Text','Neuromorphic computers do not only operate in a preprogrammed way, like conventional semiconductor-based computers, but can develop their processing power by detecting the surrounding context and learning autonomously: Since devices equipped with the neuromorphic chip can increase learning, operation capability, and power efficiency, can apply intelligence to all computing, ranging from loT, smartphones, robots, automobiles, cloud computing, and supercomputing: However, there is still a lack of understanding of how human neural circuits process data at the level, and neuromorphic computers still remain at a level that simulates single neurons There are many problems to resolve they they system from the technical aspect in order for them to have the same level of complex and highly integrated structure as the human brain. Research on neuromorphic processors with various materials and structures is ongoing worldwide, but there is no clear leading group with clear superior competitiveness','',2,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 13:46:15','2025-02-19 13:46:15'),(1426,'473','App\\Models\\Section','Tables',NULL,'(Table 14) Types of Quantum Computer and Comparison',4,'67b5e0b7cd643.png','/storage/tables/67b5e0b7cd643.png','2025-02-19 13:46:15','2025-02-19 13:46:31'),(1427,'473','App\\Models\\Section','Tables',NULL,'',6,'67b5e0b8096a6.png','/storage/tables/67b5e0b8096a6.png','2025-02-19 13:46:15','2025-02-19 13:46:32'),(1428,'473','App\\Models\\Section','Text','A quantum computer is a new conceptual computer that can simultaneously process a large volume of information at a high speed, based on the principle of ultra-high-speed, large-capacity computing technology optimized for specific operations, according to the principle of overlapping and entanglement inherent in quantum mechanics Quantum parallel processing, which uses quantum bits (qubits) as a basic unit of information processing, exponentially increases information processing and computation speed. <Table 13  shows the difference conventional omnuter structures from','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 13:46:15','2025-02-19 13:46:15'),(1429,'473','App\\Models\\Section','Text','quantum computer can be an analog or digital type  <Table 14  shows the characteristics of each type','',3,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 13:46:15','2025-02-19 13:46:15'),(1430,'474','App\\Models\\Section','Text','Parallel processing refers to one or more independent operating systems managing multiple processors and performing multiple tasks There are separate programming languages and syntax for parallel processing: Parallel processing is very fast and can share the memory unit. Since several processors operate it, the impact of failed hardware parts on the entire system is small It is widely used in the field of Al, consisting of a lot of data and repetitive complex operations, military equipment that is needed to obtain accurate results in a short time, and searching services that extract results from a wide range of data in a short time Flynn s taxonomy and classification by memory structure are leading examples of parallel processing system classification','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 13:46:16','2025-02-19 13:46:16'),(1431,'651','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','SISD is a single processor that sequentially processes an instruction and data, one at a time. It is the conventional computer architecture that follows von Neumann\'s concept The controller interprets an instruction and operates the processor in order to run the instruction while fetching a piece of data from the memory unit and processing it: The performance may deteriorate, since it requires reading the instruction each time it acquires the processing data The performance may be improved by using simultaneous processing techniques, such as pipelining and cunerccalar system','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 13:46:16','2025-02-19 13:46:16'),(1432,'652','App\\Models\\Subsection','Figures',NULL,'',2,'67b5e0b8215d8.png','/storage/figures/67b5e0b8215d8.png','2025-02-19 13:46:16','2025-02-19 13:46:32'),(1433,'652','App\\Models\\Subsection','Figures',NULL,'[Figure 43] SIMD Structure',3,'67b5e0b82b5ff.png','/storage/figures/67b5e0b82b5ff.png','2025-02-19 13:46:16','2025-02-19 13:46:32'),(1434,'652','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','The structure of processing multiple data with an instruction to simultaneously perform the same operation on multiple data It is also called an array processor, as it enables synchronous parallel processing Intels processor made in the SIMD structure, is the Pentium processor with the MMX instruction set: The name is \"multimedia acceleration,\" which is the code that can quickly process frequently-used arithmetic operations The processing speed is high because it can process multiple operations with an instruction floating\" point','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 13:46:16','2025-02-19 13:46:16'),(1435,'653','App\\Models\\Subsection','Figures',NULL,'',2,'67b5e0b837785.png','/storage/figures/67b5e0b837785.png','2025-02-19 13:46:16','2025-02-19 13:46:32'),(1436,'653','App\\Models\\Subsection','Figures',NULL,'[Figure 44] MISD Structure',3,'67b5e0b844260.png','/storage/figures/67b5e0b844260.png','2025-02-19 13:46:16','2025-02-19 13:46:32'),(1437,'653','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','Tvuicipic Ioli ucliun| Bli caind Tnuitpic uala \"u caitt, iviuilipic Iol ucliui Jli caii iviuicipic Data Jlicai| (vid| In a MIMD structure, multiple processors process different programs and different data, and most parallel computers fall into this category: It can be classified into a shared memory model and a distributed memory model, depending on how it uses the memory: According to the degree of data interaction, the shared memory model is called a tightly- Inloc cucton and bc Aictriku tod Oaonen modclic cleccificd 3c lcecel_counled cucton','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 13:46:16','2025-02-19 13:46:16'),(1438,'475','App\\Models\\Section','Figures',NULL,'[Figure 41] Structure of Parallel Computer Processor',1,'67b5e0b8554c4.png','/storage/figures/67b5e0b8554c4.png','2025-02-19 13:46:16','2025-02-19 13:46:32'),(1439,'654','App\\Models\\Subsection','Figures',NULL,'[Figure 45] MIMD Structure',2,'67b5e0b8658e9.png','/storage/figures/67b5e0b8658e9.png','2025-02-19 13:46:16','2025-02-19 13:46:32'),(1440,'654','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','SMP is a tightly-coupled system in which all processors use the main memory as the shared memory: It is easy to program since the data transfer can use shared memory: On the other hand, it has poor scalability and may experience a bus bottleneck, since it uses an internal bus to access the main memory and share the data.','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 13:46:16','2025-02-19 13:46:16'),(1441,'655','App\\Models\\Subsection','Figures',NULL,'[Figure 47] MMP Structure',2,'67b5e0b87425c.png','/storage/figures/67b5e0b87425c.png','2025-02-19 13:46:16','2025-02-19 13:46:32'),(1442,'655','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','MPP is a distributed memory type in which each processor has an independent memory: The loosely coupled exchanges data between processors through a network, such as Ethernet  The structure of connecting nodes, like the CPU, memory, and IJO device, each of which has its own system resources, through a network offers excellen scalability and programming difficulty: systent','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 13:46:16','2025-02-19 13:46:16'),(1443,'656','App\\Models\\Subsection','Figures',NULL,'[Figure 48] NUMA Structure',2,'67b5e0b883595.png','/storage/figures/67b5e0b883595.png','2025-02-19 13:46:16','2025-02-19 13:46:32'),(1444,'656','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','NUMA is a structure the combines the advantages of the SMP, which is a shared memory structure that makes it easier to develop programs and the MPP structure, which offers excellent scalability: Each processor has a separate local memory and the global memory address space that all processors can access.','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 13:46:16','2025-02-19 13:46:16'),(1445,'657','App\\Models\\Subsection','Figures',NULL,'[Figure 49] Pipelining',2,'67b5e0b89543b.png','/storage/figures/67b5e0b89543b.png','2025-02-19 13:46:16','2025-02-19 13:46:32'),(1446,'657','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','The technology improves the CPU performance by dividing a operation into several stages and configuring a hardware unit for processing each stage separately in order to process different instructions simultaneously: In other words, it does not process only one instruction at a time, but it processes multiple instructions simultaneously by processing aother instruction while still processing an original instruction: There are several types of pipelines: a two-stage instruction pipeline, a four-stage instruction pipeline, and a six-stage instruction pipeline The four-stage instruction pipeline is the most widely used Although the instruction set consists of two stages in the four-stage instruction pipeline, the processing time of the stages is divided into 4 in order to prevent efficiency degradation, which occurs because the processing time of the pipeline stages is not the same The stages of the four-stage instruction pipeline are instruction fetching (IF), instruction decoding (ID) , operand fetching (OF), and execution (EX):','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 13:46:16','2025-02-19 13:46:16'),(1447,'657','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','The IF stage is a process that fetches instructions from the memory unit It fetches an instruction from the program counter\'s memory unit address and transfers it to the register The ID stage interprets the fetched instruction using an instruction decoder The OF stage fetches an operand that becomes a variable or data, to be used in operation, the memory unit: The EX stage runs the operation specified by the instruction from','',3,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 13:46:16','2025-02-19 13:46:16'),(1448,'658','App\\Models\\Subsection','Figures',NULL,'[Figure 50] Superscalar Process',2,'67b5e0b8a6db6.png','/storage/figures/67b5e0b8a6db6.png','2025-02-19 13:46:16','2025-02-19 13:46:32'),(1449,'658','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','The Superscalar process is a structure that includes a number of instruction pipelines to speed up the central processing unit: It can run instructions out of order, since it independently processes instructions using multiple pipelines. The superscalar process has a basic configuration in which several functional units,that are implemented as superscalar pipelines, support the parallel processing of instructions','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 13:46:16','2025-02-19 13:46:16'),(1450,'659','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','A pipeline hazard refers to the pipeline exceptionally slowing down: Pipeline hazards include the data hazard, the control hazard, and the structural hazard. Data hazards occur when the next instruction execution has to be delayed until the previous instruction has been completed because of the dependency between instruction operands. Control hazards are generated by branch instructions, like branch and jumpwhich change the execution order of the instructions. Structural hazards are generated when instructions cannot be processed in parallel in the same clock cycle, due to hardware limitations. In other words,it means the hardware cannot support the combination of instructions in the same clock speed cycle','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 13:46:16','2025-02-19 13:46:16'),(1451,'660','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','OpenMP is a compiler directive-based parallel programming API. Here, directive-based means processing only the desired parts in parallel, by adding a directive to a program written sequentially without parallel processing: The execution model of OpenMP is the forkljoin model. A program initially operates as a master thread, and when it encounters a directive, it creates threads and independently executes them: When the parallel processing is finished (when the area selected as a directive is finished), are joined into one master thread in order to run the code sequentially: they','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 13:46:16','2025-02-19 13:46:16'),(1452,'661','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','The message passing interface is a parallel programming model suitable to a distributed memory system structure Since MPI is not a memory sharing mode, the nodes share the information by transferring messages over the network Therefore, the network communication speed is the most important factor for performance, and it is widely used by supercomputers that require a high-speed operation. Parallel programming tools for message passing include High Performance FORTRAN (HPF), Parallel Virtual Machine (PVM) , and Message Passing Interface (MPI): MPI has become the standard.','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 13:46:16','2025-02-19 13:46:16'),(1453,'662','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','Load balancing adequately distributes jobs to the cores in order to increase the multi-core performance: The multiprocessing models include asymmetric multiprocessing (AMP) , symmetric multiprocessing (SMP) , and bound multiprocessing (BMP): AMP: An OS is executed independently in each processor core SMP: An OS manages all processor cores simultaneously: Application programs can operate in any core BMP model: An OS manages all process cores simultaneously, ad an application program can run on a specific core','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 13:46:16','2025-02-19 13:46:16'),(1454,'663','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','The hardware specializes in computer graphics calculation and is mainly used for the rendering of 3D graphics Since a GPU is configured with thousands of small cores that perform floating-point operations processed in parallel, its performance is superior to a CPU that is configured with a small number of cores A GPU dedicated to processing capacity image data generates results through parallel jobs using multiple cores. Although recent GPUs were mainly used for graphics processing functions, they are evolving into more flexible, programmable GPUs large-(','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 13:46:16','2025-02-19 13:46:16'),(1455,'664','App\\Models\\Subsection','Figures',NULL,'[Figure 51] Difference of CPU and GPU Structures',2,'67b5e0b8b9192.png','/storage/figures/67b5e0b8b9192.png','2025-02-19 13:46:16','2025-02-19 13:46:32'),(1456,'664','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','Based on the fact that a GPU shows high computational performance in matrix and vector operations that are mostly used for graphic rendering, the computing intends to utilize GPUs in the general computing domain as well Many models supporting GPGPU programming have appeared. include CUDA and OpeACC NVIDIA, OpenCL from Khronos Group and Ct  AMP from Microsoft. system They \' from','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 13:46:16','2025-02-19 13:46:16'),(1457,'665','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','In 2006, NVIDIA introduced CUDA, a tool for GPU development. CUDA is a parallel computing platform and a programming model that can significantly improve computing with a large number of GPU cores It provides speed intuitive GPI programming, based on the C language, and it enables quick operation using shared memory: CUDA consists of CUDA Runtime API and Driver API. Runtime API provides user-friendliness by automatically allocating necessary values for settings ad others. Driver API, which helps the Runtime API to operate, allows the programs to directly manage memory or devices without using Runtime API. The CUDA is expected to show an excellent performance improvement when to performing tasks suitable for parallel processing operations in various fields that require a large amount of computation, such as simulation Excellent performance can also be expected applied','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 13:46:16','2025-02-19 13:46:16'),(1458,'666','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','OpenCL, maintained and managed by Khronos Group, is an open, general-purpose parallel computing framework developed by Apple, AMD, IBM, Intel, and NVIDIA It is an industry standard programming model for heterogeneous computer systems, consisting of GPUs, CPUs, and other processors It is a parallel programming model based on data and tasks and has characteristics of the open specification to use GPU, CPU, and DSP OpenCL mainly consists of the OpenCL compiler &d the OpenCL runtime library: Programs running on a computational processor (accelerator) are written in OpenCL C language, and the OpenCL compiler gathers the source code to convert it into a binary code Moreover, a control program to run or manage programs running on a CPU is necessary: It can be written using € or Ctt through the OpenCL runtime library:','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 13:46:16','2025-02-19 13:46:16'),(1459,'667','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','Ct  AMP was developed by Microsoft in an open programming language for heterogeneous computing, using CPU and GPU. Ct  AMP, when added to Visual Studio 2021, can increase the execution of Ct  codes using GPU: The C   language-based Ct  AMP intends to help developers create general-purpose programs using GPU without a high level of understanding or application capability about DirectX APL. speed','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 13:46:16','2025-02-19 13:46:16'),(1460,'668','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','Although the concept and usefulness of GPU programming have been widely known with the emergence of platforms like CUDA, it is not easy to write a program that can expect a significant performance improvement by making use of parallel computing: NVIDIA introduced OpenACC, a programming model based on compiler directives that abstract CUDA Open ACC is a programming model for higher productivity, since it provides a relatively simple programming environment for developers It has another advantage of having lower dependence on an OS and platform, since it is a cross-platform model, unlike the above programming models. good','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 13:46:16','2025-02-19 13:46:16'),(1461,'481','App\\Models\\Section','Text','Computer systems use a storage unit to access data and run commands. Although a system uses main memory for the main storage unit, it uses auxiliary memory to permanently store and utilize data The web server WAS, and the database of information systems also need a storage unit as the permanent auxiliary memory unit. The web server WAS requires a storage unit to store its OS or the binary files of its application program Although the data used by an information system is stored and managed through a database, the storage unit is necessary to ensure that data is not corrupted or lost','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 13:46:16','2025-02-19 13:46:16'),(1462,'669','App\\Models\\Subsection','Figures',NULL,'[Figure 52] DAS',2,'67b5e0b8c9443.png','/storage/figures/67b5e0b8c9443.png','2025-02-19 13:46:16','2025-02-19 13:46:32'),(1463,'669','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','The storage connects a computer system with disks directly through a fiber channel or SCSI cable in order to utilize the storage capacity: It allows the computer system to manage the file directory: Since the storage is directly connected to the computer system, it works like a external hard disk at high speed. Its advantage is that its configuration is simple, and the cost is low without a separate switch, but there is a limitation in the number of disks that can be connected: Moreover, files in the storage cannot be shared with other computers since it is directly connected to a computer system','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 13:46:16','2025-02-19 13:46:16'),(1464,'670','App\\Models\\Subsection','Figures',NULL,'[Figure 53] NAS',2,'67b5e0b8d96dd.png','/storage/figures/67b5e0b8d96dd.png','2025-02-19 13:46:16','2025-02-19 13:46:32'),(1465,'670','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','The storage has a separate file management server (controller) to manage the storage media such as HDD and SSD. It is connected to a computer system through an Ethernet network interface like LAN or WAN. Since it has separate file system management server, it is easier to manage data, and multiple servers can share the storage Moreover, multiple computer systems on the same network can use the storage, regardless of the physical location As the storage is connected over a network its speed and capacity are limited by the network speed. system','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 13:46:16','2025-02-19 13:46:16'),(1466,'671','App\\Models\\Subsection','Figures',NULL,'[Figure 54] SAN',2,'67b5e0b8e7f90.png','/storage/figures/67b5e0b8e7f90.png','2025-02-19 13:46:16','2025-02-19 13:46:32'),(1467,'671','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','A disadvantage of the DAS type is the limitation of the number of disks, ad the difficulty of management, while the NAS type has a problem of possible depending on the network connection. SAN was developed to overcome the disadvantages It uses a dedicated fiber channel switch for fast connection, and it enabled the ability to scale up the number of connected servers and storage, with less impact to the connected network load. Using the channel allows the connection to speed up to 8Gbps 16Gbps. However, it increases costs since it requires the dedicated switch and expensive cables, and it can cause a consistency problem, due to locking, when multiple computer systems share a specific file speed delay, fiber','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 13:46:16','2025-02-19 13:46:16'),(1468,'482','App\\Models\\Section','Text','Multimedia services using a large volume of data, led to computer systems storing an increased volume of data. A large-capacity storage system is necessary, since a single disk cannot support the increasing data capacity A storage system logically groups multiple disks in order to store large capacity data that a single disk cannot handle It is classified into DAS, NAS, and SAN, depending on how it is connected to the computer','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 13:46:16','2025-02-19 13:46:16'),(1469,'672','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','This type of SAN uses the gigabit Ethernet Internet protocol (IP), instead of a fiber channel. While the SAN requires SAN switch and SAN storage disks, it increases interconnectivity, since it is connected using the existing Ethernet network It can unify the network management and overcome the distance limitation of SAN, since it can use an IP IP-SAN includes FCIP, iFCP, and iSCSI, while iSCSI is the most widely-used type','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 13:46:16','2025-02-19 13:46:16'),(1470,'673','App\\Models\\Subsection','Figures',NULL,'[Figure 55] FCIP',2,'67b5e0b9001a8.png','/storage/figures/67b5e0b9001a8.png','2025-02-19 13:46:16','2025-02-19 13:46:33'),(1471,'673','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','FCIP is used to connect a remote SAN. It encapsulates data to TCPIIP for interconnection when transferring a frame to a remote location. It groups the scattered SANs into a massive fiber channel fabric A failure of a SAN can affect SANs in other regions included in the fabric','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 13:46:16','2025-02-19 13:46:16'),(1472,'674','App\\Models\\Subsection','Figures',NULL,'[Figure 56] iFCP',2,'67b5e0b90d55a.png','/storage/figures/67b5e0b90d55a.png','2025-02-19 13:46:16','2025-02-19 13:46:33'),(1473,'674','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','iFCP provides a TCPIIP connection dedicated to regional SAN, using the iFCP gateway Unlike FCIP, a SAN failure does not affect SAN in other regions, since it does not create a massive fabric Since it converts protocols using a gateway and can be implemented without changing the infrastructure, it provides highly compatible interconnectivity in both hardware and software','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 13:46:16','2025-02-19 13:46:16'),(1474,'675','App\\Models\\Subsection','Figures',NULL,'[Figure 57] iSCSI',2,'67b5e0b91c490.png','/storage/figures/67b5e0b91c490.png','2025-02-19 13:46:16','2025-02-19 13:46:33'),(1475,'675','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','iSCSI encapsulates SCSI commands into IP packets and transfer the IO block data through TCPIIP Technologies like IPSec ensure reliability: It reduces the network storage implementation cost, since it can use the existing network environment asis.','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 13:46:16','2025-02-19 13:46:16'),(1476,'676','App\\Models\\Subsection','Figures',NULL,'',2,'67b5e0b932197.png','/storage/figures/67b5e0b932197.png','2025-02-19 13:46:16','2025-02-19 13:46:33'),(1477,'676','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','The existing fixed-allocation storage technology uses a thick logical unit number (LUN) wasted data storage spac Thin provisioning is a storage virtualization technology that allocates data by mapping actual data space into a th LUN It can flexibly expand the disk space required by users in cloud computing, and it offers a higher data utilizatic rate than the conventional thick LUN tvpe','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 13:46:16','2025-02-19 13:46:16'),(1478,'677','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','The technology provides a high efficiency of disk space used by removing any duplicated data when saving the dat The removal methods include an inline method, which immediately removes redundant data as it enters the storag system, and an offline method, which removes the redundant data after storing the new data.','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 13:46:16','2025-02-19 13:46:16'),(1479,'678','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','A disk drive that stores data is a device using a rotating magnetic disk When inputs and outputs are requested to disk drive, the system performance varies significantly, according to which request is processed first, and the proc in moving the head to access the data. Disk scheduling is a technique of efficiently processing IJO requests, V multiple users request them, in order to process different tasks Using disk scheduling has the following purposes: Maximization of IO requests to service during a unit time Maximization throughput per unit time Minimization of the mean response time Minimization of response time Minimization of the variation of response time','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 13:46:16','2025-02-19 13:46:16'),(1480,'679','App\\Models\\Subsection','Figures',NULL,'[Figure 58] Inexpensive Thin Provisioning',2,'67b5e0b944de0.png','/storage/figures/67b5e0b944de0.png','2025-02-19 13:46:16','2025-02-19 13:46:33'),(1481,'679','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','Disk scheduling can be compared with the indicators that measure disk performance Disk performance measuremen indicators include the access time, seeking time, rotational delay or rotational latency and data transfer time','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 13:46:16','2025-02-19 13:46:16'),(1482,'679','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','The seeking time indicates how it takes to move the head from the current head position, to the track containing the data The rotational latency indicates how it takes from the moment the head begins rotating to move to the track containing the data, to the moment it reaches the sector that contains the data Seeking time is the time it takes to move the head the current head position, to the track containing the data. Recent disk drives minimize the rotational latency by having an interal buffer and by storing al the data in the track long long from within the buffer The data transfer time indicates how it takes to transfer the read data to the main memory: The access time is the sum of the seeking time, the rotational latency, and the data transfer time This section describes techniques to minimize the access time by minimizing the seeking time ad the rotational latency long','',3,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 13:46:16','2025-02-19 13:46:16'),(1483,'680','App\\Models\\Subsection','Figures',NULL,'[Figure 60] FCFS Disk Scheduling',2,'67b5e0b95446f.png','/storage/figures/67b5e0b95446f.png','2025-02-19 13:46:16','2025-02-19 13:46:33'),(1484,'680','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','FCFS services the requests in the order are received. The head position moves in the order of the requested tracks in the disk standby queue. It is easy to program and provides fair service to all requests. However, the head movement may be inefficient, and it can unnecessarily increase the response time The execution sequence does not even when it receives a priority request they change,','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 13:46:16','2025-02-19 13:46:16'),(1485,'681','App\\Models\\Subsection','Figures',NULL,'[Figure 61] SSTF Disk Scheduling',2,'67b5e0b961ee5.png','/storage/figures/67b5e0b961ee5.png','2025-02-19 13:46:16','2025-02-19 13:46:33'),(1486,'681','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','The scheduling technique first services the request that is closest to the current head position, among the requested services waiting in the queue It minimizes head movement because it takes a lot of time to move the head in the disk drive: It maximizes the service response rate per unit time by minimizing the head movement in order to process the queue requests The response time variation can increase depending on where the requested input or output data is on the disk It can cause starvation for the requests seeking data that are positioned in the inner or outer cylinder It offers a higher processing rate and a shorter mean response time than FCFS.','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 13:46:16','2025-02-19 13:46:16'),(1487,'682','App\\Models\\Subsection','Figures',NULL,'[Figure 62] SCAN Disk Scheduling',2,'67b5e0b96f166.png','/storage/figures/67b5e0b96f166.png','2025-02-19 13:46:16','2025-02-19 13:46:33'),(1488,'682','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','The scheduling technique first services the request that has the shortest seeking distance from the current direction of the moving head. It can reduce the response time variation of SSTF, and it generally offers excellent throughput per unit time ad mean response time. On determining the heading direction, the head services all the requests waiting in the request queue in the same direction as the order of the shortest search distance, ad it changes the seeking direction after it reaches the outermost or innermost cylinder It has improved both the throughput per unit time and the response time significantly compared to SSTF, and it solved the starvation','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 13:46:16','2025-02-19 13:46:16'),(1489,'683','App\\Models\\Subsection','Figures',NULL,'[Figure 63] LOOK Disk Scheduling',2,'67b5e0b97be47.png','/storage/figures/67b5e0b97be47.png','2025-02-19 13:46:16','2025-02-19 13:46:33'),(1490,'683','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','The technique is the same as the SCAN disk scheduling, except that the head changes its direction before reaching the outermost or innermost cylinder It checks the waiting queue while moving the head, and it does not move furtherlt changes direction when there are no more requests in the moving direction:','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 13:46:16','2025-02-19 13:46:16'),(1491,'684','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','The SCAN technique moves the head by connecting the inner and outer tracks in a circular model Like SCAN disk scheduling, the head services the request with the shortest distance in its moving direction first, then it moves to the initial direction to service requests after all the requests in the moving direction are serviced It services all requests in a predetermined service direction Since it responds equally to input and output requests by improving the SCAN scheduling, the response time variation is very small, making it easy to predict the response time','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 13:46:16','2025-02-19 13:46:16'),(1492,'685','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','ike C-SCAN,itis a LOOK scheduling technique that connects the inner and outer tracks in an annular model in order make the head move. The head moves to the initial beginning position and services the next requests, if there are 10 more requests in the moving direction, even when the head does not reach the end.','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 13:46:16','2025-02-19 13:46:16'),(1493,'686','App\\Models\\Subsection','Figures',NULL,'[Figure 64] RAID-0',2,'67b5e0b98922b.png','/storage/figures/67b5e0b98922b.png','2025-02-19 13:46:16','2025-02-19 13:46:33'),(1494,'686','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','RAID-0 consists of two or more drives and uses disk striping, which stores data by dividing it into pieces of a specific size and saves it on multiple disks at once. Although it increases the IJO it cannot protect data because there is no redundancy: A stripe, which means the size of the stored data, is a unit for dividing data into pieces of a specific size. RAID-0 can reduce the IJO time by enabling parallel processing of IO requests However, data is lost if any drive fails. Although the technology is not used much in business environments, RAID-I0 uses it by taking its advantages and overcoming its disadvantages. speed,','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 13:46:16','2025-02-19 13:46:16'),(1495,'687','App\\Models\\Subsection','Figures',NULL,'[Figure 65] RAID-1',2,'67b5e0b9967af.png','/storage/figures/67b5e0b9967af.png','2025-02-19 13:46:16','2025-02-19 13:46:33'),(1496,'687','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','RAID-1 uses & mirroring technique that redundantly stores data on two drives. Since data is stored in redundancy data can be restored, even if a drive fails. It can improve the reading performance, but the writing performance is somewhat low, since it performs reading operations on a drive with low IO. Although the system is highly stable, the cost is high because only half of the physical capacity can be used, as the other half is used for redundant storage','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 13:46:16','2025-02-19 13:46:16'),(1497,'688','App\\Models\\Subsection','Figures',NULL,'[Figure 66] RAID-5',2,'67b5e0b9a647b.png','/storage/figures/67b5e0b9a647b.png','2025-02-19 13:46:16','2025-02-19 13:46:33'),(1498,'688','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','RAID-4 has a separate parity drive and collects and stores parities for data verification and recovery RAID-5 is an improvement of RAID-4 by distributing the load of the drive that stores the parities. At least three drives are required, and the data and parity are stored by distributing them to different drives. It is highly effective in cost and performance, and recently, most SSDs are configured in RAID-5. If three drives are configured, data cannot be restored if two or more drives fail,','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 13:46:16','2025-02-19 13:46:16'),(1499,'689','App\\Models\\Subsection','Figures',NULL,'[Figure 67] RAID-6',2,'67b5e0b9b55d3.png','/storage/figures/67b5e0b9b55d3.png','2025-02-19 13:46:16','2025-02-19 13:46:33'),(1500,'689','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','RAID-6 is similar to RAID-5, except that while RAID-5 stores one parity, RAID-6 redundantly stores a parity in two drives The configuration is more durable than RAID-5 and can store data safely: In a RAID-5 configuration, the rebuild time restores data to the new drive when a drive fails and is replaced. The rebuilding takes a time in a storage system with a large storage capacity: If another drive fails this rebuilding time, there is a possibility of data loss Therefore, RAID-6 is recommended, long during','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 13:46:16','2025-02-19 13:46:16'),(1501,'690','App\\Models\\Subsection','Figures',NULL,'[Figure 68] RAID-10',2,'67b5e0b9c7331.png','/storage/figures/67b5e0b9c7331.png','2025-02-19 13:46:16','2025-02-19 13:46:33'),(1502,'690','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','RAID-10 requires at least four drives and is a combination of RAID-0 and RAID-1 to improve IJO speed while providing data stability It eliminates the concern with stability, which is an important drawback of RAID-0, and it can significantly improve performance, which is the biggest drawback of RAID-1. However its disadvantage is that the cost is high RAID 1 0 configures two drives in mirroring first, then RAID-1 drives, configured of two drives, are configured in RAID-0. RAID 0 1 divides the drives to be configured in half configures them in RAID-0, and reconfigures Vz of the drives and the remaining 1/2 of the drives in RAID-1. The RAID-10 configuration features better stability and generally uses RAID-10 more than RAID-0 1.','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 13:46:16','2025-02-19 13:46:16'),(1503,'486','App\\Models\\Section','Text','Large-capacity storage systems generally have an error controller and backup tunction to sately store the massive volume of data RAID technology is a storage technology that minimizes the factors that can cause failure, ad it improves access performance by arranging a number of disks, and by creating a separate disk unit by them with each other The main features of RAID are improved availability, increased capacity, and increased Firstly, the improved availability feature provides a hot-swap function to replace a failed disk without shutting down the system, and it recovers the original data to the replaced disk online Secondly, the increased capacity feature organizes several disks into a large virtual disk, and it recognizes them as large-capacity storage disks Thirdly, the increased speed improves the overall data transfer rate by partitioning reading and writing data, and by transferring it to multiple disks in parallel RAID implementation includes RAID-0, 1,2,3,4 5,6,and 10. RAID-0, RAID-I, RAID-5, RAID-6, and RAID-I0 (1 0 or 0 1) are widely used technologies, while RAID-2, RAID-3,and RAID-4 are rarely used. linking speed','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 13:46:16','2025-02-19 13:46:16'),(1504,'691','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','LTO is a standard open tape drive technology that supports high-speed data processing and a large capacity: Although LTO refers to physical devices and technology, are also used interchangeably: It is also called the tape backup machine, tape media machine, LTO machine, LTO library, and LTO. LTO-1, first released in 2000, provided a maximum speed of 20 MB/s at a uncompressed capacity of 100 GB. The LTO-8 that is currently available, supports the performance of a maximum of 427MB/s based on a uncompressed capacity of 12.8TB. The LTO-10 is expected to provide a maximum speed of 1IOOMBIs at an uncompressed capacity of 48TB. they speed','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 13:46:16','2025-02-19 13:46:16'),(1505,'692','App\\Models\\Subsection','Figures',NULL,'[Figure 69] VTL Conceptual Diagram',2,'67b5e0b9d60c9.png','/storage/figures/67b5e0b9d60c9.png','2025-02-19 13:46:16','2025-02-19 13:46:33'),(1506,'692','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','VTL is a backup solution that emulates disk storage and makes it into a virtual tape device to compensate problems such as limited performance, scalability, ad the recovery time of existing tape backup devices. Backup simplified, and high-speed backup is enabled through tape virtualization.','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 13:46:16','2025-02-19 13:46:16'),(1507,'693','App\\Models\\Subsection','Tables',NULL,'(Table 15) Lossless Compression',2,'67b5e0b9ecc18.png','/storage/tables/67b5e0b9ecc18.png','2025-02-19 13:46:16','2025-02-19 13:46:33'),(1508,'693','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','Since the compression and decompression algorithms are exactly the opposite of each other, the compression method preserves the original data\'s integrity, and no part of the data is lost processing: Leading lossless compression methods include run-length decoding, dictionary decoding, Huffman coding, dictionary coding, and arithmetic coding: during','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 13:46:16','2025-02-19 13:46:16'),(1509,'694','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','The lossy compression method compromises some accuracy to increase the compression rate, by allowing the loss of redundant or unnecessary data. There are two types of compression methods: prediction coding ad transform coding: The prediction coding method is used for digitizing the analog signal. Instead of separately quantizing the PCM (Pulse Code Modulation) samples it quantizes the difference: The difference values are smaller than the actual sample values, so fewer bits are required. The transform coding method transforms a signal from one domain (mainly a time and space domain) to another domain (mainly a frequency domain), then compresses it lossy','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 13:46:16','2025-02-19 13:46:16'),(1510,'488','App\\Models\\Section','Text','Video data compression, which accounts for most of the traffic in a multimedia network, can be divided into lossless compression (reversible compression) and lossy compression (irreversible compression): Lossless compression is also called reversible compression.lt refers to a method of restoring a compressed image without information loss from the original data while decompressing: It is characterized by a lower compression rate than compression. Lossy compression is also called irreversible compressionlt refers to a compression method when the compressed data is restored, but it does not match the original data before the compression because some data is lost lossy','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 13:46:16','2025-02-19 13:46:16'),(1511,'695','App\\Models\\Subsection','Tables',NULL,'<Table 16  Compression Format and Additional Standard',2,'67b5e0ba12c62.png','/storage/tables/67b5e0ba12c62.png','2025-02-19 13:46:16','2025-02-19 13:46:34'),(1512,'695','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','The Moving Picture Experts Group (MPEG) is a international standardization organization The official name of the standard is ISOJIEC JTCI/SCZINGII. MPEG created the following compression formats and additional standards','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 13:46:16','2025-02-19 13:46:16'),(1513,'695','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','Ivanced video coding (AVC) and high efficiency video coding (HVEC','',3,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 13:46:16','2025-02-19 13:46:16'),(1514,'696','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','AVC codec is a video compression technology jointly proposed by the international standard organizations ITU-L and ISO. It uses the name H.264, proposed by ITU-T, or MPEG4 PartIOJAVC, proposed by ISO. The standard name fo HEVC is ISOJIEC 23008-2 by ISOJIEC','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 13:46:16','2025-02-19 13:46:16'),(1515,'489','App\\Models\\Section','Figures',NULL,'[Figure 70] Image Data Transformation Process',2,'67b5e0ba2934a.png','/storage/figures/67b5e0ba2934a.png','2025-02-19 13:46:16','2025-02-19 13:46:34'),(1516,'489','App\\Models\\Section','Text','Multimedia data includes text,, image, video, and audio data. The text has the form of plain text and non-linear hypertext: The basic language is Unicode for expressing symbols, and it uses a lossless compression method In multimedia, an image is called a still image and refers to a photo, fax page, or a video frame As shown in [Figure 70], an image is transmitted as data through a transformation process, a quantization process, and an encoding process, before converted back into an image through the reverse process In the transformation process the JPEG uses DCT (Discrete Cosine Transform) in the first stage of compression, and the decompression uses the inverse DCT method. The transformation and inverse transformation apply 8 X 8 blocks. The quantization process creates integers from the real number of the DCT transform output ad converts some values to zero The coding process arranges data in a zigzag order after quantization and before encoder input, then lossless compression is performed using run-length decoding and arithmetic coding [1]. binary being','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 13:46:16','2025-02-19 13:46:16'),(1517,'489','App\\Models\\Section','Text','Video data is composed of several frames Since each frame is an image, a video file requires a high transmission rate Video data can be compressed with a spatial compression or a temporal compression method. JPEG performs spatial compression of each frame, and each frame is compressed independently: Temporal compression removes redundant frames and configures each frame into I-frames, which are independent frames, B-frames, and P-frames, which reference other I-frames to compress data temporally: Analog audio signals are digitized using a analog-to-digital converter (ADC) , and the ADC consists of two processes: sampling and quantization','',3,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 13:46:16','2025-02-19 13:46:16'),(1518,'490','App\\Models\\Section','Tables',NULL,'(Table 17) Examples of Embedded System',4,'67b5e0ba45736.png','/storage/tables/67b5e0ba45736.png','2025-02-19 13:46:17','2025-02-19 13:46:34'),(1519,'490','App\\Models\\Section','Figures',NULL,'[Figure 71] Embedded System Configuration',2,'67b5e0ba61ff7.png','/storage/figures/67b5e0ba61ff7.png','2025-02-19 13:46:17','2025-02-19 13:46:34'),(1520,'490','App\\Models\\Section','Text','An embedded system is a computer system that performs a specific function for controlling a machine or other systems requiring control, and an electronic system in the device In more detail, it is a with a built-in microprocessor and a program that drives the microprocessor to perform specific function, more than just simple circuits in various electronic devices, home appliances, and control devices used in our daily life An embedded system is configured of a set of hardware and software, as shown in [Figure 71]. Embedded hardware: Embedded hardware consists of a microprocessorlmicrocontroller, equivalent to a CPU, memory, input/output device, network device, sensor, driver, etc Embedded software: Embedded software consists of an operating system (OS) that directly controls hardware and manages the software, software, ad application software: Unlike conventional software, the main purpose of the embedded software is to provide a appropriate response to the physical world. Therefore, embedded software has the characteristics of the physical world, such as time, energy, and permanence system system','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 13:46:17','2025-02-19 13:46:17'),(1521,'490','App\\Models\\Section','Text','Embedded systems control many devices used in everyday life. As shown in <Table 17  , embedded systems are usec in a wide range of areas, portable digital watches and health bands, to large fixed facilities, such as traffic lights factory control devices, and nuclear power plant control systems from','',3,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 13:46:17','2025-02-19 13:46:17'),(1522,'697','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','embedded systems are mass-produced in units of millions and the reduction of production costs is one of the crucial factors. Some embedded systems that do not require high processing performance or resources can have relatively slow processor and small memory in order to reduce costs Many','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 13:46:17','2025-02-19 13:46:17'),(1523,'698','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','Many embedded system have low performance: Here, being slow does not simply refer to a slow clock speed. In parts general, an embedded system\'s overall structure is intentionally simplified to reduce cost, compared to the hardware of general-purpose computer systems For example, embedded systems often use peripherals controlled by a serial bus that is 1024 times slower than the conventional peripheral interfaces that are used in personal computers.','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 13:46:17','2025-02-19 13:46:17'),(1524,'699','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','Programs on embedded systems usually operate with real-time constraints on limited hardware resources There is ften no disk drive, operating system, keyboard, or screen on the system. It may not have a file system, or it may use  flash drive as a storage medium: Even if there is a user interface, it could be a small keypad or LCD.','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 13:46:17','2025-02-19 13:46:17'),(1525,'700','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','Embedded systems are designed to run reliably, without error, for many years. Therefore, firmware goes through a more careful development and testing process than the software used in personal computers Most embedded systems avoid the use of parts damaged by mechanical actions, such as disk drives, switches, and buttons Instead, use chip materials that are relatively free from physical damage, such as flash memory: they \'.','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 13:46:17','2025-02-19 13:46:17'),(1526,'701','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','Embedded systems may be applied in places where it is difficult for humans to immediately and directly control, such as oil boreholes ad outer space: Therefore, an embedded system must be able to restart itself even in the worst- case scenario An electronic part, called a watchdog timer\' enables such an emergency recovery:','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 13:46:17','2025-02-19 13:46:17'),(1527,'491','App\\Models\\Section','Text','Since an embedded system performs a specific mission, engineers can optimize the design in order to reduce the size and production cost and to increase reliability and performance','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 13:46:17','2025-02-19 13:46:17'),(1528,'492','App\\Models\\Section','Tables',NULL,'',5,'67b5e0baafc6a.png','/storage/tables/67b5e0baafc6a.png','2025-02-19 13:46:17','2025-02-19 13:46:34'),(1529,'492','App\\Models\\Section','Figures',NULL,'[Figure 72] Embedded System Development Procedure',2,'67b5e0bada3c0.png','/storage/figures/67b5e0bada3c0.png','2025-02-19 13:46:17','2025-02-19 13:46:34'),(1530,'492','App\\Models\\Section','Text','An embedded system is developed by the procedure, shown in [Figure 72] Unlike conventional information system development, it includes a hardware development process 5 Watchdog Timer (WDT): An electronic timer used to detect ad recover computer failure Computers in normal operation restart the watchdog timer periodically to prevent a timeout','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 13:46:17','2025-02-19 13:46:17'),(1531,'492','App\\Models\\Section','Text','<Table 18  below shows details of the above development procedure','',3,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 13:46:17','2025-02-19 13:46:17'),(1532,'493','App\\Models\\Section','Tables',NULL,'(Table 19) Embedded Processor Types',2,'67b5e0baf28de.png','/storage/tables/67b5e0baf28de.png','2025-02-19 13:46:17','2025-02-19 13:46:34'),(1533,'493','App\\Models\\Section','Text','An embedded system can handle more functions and performance because the processor provides the performance required to drive the device. Early microprocessor units (MPUs) were made in a single chip, in which registers data processing, arithmetic logic unit (ALU) for mathematical operation, and for storing result values were integrated into a chip. Although CPU and MPU were separated according to use ad purpose in the past, the boundaries now are somewhat ambiguous Since then, microcontrollers, with a built-in processor, memory, and control interface on single chip, have emerged to be used for real-time operating systems or automatic controls flags t is not far-fetched to consider that the MPU is included in all the electronic devices that are open to user ntervention in its use or configuration It is currently used in smartphones, smart bands, and tablet PCs that are used in daily life It is also used in mechanical keyboards that provide functions, such as various shortcut and infinite inputs. It is also in a TV or air conditioneras well as in the remote control that controls the TV and air conditioner: Moreover, it is in game consoles, car trip computers, and smart While Intel and AMD are everything when it comes to CPU for computers, many companies make MPUs. Many companies, like Broadcom, Mediatek, Samsung Electronics, Apple, Nvidia, Qualcomm, and Texas Instruments, make MPUs used in electronic devices As shown in <Table 19  , various CPU architectures, 8-bit to 64-bit, such as ARM, MIPS, ColdFire/68K, PowerPC, x86, PIC microcontroller, and 8051, are used for embedded systems That is what differentiates the embedded system market from the personal computer market Moreover, one of the latest trends of embedded systems is the System on Chip (SoC) concept that integrates all ICs for a specific field into a single CPU chip in order to eliminate the need to mount separate peripheral chips on the board keys key\' keys: from','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 13:46:17','2025-02-19 13:46:17'),(1534,'702','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','Studies of applying connectivity technologies, such as WiFi, LTE, BLE, and ZigBee,, used by mobile devices and servers/PCs, to embedded systems, have increased with the convergence of the IT industry Traditional industries and interoperability between devices, such as loT and MZM sensor networks, have also become important','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 13:46:17','2025-02-19 13:46:17'),(1535,'703','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','Processors for embedded systems were mostly converted from 8 bits to 32 bits. As such, the number of embedded systems using an OS has rapidly increased, and the portion of general-purpose OS, like Linux has significantlvincreased','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 13:46:17','2025-02-19 13:46:17'),(1536,'704','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','Embedded operating systems, supporting wearables and loT devices, require lighter weight and lower power consumption, while operating systems applied to conventional embedded devices include middleware, related to high functionality and stability and convenience functions like 3D acceleration GUl and multimedia As a result, technology polarization is accelerating,','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 13:46:17','2025-02-19 13:46:17'),(1537,'495','App\\Models\\Section','Tables',NULL,'(Table 20} Technology Fields and Examples of Embedded Software',2,'67b5e0bb1520f.png','/storage/tables/67b5e0bb1520f.png','2025-02-19 13:46:17','2025-02-19 13:46:35'),(1538,'495','App\\Models\\Section','Text','Embedded software refers to software installed in embedded systems. As the application fields of embedded systems diversify, embedded software is becoming increasingly complex to handle various functions As shown in <Table 20  , the main technology fields of embedded software can be classified into basic embedded applications, embedded middleware,, embedded system software,, embedded system development tools, and embedded software platforms','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 13:46:17','2025-02-19 13:46:17'),(1539,'496','App\\Models\\Section','Tables',NULL,'',3,'67b5e0bb2f0b3.png','/storage/tables/67b5e0bb2f0b3.png','2025-02-19 13:46:17','2025-02-19 13:46:35'),(1540,'496','App\\Models\\Section','Text','Embedded software is embedded in a physical product and continuously interacts with the physical environment: In other words, it must continuously receive and process signals from the physical environment. In some cases, it is necessary to receive the user\'s requirements and respond to them, by considering changes in the physical environment. There are also cases, such as computers and smartphones, where it only responds to user requirements Therefore, embedded software has characteristics, such as reactivity, timeliness, concurrency heterogeneity, liveness, resource and environmental constraints, and determinism. <Table 21  below shows features of each characteristic,','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 13:46:17','2025-02-19 13:46:17'),(1541,'497','App\\Models\\Section','Text','An embedded OS is an operating system that is optimized to execute the application programs running on a computer that perform specific functions for controlling a machine or other systems It is optimized for a specific system that has hardware with a built-in microprocessor, and it performs set purposes. In the early embedded systems the hardware was directly controlled using the assembly language, ad it operated without a separate OS. However, as the embedded system applications have diversified, the need to use a OS has increased system','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 13:46:17','2025-02-19 13:46:17'),(1542,'498','App\\Models\\Section','Tables',NULL,'(Table 22) Embedded OS Application',4,'67b5e0bb49079.png','/storage/tables/67b5e0bb49079.png','2025-02-19 13:46:17','2025-02-19 13:46:35'),(1543,'498','App\\Models\\Section','Figures',NULL,'[Figure 73] Embedded OS Structure',2,'67b5e0bb5efa3.png','/storage/figures/67b5e0bb5efa3.png','2025-02-19 13:46:17','2025-02-19 13:46:35'),(1544,'498','App\\Models\\Section','Text','As shown in [Figure 73], an embedded OS generally has a structure to support the stable application program execution with a low-specification processor, a limited memory and storage device, and poor operating environment conditions','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 13:46:17','2025-02-19 13:46:17'),(1545,'498','App\\Models\\Section','Text','Technologies applied to embedded OS can be characterized by real-time, small/lightweight, and low power consumption, as shown in <Table 22  .','',3,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 13:46:17','2025-02-19 13:46:17'),(1546,'499','App\\Models\\Section','Code',NULL,'[Figure 74] Status of Embedded OS Use (2017)',2,'67b5e0bb754e3.png','/storage/code/67b5e0bb754e3.png','2025-02-19 13:46:17','2025-02-19 13:46:35'),(1547,'499','App\\Models\\Section','Text','Embedded software runs in a wide range of devices and supports many operating systems: However, it is largely divided into real-time operating systems that must satisfy conditions to operate within a set time, and operating systems that do not Real-time OS (RTOS): Mainly focuses on controlling application programs or hardware affected by a limited amount of time: The operating systems include VxWorks, VRTX, QNX, and pSOS. Non real-time OS: Mainly focuses on development convenience, scalability, and diverse operating environments. The leading operating systems include Linux series, embedded Window XP and Windows CE leading \" Traditionally an embedded OS was used because systems, such as satellites ad missile controllers, that must have flawless protection errors needed to have an OS optimized for real-time systems In that case, the systems used RTOS, instead of a general-purpose OS. However, one of the latest trends in embedded OS technology is that the portion of Linux and free RTOS is steadily increasing, when compared to traditional embedded RTOS, such as VxWorks, pSOS, QNX, and VRTX, which have led the existing information home appliance market and other embedded application industries (see [Figure 74]). Linux is installed in about 65% of all embedded devices and is still growing very fast, at an annual average of 17%. Meanwhile, the UK\'s FreeRTOS is rapidly expanding its base The market share is around 50%,which makes it the de- facto standard. In addition to FreeRTOS, ARMs mbed, which was recently acquired by Softbank in Japan, is spreading rapidly: Of course, commercial products are still leading in markets that require a high degree of safety, such as in tomobiloc Jircnftc 9n ia against','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 13:46:17','2025-02-19 13:46:17'),(1548,'500','App\\Models\\Section','Figures',NULL,'[Figure 75] Information System and IT-Based Structure',2,'67b5e0bb88ee8.png','/storage/figures/67b5e0bb88ee8.png','2025-02-19 13:46:18','2025-02-19 13:46:35'),(1549,'500','App\\Models\\Section','Text','An information system uses information technology (IT) to perform business procedures, such as providing necessary information, or business processing required by enterprises It creates a system that enables IT personnel to provide IT services by using IT components, such as hardware ad software, to perform organizational business procedures As shown in [Figure 75], the information system provides services by using the technology resources of the IT infrastructure The IT infrastructure includes computing platforms, such as networks, hardware, software, IT personnel, and IT services:','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 13:46:18','2025-02-19 13:46:18'),(1550,'705','App\\Models\\Subsection','Tables',NULL,'',4,'67b5e0bbabb21.png','/storage/tables/67b5e0bbabb21.png','2025-02-19 13:46:18','2025-02-19 13:46:35'),(1551,'705','App\\Models\\Subsection','Figures',NULL,'[Figure 77] Information System Hardware Configuration (Example)',6,'67b5e0bbcb787.png','/storage/figures/67b5e0bbcb787.png','2025-02-19 13:46:18','2025-02-19 13:46:35'),(1552,'705','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','A server is the most fundamental component required when implementing an information system, and devices,such as storage and backup disks, are added and configured as needed A server is a hardware platform that runs server application programs and is classified in various ways, according to performance and type as follows Classification according to performance','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 13:46:18','2025-02-19 13:46:18'),(1553,'705','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','Classification according to the configuration','',3,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 13:46:18','2025-02-19 13:46:18'),(1554,'705','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','Storage is classified into enterprise or mid-range storage, according to processing capacity It provides a large storage space, high performance, and high availability, compared to general disk arrays. space, high performance, and high availability, compared to general disk arrays. [Figure 77] below shows an example of an information hardware configuration, using a server ad various devices A system architecture or technical architecture design describes its details system [Figure 77] below shows an example of a information system hardware configuration, using a server and various devices A system architecture or technical architecture design describes its details','',5,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 13:46:18','2025-02-19 13:46:18'),(1555,'706','App\\Models\\Subsection','Figures',NULL,'[Figure 78] Webserver',2,'67b5e0bbdf153.png','/storage/figures/67b5e0bbdf153.png','2025-02-19 13:46:18','2025-02-19 13:46:35'),(1556,'706','App\\Models\\Subsection','Figures',NULL,'[Figure 79] WAS',4,'67b5e0bbedc00.png','/storage/figures/67b5e0bbedc00.png','2025-02-19 13:46:18','2025-02-19 13:46:35'),(1557,'706','App\\Models\\Subsection','Figures',NULL,'[Figure 80] DB Server',6,'67b5e0bc07dd5.png','/storage/figures/67b5e0bc07dd5.png','2025-02-19 13:46:18','2025-02-19 13:46:36'),(1558,'706','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','OS: An OS is defined as system software that operates and manages a application platform and that provides an interface between an application program ad the platform The OS for the server includes Linux, UNIX (BSD, Solaris etc ), Windows, and macOS. The OS for the server market is quite different from the desktop market, which is dominated by Windows Linux and UNIX are the most widely used OS, followed by Windows. UNIX servers have replaced most mainframes, and they were followed by Linux,which is a UNIX-like OS. ebserver: A webserver provides media content, such as HTML and text, images, ad video, to web clients lik eb browsers It provides data through the HTTP protocol to enable a web browser to present information Leadin ebserver products include Apache, Nginx and IIS (see [Figure 78]).','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 13:46:18','2025-02-19 13:46:18'),(1559,'706','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','Web application server (WAS): A WAS is a middleware that enables the stable transaction processing of web client requests and helps develop the distributed systems It is an engine for database queries or business logic processing which supports component development and use, application development, web, distributed objects, security, IED, system management, ad interface to legacy systems Leading WAS products include Tomcat, Jetty, JEUS, JBoss, WebLogic, WebSphere, and Nodejs (see [Figure 79]).','',3,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 13:46:18','2025-02-19 13:46:18'),(1560,'706','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','Transaction processing (TP) monitor: A TP-monitor is transaction management middleware that supports the distributed transaction processing and monitors transactions, which are the minimum processing units between active sessions and systems in various protocols, in order to maintain them consistently: Most TP-monitor products comply with the DTP (distributed transaction process) model specified by XOpen, the UNIX environment standardization organization The leading TP-monitor products include Tmax and Tuxedo. DB server (Database management system, DBMS): A DB server provides the database type, database management technology, and query language for the access to ad modification of structural data. It is large-scale storage of consolidated data with minimum duplication and is used by multiple users concurrently: It provides independence between application programs and data and efficient access to data through queries The system catalog is the tool for database administrators (DBAs) and & table that lists the definitions or statements of all data objects stored in the database The leading DBMS products include Oracle, MS-SQL, PostgreSQL, Maria and Cubrid (see [Figure 807) system DB,','',5,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 13:46:18','2025-02-19 13:46:18'),(1561,'501','App\\Models\\Section','Figures',NULL,'[Figure 76] 3-Tier Web System Architecture',2,'67b5e0bc19a90.png','/storage/figures/67b5e0bc19a90.png','2025-02-19 13:46:18','2025-02-19 13:46:36'),(1562,'501','App\\Models\\Section','Text','There are several types of structures for an information A web architecture and a client-serv architecture are leading examples The most recent information systems are generally composed of a 3-t web system architecture, and these information systems can be divided into physical areas (hardware) and progra areas (software) , as shown in [Figure 76], from a structural viewpoint system. system Isystem','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 13:46:18','2025-02-19 13:46:18'),(1563,'502','App\\Models\\Section','Tables',NULL,'',4,'67b5e0bc4ac25.png','/storage/tables/67b5e0bc4ac25.png','2025-02-19 13:46:18','2025-02-19 13:46:36'),(1564,'502','App\\Models\\Section','Text','System sizing is to estimate or calculate a system\' $ size using a mathematical methodology, based on actual work and applications. It can be defined as a lower-level concept of capacity planning or capacity management to determine performance requirements and performance based on the system architecture application, as shown in [Figure 81]. Sizing is temporarily performed for a specific system or server, and it is also called size estimation because bac nradictiva natura','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 13:46:18','2025-02-19 13:46:18'),(1565,'502','App\\Models\\Section','Text','Sizing is a matter of prediction, and the calculation method significantly affects the accuracy of the calculation Hardiware size calculation methods are generally classified into the mathematical calculation, reference, and simulation methods, as shown in [Figure 82]. It is necessary to apply an appropriate sizing method to get accurate sizing: This guideline uses a mathematical calculation method However, it is necessary to use all three methods appropriately for cize calculation in order to increace the accuraci the calculation recultc and obiectii','',3,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 13:46:18','2025-02-19 13:46:18'),(1566,'503','App\\Models\\Section','Tables',NULL,'[Figure 84] Performance Standard Applicable for CPU and Storage',4,'67b5e0bc69a3a.png','/storage/tables/67b5e0bc69a3a.png','2025-02-19 13:46:18','2025-02-19 13:46:36'),(1567,'503','App\\Models\\Section','Figures',NULL,'[Figure 83] Size Calculation Target',2,'67b5e0bc79f7e.png','/storage/figures/67b5e0bc79f7e.png','2025-02-19 13:46:18','2025-02-19 13:46:36'),(1568,'503','App\\Models\\Section','Text','Generally, the target for sizing includes not only hardware, but also software or network As shown in [Figure 83], the size calculation target in the capacity calculation guidelines is hardware, which is defined as servers, not PCs or other peripherals While there are several hardware configuration areas, the four areas CPU, memory disk, and storage are the most important in terms of system price and performance, and are defined by sizing areas they - CPU: Calculates the CPU size to process the necessary tasks and selects the server model that shows adequate performance Memory: Calculate memory usage by the software and applications programs for each server, based on the server configuration, according to the CPU size Disk: Calculates disk usage by the OS, system software, database, and database archive/backup for each server based on the server configuration, according to the CPU size Storage: Calculates the size of the needed storage, based on the server size, according to the CPU: system','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 13:46:18','2025-02-19 13:46:18'),(1569,'503','App\\Models\\Section','Text','Then apply the performance standard for each size calculation target, as shown in [Figure 84]','',3,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 13:46:18','2025-02-19 13:46:18'),(1570,'504','App\\Models\\Section','Figures',NULL,'[Figure 85] 3-Tier Architecture',2,'67b5e0bc8b5db.png','/storage/figures/67b5e0bc8b5db.png','2025-02-19 13:46:18','2025-02-19 13:46:36'),(1571,'504','App\\Models\\Section','Figures',NULL,'[Figure 86] Reference Model for 3-Tier Physical Server Configuration',4,'67b5e0bca61ca.png','/storage/figures/67b5e0bca61ca.png','2025-02-19 13:46:18','2025-02-19 13:46:36'),(1572,'504','App\\Models\\Section','Text','nce the size is calculated for each server the person who calculates the size needs to understand the conceptu odel of the overall system architecture that is to be implemented. Most information systems nowadays ha\' Jopted the 3-tier architecture, as shown in [Figure 85].','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 13:46:18','2025-02-19 13:46:18'),(1573,'504','App\\Models\\Section','Text','The government standard suggests three types of reference architectures, as shown in [Figure 86], to establish th standard for size calculation and presents the size calculation method for each layer in the architecture for eacl architecture type','',3,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 13:46:18','2025-02-19 13:46:18'),(1574,'707','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','Basic data on the tasks and system to be implemented are necessary to ensure the hardware capacity calculation accuracy: To accurate information,, cooperation with the users is crucial, and the basic task analysis and implementation direction are established through consultation with them get','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 13:46:18','2025-02-19 13:46:18'),(1575,'708','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','If necessary, analyze the newly added workload,as well as the relevance and complexity of each work, and determine each tasks expected load, through the basic data and task analysis results Calculate the reference load by calculating the sum of the expected load for each task Validate the basic data and task analysis,','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 13:46:18','2025-02-19 13:46:18'),(1576,'709','App\\Models\\Subsection','Tables',NULL,'',2,'67b5e0bcc53ae.png','/storage/tables/67b5e0bcc53ae.png','2025-02-19 13:46:18','2025-02-19 13:46:36'),(1577,'709','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','Select the reference model suitable for the architecture type of the calculation target system:','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 13:46:18','2025-02-19 13:46:18'),(1578,'709','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','Select various correction coefficients, based on the task analysis data investigated in Step 2 Calculate the size for each component of the server in the reference model.','',3,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 13:46:18','2025-02-19 13:46:18'),(1579,'710','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','fter the capacity calculation of each item of the server in 3, 4 applies the weight factor for each server ccording to the architecture type Step Step','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 13:46:18','2025-02-19 13:46:18'),(1580,'505','App\\Models\\Section','Figures',NULL,'',1,'67b5e0bcdc074.png','/storage/figures/67b5e0bcdc074.png','2025-02-19 13:46:18','2025-02-19 13:46:36'),(1581,'506','App\\Models\\Section','Text','This section describes how to select the size for each server component. As mentioned in the section for the procedure for size calculation, determine the server, based on the architecture type, and calculate the CPU, memory, disk, and storage sizes for each server Refer to \"TTA Guidelines on Calculating Information System Hardware\" for how to calculate the detailed size of each element','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 13:46:18','2025-02-19 13:46:18'),(1582,'507','App\\Models\\Section','Figures',NULL,'[Figure 89] Availability Calculation Formula',2,'67b5e0bce8a1d.png','/storage/figures/67b5e0bce8a1d.png','2025-02-19 13:46:19','2025-02-19 13:46:36'),(1583,'507','App\\Models\\Section','Figures',NULL,'[Figure 90] Availability Indicators',3,'67b5e0bd03802.png','/storage/figures/67b5e0bd03802.png','2025-02-19 13:46:19','2025-02-19 13:46:37'),(1584,'507','App\\Models\\Section','Text','In information systems, HA refers to an uninterrupted service However, it is not easy to make a system,that consists of numerous parts and software, 100% available There must be no failure, or services must be available to users in a usable state, even at the time of failure, in order to guarantee uninterrupted availability In general, the system fails at some Therefore, the way to guarantee service continuity is to prepare for failure, rather than preventing failure HA prepares for failure by configuring two or more systems using clustering: A typical HA criterion targets 99.999% (called 5 nines) , representing less than 5 minutes and 15 seconds of unplanned service downtime per year The scale of the HA level is expressed by the number of nine, and the formula for calculating the availability is the mean time between failures (MTBF), divided by the sum of the MTBF and the mean time to repair (MTTR) point.','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 13:46:19','2025-02-19 13:46:19'),(1585,'711','App\\Models\\Subsection','Figures',NULL,'[Figure 91] Hot Standby Configuration',2,'67b5e0bd0f3f1.png','/storage/figures/67b5e0bd0f3f1.png','2025-02-19 13:46:19','2025-02-19 13:46:37'),(1586,'711','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','Hot standby is the simplest structure of HA clustering implementation It consists of an active server and a standby server that are normally in a standby state The standby server is powered on, and the operating system is running In some cases, a standby server is used as a development system: If the active server fails, due to hardware, network or process problem, the failure is detected by the heartbeat network and all HA service operations are automatically switched to the standby server, through a fail-over operation,','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 13:46:19','2025-02-19 13:46:19'),(1587,'712','App\\Models\\Subsection','Figures',NULL,'[Figure 92] Mutual Takeover Configuration',2,'67b5e0bd1a393.png','/storage/figures/67b5e0bd1a393.png','2025-02-19 13:46:19','2025-02-19 13:46:37'),(1588,'712','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','The mutual takeover is the case of two or more systems operating with separate servers. When a server fails, its services are switched to the designated server (takeover) to continue the services Each server must have sufficient system capacity in order to provide services for the two servers, in preparation for a fail-over at the time of a failure','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 13:46:19','2025-02-19 13:46:19'),(1589,'713','App\\Models\\Subsection','Figures',NULL,'[Figure 93] Concurrent Access Configuration',2,'67b5e0bd2696d.png','/storage/figures/67b5e0bd2696d.png','2025-02-19 13:46:19','2025-02-19 13:46:37'),(1590,'713','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','It is a structure in which multiple systems process tasks in parallel in order to provide availability: All servers operat in an active state Even if a server fails, the service continuity can be guaranteed without a fail-over In this structur two or more servers perform load balancing, using a L4 switch to perform the same task','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 13:46:19','2025-02-19 13:46:19'),(1591,'509','App\\Models\\Section','Tables',NULL,'',3,'67b5e0bd423d4.png','/storage/tables/67b5e0bd423d4.png','2025-02-19 13:46:19','2025-02-19 13:46:37'),(1592,'509','App\\Models\\Section','Text','A fault-tolerant system can continuously perform the functions specified in the design, even if a system part fails fault-tolerant system cannot use certain functions when a component fails. When components continue to fail, the unavailable functions gradually increase, and the system shuts down when a critical failure occurs','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 13:46:19','2025-02-19 13:46:19'),(1593,'510','App\\Models\\Section','Tables',NULL,'[Table 25] DR Center Types',2,'67b5e0bd63795.png','/storage/tables/67b5e0bd63795.png','2025-02-19 13:46:19','2025-02-19 13:46:37'),(1594,'510','App\\Models\\Section','Text','DRS is a overall plan and system to minimize the impact of a disaster on a business, by locating all or part of the information system infrastructure in a location different the disaster point,then quickly recovering from a disaster from when it occurs','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 13:46:19','2025-02-19 13:46:19'),(1595,'511','App\\Models\\Section','Tables',NULL,'[Table 26] RTO and RPO',2,'67b5e0bd75ce8.png','/storage/tables/67b5e0bd75ce8.png','2025-02-19 13:46:19','2025-02-19 13:46:37'),(1596,'511','App\\Models\\Section','Text','The most important factors to consider when implementing a DR system are RTO and RPO. RTO represents the tin required to return to normal operation, When a disaster or failure occurs in the operating RPO represents indicator of tolerable data loss, i.e,the amount of data that can be lost. system','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 13:46:19','2025-02-19 13:46:19'),(1597,'714','App\\Models\\Subsection','Tables',NULL,'(Table 28) Differentiation between Grid Computing and Cloud Computing',2,'67b5e0bd88f34.png','/storage/tables/67b5e0bd88f34.png','2025-02-19 13:46:19','2025-02-19 13:46:37'),(1598,'714','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','Grid computing is defined as \"a structure for virtualizing ad resources, such as computers ad data, on a network for integration and dynamically creating virtual computers if needed \" Grid computing and cloud computing are similar in that use a distributed computing structure and provide virtualized computing resources. The difference is that computing uses all the computer resources on the Internet, while cloud computing uses only the computing owned hv the onerator they grid','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 13:46:19','2025-02-19 13:46:19'),(1599,'715','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','Utility computing is a type that provides computing resources and charges for the resources used Utility computing and cloud computing are similar, in that charge for the resources used. Cloud computing has developed the abstraction of computing resources, based on utility computing: they','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 13:46:19','2025-02-19 13:46:19'),(1600,'716','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','laaS provides infrastructure resources (server, storage, and network) as a service through the Internet: Although the infrastructure resources provided by laaS are generally in a virtualized environment, it is not a must for laaS. The service that provides non-virtualized physical infrastructure resources is called a bare-metal cloud. laaS users must directly manage areas beyond the OS The service is similar to receiving a server that is hosting from an existing service, provided from the users aspect.','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 13:46:19','2025-02-19 13:46:19'),(1601,'717','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','PaaS is a service method in which the concept of SaaS is applied to the development environment: It uses the necessary development and operating environment as a service without building a development and operation environment: The service scope of PaaS ranges, from the application development environment, to the service distribution and operation environment: PaaS provides the network infrastructure to the runtime for application execution, and the management scope of the user is the applications and data above the application runtime For example, a user developing a new Java web application that uses MySQL as a database, can quickly prepare a development/operation environment, and can quickly develop and service applications, by using PaaS service that provides MySQL and Apache Tomcat','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 13:46:19','2025-02-19 13:46:19'),(1602,'718','App\\Models\\Subsection','Figures',NULL,'[Figure 94] Management Scope of in Each Cloud Service Type',2,'67b5e0bd99b1e.png','/storage/figures/67b5e0bd99b1e.png','2025-02-19 13:46:19','2025-02-19 13:46:37'),(1603,'718','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','SaaS is a service that provides software and is a model that delivers software serviced from the center to users,, through a client, such as a web browser SaaS users can use functions need, without knowing where the software is located, which OS it uses, and in which language it is developed: Leading examples of SaaS include Google Docs and SalesForcecom: SaaS services generally have the following characteristics: Access with a web browser: Access with a web browser, instead of an installed software Usage-based cost: Paying fees, based on software use On-demand: Needed software available immediately IT requirement optimization: No management and scalability issues with the IT infrastructure [Figure 94] shows the management scope of laaS, PaaS, and SaaS users and service providers. they','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 13:46:19','2025-02-19 13:46:19'),(1604,'513','App\\Models\\Section','Text','Cloud services can be classified into laaS (Infrastructure as a Service), PaaS (Platform as a Service), and SaaS (Software as a Service), according to the service type','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 13:46:19','2025-02-19 13:46:19'),(1605,'514','App\\Models\\Section','Tables',NULL,'(Table 29) Cloud Service Type Based on Disclosure Level',2,'67b5e0bdac769.png','/storage/tables/67b5e0bdac769.png','2025-02-19 13:46:19','2025-02-19 13:46:37'),(1606,'514','App\\Models\\Section','Text','Cloud services can be classified into three levels, based on the service operation form: The following table shows th classification.','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 13:46:19','2025-02-19 13:46:19'),(1607,'515','App\\Models\\Section','Text','In server virtualization, a host OS is a physical server and a guest OS is a virtually provided server Server virtualization technology can be classified, according to how a virtual server allocates physical resources in order to make it look like a physical server A hypervisor is a technology of virtualizing a physical server It is a logical platform for server virtualization It is also called a virtual machine monitor (VMM). The hypervisor can be classified by how it is installed and virtualized.','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 13:46:19','2025-02-19 13:46:19'),(1608,'719','App\\Models\\Subsection','Figures',NULL,'[Figure 95] Native Type Hypervisor',2,'67b5e0bdbc706.png','/storage/figures/67b5e0bdbc706.png','2025-02-19 13:46:19','2025-02-19 13:46:37'),(1609,'719','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','This type installs a VMM on physical hardware and requires no host OS. It saves resources, compared to the virtualization requiring a host OS, since there is no host OS. The native type is also called typel . The leading native virtualization technologies include Xen, XenServer from Citri, ESXServerBMWare, Power Hypervisor from IBM, and Hyper-V and KVM from Microsoft','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 13:46:19','2025-02-19 13:46:19'),(1610,'720','App\\Models\\Subsection','Figures',NULL,'[Figure 96] Native Hypervisor',2,'67b5e0bdc9d1f.png','/storage/figures/67b5e0bdc9d1f.png','2025-02-19 13:46:19','2025-02-19 13:46:37'),(1611,'720','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','The hosted hypervisor (see [Figure 96]) is software installed on an existing OS. The leading hosted type hypervisc includes VirtualPC Microsoft, Workstation from VMWare, and VirtualBox from Oracle from','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 13:46:19','2025-02-19 13:46:19'),(1612,'516','App\\Models\\Section','Text','Hyperviors are classified into native types and hosted types, according to the installation method. The native type is installed directly on the hardware, while the hosted type (see [Figure 95]) is installed on an OS, like conventional programs,','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 13:46:19','2025-02-19 13:46:19'),(1613,'721','App\\Models\\Subsection','Figures',NULL,'[Figure 97] Full Virtualization Conceptual Diagran',2,'67b5e0bdd812e.png','/storage/figures/67b5e0bdd812e.png','2025-02-19 13:46:19','2025-02-19 13:46:37'),(1614,'721','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','Full virtualization completely virtualizes the hardware Although the guest OS perceives that it owns ad accesses the hardware directly, the virtual server uses the resources that the hypervisor emulates to look like hardware: If the guest OS intends to monopolize the hardware, the hypervisor must handle these commands separately. A CPU (Intels VT or AMD-V) that supports virtualization is necessary to emulate hardware resources other than the CPU, fully: The performance has greatly increased since the hypervisor, included in the CPU, handles it at high speed. There is no need to modify the guest OS, since the CPU handles full virtualization: Therefore, there are no restrictions on the guest OS. Linux-based guest OS and Windows guest OS can operate simultaneously: The native hypervisor generally corresponds to full virtualization','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 13:46:19','2025-02-19 13:46:19'),(1615,'722','App\\Models\\Subsection','Figures',NULL,'[Figure 98] Para-virtualization Conceptual Diagram',2,'67b5e0bde5430.png','/storage/figures/67b5e0bde5430.png','2025-02-19 13:46:19','2025-02-19 13:46:37'),(1616,'722','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','Para-virtualization does not completely virtualize the hardware, and the guest OS must operate through the hypervisor in order to access the hardware resources. It is a method of using the hypervisor API, without hardware emulation It is necessary to partially modify the guest OSs kernel to use the hypervisor API. It has the advantage of providing a high performance, since it can control it through a hypervisor, without hardware emulation.It has the disadvantage that it can use only an open-source OS as a guest OS, since the kernel of the guest OS needs to be partially modified,','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 13:46:19','2025-02-19 13:46:19'),(1617,'723','App\\Models\\Subsection','Tables',NULL,'(Table 30) Comparison of Hypervisor Virtualization and OS-Level Virtualization',4,'67b5e0be06e23.png','/storage/tables/67b5e0be06e23.png','2025-02-19 13:46:19','2025-02-19 13:46:38'),(1618,'723','App\\Models\\Subsection','Figures',NULL,'[Figure 99] OS-Level Virtualization',2,'67b5e0be1893a.png','/storage/figures/67b5e0be1893a.png','2025-02-19 13:46:19','2025-02-19 13:46:38'),(1619,'723','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','It is a virtualization technology that makes the system look like its another OS on the OS. It uses the virtualization technology included in the OS, instead of a hypervisor The container technology that allocates and isolates the resources included in the OS has gained interest The leading OS-level virtualization technologies include Solaris Containers, FreeBSD Jails, and Linux Docker: The guest OS must be the same as the host OS, since it uses the OSs container function, instead of a hypervisor Containers on the OS are allocated resources, such as memory, storage, and network which are independently operated between containers. using','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 13:46:19','2025-02-19 13:46:19'),(1620,'723','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','Container virtualization technology can be characterized as being lighter and more portable than existing virtualization technologies In Linux containers (LXC) , there is kernel space for managing physical resources, and a user space for executing user processes inside the OS. The container virtualization technology partitions the user space into ten and limits the resources visible in each user process:','',3,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 13:46:19','2025-02-19 13:46:19'),(1621,'723','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','OS-level virtualization (container virtualization) has the following advantages: Quick start and finish: fast compared to hypervisor-based virtualization High density: Minimized resource consumption, since an OS can operate multiple containers Low overhead: Userspace isolated without emulation Very ` level virtualization has the following disadvantages: st OS-dependent t possible to configure the kernel for each container','',5,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 13:46:19','2025-02-19 13:46:19'),(1622,'517','App\\Models\\Section','Text','According to the virtualization method, server virtualization technology can be classified into full virtualization, para virtualization, and OS-level virtualization:','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 13:46:19','2025-02-19 13:46:19'),(1623,'518','App\\Models\\Section','Text','It enables service implementation by virtually allocating only the minimum space initially required, with thin- provisioning technology, instead of configuring the required storage space Moreover it provides a environment use heterogeneous storage system integration.','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 13:46:19','2025-02-19 13:46:19'),(1624,'519','App\\Models\\Section','Text','It implements L2, L3, and L7 switches, network firewalls, and security devices that existed in the form of hardwar appliances as virtual machines It enables networking resources to operate separately through intemal virtualizatio even in a shared physical environment','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 13:46:19','2025-02-19 13:46:19'),(1625,'520','App\\Models\\Section','Text','A cloud platform is a cloud operation system to collect, control, and operate resources, such as servers, storage networks, and virtualization technologies','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 13:46:19','2025-02-19 13:46:19'),(1626,'724','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','Nova: The core component for automatic control and the operation of large-scale virtual computer instances Swift: Implementation of large-scale, reliable cloud object storage services Glance: Storage, registration, management, and delivery of virtual disk image files Keystone: Integrated authentication and authority system Cinder: Volume replication, snapshot support, and block storage Ceilometer: Mirroring support HoriZone: Self-service portal Heat: Restoration and system recovery Neutron: Network service Trove: Delivery of database services Sahara: Support for Sparkldata process and Hadoo','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 13:46:19','2025-02-19 13:46:19'),(1627,'521','App\\Models\\Section','Text','Openstack is an open-source project that develops all software blocks needed to build public and private clou computing platforms It also refers to the community of open-source developers, enterprises, and users that want implement and operate cloud computing with open source: Moreover Openstack establishes industry standards cloud computing platforms, independent of the equipment type or vendors implementation technology:','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 13:46:19','2025-02-19 13:46:19'),(1628,'522','App\\Models\\Section','Text','CloudStack is the cloud computing open-source project developed by cloud.com and managed by the Apache Foundation by Citrix','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 13:46:19','2025-02-19 13:46:19'),(1629,'523','App\\Models\\Section','Text','Kubernetes is an orchestration platform for container management and operation. Google open-sourced the operation know-how that was developed for its services. Developers can manage and schedule multiple containers from a node with declarative programming: When a specific configuration is specified through the Kubernetes Control Plane, Kuberetes utomatically maintains the state','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 13:46:19','2025-02-19 13:46:19'),(1630,'524','App\\Models\\Section','Text','Mesos is a resource management project that enables that integrated management of cloud infrastructure resources and computing engine resources. It provides a function to group distributed computing resources connected by a network into a resource pool and make it look like single computing resources When a user requests the execution of an application program, it allocates an instance and allows the application program to run: Mesos consists of the Marathon and Chronos frameworks. Marathon allocates resources and creates jobs, while Chronos is responsible for schedulino','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 13:46:19','2025-02-19 13:46:19'),(1631,'525','App\\Models\\Section','Figures',NULL,'[Figure 100] Hadoop Ecosystem',2,'67b5e0be33468.png','/storage/figures/67b5e0be33468.png','2025-02-19 13:46:19','2025-02-19 13:46:38'),(1632,'525','App\\Models\\Section','Text','Understanding the big data system structure begins with understanding the Hadoop ecosystem Hadoop, the abbreviation of High-availability distributed object-oriented platform, refers to a Java-based framework for the distributed processing of a large volume of data in multiple distributed storage It is an initial solution and consists of the Hadoop distributed file system (HDFS) and Map Reduce: However, these two modules are based on open source, and it was difficult for non-: specialists to utilize big data: The modules are packaged with various peripheral modules, as shown in [Figure 100], to solve the problem: These peripheral modules support data integration and migration, application management, and system management, and have been developed as part of the Hadoop project they','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 13:46:19','2025-02-19 13:46:19'),(1633,'725','App\\Models\\Subsection','Figures',NULL,'[Figure 101] HDFS Architecture',2,'67b5e0be480be.png','/storage/figures/67b5e0be480be.png','2025-02-19 13:46:19','2025-02-19 13:46:38'),(1634,'725','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','HDFS is a distributed file system to store data in the devices connected to the Hadoop network HDFS prevents data loss by also storing replicated data in multiple nodes. It is necessary to access data through streaming in order to store files in HDFS or query the stored files. The data integrity is ensured as stored data cannot be modified and can be read-only: (Version 2.0 or higher allows appending to the saved file) Although it does not allow data modification it provides an interface to move, delete, and copy files As shown in [Figure 101], HDFS consists of one NameNode serverthat serves as a master, and multiple DataNode servers, that serve as slaves. The NameNode server manages all metadata (the name of the directory where the blocks are stored, the file name, etc:) of HDFS, and the client can access the files stored in the HDFS by using it Hadoop applications use HDFS clients to store files or to read the stored files in HDFS, and provide the clients to users in API. The DataNode server periodically transfers a block report (information of the block stored in the node) from the NameNode, which helps the NameNode to confirm the DataNode\'s normal operation Therefore, the client can log in to the NameNode to check the blocks location that stores the file and directly query the data from the DataNode that stores the block they','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 13:46:19','2025-02-19 13:46:19'),(1635,'726','App\\Models\\Subsection','Figures',NULL,'[Figure 102] Process of Outputting the Frequency of Words Included in a Character String through MapReduce',2,'67b5e0be5d984.png','/storage/figures/67b5e0be5d984.png','2025-02-19 13:46:19','2025-02-19 13:46:38'),(1636,'726','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','MapReduce is a distributed programming model and software framework for processing a large volume of data The MapReduce framework makes it possible to analyze data in with a large-scale distributed computing environment MapReduce consists of two methods, Map and Reduce, that the programmer writes parallel Classifies scattered data into relevant data (key or value type). Reduce: Removes duplicate data from data output by the map and extracts the desired data Map: Reduce: Removes duplicate data from data output by the map and extracts the desired data. [Figure 102] below shows an example of MapReduce outputting the frequency of words included in a character string: The process consists of dividing the string data by line (splitting) 5 Receiving the string by line and outputting it in the form of Value  (mapping) 3 Separating data by the key (shuffling) ~Calulating the sum of the frequency of each and outputting it (reducing) Combines the output data and stores it in the Hadoop file system (final result) <Key, key','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 13:46:19','2025-02-19 13:46:19'),(1637,'527','App\\Models\\Section','Tables',NULL,'',3,'67b5e0be94463.png','/storage/tables/67b5e0be94463.png','2025-02-19 13:46:19','2025-02-19 13:46:38'),(1638,'527','App\\Models\\Section','Text','As shown in <Table 31  , Hadoop support service programs to collect, store, utilize, process, and manage big data, are in development','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 13:46:19','2025-02-19 13:46:19'),(1639,'528','App\\Models\\Section','Tables',NULL,'',3,'67b5e0bebd62b.png','/storage/tables/67b5e0bebd62b.png','2025-02-19 13:46:19','2025-02-19 13:46:38'),(1640,'528','App\\Models\\Section','Text','Leading companies that develop and distribute open-source commercial Hadoop solutions include Cloudera, Hortonworks, and Map R These companies create internal platforms, based on Hadoop, and distribute solutions through the strategic alliance with existing databases, data warehousing, and business intelligence solution companies :','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 13:46:20','2025-02-19 13:46:20'),(1641,'727','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','Big data service providers form a corporate ecosystem by promoting strategies to solve problems, such as real-time processing, memory-based processing, ease of query, and accessibility to various file systems that big data must overcome system Companies like Amazon, that have already secured cloud capabilities, are trying to build unique platforms by their cloud and open source-based big data solutions. IBM, Microsoft, and others, that were leaders in corporate information systems, have modified their strategies to focus on big data, utilizing their existing competency Google, Apple, and other mobile-based emerging companies, are building big data analysis systems, based on existing servers and user data to provide their services linking','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 13:46:20','2025-02-19 13:46:20'),(1642,'728','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','Companies that are implementing big data systems are divided into those that provide a total solution and those that provide solutions in a specific area. Companies like Amazon, IBM, and Google create internal platforms that support the entire process of big data analysis and provide consulting to other enterprises, based on them generating revenue Solution companies like Teradata and Good Data that implement functions, such as analysis and visualization for big data, also strive to implement unique performance','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 13:46:20','2025-02-19 13:46:20'),(1643,'729','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','Many technologies related to Hadoop, the leading technology for big data, are currently being developed to the extent that it has the Hadoop ecosystem: However it is still technically too difficult for non-engineers to use, without significant help from engineers','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 13:46:20','2025-02-19 13:46:20'),(1644,'730','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','With the growth of open source-based technologies, the competitive landscape has been established to facilitate small venture companies that provide user-centered customized software, as well as traditional cloud companies, to grow in the market','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 13:46:20','2025-02-19 13:46:20'),(1645,'731','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','Starting with IBM Watson and Google AlphaGo, expectations for the industrial use of Al has risen significantly: Traditional cloud companies target consumers by linking their infrastructure and Al, and are building newly expanded ecosystems by cooperating with competitors they','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 13:46:20','2025-02-19 13:46:20'),(1646,'531','App\\Models\\Section','Figures',NULL,'[Figure 104] Encapsulation of the Datalink Layer',2,'67b5e0becfe13.png','/storage/figures/67b5e0becfe13.png','2025-02-19 13:46:20','2025-02-19 13:46:38'),(1647,'531','App\\Models\\Section','Text','As shown in the following figure, the datalink layer frame adds a header and a trailer to the network layer packet: This process is called encapsulation of the datalink layerThe process is reversed on the receiving end ad is called decapsulation:','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 13:46:20','2025-02-19 13:46:20'),(1648,'532','App\\Models\\Section','Text','The frame header includes a preamble for bit synchronization between hosts, a start of frame delimiter (SFD) that indicates the start of a frame, and destination and source addresses, which are physical addresses Physical addresses have a 48-bit address system and have unique values for each device, unlike logical IP addresses. It is necessary to use the physical address to check a device location below layer 2, since IP addresses are used in layer 3. Trailers include a check sequence (FCS) to check for errors a data transfer frame during','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 13:46:20','2025-02-19 13:46:20'),(1649,'533','App\\Models\\Section','Figures',NULL,'[Figure 105] Sub-layers of datalink layer',2,'67b5e0bedcccb.png','/storage/figures/67b5e0bedcccb.png','2025-02-19 13:46:20','2025-02-19 13:46:38'),(1650,'533','App\\Models\\Section','Text','A datalink layer consists of two sub-layers: an LLC (Logical Link Control) sub-layer and a MAC (Media Access Control) sub-layer The LLC sub-layer is responsible for the connection between the MAC sub-layer &d the network layer (layer 3). The lower MAC sub-layers are responsible for control according to the topology on physical layers or other characteristics','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 13:46:20','2025-02-19 13:46:20'),(1651,'732','App\\Models\\Subsection','Figures',NULL,'[Figure 106] IEEE 802.3 Frame Structure',1,'67b5e0beea3cc.png','/storage/figures/67b5e0beea3cc.png','2025-02-19 13:46:20','2025-02-19 13:46:38'),(1652,'732','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','The sub-layer is located at a higher level among the sub-layers of the datalink layer: It is responsible for the data transfer between two adjacent nodes on the IEEE 802.2 or datalink layer network The adjacent nodes have the destination service access point (DSAP) and the source service access point (SSAP) on the LLC layer The LLC layer can use various MAC sub-layer protocols to facilitate the communication, regardless of the network topology:','',2,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 13:46:20','2025-02-19 13:46:20'),(1653,'733','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','The LLC options include Type 1, Type 2, and Type 3. Type is a unconfirmed datagram service and called an unconnected service, as it does not require a receipt confirmation message Type 2 is a virtual circuit access type and, as a TCP service, transfers data after establishing a virtual session Type 3 is a confirmed datagram service and provides the receipt confirmed datagram in the point-to-point method.','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 13:46:20','2025-02-19 13:46:20'),(1654,'535','App\\Models\\Section','Figures',NULL,'[Figure 107] MAC Address Configuration',2,'67b5e0bf0260e.png','/storage/figures/67b5e0bf0260e.png','2025-02-19 13:46:20','2025-02-19 13:46:39'),(1655,'535','App\\Models\\Section','Text','The MAC sub-layer is responsible for determining how to transfer data through the physical media. The MAC layer includes the MAC addresses of the transmitting and receiving systems, as shown in [Figure 107] below: The MAC address is mainly divided into two addresses The first 224is OUI (Organizationally Unique Identifier), representing the manufacturer identification code, and the remaining 224 is the serial number of the NIC produced by the manufacturer','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 13:46:20','2025-02-19 13:46:20'),(1656,'535','App\\Models\\Section','Text','The standardized MAC protocols include the CSMACD type IEEE 802.3,the token bus type IEEE 802.4, and the token ring type IEEE 802.5 for wired LAN The CSMACA type IEEE 802.11 MAC sub-layer is used for wireless LAN.','',3,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 13:46:20','2025-02-19 13:46:20'),(1657,'536','App\\Models\\Section','Figures',NULL,'[Figure 108] ARP packet structure',2,'67b5e0bf126eb.png','/storage/figures/67b5e0bf126eb.png','2025-02-19 13:46:20','2025-02-19 13:46:39'),(1658,'536','App\\Models\\Section','Text','To transfer & packet to another host, requires the host\'s MAC address. ARP (Address Resolution Protocol) is responsible for it. The protocols to convert the IP ad MAC addresses are the ARP and RARP (Reverse Address Resolution Protocol): The ARP that has the following address checks the MAC address through the IP address, and RARP is the inverse address conversion protocol that checks the IP address through the MAC address','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 13:46:20','2025-02-19 13:46:20'),(1659,'536','App\\Models\\Section','Text','The ARP packet is organized of the 6-byte destination MAC address, 6-byte source MAC address, 2-byte Etheret protocol type, 2-byte hardware type, 2-byte protocol type, 1-byte hardware address length, 1-byte protocol address length, 2-byte operation code, 6-byte sender hardware address, 4-byte sender protocol address, 6-byte target hardware address, 4-byte target protocol address, and 18-byte padding:','',3,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 13:46:20','2025-02-19 13:46:20'),(1660,'537','App\\Models\\Section','Text','Since Router C and computer with user A are in the same network section, with user A, as shown in [Figure 103], the MAC address is required for communication In that case, the computer with user A sends & ARP request through broadcasting to all systems in the network section The data section of the frame, transferred through the ARP request, contains the ARP packet, as shown in [Figure 108]. On receiving the response, router € transfers its MAC address in the ARP packet to the computer with user A through unicast, to find each other\'s MAC address The MAC address is stored in each system\'s cache memory: In that case, wiredjwireless router B stores the port-MAC address table of the svstem connected to its cache memorv ports','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 13:46:20','2025-02-19 13:46:20'),(1661,'538','App\\Models\\Section','Figures',NULL,'[Figure 109] Error Control Types',2,'67b5e0bf25a16.png','/storage/figures/67b5e0bf25a16.png','2025-02-19 13:46:20','2025-02-19 13:46:39'),(1662,'538','App\\Models\\Section','Text','Transferring frames through the data link layer can cause various errors, depending on the network condition or the operation of the transmitting and receiving device Types of errors include single-bit errors, in which only one bit of the data part is changed, multi-bit errors, in which two or more non-contiguous bits are changed in the data unit, and burst errors, in which two or more consecutive bits are changed Error control is the function of detecting and correcting errors when transmitted data does not arrive properly, or when an error occurs during transmission: Error control methods can be divided into two types, as shown in [Figure 109]. Forward error correction (FEC) allows the receiving device to detect errors and recover from them by itself by transmitting a spare bit for error recovery in the packet Backward error correction (BEC) notifies an error to the transmitting device to recover from the error, when an error occurs during the data transmission','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 13:46:20','2025-02-19 13:46:20'),(1663,'734','App\\Models\\Subsection','Tables',NULL,'(Table 32) Error Detection Methods',2,'67b5e0bf38a61.png','/storage/tables/67b5e0bf38a61.png','2025-02-19 13:46:20','2025-02-19 13:46:39'),(1664,'734','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','Error detection uses the redundancy (spare) concept by adding a spare bit to detect the destinations error Errc detection methods include VRC (Vertical Redundancy Check), LRC (Longitudinal Redundancy Check) , CRC (Cycli Redundancy Check) , and checksum, <Table 32  shows details of each detection method,','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 13:46:20','2025-02-19 13:46:20'),(1665,'735','App\\Models\\Subsection','Tables',NULL,'(Table 33) Error Correction Methods',2,'67b5e0bf4e6c6.png','/storage/tables/67b5e0bf4e6c6.png','2025-02-19 13:46:20','2025-02-19 13:46:39'),(1666,'735','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','Error correction methods include a method in which the receiving device requests the sending device to retransmit the entire data, or the receiving device automatically performs a correction using an error correction code','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 13:46:20','2025-02-19 13:46:20'),(1667,'736','App\\Models\\Subsection','Tables',NULL,'(Table 34) ARQ Types',2,'67b5e0bf6e035.png','/storage/tables/67b5e0bf6e035.png','2025-02-19 13:46:20','2025-02-19 13:46:39'),(1668,'736','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','ARQ is an algorithm in Which the receiving side informs the sending side of the error and the sending side retransmit= the error to correct the error Typical ARQ methods include stop-and-wait ARQ, Go-back-N ARQ, and adaptive ARQ Details of each retransmission algorithm type are shown in the <Table 34  below: frame','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 13:46:20','2025-02-19 13:46:20'),(1669,'540','App\\Models\\Section','Figures',NULL,'[Figure 110] Services for Each Layer',2,'67b5e0bf93eaa.png','/storage/figures/67b5e0bf93eaa.png','2025-02-19 13:46:20','2025-02-19 13:46:39'),(1670,'540','App\\Models\\Section','Text','[Figure 110] shows the services for each layer ad defined by the IEE Committee The LLC layer includes, Type 3 unconfirmed datagram service, Type2 virtual circuit service, and Type 3 confirmed datagram service The physical medium access control (MAC) layer includes the IEEE 802.3 CDMACD MAC, IEEE 802.4 token bus MAC, and IEEE 802.5 token ring MAC.','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 13:46:20','2025-02-19 13:46:20'),(1671,'541','App\\Models\\Section','Figures',NULL,'[Figure 111] IEEE 802.3 Protocol Stack',2,'67b5e0bfa6b1f.png','/storage/figures/67b5e0bfa6b1f.png','2025-02-19 13:46:20','2025-02-19 13:46:39'),(1672,'541','App\\Models\\Section','Text','The IEEE 802.3 protocol stack the most widely used IEE 802 standard, includes IEEE 802.2 that corresponds to the LLC layer of the datalink layer and IEEE 802.3 that include the MAC layer and the physical layer, IEEE 802.5 token ring and FDDI','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 13:46:20','2025-02-19 13:46:20'),(1673,'542','App\\Models\\Section','Tables',NULL,'(Table 35) IEEE 802.11 Protocol Standards',2,'67b5e0bfbaa9c.png','/storage/tables/67b5e0bfbaa9c.png','2025-02-19 13:46:20','2025-02-19 13:46:39'),(1674,'542','App\\Models\\Section','Text','EEE 802.11 is the name of the wireless communication standardization committee for wireless LAN, called Wi-Fi, It seeks to minimize work ad maintenance costs to compensate for the shortcomings of wired LAN-type Ethernet It includes IEEE 80211b using the DSSS modulation method at the maximum transmission speed of 11 Mbps, IEEE 802.11a supporting a of up to 54 Mbps by using the frequency of the 5 GHz band and the OFDM modulation method, and IEEE 80211g using the frequency of the 2.4 GHz band to support the speed of 54 Mbps. IEEE 802.1In uses the 2.4GHz and the SGHz bands and supports MIMO (Multiple-Input, Multiple-Output) to increase the transmission speed up to 600Mbps Wireless AP products supporting the speed of Gpbs have recently been introduced. IEEE 802.IIac supports a theoretical maximum speed of 6.93Gbps by applying the 80/16OMHz bandwidth, multi-user MIMOmulti-spatial stream MIMO, 256-QAM modulation, and beamforming IEEE 802.11ad is a standard that supports the speed of Gbps by applying various technologies in the 6OGHz bandwidth The standard for gigabit wireless LAN technology to transmitting UHD-level video and explosively increasing wireless data at high speed is in development wiring speed','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 13:46:20','2025-02-19 13:46:20'),(1675,'543','App\\Models\\Section','Tables',NULL,'(Table 36) IEEE 802.15 Protocol Standards',2,'67b5e0bfcb19f.png','/storage/tables/67b5e0bfcb19f.png','2025-02-19 13:46:20','2025-02-19 13:46:39'),(1676,'543','App\\Models\\Section','Text','IEEE 802.15 is the name of the short-range wireless communication standardization committee separated from IEEE 802.11, which standardizes wireless LAN. It seeks to establish wireless networks for mobile communication devices, PCs, and other peripheral devices in the home. Sub-organizations include, the WPAN (Wireless Personal Area Network) research group, for a maximum transmission rate of IMbps, and WPAN HSRC (WPAN High Rate Study Group) , with a maximum transmission rate of 2OMbps. The leading WPAN technologies, corresponding to the IEEE 802.15 standard, are IEEE 802.15.1 Bluetooth, IEEE 802.15.3 UWB, and IEEE 802.15.4 ZigBee: IEEE 802.15.1 Bluetooth is a short-range wireless communication technology standard for exchanging information by connecting mobile devices, such as mobile phones and laptops. IEEE 802.15.3 UAB is a wireless technology that quickly transmits a large volume of digital data through a large spectrum frequency at low power in an ultra- broadband and short distance. IEEE 802.15.4 ZigBee is a standard technology for home automation and data networks with low data transmission rates:','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 13:46:20','2025-02-19 13:46:20'),(1677,'543','App\\Models\\Section','Text','Embedded software developers should be able to select the chipset and the communication method to control the chipset, ad to check which development tools are available, and have a broad understanding of the chipset by reviewing the specification of ZigBee and Bluetooth In general,, the software developer should check the following in the chipset specification: Block diagram: Understanding of the overall configuration and of the chipset Communication method: Chipset control methods, such as SPI I2C, etc, Memory: RAM, ROM, and memory size available to developers, address methods, etc: GPIO: Port type and setting method for external signal input and output control Development tool: Tools necessary to develop with the chipset flow According to the application field, the hardware developer reviews the initial chipset to develop an embedded product and reviews the entire circuit configuration through the chipset. The hardware developer reviews the chipset in terms of electrical characteristics, reliability, complexity in circuit configuration, and chipset package according to device design, and cost The software developer reviews if the chipset meets the standard, whether the control method is convenient, whether the existing control method can be reused, whether the memory capacity is adequate, whether the number of ports for IO control required by the target product is sufficient, whether the chipset should be separated, and whether it is preferable to have multiple functions in a chipset The software developer should select the ontimal chincet after cufficient concultation with the hardiware develoner','',3,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 13:46:20','2025-02-19 13:46:20'),(1678,'544','App\\Models\\Section','Figures',NULL,'[Figure 112] Router Conceptual Diagram',1,'67b5e0bfdef58.png','/storage/figures/67b5e0bfdef58.png','2025-02-19 13:46:21','2025-02-19 13:46:39'),(1679,'544','App\\Models\\Section','Text','The above sections described the network layer operation and related scenarios, as shown in [Figure 112] [Step 3-2]) Information created by the TCP protocol is capsulized in order to be routed to the 220.17.23.0 network, in which my servercom is present, through several hops (IP): [Step 3-3] An initial packet that contains the information for routing between networks is created. However, it must be further modified to be transferred between networks. The IPv4 address of user As computer is 192.168.11.5 and cannot be transmitted to myservercom directly: It must be transmitted to the computer\'s gateway wiredjwireless router B (192.168.11.1). However, an IP address cannot be used for data transfer in a network so the MAC address is needed. After the MAC address that corresponds to 192.168.11.1, the gateways IP address, the packet is transmitted to wired ireless router B, through network broadcasting: Step 3-4] Upon receiving the packet user As computer, wiredjwireless router B, aware that the packet is not sent to the router as the final destination, examines to which address the packet must be transmitted The IP header indicates that the packet\'s final destination is myserver com, and since it does not belong to network 192.168.11.0 or 14.32.172.0, to Which wired/ wireless router B belongs, it transmits the packet to router C, to Which it belongs [Step 3-6] Upon receiving the packet, myservercom examines the IP address and recognizes that the packet was sent to it It removes the header data, such as the IP address, and sends the remaining data up to a higher layer finding from','',2,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 13:46:21','2025-02-19 13:46:21'),(1680,'545','App\\Models\\Section','Figures',NULL,'[Figure 113] Network Layer in TCPIIP',2,'67b5e0bfeee3a.png','/storage/figures/67b5e0bfeee3a.png','2025-02-19 13:46:21','2025-02-19 13:46:39'),(1681,'545','App\\Models\\Section','Text','The network layer is the third layer of the OSI 7 model and TCPIIP and sends packets, from a transmitting side, to receiving side It receives a segment from the transmitting layer, encapsulates it, and sends it to the datalink layer','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 13:46:21','2025-02-19 13:46:21'),(1682,'546','App\\Models\\Section','Tables',NULL,'(Table 37) Network Layer Functions',2,'67b5e0c00b6d2.png','/storage/tables/67b5e0c00b6d2.png','2025-02-19 13:46:21','2025-02-19 13:46:40'),(1683,'546','App\\Models\\Section','Text','The transmitting side of the network layer performs payload encapsulation, and the receiving side performs payload decapsulation The packetizing function is responsible for ensuring that there is no change to the payload data transmission The routing function finds a through which packets can be delivered. The forwarding function is performed by a router when a packet arrives through one interface on the router When performing forwarding, the router creates a decision table by applying the routing rules The decision table is also called the forwarding or routing table during path','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 13:46:21','2025-02-19 13:46:21'),(1684,'547','App\\Models\\Section','Tables',NULL,'(Table 39} Protocol Layers and Device for Each Layer',4,'67b5e0c0218e0.png','/storage/tables/67b5e0c0218e0.png','2025-02-19 13:46:21','2025-02-19 13:46:40'),(1685,'547','App\\Models\\Section','Text','Internetworking refers to a connection between networks. The leading interetworking equipment includes repeaters, bridges, switches, and routers.','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 13:46:21','2025-02-19 13:46:21'),(1686,'547','App\\Models\\Section','Text','This section describes for which of the OSI 7 layers and TCPIIP 4 layers these internetworking devices are responsible The router performs packet routing through the IP address on the network layer The bridge and switch are responsible for frame transfer on the datalink layer, while the hub and repeater transfer physical signals on the physical layer < Table 39  compares the function of each device with the protocol layer','',3,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 13:46:21','2025-02-19 13:46:21'),(1687,'737','App\\Models\\Subsection','Tables',NULL,'(Table 40) Routing Metrics [3]',6,'67b5e0c03c822.png','/storage/tables/67b5e0c03c822.png','2025-02-19 13:46:21','2025-02-19 13:46:40'),(1688,'737','App\\Models\\Subsection','Figures',NULL,'[Figure 114] Router Conceptual Diagram',2,'67b5e0c0552ec.png','/storage/figures/67b5e0c0552ec.png','2025-02-19 13:46:21','2025-02-19 13:46:40'),(1689,'737','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','As shown in [Figure 114], a router mostly consists of a router control plane and a forwarding plane: The control plane, implemented in the software in a router determines where to send the packets it receives and uses tables to decide The forwarding plane actually sends the packets according to the requirements created by the control plane','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 13:46:21','2025-02-19 13:46:21'),(1690,'737','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','<Table 39  shows the shapes of a router: Small networks mostly use cisco 2500, while larger networks use cis 7300.','',3,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 13:46:21','2025-02-19 13:46:21'),(1691,'737','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','It refers to the data collected by a router at a given time, when the traffic passes through the <Table 40 shows the metric types. path','',5,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 13:46:21','2025-02-19 13:46:21'),(1692,'738','App\\Models\\Subsection','Figures',NULL,'[Figure 115] Routing Table',2,'67b5e0c06aab4.png','/storage/figures/67b5e0c06aab4.png','2025-02-19 13:46:21','2025-02-19 13:46:40'),(1693,'738','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','A routing table is a database that stores the output interface of each destination network and the next IP address, hop','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 13:46:21','2025-02-19 13:46:21'),(1694,'548','App\\Models\\Section','Text','router forwards traffic and determines the optimal path, using one or more metrics In other words, it forwards packets one network, to aother based on the network layer information from','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 13:46:21','2025-02-19 13:46:21'),(1695,'549','App\\Models\\Section','Tables',NULL,'(Table 41) Main Switch Functions',2,'67b5e0c07d576.png','/storage/tables/67b5e0c07d576.png','2025-02-19 13:46:21','2025-02-19 13:46:40'),(1696,'549','App\\Models\\Section','Text','A switch is a device that connects network units, A switch device has a important role in MAC address learning filtering, and prevention: Other switch functions include port mirroring and VLAN. Port mirroring, also callec port monitoring, is the function of sending a replicate of the data sent from a specific port to a mirrored port: It is ar mportant function used by administrators to monitor network traffic through the mirrored port loop','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 13:46:22','2025-02-19 13:46:22'),(1697,'550','App\\Models\\Section','Tables',NULL,'(Table 42) Comparison of Switch and Router',3,'67b5e0c08f291.png','/storage/tables/67b5e0c08f291.png','2025-02-19 13:46:22','2025-02-19 13:46:40'),(1698,'550','App\\Models\\Section','Figures',NULL,'[Figure 116] VLAN Configuration [4]',2,'67b5e0c0a15ac.png','/storage/figures/67b5e0c0a15ac.png','2025-02-19 13:46:22','2025-02-19 13:46:40'),(1699,'550','App\\Models\\Section','Text','VLAN is a method of configuring a logical network, desired by the user, to overcome the physical and regional constraints of the existing networks In other words, it uses the IP unit, protocol unit, MAC address, and connecting to configure a logical network instead of separating networks by and geographical locations The VLAN protocols of a switch include ISL, 802.1Q, and VTP ISL and 802.1Q are the VLAN tagging protocols, and VTP is a AN management protocol spatial port','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 13:46:22','2025-02-19 13:46:22'),(1700,'551','App\\Models\\Section','Figures',NULL,'[Figure 117] Network Layer Encapsulation',2,'67b5e0c0afacf.png','/storage/figures/67b5e0c0afacf.png','2025-02-19 13:46:22','2025-02-19 13:46:40'),(1701,'551','App\\Models\\Section','Text','As shown in [Figure 117], the packets on the network layer are configured by adding a header to the transmitting layer segment This process is called encapsulation of the datalink layer, and the process is reversed on the receiving end and is called decapsulation','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 13:46:22','2025-02-19 13:46:22'),(1702,'552','App\\Models\\Section','Figures',NULL,'[Figure 118] Network Packet Structure [5]',1,'67b5e0c0c94f0.png','/storage/figures/67b5e0c0c94f0.png','2025-02-19 13:46:22','2025-02-19 13:46:40'),(1703,'552','App\\Models\\Section','Text','In [Figure 118] above, Version\" refers to the protocol version of the datagram, \"IHL\" refers to the header length, and Type of Service\" refers to which type of service the host wants in the subnet Total length\" refers to the sum of the header and data lengths in the datagram, \'Time to Live\" refers to the packet life limit, and Protocol\" refers to the notification of TCP or UDP for the recombination of the datagram on the network layer \"Source Address\" and Destination Address\" refer to the source and destination addresses of the 32-bit datagram:','',2,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 13:46:22','2025-02-19 13:46:22'),(1704,'553','App\\Models\\Section','Text','The methods of finding the packet in a packet-exchanging network, include the datagram approach and the virtual circuit approach: The datagram approach is a non-connected service that independently processes all packets Packets can be transferred through different paths, and the packet\'s destination address determines the forwarding The virtual circuit approach is a connection-oriented service It establishes a virtual for the datagram before the transfer, and all datagrams are transmitted to the same after the connection The forwarding is determined by the packet label (virtual circuit identifier): path path path: path path','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 13:46:22','2025-02-19 13:46:22'),(1705,'554','App\\Models\\Section','Tables',NULL,'(Table 43) Network Layer Protocols',3,'67b5e0c0dfe6f.png','/storage/tables/67b5e0c0dfe6f.png','2025-02-19 13:46:22','2025-02-19 13:46:40'),(1706,'554','App\\Models\\Section','Figures',NULL,'[Figure 119] Network Layer Protocols',2,'67b5e0c101fe0.png','/storage/figures/67b5e0c101fe0.png','2025-02-19 13:46:22','2025-02-19 13:46:41'),(1707,'554','App\\Models\\Section','Text','The network layer protocols that convert the IP and MAC addressesinto an IP address, are the ARP (Address Resolution Protocol) and the RARP (Reverse Address Resolution Protocol): ICMP (Internet Control Message Protocol) is a protocol used to transfer the network error information, and IGMP (Internet Group Management Protocol) is the protocol for IP multicast transfer','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 13:46:22','2025-02-19 13:46:22'),(1708,'555','App\\Models\\Section','Tables',NULL,'(Table 44} Network Layer Commands',2,'67b5e0c1189b8.png','/storage/tables/67b5e0c1189b8.png','2025-02-19 13:46:22','2025-02-19 13:46:41'),(1709,'555','App\\Models\\Section','Text','Table 44  shows commands to check the network layer status or perform a specific actio','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 13:46:22','2025-02-19 13:46:22'),(1710,'556','App\\Models\\Section','Tables',NULL,'(Table 45) QoS Measurements',2,'67b5e0c12b5a8.png','/storage/tables/67b5e0c12b5a8.png','2025-02-19 13:46:22','2025-02-19 13:46:41'),(1711,'556','App\\Models\\Section','Text','QoS is the technology of guaranteeing a service quality and performance of a communication service to meet use requirements. The attributes to determine the QoS include confidence, delay, jitter, and bandwidth, as shown <Table 45','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 13:46:22','2025-02-19 13:46:22'),(1712,'739','App\\Models\\Subsection','Tables',NULL,'(Table 46} Packet Scheduling Methods',2,'67b5e0c13e990.png','/storage/tables/67b5e0c13e990.png','2025-02-19 13:46:22','2025-02-19 13:46:41'),(1713,'739','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','Routers are responsible for handling packets over the Internet  Therefore, the packet flow can differ according to the schedule:','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 13:46:22','2025-02-19 13:46:22'),(1714,'740','App\\Models\\Subsection','Tables',NULL,'(Table 47) Traffic Shaping and Traffic Policing',2,'67b5e0c14ea6c.png','/storage/tables/67b5e0c14ea6c.png','2025-02-19 13:46:22','2025-02-19 13:46:41'),(1715,'740','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','As a way to control the traffic speed and volume, traffic shaping is used when the traffic leaves the network, and traffic policing is used when the traffic enters the network','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 13:46:22','2025-02-19 13:46:22'),(1716,'741','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','It is the method of reserving resources, such as buffer, bandwidth, CPU, and time needed for data flowfor a specific service to ensure the service quality:','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 13:46:22','2025-02-19 13:46:22'),(1717,'742','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','It is a procedure used by the control unit of a communication network to determine whether to accept a connection request.','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 13:46:22','2025-02-19 13:46:22'),(1718,'743','App\\Models\\Subsection','Tables',NULL,'(Table 48} Service Quality Model and Protocol [6]',2,'67b5e0c16202e.png','/storage/tables/67b5e0c16202e.png','2025-02-19 13:46:22','2025-02-19 13:46:41'),(1719,'743','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','Service quality models include the integrated service (IntServ) model and the differentiated service (DiffServ) mode The service quality protocol is the resource reservation protocol (RSVP):','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 13:46:22','2025-02-19 13:46:22'),(1720,'558','App\\Models\\Section','Text','Routing protocol defines the types of messages exchanged between routers, exchange procedure, and actions when receiving a message, for efficient setting and updating of the routing tables.','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 13:46:22','2025-02-19 13:46:22'),(1721,'744','App\\Models\\Subsection','Code',NULL,'[Figure 120] Pseudo Code of Dijkstra\'s Algorithm',2,'67b5e0c17952b.png','/storage/code/67b5e0c17952b.png','2025-02-19 13:46:22','2025-02-19 13:46:41'),(1722,'744','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','[Figure 120] shows the pseudo-code of the Dijkstra Algorithm, the leading link-state routing algorithm.','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 13:46:22','2025-02-19 13:46:22'),(1723,'745','App\\Models\\Subsection','Code',NULL,'[Figure 121] Bellman-Ford Algorithm\'s Pseudo-code',2,'67b5e0c189503.png','/storage/code/67b5e0c189503.png','2025-02-19 13:46:22','2025-02-19 13:46:41'),(1724,'745','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','The Bellman-Ford Algorithm is the leading distance vector routing algorithm. The shortest can be decomposed as follows, by expanding the optimal substructure of the shortest pat problem: The shortest the starting node s to V, is the sum of the shortest from s to U, and the weigt factor (distance) between u and v: D(s,v) = D(s, u)   w(u, v) The Bellman-Ford Algorithm performs edge relaxation of all edges in the graph, when calculating the shortest pat between s and u. Then, how many times should it be performed? The shortest between s and u may be only path path from path path and u, and all (VI-1) nodes of the graph, excluding u, can be the shortest distance between s and u. Therefore, Bellman-Ford Algorithm performs the edge-relaxation |VI- 1 times for all edges. [Figure 121] shows Bellman-Ford Algorithm\'s pseudo-code.','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 13:46:22','2025-02-19 13:46:22'),(1725,'559','App\\Models\\Section','Tables',NULL,'(Table 49} Routing Algorithm Types',2,'67b5e0c19d217.png','/storage/tables/67b5e0c19d217.png','2025-02-19 13:46:22','2025-02-19 13:46:41'),(1726,'559','App\\Models\\Section','Text','The routing algorithm finds the low-cost between a source router and a destination router in a network connected by links with a cost between routers The low-cost refers to the of minimum value among the sum f link costs out of all possible paths from the source to the destination <Table 49  shows the type= of routing algorithms path graphica path path','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 13:46:22','2025-02-19 13:46:22'),(1727,'560','App\\Models\\Section','Figures',NULL,'[Figure 122] Routing Protocol Classification',2,'67b5e0c1b028c.png','/storage/figures/67b5e0c1b028c.png','2025-02-19 13:46:22','2025-02-19 13:46:41'),(1728,'560','App\\Models\\Section','Text','The routing protocol is classified into static routing and dynamic routing, depending the routing type, as shown in [Figure 122]. The dynamic routing method is divided into the EGP (Exterior Gateway Protocol) method and the IGP (Interior Gateway Protocol) method,, according to the classification of AS (Autonomous System): The IGP (Interior Gateway Protocol) method is further divided into the distance vector method, the link-state method, and the hybrid method, according to the routing setting method. on','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 13:46:22','2025-02-19 13:46:22'),(1729,'560','App\\Models\\Section','Text','The type of routing protocol can be divided into an internal router protocol and an external router protocol, based or the autonomous (AS): Here, AS refers to networks with an independent management system and the same operating policy: system When classifying routing protocols, based on AS, the routing protocol within the AS is called the inter gateway protocol (IGP). The leading IGP includes the routing information protocol (RIP) , using a distance vector routing algorithm, and the open shortest first (OSPF) using a link-state routing algorithm: The routing protocol between AS is called the exterior gateway protocol (EGP): The EGP is the border gateway protocol (BGP) that uses a path-vector routing algorithm path leading','',3,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 13:46:22','2025-02-19 13:46:22'),(1730,'561','App\\Models\\Section','Tables',NULL,'(Table 50) Routing Protocol Types',2,'67b5e0c1caa3b.png','/storage/tables/67b5e0c1caa3b.png','2025-02-19 13:46:22','2025-02-19 13:46:41'),(1731,'561','App\\Models\\Section','Text','The protocol includes RIP, which uses the distance-vector routing algorithm ad delivers the routing table information every 30 seconds through broadcasting, IGRP, which improves some of the RIP problems by reflecting the network state (bandwidth, delay time, load, etc ), OSPF, which uses the link-state routing algorithm, and BGP, whict connects between AS. <Table 50  shows the details of each protocol: routing','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 13:46:22','2025-02-19 13:46:22'),(1732,'562','App\\Models\\Section','Figures',NULL,'[Figure 123] IPv4 Address Structure',2,'67b5e0c1dca9b.png','/storage/figures/67b5e0c1dca9b.png','2025-02-19 13:46:22','2025-02-19 13:46:41'),(1733,'562','App\\Models\\Section','Text','The IPv4 address is the 32-bit address used on the IP layer, as shown in [Figure 123] It is an identifier that makes the router or host connection to the Internet unique and universal','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 13:46:22','2025-02-19 13:46:22'),(1734,'562','App\\Models\\Section','Text','The elements of the IPv4 address include an IP address, which is a unique identification address given to all communication networks that are connected to the Internet and computers connected to the network, a network ID, which identifies TCPIIP hosts in the same physical network, a host ID, which identifies the TCPIIP host on the network, and the 32-bit subnet mask, which specifies the network name for the iP address from the hostname CIDR (Classless Inter-Domain Routing, RFC 1519) is a method of expressing the IPv4 address and one of IP allocating methods that does not divide the network part from the host part in 8-bit units. Moreover, subnetting and supernetting can flexibly express the network and host Ips, according to the number of IPs required by the network without dividing the IPv4 address ad the network ID into fixed 8-bit units Here, subnetting refers to dividing a given IP address into small subnets, according to the network environment, and supernetting refers to combining multiple network IDs into one network Here, subnetting refers to dividing a given IP address into small subnets to suit the network environment, and supernetting refers to combining multiple network IDs into one network ID.','',3,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 13:46:22','2025-02-19 13:46:22'),(1735,'563','App\\Models\\Section','Figures',NULL,'[Figure 124] Network Using IPv4',1,'67b5e0c1ee0ec.png','/storage/figures/67b5e0c1ee0ec.png','2025-02-19 13:46:22','2025-02-19 13:46:41'),(1736,'564','App\\Models\\Section','Figures',NULL,'',1,'67b5e0c207e09.png','/storage/figures/67b5e0c207e09.png','2025-02-19 13:46:22','2025-02-19 13:46:42'),(1737,'564','App\\Models\\Section','Text','Binary expression: 01110101 10010101 00011101 00000010 Dotted decimal notation','',2,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 13:46:22','2025-02-19 13:46:22'),(1738,'565','App\\Models\\Section','Tables',NULL,'(Table 51) IPv4 Address Designation System [7]',3,'67b5e0c219457.png','/storage/tables/67b5e0c219457.png','2025-02-19 13:46:22','2025-02-19 13:46:42'),(1739,'565','App\\Models\\Section','Figures',NULL,'[Figure 125] IPv4 Address Designation System',1,'67b5e0c233ca5.png','/storage/figures/67b5e0c233ca5.png','2025-02-19 13:46:22','2025-02-19 13:46:42'),(1740,'565','App\\Models\\Section','Text','The IPv4 addressing consists of a network address, assigned by an Internet address resource management organization, and a host address, assigned by a network administrator to identify individual hosts on the network As shown in < Table 51 ,it is divided Classes A, B, C, D, ad E, depending on the network size or the number of hosts. Classes A B, and C are for network configuration assigned to general users, Class D is for multicast, and Class Fis an address resenved for future use system into','',2,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 13:46:22','2025-02-19 13:46:22'),(1741,'565','App\\Models\\Section','Text','In the IPv4 address designation method, subnetting is the address partition method used to separate a network ID into multiple network Ids, and supernetting is a method of integrating multiple networks into a large network The 169.254.0.0 network band is reserved for automatic private IP addressing: For versions after Windows 2000, DHCP automatically generates it to set the IPv4 address ad cannot be routed on the Internet: The addressing system is called the automatic private IP addressing (APIPA):','',4,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 13:46:22','2025-02-19 13:46:22'),(1742,'566','App\\Models\\Section','Tables',NULL,'(Table 52) Special IPv4 Address [7]',2,'67b5e0c24ecbf.png','/storage/tables/67b5e0c24ecbf.png','2025-02-19 13:46:22','2025-02-19 13:46:42'),(1743,'566','App\\Models\\Section','Text','In IPv4, there is an addressing system in a different form from the conventional A B, and class addressing system: These addresses are called the special IPv4 addresses. <Table 52  below shows the special IPv4 addresses','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 13:46:22','2025-02-19 13:46:22'),(1744,'746','App\\Models\\Subsection','Figures',NULL,'[Figure 126] IP Address Applying Subnetting',2,'67b5e0c263401.png','/storage/figures/67b5e0c263401.png','2025-02-19 13:46:22','2025-02-19 13:46:42'),(1745,'746','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','Subnetting is a method of dividing a network address into multiple smaller networks. A subnet mask refers to a mas to separate the network address of the IP address [8]','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 13:46:22','2025-02-19 13:46:22'),(1746,'747','App\\Models\\Subsection','Figures',NULL,'[Figure 127] Addressing with and without a Subnetting Application',2,'67b5e0c2769ec.png','/storage/figures/67b5e0c2769ec.png','2025-02-19 13:46:22','2025-02-19 13:46:42'),(1747,'747','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','Adding : a sub-network generates an intermediate layer in the IP address in order to separate the address into the si subnet, and host','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 13:46:22','2025-02-19 13:46:22'),(1748,'747','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text',') Use of subnet (Results of subnetting using 2 or 3 bits in a class C address)','',3,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 13:46:22','2025-02-19 13:46:22'),(1749,'748','App\\Models\\Subsection','Tables',NULL,'(Table 53) Subnetting Results',1,'67b5e0c288db7.png','/storage/tables/67b5e0c288db7.png','2025-02-19 13:46:22','2025-02-19 13:46:42'),(1750,'749','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','CIDR is a method of combining multiple class € addresses into a network It can reduce the size of the table and use IP addresses in various subnet formats. routing','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 13:46:22','2025-02-19 13:46:22'),(1751,'750','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','Provides flexibility in IP address operation, by allowing users to freely specify the range of network identifiers without classifying the IP addresses for each A B, and C class. The network address can be set freely, preventing wasted IP addresses ad enabling effective network configuration It is an address allocation technique that enables the effective management of IP addresses used for routing between domains.','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 13:46:22','2025-02-19 13:46:22'),(1752,'751','App\\Models\\Subsection','Figures',NULL,'[Figure 128] CIDR Notation',2,'67b5e0c297c6c.png','/storage/figures/67b5e0c297c6c.png','2025-02-19 13:46:22','2025-02-19 13:46:42'),(1753,'751','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','The subnet part of an IP address has an arbitrary length with a format of abcdx In the address format, X refers the subnet of the address','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 13:46:22','2025-02-19 13:46:22'),(1754,'752','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','Supernetting is the opposite concept of subnetting, referring to the consolidation of several small networks into or large network: It is an address allocation technique that allocates consecutive class address blocks to an organizatic and enables routing from the outside, asifit were one address block [9].','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 13:46:22','2025-02-19 13:46:22'),(1755,'753','App\\Models\\Subsection','Figures',NULL,'[Figure 129] Supernetting Method',2,'67b5e0c2a6270.png','/storage/figures/67b5e0c2a6270.png','2025-02-19 13:46:22','2025-02-19 13:46:42'),(1756,'753','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','Grouping multiple class C addresses into a network Use of part of the network identifier as the host identifier The number of consolidated class C addresses must be a power of 2 and must consist of sequential addresse','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 13:46:22','2025-02-19 13:46:22'),(1757,'754','App\\Models\\Subsection','Tables',NULL,'(Table 54) DHCP Message [10]',2,'67b5e0c2b766f.png','/storage/tables/67b5e0c2b766f.png','2025-02-19 13:46:22','2025-02-19 13:46:42'),(1758,'754','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','DHCP is a protocol that provides a method of dynamically allocating IP addresses, and other related configuration details, to DHCP-enabled clients on a network using a DHCP server: The DHCP server can assign a default gateway, a DNS server address, local router a lease period, and a domain name as DHCP options, in addition to the IP address and subnet mask The IPv4 DHCP lease process is established through the exchange of four UDP messages The four UDP messages are DHCPDISCOVER, DHCPOFFER, DHCPREQUEST, and DHCPACK. <Table 54  lists the details.','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 13:46:22','2025-02-19 13:46:22'),(1759,'755','App\\Models\\Subsection','Tables',NULL,'(Table 55) NAT Type [11]',2,'67b5e0c2c7bda.png','/storage/tables/67b5e0c2c7bda.png','2025-02-19 13:46:22','2025-02-19 13:46:42'),(1760,'755','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','NAT is function that interconnects terminals on a private network to communicate with public networks, such as the Internet. It is defined in RFC 3022 and RFC 2663. The purpose of NAT is to hide internal IPs to defend them from outside attacks while solving insufficient IP addresses NAPT (Network Address Port Translation) is an extension of the basic NAT ad converts the packet\'s source port number The reason for using NAPT is to connect to multiple internal hosts with an IP address NAPT can theoretically process communication with up to 65,535 internal hosts with an official IP address using','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 13:46:22','2025-02-19 13:46:22'),(1761,'571','App\\Models\\Section','Text','Pv6 is the next-generation Internet protocol with a 128-bit addressing system developed to solve the current IPv4 roblems, such as address depletion, security, and mobility support','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 13:46:22','2025-02-19 13:46:22'),(1762,'572','App\\Models\\Section','Text','The rapidly increasing hosts ad terminals connected to networks have led to problems with the existing IPv4 addressing system, such as a shortage of IP address space ad poor Internet security: The IPv6 protocol [16] was developed in the mid-90s to solve the problems. Compared to the existing IPv4, the most notable feature of IPv6 is the expansion of the address space, 32 bits, to 128 bits, to enable the use of approximately 3.4 x 1032 addresses, thereby fundamentally solving the problem of address shortage Moreover, it has simplified the head format, by removing header fields that IPv4 does not frequently use and supports effective QoS services While IPv4 does not include security functions, it is necessary to install a security protocol called IPsec (Internet Protocol Security) [17][18] separately: IPv6 has added security and personal protection functions, by providing the end-to-end encryption function in order to solve these problems from','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 13:46:22','2025-02-19 13:46:22'),(1763,'573','App\\Models\\Section','Tables',NULL,'(Table 57) IPv6 Address Notation',4,'67b5e0c2e5c6c.png','/storage/tables/67b5e0c2e5c6c.png','2025-02-19 13:46:22','2025-02-19 13:46:42'),(1764,'573','App\\Models\\Section','Text','IPv6 addresses are 128 bit four times that of IPv4, and expressed in hexadecimal. It consists of the format fix (PFJthat describes the address format and the address field. colon separates each 16-bit field, and each field is expressed in hexadecimal to make it easier to read the addresses. The notation of the IPv6 address network prefix is similar to the CIDR notation of IPv4 The IPv6 address is followed by \"/, and the length of the network prefix is written in decimal. <Table 56  below shows an example of the IPvb address format prefix long, long','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 13:46:22','2025-02-19 13:46:22'),(1765,'573','App\\Models\\Section','Text','The IPv6 addresses are classified into link-local, unicast, multicast, and anycast addresses, according to use: <Table 57  summarizes the IPv6 address notation.','',3,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 13:46:22','2025-02-19 13:46:22'),(1766,'574','App\\Models\\Section','Tables',NULL,'',6,'67b5e0c3135b6.png','/storage/tables/67b5e0c3135b6.png','2025-02-19 13:46:22','2025-02-19 13:46:43'),(1767,'574','App\\Models\\Section','Figures',NULL,'',2,'67b5e0c32c468.png','/storage/figures/67b5e0c32c468.png','2025-02-19 13:46:22','2025-02-19 13:46:43'),(1768,'574','App\\Models\\Section','Figures',NULL,'(Table 59} IPv6 Extension Header Structure and Components',5,'67b5e0c33baeb.png','/storage/figures/67b5e0c33baeb.png','2025-02-19 13:46:22','2025-02-19 13:46:43'),(1769,'574','App\\Models\\Section','Text','<Table 58  describes the IPv6s basic header structure and component IPv6 can have extended headers, in addition to the basic header','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 13:46:22','2025-02-19 13:46:22'),(1770,'574','App\\Models\\Section','Text','IPv6\'s extension header is set to 64 bits ad configured in a chain type  <Table 59  shows the structure and type of extension headers. daisy','',4,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 13:46:22','2025-02-19 13:46:22'),(1771,'575','App\\Models\\Section','Figures',NULL,'',3,'67b5e0c3516e8.png','/storage/figures/67b5e0c3516e8.png','2025-02-19 13:46:23','2025-02-19 13:46:43'),(1772,'575','App\\Models\\Section','Header','Practical preview','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 13:46:23','2025-02-19 13:46:23'),(1773,'575','App\\Models\\Section','Text','The transport layer protocols operate between the computer of user A, and the webserver myservercom that requests data, ie, end-to-end service: Data packets are delivered through many hops between & client and a server The nodes, positioned between the terminals, such as the wiredireless routers, are not involved in the transport layer protocol operation TCP [1], UDP [2], and SCTP [3] are the transport leading','',2,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 13:46:23','2025-02-19 13:46:23'),(1774,'575','App\\Models\\Section','Text','[Figure 130] Protocol Operation Path of Transport Layer','',4,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 13:46:23','2025-02-19 13:46:23'),(1775,'756','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','Flow control controls the packet flow volume to prevent packet loss, due to packet inputs exceeding the reception limit when transmitting data packets The flow control uses transmission and reception buffers that can store packets at the sending/receiving sides, ad the sizes of the sending/receiving buffers are specified in the files Iproc/sysInet/ corelmem_max and Iproc/syshnet/core/rmem_max, respectively for Linux systems.','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 13:46:23','2025-02-19 13:46:23'),(1776,'757','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','Error control detects code errors, that occur transmission, and reproduces accurate information It detects anc liscards damaged packets, tracks and resends lost or removed packets, and checks and discards duplicate receivec ackets during','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 13:46:23','2025-02-19 13:46:23'),(1777,'758','App\\Models\\Subsection','Tables',NULL,'(Table 60) Well-known TCP Ports',2,'67b5e0c364733.png','/storage/tables/67b5e0c364733.png','2025-02-19 13:46:23','2025-02-19 13:46:43'),(1778,'758','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','Congestion occurs when the network load, representing the number of packets transmitted to the network per unit time, exceeds the network capacity, representing the number of packets that can be processed by the network per unit time: In TCP, the congestion control controls issues, such as end-to-end congestion, and ensures that the load is smaller than the network bandwidth, The following table shows well-known ports for widely used TCP services. These services include FTP, for file transfer SSH, for secure remote login, SMTP, POP3, and IMAP4, to send and receive e-mail, and HTTP for web services','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 13:46:23','2025-02-19 13:46:23'),(1779,'576','App\\Models\\Section','Text','TCP is positioned between the application layer and the network layer in a TCPIIP model and provides communication between the application layer processes TCP is a stream-based protocol and has the transmission buffer ad the reception buffer to transfer data. IP at the lower layer of the TCP protocol, transmits data in a packet format, rather than a stream format, by partitioning the data into several segments Flow control, error control, and congestion control techniques are defined to reliably deliver data. TCP is numbered in units of bytes. When a byte is numbered, a sequence number is assigned to the segment The maximum value must be set for a header to include the sequence number of each packet If m bits are set for the sequence number in the packet header, the sequence number ranges from 0 to Zm-1. The sequence number is modular Zm.','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 13:46:23','2025-02-19 13:46:23'),(1780,'577','App\\Models\\Section','Figures',NULL,'[Figure 131] Virtual TCP Operation Scenario',2,'67b5e0c37d85f.png','/storage/figures/67b5e0c37d85f.png','2025-02-19 13:46:23','2025-02-19 13:46:43'),(1781,'577','App\\Models\\Section','Text','The figure below shows a case of data transfer on the TCP protocol layer when user A enters the myservercor homepage and downloads the mypdf fileThe web browser exchanges requests and responses: the transport protocol,, TCP deliver an application layer program, ad the webserver Httpd. Here, the discussion focuses on t operation of the TCP protocol laye','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 13:46:23','2025-02-19 13:46:23'),(1782,'577','App\\Models\\Section','Text','The connection request in step 0 is actually a simple drawing of steps through  , and the connection termination in step is also a simple drawing of steps through Steps through and through are application layer data that is immediately appended after the TCP header According to the HTTP protocol, this data is generated by the web browser on user A\'s computer ad the myservercom web server program: The following section describes the TCP protocol and corresponding steps in detail, TCP flow control is important when a large volume of data, such as PDF files,, is transmitted simultaneously, as shown in through because IP packets can be transmitted through multiple network Error control is crucial to cope with transmission errors Moreover, it is also necessary to understand congestion control, since the transmission of more packets that can be processed per unit time in the network greatly affects TCP performance paths, steps','',3,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 13:46:23','2025-02-19 13:46:23'),(1783,'759','App\\Models\\Subsection','Figures',NULL,'[Figure 132] Three-way Handshake for Connection Establishment [1]',2,'67b5e0c392270.png','/storage/figures/67b5e0c392270.png','2025-02-19 13:46:23','2025-02-19 13:46:43'),(1784,'759','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','The basic way to establish a TCP connection is with a three-way handshake procedure This procedure begins by sending &n SYN segment with a sequence number (SEQ) 100, one TCP endpoint, to another TCP end, as shown in the second step of [Figure 132] The SYN segment means that the SYN control of the TCP header is set to 1_ The ACK segment means that the ACK control is set to 1. The SYN and ACK segments mean that both the SYN control and the ACK control are set to 1 Upon receiving the SYN segment, TCP B sets the SYN control flag (SEQ-300), requesting connection establishment with TCP A TCP B, along with acknowledgment number (ACK) 1011, and sends the SYN and ACK segments, as shown in step 3 in [Figure 132] Upon receiving it, TCP A confirms the ACK control and ACK-101 to recognize that the connection request has been properly delivered: The SYN control set together indicates that TCP B sent the connection request The three-way handshake is complete when the ACK segment (ACK-3OI) is sent to TCP B, and the bidirectional connection, between TCP A and TCP B, is established. As described above, the three-way handshake for TCP connection confirms that the SYN segment, the SYN and ACK segment, and the ACK segment are transferred between TCP terminals At the same time, the sequence number (SEQ) that is transferred between TCP terminals plays an important role in flow and error controls to check whether the data streams are transferred properly in byte units. from flag flag flag \" flag = from flag flag','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 13:46:23','2025-02-19 13:46:23'),(1785,'759','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','TCP manages connection by allocating a system resource, TCB (Transmission Control Block) , upon receiving the SYN segment for connection If a large number of SYN segments are sent in a short time for malicious purposes, the TCP end-host that has received it may not be able to allocate any more TCBs, resulting in the service unavailable This attack is called SYN flooding, and it can be referred to as a type of denial-of-service attack being )According to the TCP flow control method, the next desired byte sequence number 101 is sent as the acknowledgment number','',3,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 13:46:23','2025-02-19 13:46:23'),(1786,'760','App\\Models\\Subsection','Figures',NULL,'[Figure 133] Typical Termination Sequence [1]',2,'67b5e0c3a3ffe.png','/storage/figures/67b5e0c3a3ffe.png','2025-02-19 13:46:23','2025-02-19 13:46:43'),(1787,'760','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','The TCP connection is terminated in the following sequence: The terminal TCP A that intends to terminate the connection, sends the FIN segment (SEQ-100,ACK-300) to TCP B, as in step 2. Here, the ACK control is set and sent a5 an acknowledgment response to the previous transmission Upon receiving it, TCP B sends an ACK segment (SEQ-300, ACK-101) in response, as in step 3. In response to SEQ-100 of the FIN segment, the ACK segment increased by increments of to 101 is transmitted. TCP B then sends the FIN segment (SEQ-300, ACK=101) to TCP A to terminate the connection, as in step 4 As in step 2, ACK is sent together for acknowedgment of previous data transmission Then, TCP A completely terminates the TCP connection by sending an ACK segment (SEQ-101, ACK-301), as in step 5. flag','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 13:46:23','2025-02-19 13:46:23'),(1788,'760','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','In the virtual TCP operation scenario shown in [Figure 133], steps and through correspond to TCP connection termination','',3,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 13:46:23','2025-02-19 13:46:23'),(1789,'761','App\\Models\\Subsection','Tables',NULL,'(Table 63) RWND and CWND',6,'67b5e0c3be461.png','/storage/tables/67b5e0c3be461.png','2025-02-19 13:46:23','2025-02-19 13:46:43'),(1790,'761','App\\Models\\Subsection','Figures',NULL,'[Figure 134] Example of Packet Sending and Receiving by Sliding Window Protocol',2,'67b5e0c3d93dd.png','/storage/figures/67b5e0c3d93dd.png','2025-02-19 13:46:23','2025-02-19 13:46:43'),(1791,'761','App\\Models\\Subsection','Figures',NULL,'[Figure 135] Concept of Sliding Window Protocol',3,'67b5e0c3ec8b5.png','/storage/figures/67b5e0c3ec8b5.png','2025-02-19 13:46:23','2025-02-19 13:46:43'),(1792,'761','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','The flow control balances the rate of data creation and use. TCP uses the window protocol The receiving TCF notifies it by designating the number of octets (1 byte) prepared in advance: The sending TCP may refer to it anc adjust the number of windows Since this field is 16 bits the maximum size of the window is 65,535 bytes sliding sliding long','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 13:46:23','2025-02-19 13:46:23'),(1793,'761','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','The sliding window protocol uses the receiver window (RWND) and the congestion window (CWND): The window size is the lesser of the RWND and CWND:','',5,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 13:46:23','2025-02-19 13:46:23'),(1794,'762','App\\Models\\Subsection','Tables',NULL,'(Table 64} TCP Error Control Tools',2,'67b5e0c409706.png','/storage/tables/67b5e0c409706.png','2025-02-19 13:46:23','2025-02-19 13:46:44'),(1795,'762','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','or control is activated when the transmitted segment is lost, damaged, out of order, or duplicated','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 13:46:23','2025-02-19 13:46:23'),(1796,'763','App\\Models\\Subsection','Figures',NULL,'[Figure 1362] Concept of Slow Start',2,'67b5e0c41c8f8.png','/storage/figures/67b5e0c41c8f8.png','2025-02-19 13:46:23','2025-02-19 13:46:44'),(1797,'763','App\\Models\\Subsection','Figures',NULL,'[Figure 137] Concept of Congestion Avoidance',4,'67b5e0c43212a.png','/storage/figures/67b5e0c43212a.png','2025-02-19 13:46:23','2025-02-19 13:46:44'),(1798,'763','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','Congestion control is a mechanism and technique of maintaining the user traffic volume input to the network to ensure that it does not exceed the network capacity: TCP performs the congestion control, based on the slow start algorithm ad the congestion avoidance algorithm: The slow start algorithm exponentially increases the congestion window size for congestion control, until it reaches the limit','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 13:46:23','2025-02-19 13:46:23'),(1799,'763','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','The congestion avoidance algorithm additively increases the congestion window size, until the congestion stat is detected.','',3,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 13:46:23','2025-02-19 13:46:23'),(1800,'764','App\\Models\\Subsection','Tables',NULL,'(Table 65} Types of TCP Timers',2,'67b5e0c44954e.png','/storage/tables/67b5e0c44954e.png','2025-02-19 13:46:23','2025-02-19 13:46:44'),(1801,'764','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','TCP mostly uses four timers for its operation','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 13:46:23','2025-02-19 13:46:23'),(1802,'578','App\\Models\\Section','Tables',NULL,'(Table 61) TCP Protocol Header Components',2,'67b5e0c46e7f8.png','/storage/tables/67b5e0c46e7f8.png','2025-02-19 13:46:23','2025-02-19 13:46:44'),(1803,'578','App\\Models\\Section','Text','The header format used in the TCP protocol is shown in the following figure [1]. When adding an option,, it is necessary to add a padding byte to fit the 4-byte unit When there is no option, the TCP header is 20 bytes, which is the same size as the IP header Therefore, the TCPIIP header is 40 bytes and must be sent, even when sending one byte of user data. For effective network transmission in an application layer program,, data larger than an appropriate size must be sent to the transport layer','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 13:46:23','2025-02-19 13:46:23'),(1804,'578','App\\Models\\Section','Text','The sequence number SEQ (sequence number) increases by increments of for each 8-bit octet and performs th unsigned module 232 calculation Therefore, the sequence value changes to make 0 _ 232_ 1-0 _ unsigned module 232 calculation Therefore, the sequence value changes to make 0 _ 232_ 1_0   The six for control have the following meanings The SYN, ACK ad FIN control are widely used in the TCP protocol:. URG: The urgent field is meaningful. flags ` flags pointer - The six for control have the following meanings The SYN, ACK, and FIN control flags are widely used in the TCP protocol. flags ` ACK: The acknowledged response field is meaningful PSH: Push function RST: Connection reset SYN: Sequence number synchronization FIN: No more data from the sender','',3,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 13:46:23','2025-02-19 13:46:23'),(1805,'579','App\\Models\\Section','Tables',NULL,'(Table 66) Well-known UDP Ports',2,'67b5e0c48702f.png','/storage/tables/67b5e0c48702f.png','2025-02-19 13:46:23','2025-02-19 13:46:44'),(1806,'579','App\\Models\\Section','Text','User datagram protocol (UDP) provides a connectionless service for sending and receiving data without a pre configuration process for connection. Unlike TCP, it is a protocol that does not guarantee the reliability of the transport layer level Each user datagram of UDP is an independent datagram and is not assigned a number, unlike TCP UDP is a very simple protocol, and there is no control, so there is no window mechanism, and packet overflow may occur: Error Control also has no other error control mechanism, except for checksum: When the receiver detects an error through a checksum, the user datagram is removed, and congestion control is not provided. Due to this nature of the UDP transport protocol, the application layer may be necessary in order to define and implement the control and error control As described above, since the UDP has a continuous minimum transmission rate, despite some packet due to a lack of reception confirmation and retransmission function, it is suitable for video play service and is considered to provide the best effort service In particular, for playing video that is transmitted in real time, the transmitting side must separately include the image frame order in the data. The receiving side must store it in a separate buffer, according to the frame order and process it in order In the case of a streaming method, instead of a download method, if there is a delay for more than a certain time, or if only the B and P frames are received without the frame, the application layer needs to maintain the real-time property by destroying the data. flow flow loss, The UDP protocol is mainly used for the following purposes Aprocess requiring simple request-response communication, without flow and error controls A process with internal flow and error control techniques Multicasting transmission technology Management processes like SNMP <Table 66  below shows well-known ports for widely used UDP services. It supports the NTP service that corrects the host time through the network, the BOOTP and DHCP services that network IP management protocols, the TFTP service that is simpler than FTP, the RIP and OLSR services that are routing protocols, and the Kerberos service that is a computer network authentication protocol. are','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 13:46:23','2025-02-19 13:46:23'),(1807,'580','App\\Models\\Section','Tables',NULL,'<Table 67  User Datagram Header Fields',2,'67b5e0c49c2c0.png','/storage/tables/67b5e0c49c2c0.png','2025-02-19 13:46:23','2025-02-19 13:46:44'),(1808,'580','App\\Models\\Section','Text','UDP packet, called the user datagram, has a fixed-size 8-byte header made of four 2-byte (16-bit) fields, as show elow: Each field of the UDP header is used for the purposes shown in < Table 67  .','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 13:46:23','2025-02-19 13:46:23'),(1809,'580','App\\Models\\Section','Text','The source port refers to the port of the transmitting process, and the destination port refers to the port of a specific destination host The length is the sum of the UDP header (minimum 8) and the data size. The checksum is the result of adding 16-bit Is complement to the pseudo-IP header, UDP header, and data. The checksum field is filled with zeros before the calculation As described above, unlike TCP the UDP protocol is simple to implement because it receives data the application layer and sends it down to the IP layer: It also analyzes the UDP user datagram, that is received from the IP layer, and delivers it to an appropriate application program: from','',3,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 13:46:23','2025-02-19 13:46:23'),(1810,'581','App\\Models\\Section','Tables',NULL,'',3,'67b5e0c4b304b.png','/storage/tables/67b5e0c4b304b.png','2025-02-19 13:46:23','2025-02-19 13:46:44'),(1811,'581','App\\Models\\Section','Text','The stream control transmission protocol (SCTP) is a new transport layer protocol designed by combining UDP and TCP advantages for multimedia communication [3]. The service characteristics of the SCTP are described in the following table The SCTP association is a broader concept than the end-to-end TCP connection In an SCTP association, one or more IP addresses can be connected at each endpoint: It is called multi-homing, and it enables network-level fault tolerance: SCTP is called association in order to highlight its multi-homing nature While a stream is transmitted and received to an end-to-end connection in TCP, multiple streams can be transmitted and received per association in SCTP','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 13:46:23','2025-02-19 13:46:23'),(1812,'581','App\\Models\\Section','Text','The number systems used by the SCTP include the transmission sequence number (TSN), the stream identifier (SI), and the stream sequence number (SSN): The data units in TCP are bytes, whereas data chunks are data units in SCTP A transmission sequence number (TSN) is used to number data chunks. The SCTPs TSN plays a similar role to the TCPs sequence number: Moreover, since multiple streams may exist per SCTP association, a 16-bit stream identifier, starting from 0, is used to distinguish them.','',4,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 13:46:23','2025-02-19 13:46:23'),(1813,'765','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','An association begins with an SCTP user\'s request When end-point A sends an INIT chunk to end-point Z, in order to prevent a SYN attack (synchronization attack) end-point Z sends the INIT ACK chunk containing cookie information Upon receiving it, end-point A copies the received cookie and sends the COOKIE ECHO chunk back to end-point Z to inform that it has been properly received, and end- 2 sends the COOKIE-ACK chunk to complete the four- way handshake Generating a transmission control block (TCB) , which is the main resource, only when the normal COOKIE ECHO chunk is received at end-point Z, solves the denial of service (DoS) problem caused by a SYN attack, due to generating a TCB as soon as the SYN segment is received during the TCB connection establishment point again, system','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 13:46:23','2025-02-19 13:46:23'),(1814,'766','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','In SCTP a stream means a series of user messages The SCTP user can set the number of streams that can be supported when setting the association, and these streams are identified by the stream identifier Sl. Moreover assigning the SSN to the user message in the stream, enables the delivery of data chunks in normal order: Other streams can be transmitted even if one stream is blocked to deliver the next sequence of user messages','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 13:46:23','2025-02-19 13:46:23'),(1815,'767','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','Is in TCP, user messages are limited by a maximum transmission unit (MTU) in SCTP and a fragmentation path echnique is provided to resolve it Each fragment that has been divided and transmitted is reassembled in the SCTP ayer to become one user message','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 13:46:23','2025-02-19 13:46:23'),(1816,'768','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','SCTP transmits a data chunk by assigning a TSN to it, regardless of the stream. The receiving side separately secures the transmission reliability from the sequenced stream transmission by acknowledging (ACK) all the received TSNs Acknowledgment and congestion control functions are related to packet retransmission if an acknowledgment is not received within a given time. Packet retransmission is performed according to a congestion avoidance procedure, similar to TCP congestion control:','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 13:46:23','2025-02-19 13:46:23'),(1817,'769','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','chunk with multiple user data or SCTP control information may follow an SCTP packet\'s common header An SCTF ser can request to bundle multiple user messages in a single SCTP packet The SCTP chunk bundling function is sponsible for assembling multiple chunks into one SCTP packet and decomposing it','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 13:46:23','2025-02-19 13:46:23'),(1818,'770','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','The SCTP common header has a verification (VT) and a 32-bit checksum field. The VT is a value selected each endpoint when setting up the association. the set association, SCTP packets must be transmitted using the same VT, and if an SCTP packet with a wrong VT is received, it is discarded. Moreover, generating a CRC32 checksum and transmitting the SCTP packet prevents data corruption in the network tag During -','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 13:46:23','2025-02-19 13:46:23'),(1819,'771','App\\Models\\Subsection','Tables',NULL,'(Table 70} Chunk Types',4,'67b5e0c4cb006.png','/storage/tables/67b5e0c4cb006.png','2025-02-19 13:46:23','2025-02-19 13:46:44'),(1820,'771','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','The transmitting SCTP user can use the management function to manipulate the transport address, SCTP port number, and IP address, used in the SCTP packet destination When the association is established, the primary of each SCTP endpoint is defined and used to transmit and receive SCTP packets However, if there is a problem with the current and available transmission address among the addresses, defined by multi-homing, can be designated as an alternative The management ad the packet verification that uses the VT ad checksum are performed simultaneously: SCTP packets have a general header and set of blocks called chunks. There are two types of chunks: control chunks and data chunks. Control chunks are delivered before data chunks The general header defines the endpoint of each association of the packet, guarantees a packet belonging to a specific association, and preserves the integrity of the contents of the packet, including the header itself path path path, path path','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 13:46:23','2025-02-19 13:46:23'),(1821,'771','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','Control information and user data are carried in chunks, and three fields of Type,, and Length are common in all Flag, chunks The information field indicates the type of the chunk, ad the Type field is defined up to 256 bytes of chunk but only some are defined, and the rest are reserved for future use. The Flag field defines special flags may require special chunks. In some chunk types, the data chunk is identified as the control chunk <Table 70  shows major chunk types','',3,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 13:46:23','2025-02-19 13:46:23'),(1822,'582','App\\Models\\Section','Text','Since it is not feasible to discuss everything about SCTP this section briefly describes the SCTP transmission service, as shown in the following figure SCTP functions can be classified into the following eight types. Association start and eni Sequenced delivery User data fragmentation Acknowledgment Congestion avoidance Chunk bundling Packet validation Path management','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 13:46:23','2025-02-19 13:46:23'),(1823,'583','App\\Models\\Section','Tables',NULL,'',4,'67b5e0c4e07e6.png','/storage/tables/67b5e0c4e07e6.png','2025-02-19 13:46:24','2025-02-19 13:46:44'),(1824,'583','App\\Models\\Section','Figures',NULL,'',2,'67b5e0c4f1751.png','/storage/figures/67b5e0c4f1751.png','2025-02-19 13:46:24','2025-02-19 13:46:45'),(1825,'583','App\\Models\\Section','Figures',NULL,'',8,'67b5e0c510c60.png','/storage/figures/67b5e0c510c60.png','2025-02-19 13:46:24','2025-02-19 13:46:45'),(1826,'583','App\\Models\\Section','Figures',NULL,'',11,'67b5e0c51f8e6.png','/storage/figures/67b5e0c51f8e6.png','2025-02-19 13:46:24','2025-02-19 13:46:45'),(1827,'583','App\\Models\\Section','Code',NULL,'',6,'67b5e0c52c84a.png','/storage/code/67b5e0c52c84a.png','2025-02-19 13:46:24','2025-02-19 13:46:45'),(1828,'583','App\\Models\\Section','Code',NULL,'',10,'67b5e0c5375d3.png','/storage/code/67b5e0c5375d3.png','2025-02-19 13:46:24','2025-02-19 13:46:45'),(1829,'583','App\\Models\\Section','Text','FTP uses the control connection to facilitate communication between a server control process and a clier control process','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 13:46:24','2025-02-19 13:46:24'),(1830,'583','App\\Models\\Section','Text','It is processed interactively and is divided into a command that a user to the server as well as recnonse to gives Command types included in FTP command messages','',3,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 13:46:24','2025-02-19 13:46:24'),(1831,'583','App\\Models\\Section','Text','The general transfer mode and passive transfer mode operate in the time sequence shown in the figure below:','',5,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 13:46:24','2025-02-19 13:46:24'),(1832,'583','App\\Models\\Section','Text','General transfer mode operation','',7,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 13:46:24','2025-02-19 13:46:24'),(1833,'583','App\\Models\\Section','Text','1) The client connects to the server\'s port 21 and informs the server of the second port it intends to 2) The server responds with ACK 3) The servers 20 attempts to connect to the second port informed by the client The client responds with ACK port Passive FTP mode operation','',9,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 13:46:24','2025-02-19 13:46:24'),(1834,'583','App\\Models\\Section','Text','1) The client attempts to connect to the command port 2) The server informs the second it intends to use 3) The client opens another port and attempts to connect to the informed by the server The server responds with ACK port port','',12,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 13:46:24','2025-02-19 13:46:24'),(1835,'772','App\\Models\\Subsection','Tables',NULL,'(Table 72) Lossless Compression',2,'67b5e0c54b1ec.png','/storage/tables/67b5e0c54b1ec.png','2025-02-19 13:46:24','2025-02-19 13:46:45'),(1836,'772','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','Since the compression and decompression algorithms are the exact opposite of each other the compression method preserves the original data\'s integrity, and no of the data is lost processing: Leading lossless compression methods include run-length encoding, dictionary decoding, Huffman coding, dictionary coding, ad arithmetic coding: during part','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 13:46:24','2025-02-19 13:46:24'),(1837,'773','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','The compression method compromises some accuracy in order to increase the compression rate, by allowing the loss of redundant or unnecessary data. There are two types of lossy compression methods: prediction coding and transform coding: The prediction coding method is used for digitizing the analog signal. Instead of separately quantizing the PCM (Pulse Code Modulation) samples, it quantizes the difference: The difference values are smaller than the actual sample values, so fewer bits are required. The transform coding method transforms a signal, from one domain (mainly time ad space domain) , to another domain (mainly frequency domain), then compressesit lossy','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 13:46:24','2025-02-19 13:46:24'),(1838,'584','App\\Models\\Section','Text','Video data compression, which accounts for most of the traffic in a multimedia network, can be divided into lossless compression (reversible compression) and compression (irreversible compression): Lossless compression, also called reversible compression, refers to restoring a compressed image, without information loss of the original data when decompressing: It is characterized by a lower compression rate than compression Lossy compression, also called irreversible compression, refers to a compression method that the restored data, when the compressed data is restored, does not match the original data before compression because some data is lost lossy lossy \' from','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 13:46:24','2025-02-19 13:46:24'),(1839,'585','App\\Models\\Section','Figures',NULL,'[Figure 140] Image Data Transformation Process',2,'67b5e0c5649f6.png','/storage/figures/67b5e0c5649f6.png','2025-02-19 13:46:24','2025-02-19 13:46:45'),(1840,'585','App\\Models\\Section','Text','Multimedia data includes text,, image, video, and audio data. The text has the form of plain text and non-linear hypertext, and the basic language is Unicode for expressing symbols and uses a lossless compression method. In multimedia,an image is called a still image and refers to a photo, fax page, or video frame. As shown in [Figure 1], an image is transmitted as binary data, through a transformation process, a quantization process, ad a encoding process. The data is converted back into an image, through the reverse process: In the transformation process, the JPEG uses DCT (Discrete Cosine Transform) in the first stage of compression, and the decompression uses the inverse DCT method. The transformation and inverse transformation apply 8 X 8 blocks The quantization process integerizes the real number of the DCT transform output and converts some values to zero. The coding process arranges data in a zigzag order after quantization and before encoder input, and lossless compression is performed using run-length decoding and arithmetic coding [1].','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 13:46:24','2025-02-19 13:46:24'),(1841,'585','App\\Models\\Section','Text','Video data is composed of several frames Since each frame is an image, a video file requires a high transmission rate Video data can be compressed with a compression or a temporal compression method. JPEG performs spatial compression of each frame, and each frame is compressed independently: Temporal compression removes redundant frames ad configures each frame into I-frames, which are independent frames and B-frames ad P-frames, which reference other |-frames in order to compress data temporally: audio signals are digitized an analog-to-digital converter (ADC), and ADC consists of two processes: sampling ad quantization spatial Analog using','',3,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 13:46:24','2025-02-19 13:46:24'),(1842,'586','App\\Models\\Section','Tables',NULL,'(Table 73) TOS Field Values [4]',4,'67b5e0c576b5d.png','/storage/tables/67b5e0c576b5d.png','2025-02-19 13:46:24','2025-02-19 13:46:45'),(1843,'586','App\\Models\\Section','Figures',NULL,'[Figure 141] QoS Utilizing RSVP',2,'67b5e0c586e05.png','/storage/figures/67b5e0c586e05.png','2025-02-19 13:46:24','2025-02-19 13:46:45'),(1844,'586','App\\Models\\Section','Text','Methods for guaranteeing QoS in a multimedia network include the RSVP (resource reservation protocol) and th TOS (type of service) field utilization As shown in [Figure 141], the RSVP method processes data transmission wit fixed network bandwidth allocation from the source to the destination. The TOS field utilization designates the TO field class in each packet to determine the processing priority:','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 13:46:24','2025-02-19 13:46:24'),(1845,'586','App\\Models\\Section','Text','RSVP is one of the IETF signaling protocols, and data flow is allocated by a static bandwidth by signaling from end-to- end. It basically uses the method of reserving the queue space [2]. The RSVP message starts from the source device and is delivered to all the receiving devices on the It is a message that contains the necessary information for the receiver and a message sent by the receiver upon receiving the message A RESV message reserves the resource of a router that moves toward the source device (upstream) to support RSVP If a router on the does not support RSVP, packets are delivered, based on the best-effort delivery method The priority method, the TOS field of IP datagram, checks the I-byte TOS field, as shown in [Figure 140], and determines the processing priority according to the set value: The TOS class is divided into eight levels from class 0 to 7,and the higher the number the higher the processing priority: Precedence, the first field, indicates the priority or importance of the packet, and the TOS fields indicate whether the network maintains a balance between throughput, delay, reliability, and cost: The last MBZ (must be zero) field is a field that is not currently The TOS field is expressed asa 4-bit binary number <Table 73  shows the meaning of each value path: path path path using used','',3,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 13:46:24','2025-02-19 13:46:24'),(1846,'587','App\\Models\\Section','Figures',NULL,'[Figure 142] VolP System Structure',2,'67b5e0c59d94d.png','/storage/figures/67b5e0c59d94d.png','2025-02-19 13:46:24','2025-02-19 13:46:45'),(1847,'587','App\\Models\\Section','Text','VoIP is a communication technology that facilitates voice calls through packet data, based on the IP network [Figure 142] shows the VolP system structure: The main service components are the media gateway and the signaling gateway The media gateway exchanges multimedia data, delivers the changed date to the corresponding network and controls it through the media gateway control protocol (MGCP): The signaling gateway performs call signaling, protocols, such as H.323, SIP, MGCP, and MEGACO, and converts the signals of the PSTN and IP networks, so thev can be used with each other using','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 13:46:24','2025-02-19 13:46:24'),(1848,'774','App\\Models\\Subsection','Tables',NULL,'(Table 74) SIP Protocol Components',3,'67b5e0c5b4354.png','/storage/tables/67b5e0c5b4354.png','2025-02-19 13:46:24','2025-02-19 13:46:45'),(1849,'774','App\\Models\\Subsection','Figures',NULL,'[Figure 143] SIP Protocol Stack',2,'67b5e0c5c44df.png','/storage/figures/67b5e0c5c44df.png','2025-02-19 13:46:24','2025-02-19 13:46:45'),(1850,'774','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','SIP is a application layer signaling protocol, used to establish, modify, and terminate multimedia sessions. It operates independently of the lower-layer transport protocols and has scalability as an HTTP text-based protocol It controls sessions to enable call control in a circuit-switched data network in packet-switching network and multimedia applications on the Interet, which is a packet network It can support text-based addressing methods in URL and E-mail format and message parsing or extension. [Figure 143] shows the SIP protocol stack located on of the transport layer protocols TCP and UDP< Table 74  shows the SIP protocol components top','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 13:46:24','2025-02-19 13:46:24'),(1851,'775','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','SIP uses a SIP uniform resource identifier (URI) , similar to an e-mail address, to identify users to provide services without dependent on IP addresses. A SIP message contains the START LINE to describe the method type to request ad SIP URI, the HEADER to set the value to control the session, the BODY containing the type set in Content-Type, and CRJLF a blank space between HEADER and BODY: being','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 13:46:24','2025-02-19 13:46:24'),(1852,'588','App\\Models\\Section','Text','VolP call signaling protocols include SIP (Session Initiation Protocol) and H.323. The SIP protocol is an application layer signaling protocol that specifies a procedure for intelligent terminals that are communicating on the Internet in order to identify each other, find their locations, and create or delete a multimedia communication session between them. The H.323 protocol is an ITU-T standard for providing voice, data, and video services on a LAN that does not guarantee quality Startup VolP service providers use it widely because it can provide multimedia services without changing the existing network\'s underlying structure','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 13:46:24','2025-02-19 13:46:24'),(1853,'589','App\\Models\\Section','Figures',NULL,'[Figure 144] H.323 Network Architecture',2,'67b5e0c5da5e3.png','/storage/figures/67b5e0c5da5e3.png','2025-02-19 13:46:24','2025-02-19 13:46:45'),(1854,'589','App\\Models\\Section','Text','H323 is an ITU-T standard for providing voice, data, and video services over LAN where quality is not guaranteec Startup VolP service providers use it widely because it can provide multimedia services without changing the existine network\'s underlying structure [Figure 144] shows the H.323 network architecture. The service components include terminals, such as genera telephones, fax machines,, and PCs equipped with multimedia equipment that are used by end users. Othe components are a gatekeeper that converts between E.164 and the IP address, performs redirection anc authentication for calls, and manages the components and bandwidth, and a gateway that performs the logica connection mapping (encoding, protocol,, and call control) of different networks (IP network PSTN,, ISDN, ATM, etc):','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 13:46:24','2025-02-19 13:46:24'),(1855,'590','App\\Models\\Section','Figures',NULL,'[Figure 145] VoLTE Service Model on 36 Networks',2,'67b5e0c5f1300.png','/storage/figures/67b5e0c5f1300.png','2025-02-19 13:46:24','2025-02-19 13:46:45'),(1856,'590','App\\Models\\Section','Text','VoLTE is a technology that provides data and voice through the LTE network It provides voice services in the LTE environment, the next-generation wireless broadband network technology: Although VoLTE refers to the voice service domain, since LTE technology is based on an all-IP, data-only network the VoLTE service is implemented in the form of digital data Therefore, it transmits voice, text, video chat,, and multimedia content in the SIP which is the main solution for Internet telephony services. It provides voice and text services, which exist as data, through the IMS (IP multimedia subsystem) architecture These VoLTE technology solutions were not implemented flawlessly at the beginning It was because the LTE infrastructure was not yet fully equipped, so voice services could not be transmitted over the WCDMAGSM networks freely: The problem was that while roaming and interconnection were required between LTE and 36 networks to provide seamless communication services, there was no standard agreement on roaming and interconnection between new and old networks The following two steps can be considered to resolve the problem Firstly, the circuit-switched fallback solution establishes calls, mainly over the WCDMA/GSM circuit network, and LTE terminal vendors and mobile telecommunication carriers perform minimal roaming: However, multimedia communication service is not implemented at this stage Secondly, if the coverage is established to some extent after the initial stage of LTE network construction, it evolves into the stage of implementing a multimedia communication service, through an appropriate solution, such as 3GPP MMTel (Multimedia Telephony): [Figure 145] shows how VoLTE services are implemented over 36 networks. calling','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 13:46:24','2025-02-19 13:46:24'),(1857,'591','App\\Models\\Section','Text','RTP is designed to process real-time traffic over the Internet: It is mainly used to transmit video or audio data in real time over the Internet It is performed over the UDP (user datagram protocol) of the transport layer In the RTP protocol, the transmitting side that sends the media file, converts the media unit data compressed with the codec into an RTP packet and sends it to the receiving side, using UDP Since it is transmitted using UDP, RTP does not guarantee that packets are delivered within a specified time and are not lost: Therefore, the video and audio applications must process packets, using information included in the RTP packet header RTCP can ensure the QoS of RTP and synchronization of media streams','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 13:46:24','2025-02-19 13:46:24'),(1858,'592','App\\Models\\Section','Text','TCP controls RTP, a protocol for streaming video or audio over the Internet: It is an IETF standard defined togethe ith RTP in RFC 1889 RTCP packet types include the sender report packet, receiver report packet, source descriptio essage, bye message, and application-specific packet','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 13:46:24','2025-02-19 13:46:24'),(1859,'593','App\\Models\\Section','Text','RTSP is an application layer protocol that transmits real-time media. The communication protocol developed by IETF in 1998 is defined in RFC 2326. It is a communication protocol for transmitting ad receiving audio and moving pictures in real time,as well as a standard protocol for controlling streaming data on the Internet It is used to remotely control media servers Its commands are similar to VCR operations, such as \"PLAY\" and \"PAUSE\" , and it accesses the server, based on time information','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 13:46:24','2025-02-19 13:46:24'),(1860,'776','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','MS is a communication platform defined by 3GPP to control multimedia sessions &nd provide services, based on the SIP It is a core network for providing integrated services in wired [wireless multiple access network environments','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 13:46:24','2025-02-19 13:46:24'),(1861,'777','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','IMS provides multimedia content, such as voice, audio, video, and data, based on the IP protocol, and it supports quick service development and change It uses general-purpose Internet-based technology to improve the price competitiveness of services and enable easy interface with various 3rd party applications, based on an efficient session management function and expansion of business areas, through global between services, linking','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 13:46:24','2025-02-19 13:46:24'),(1862,'778','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','The logical structure of an all-IP network is divided into a radio network domain, a GPRS-based packet-switching service domain, and an IP multimedia service domain. The GPRS-based packet-switching service domain can be replaced with an IP network by a packet router outside the 3GPP scope. The wireless domain can be replaced with other wireless network access domains and data network access domains, as Wibro and mobile-LAN that are out of the 3GPP scope The IMS service domain consists of the call session control function (CSCF) that registers and processes multimedia calls the IETFs SIP protocol and the home subscriber server (HSS) that integrates the home location register (HLR) function of the legacy mobile network with the function to mobility management ad authentication of IP multimedia users. using','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 13:46:24','2025-02-19 13:46:24'),(1863,'779','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','ID and authentication system in the convergence environment, using the IMS infrastructc Bidirectional channel for service control Service session connection, through the independent service infrastructure','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 13:46:24','2025-02-19 13:46:24'),(1864,'594','App\\Models\\Section','Text','IMS was first proposed by the 3GPP (3rd Generation Partnership Project) group that develops international standard in the wireless communication field. It is an infrastructure for providing IP multimedia services and uses SIP protocol based call control as a core technology:','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 13:46:24','2025-02-19 13:46:24'),(1865,'595','App\\Models\\Section','Figures',NULL,'[Figure 146] loT Applications',2,'67b5e0c62a841.png','/storage/figures/67b5e0c62a841.png','2025-02-19 13:46:25','2025-02-19 13:46:46'),(1866,'595','App\\Models\\Section','Text','loT (Internet of Things) is a concept that embeds sensors and communication functions in various objects to connect to the Interet It refers to the technology that can perform sensing, networking, and information processing, through cooperation, without explicit human intervention. At the same time, the ubiquitous technology that allows access to information and communication networks, regardless of time and place as a concept that exists anywhere at the same time and is ubiquitous and the machine-to-machine (MZM) technology that enables intelligent communication between objects have evolved further As such, loT enables all things to exchange information through the Internet, without boundaries between people and objects.','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 13:46:25','2025-02-19 13:46:25'),(1867,'596','App\\Models\\Section','Figures',NULL,'[Figure 147] Standard Scope of Each loT Standardization Organization [10]',2,'67b5e0c64ab06.png','/storage/figures/67b5e0c64ab06.png','2025-02-19 13:46:25','2025-02-19 13:46:46'),(1868,'596','App\\Models\\Section','Text','3GPP and ETSI have established mobile communication-based IoT standards, but since 2012, have been led by an international consultative body called, oneMZM The Open Mobile Alliance (OMA) proposed a communication method, based on a server-client structure, by establishing the Lightweight MZM (LWMZM) protocol: oneMZM has released LWMZM, which CoAP (Constrained Application Protocol) and HTTP for data transfer, as the latest standard, they applies [Figure 147] shows the standard scope of each standardization organization for protocol layer','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 13:46:25','2025-02-19 13:46:25'),(1869,'780','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','Sensors collect object information. Various sensors, such as temperature, humidity, heat, gas, illuminance, and ultrasonic waves, are installed in the object to obtain information about the surrounding situation Sensors are needed to minimize power consumption in order to operate for & time Physical sensors have evolved into smart sensors with a standardized interface and information processing capability, ad include a virtual sensing function that extracts specific information from the sensed data. As the sensor layers role has increased, the hardware platform market is evolving to facilitate connecting various sensors, control, and communication, using open-source hardware long - they CHM','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 13:46:25','2025-02-19 13:46:25'),(1870,'781','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','Although objects generally use wired means, such as Ethernet or power line communication (PLC), to access the Internet, wireless communication is more efficient when considering the installation convenience and mobility: Short- range wireless communication, such as WLAN, Bluetooth, ZigBee, and UWB, and mobile communication, such as 36 and LTE, are available Moreover, new technologies for sensor networking are constantly proposed BLE (Bluetooth Low Energy): Also called Bluetooth Smart, it is low-power, short-range wireless communication that is not compatible with existing Bluetooth but is compatible with Bluetooth 40. Z-Wave: It is a protocol for devices that use intelligent mesh network topology, do not have a master node, and reauire low power and low bandwidth being','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 13:46:25','2025-02-19 13:46:25'),(1871,'782','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','It is necessary to use ontology-based semantic web technology, cloud computing for large-scale distributec processing, and open API for accessing various services, to automatically analyze and share data collected from the sensor of an object','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 13:46:25','2025-02-19 13:46:25'),(1872,'597','App\\Models\\Section','Text','Ts main technologies are a sensing technology, a wired and wireless communication ad network infrastructure chnology, and an loT service and interface technology:','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 13:46:25','2025-02-19 13:46:25'),(1873,'783','App\\Models\\Subsection','Figures',NULL,'[Figure 148] CoAP Conceptual Diagram',2,'67b5e0c65c034.png','/storage/figures/67b5e0c65c034.png','2025-02-19 13:46:25','2025-02-19 13:46:46'),(1874,'783','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','CoAP is lightweight application layer protocol, developed by the IETF CORE Working Group, for communication between objects. Although it uses the UDP transport layer above the IP layer it is designed independently of the lower layers and can operate in other networks and transport layers. It has reduced the message size to reduce end- point load and uses binary encoding to facilitate encoding and decoding:','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 13:46:25','2025-02-19 13:46:25'),(1875,'783','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','CoAP has attracted attention as the main protocol for loT, since it communicates with endpoints using Zigbee, rather than fast and stable Ethernet or Wi-Fi.','',3,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 13:46:25','2025-02-19 13:46:25'),(1876,'784','App\\Models\\Subsection','Tables',NULL,'(Table 75} Comparison of MQTT and CoAP',4,'67b5e0c66d45e.png','/storage/tables/67b5e0c66d45e.png','2025-02-19 13:46:25','2025-02-19 13:46:46'),(1877,'784','App\\Models\\Subsection','Figures',NULL,'[Figure 149] MQTT Applications',2,'67b5e0c6811c2.png','/storage/figures/67b5e0c6811c2.png','2025-02-19 13:46:25','2025-02-19 13:46:46'),(1878,'784','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','MQTT is publish-subscribe-based protocol for delivering lightweight messages at low in high-latency and unreliable networks speed','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 13:46:25','2025-02-19 13:46:25'),(1879,'784','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','MQTT is a flexible data transfer model between multiple endpoints and multiple servers and operates by publishing and subscribing to necessary topics [Figure 149] shows a conceptual diagram of transmitting the topic of the door opening ad closing, by sending pressure sensor data to the access control system, video security system, and building energy control system, Arduino and the metadata topic that is generated by the camera\'s image sensor to multiple systems, using MQTT: Although the protocols based on CoAP and HTTP are widely used currently, the standardization organizations are still suggesting architectures using MQTT and REST. OASIS continues to update the MQTT standard: [14] using','',3,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 13:46:25','2025-02-19 13:46:25'),(1880,'598','App\\Models\\Section','Text','Protocols for loT require lightweight the most, and since have been commonly used for some time, protocols that feature compatibility and scalability are preferable. In particular CoAP and MQTT are suitable for small devices that need to connect to the Internet and transmit data, due to the nature of loT, and are proposed as communication protocols in various architectures they','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 13:46:25','2025-02-19 13:46:25'),(1881,'785','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','Current applications generate a large volume of traffic, by accessing various application servers and databases before providing users data. The environment is changing from the limited communication between the client and the serve to access between various systems','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 13:46:25','2025-02-19 13:46:25'),(1882,'786','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','Virtualization technology has dramatically increased the number of servers connected to the network fundamentally changing the assumptions about the hosts physical location','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 13:46:25','2025-02-19 13:46:25'),(1883,'787','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','Network structures are becoming more complex, as a large number of computers are configured of discrete protocol sets:','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 13:46:25','2025-02-19 13:46:25'),(1884,'788','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','Initial designs use a link oversubscription method that considers the expected traffic patterns and the numbe of concurrent users However, it is becoming more difficult to predict the network size, as traffic patterns chang dynamically:','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 13:46:25','2025-02-19 13:46:25'),(1885,'789','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','particular, the core network has had difficulties in introducing new services or technologies as certain majc uipment manufacturers dominated the communication market','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 13:46:25','2025-02-19 13:46:25'),(1886,'790','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','SDN was first proposed at the Open Network Summit, conference specializing in SDN and open flow, held at Stanford University in October 2010. SDN and OpenFlow are technologies that program and configure or operate networks, like computers have attracted attention as new innovative communication environmental technologies. In March 2011, ONF (Open Networking Foundation) was formed to promote and standardize OpenFlow and SDN They','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 13:46:25','2025-02-19 13:46:25'),(1887,'791','App\\Models\\Subsection','Figures',NULL,'[Figure 150] SDN Architecture [5]',2,'67b5e0c69391b.png','/storage/figures/67b5e0c69391b.png','2025-02-19 13:46:25','2025-02-19 13:46:46'),(1888,'791','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','As shown in [Figure 150], SDN enables programming networks by separating the control plane (to guide the networ to which it goes) from the data plane (to send packets to a specific destination). The basis of SDN is a switch tha uses industry standard control protocols, such as OpenFlow, and can be programmed through an SDN controller','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 13:46:25','2025-02-19 13:46:25'),(1889,'792','App\\Models\\Subsection','Figures',NULL,'[Figure 151] Main Components of OpenFlow Switch [6]',2,'67b5e0c6a0d01.png','/storage/figures/67b5e0c6a0d01.png','2025-02-19 13:46:25','2025-02-19 13:46:46'),(1890,'792','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','As shown in [Figure 151], the OpenFlow technology separates the functions to control and transfer the packets and controls the network through programming: OpenFlow consists of a controller and a switch The controller issues commands to the switch, and the switch performs tasks related to data flow, such as sending or modifying packets to the destination according to the commands','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 13:46:25','2025-02-19 13:46:25'),(1891,'793','App\\Models\\Subsection','Figures',NULL,'[Figure 152] Network Structure beforelafter SDN Application',2,'67b5e0c6ae2e5.png','/storage/figures/67b5e0c6ae2e5.png','2025-02-19 13:46:25','2025-02-19 13:46:46'),(1892,'793','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','As shown in [Figure 152], network devices have had a control plane and a data plane implemented in one device now: However, when SDN is applied, the controller performs the control plane function of each network device, only the data plane function remains in the actual physical network device Here, OpenFlow plays a role as an interface standard technology for SDN operation','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 13:46:25','2025-02-19 13:46:25'),(1893,'793','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','For example, it removes computational operations in medium and large routers and leaves only a simple switching function Each router simply operates according to a command issued by the controller','',3,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 13:46:25','2025-02-19 13:46:25'),(1894,'600','App\\Models\\Section','Text','SDN is a next-generation network technology that can set the network routing and control and complex operation management through software programming: The technology attracted attention when ONF introduced the OpenFlow technology, ad international standardization organizations, such as IETF and ITU-T, began to develop standards for SDN-related core technologies. There is heated competition in the industry for securing leadership in SDN technology standards','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 13:46:25','2025-02-19 13:46:25'),(1895,'794','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','With the increase in network speed and the emergence of various services, securing space and power to accommodate the rapidly increasing network equipment has become a crucial issue for Interet service providers Moreover the lifespan f network equipment is shortened, making it increasingly difficult to secure profits after introducing new equipment NFV was introduced to solve these problems through virtualization technology:','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 13:46:25','2025-02-19 13:46:25'),(1896,'795','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','NFV runs on & high-performance x86 platform and allows users to activate the necessary network functions a5 needed. It creates a VM (Virtual Machine) or service profile and implements virtualization on the network by utilizing the x86 capabilities','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 13:46:25','2025-02-19 13:46:25'),(1897,'796','App\\Models\\Subsection','Tables',NULL,'(Table 76) NFV Architecture Framework Configuration',4,'67b5e0c6be9a2.png','/storage/tables/67b5e0c6be9a2.png','2025-02-19 13:46:25','2025-02-19 13:46:46'),(1898,'796','App\\Models\\Subsection','Figures',NULL,'',2,'67b5e0c6d3098.png','/storage/figures/67b5e0c6d3098.png','2025-02-19 13:46:25','2025-02-19 13:46:46'),(1899,'796','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','As shown in <Table 76  , the NFV architecture framework consists of three function groups: VNF group, NFL infrastructure, and management and orchestration','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 13:46:25','2025-02-19 13:46:25'),(1900,'796','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','[Figure 153] NFV Architecture Framework (Five VNF Interface Types) [7]','',3,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 13:46:25','2025-02-19 13:46:25'),(1901,'797','App\\Models\\Subsection','Figures',NULL,'[Figure 154] NFV Implementation',2,'67b5e0c6e3151.png','/storage/figures/67b5e0c6e3151.png','2025-02-19 13:46:25','2025-02-19 13:46:46'),(1902,'797','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','NFV uses virtualization to implement network equipment functions It not only operates on specialized equipment but also implements the network equipment functions in a general high-performance x86 server platform, as showr in [Fioure 1541','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 13:46:25','2025-02-19 13:46:25'),(1903,'601','App\\Models\\Section','Text','NFV has emerged as a new topic, thanks to the high interest of network operators. Moreover, the NFV Group is preparing standards for major telecommunications operators and equipment manufacturers and is promoting a PoC (Proof of Concept) to check the feasibility of the technology:','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 13:46:25','2025-02-19 13:46:25'),(1904,'798','App\\Models\\Subsection','Figures',NULL,'[Figure 155] Relationship between NFV SDN [8]',1,'67b5e0c6f3580.png','/storage/figures/67b5e0c6f3580.png','2025-02-19 13:46:25','2025-02-19 13:46:47'),(1905,'798','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','SDN enables faster change by creating a abstracted network, ad NFV reduces capital expenditures (CAPEX), operating expenditures (OPEX), and space and resource consumption NFV and SDN have a complementary relationship and can be independently configured.','',2,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 13:46:25','2025-02-19 13:46:25'),(1906,'799','App\\Models\\Subsection','Tables',NULL,'',1,'67b5e0c71751d.png','/storage/tables/67b5e0c71751d.png','2025-02-19 13:46:25','2025-02-19 13:46:47'),(1907,'602','App\\Models\\Section','Text','Initially, SDN was developed mainly by researchers and data center designers, and NFV was developed by Interne service providers (ISPs): However, SDN and NFV technologies are complementary to each other and ISPs currenth combine the two technologies and apply them to networks','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 13:46:25','2025-02-19 13:46:25'),(1908,'603','App\\Models\\Section','Figures',NULL,'(a) IT utilization',2,'67b65b8bd5915.png','/storage/figures/67b65b8bd5915.png','2025-02-19 22:30:21','2025-02-19 22:30:36'),(1909,'603','App\\Models\\Section','Figures',NULL,'',3,'67b65b8c3be7e.png','/storage/figures/67b65b8c3be7e.png','2025-02-19 22:30:21','2025-02-19 22:30:36'),(1910,'603','App\\Models\\Section','Text','IT business refers to all activities that are strategically carried out by integrating IT into a broad range of processes tc realize the business objectives of a company: In the twentieth century, computers were installed mainly in computing rooms and used only sparingly in the ordinan} working environment of most businesses However, since the 1990s, with the development of computers ad the mass adoption of web technology, the use of computers has gradually been extended to the ordinary working oni iironmant This popularization of computer technology accelerated rapidly in the twenty-first century with the infiltration of IT into every corner of the national industries From this point on,, the lifestyle of the great majority of people began to transition to one centered on digital technologies, and IT began to play a key role in the business processes of almost all industries In other words, companies were not utilizing computers only partially in the workplace, rather IT began to play a key role in companies\' decision-making process from an enterprise-wide perspective to piay a key roie In companies aecision-making process Trom an enterprise-wiae perspective: Around 2005, the concept of \'IT business\' first began to be discussed and recognized in earnest by people working in the field, mainly in industries that sell products where IT is critical. After 2010,as a growing number of companies integrated IT into their business processes, the concept of IT business evolved into a structure in which IT is tightly merged with business processes in order to give companies a competitive advantage In particular decision-makers in the world of business began to recognize the importance of fully incorporating IT into their businesses in order to acquire high-quality data in a rapidly changing business environment: [Fig: 2] explains how the concept of IT business bac ouoOd cortko Vcarc','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 22:30:21','2025-02-19 22:30:21'),(1911,'605','App\\Models\\Section','Figures',NULL,'[Fig.2] The evolving concept of IT business',2,'67b65b8c44126.png','/storage/figures/67b65b8c44126.png','2025-02-19 22:30:21','2025-02-19 22:30:36'),(1912,'605','App\\Models\\Section','Figures',NULL,'[Fig.4] The strategic links between business and IT',4,'67b65b8c4d67b.png','/storage/figures/67b65b8c4d67b.png','2025-02-19 22:30:21','2025-02-19 22:30:36'),(1913,'605','App\\Models\\Section','Text','In terms of IT business, IT is more than just a tool or a support function: It is becoming established as a concept whose interdependence with business strategy objectives and processes is maximized. This maximization of interdependence not only strengthens the competitiveness of a company\' s business model but also plays a major role in creating new business value: [Figure 3] shows the interdependence between a coprorate business &nd the IT system of a corporation.','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 22:30:21','2025-02-19 22:30:21'),(1914,'605','App\\Models\\Section','Text','In IT business, the alignment of business and IT can be understood as IT application programs, IT infrastructure, and an IT organization that supports ad realizes a companysbusiness strategy and business processes The strategic alignment model of business and IT can be represented as a 2-dimensional diagram, as shown in [Fig: 4]. In this figure, the\"strategic fit\" dimension is subdivided into external focus (business environment) and internal focus (management structure), while the\"functional integration\" dimension is subdivided into business and IT','',3,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 22:30:21','2025-02-19 22:30:21'),(1915,'605','App\\Models\\Section','Text','To achieve strategic alignment,, this model defines four areas that complement each other: business strategy, strategy, organizational infrastructure ad processes IT infrastructure, and processes Each area has its own scope capabilities, goverance, infrastructure, processes, and technology:','',5,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 22:30:21','2025-02-19 22:30:21'),(1916,'606','App\\Models\\Section','Text','TvuvV icls lanc a iuK al Uie Ciiaige) m Lie |  leci m iuisy eiiviuiticiil lial iave diuus i abuul vaiiuu) | | Dusiic55 innovations in recent times A diagram that shows changes in the expected level of industrial economic value and the impact of new technologies in the IT sector over time is what the hype cycle from Gartner (released every year) is all about. In the hype cycle, the so-called \"innovation trigger\" is the time when new technologies are first introduced and people expect great from them: After that point, the level of expectation gradually increases before the new technology starts to become more exaggerated than what it can actually deliver leading to a period when the bubble reaches its maximum size (the peak of inflated expectations): The Trough of Disillusionment is the period when the bubble bursts, after which the hype cycle enters a of revival (the Slope of Enlightenment) in which the expectations for the technology start to climb steadily once In the last period of the hype the technology transitions to the Plateau of Productivity, the period when it generates steady values things period again. cycle,','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 22:30:21','2025-02-19 22:30:21'),(1917,'608','App\\Models\\Section','Text','The hype cycle allows us to understand not only those technologies which have recently become important issues but also what kind of world will unfold in the future due to the nature of such technologies Understanding the evolution of technology as presented in the hype cycle and incorporating it into an IT business can be of tremendous help to a companys growth','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 22:30:21','2025-02-19 22:30:21'),(1918,'609','App\\Models\\Section','Tables',NULL,'',5,'67b65b8c5d55b.png','/storage/tables/67b65b8c5d55b.png','2025-02-19 22:30:21','2025-02-19 22:30:36'),(1919,'609','App\\Models\\Section','Figures',NULL,'[Fig6] CPNDS ecosystem and ICBM core technology of the IT industry',2,'67b65b8c6baa1.png','/storage/figures/67b65b8c6baa1.png','2025-02-19 22:30:21','2025-02-19 22:30:36'),(1920,'609','App\\Models\\Section','Text','As IT technology continues to advance ad improve, it is creating a huge ecosystem Where different technologie both interact with and compete each other: [Fig: 6] represents this IT ecosystem: against Dul ilc  aCl Wvili alu cumpele againisl CaCit Ul ICI. [7g Oj tepiesciils Uis || Clusysleit After the Information Revolution of the 1980s brought on by the development of personal computer and telecom networks, we witnessed-from around the year 2000 onwards the birth of the Smart Revolution in which mobile devices began to be converged with smartphone-based wireless Internet, phone, and computing services The Smart Revolution not only accelerated the convergence of the IT industry but also affected other industries, acting as a catalyst for the overall \"smartification\" of entire industries Overall smartification has resulted in IT technology being adopted by such diverse sectors as education, automobiles defense, construction, shipbuilding, and medicine. Advances in sensor and network technologies are driving the transformation of MZM (Machine to Machine) into the loT (Internet of Things) and extending it to the realm the Internet of Everything (IoE) IT technology is connecting humans to humans, humans to objects, and object to objects, and leading our society towards a hyper-connected society where humans, objects, spaces, data, anc services are all connected together','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 22:30:21','2025-02-19 22:30:21'),(1921,'609','App\\Models\\Section','Text','A hyper-connected society wields a huge influence on the IT ecosystem, which is built on contents, platforms networks, devices, and security As the center of the IT ecosystem moves hardware devices to platforms anc contents, software is becoming increasingly important, and smart mobile-based IT convergence is expanding intc traditional major industries, finance, and healthcare from Meanwhile, destructive innovations like 3D printing ad unmanned vehicles with the capacity to destroy existing markets are leading the IT ecosystem ad improving competitiveness based on open innovation, ad demand customized business models ae proliferating The core technology that is currently making the hyper-connected society possible is ICBM technology, Which consists of the Interet of Things (loT), Cloud Computing, Big Data, and mobile. [Table 1] explains the changes place in the IT technology environment and the form of IT competition in terms of the following five major trends from the perspective of IT paradigm change: the change from HW to SW platforms, the change IT convergence to smart convergence, the ICBM-based hyper-connected society, the changes in the IT technology environment and the IT business transformation of competition taking from rapid','',3,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 22:30:21','2025-02-19 22:30:21'),(1922,'610','App\\Models\\Section','Tables',NULL,'',4,'67b65b8c84abf.png','/storage/tables/67b65b8c84abf.png','2025-02-19 22:30:21','2025-02-19 22:30:36'),(1923,'610','App\\Models\\Section','Text','The table below describes the characteristics of the 5 components (contents, platform, network, device, and security) that constitute an IT ecosystem:','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 22:30:21','2025-02-19 22:30:21'),(1924,'610','App\\Models\\Section','Text','The sophistication and smartification of IT cyber threats is leading to an increase in damages and threats due tothe increased use of IT by key national infrastructures There is a growing threat of cyber targeted attacks such as cyber terrorism,, which aims to neutralize information and communication networks and computer systems, and hacktivism,in Security (S) which hackers attack computer systems for political and social purposes The response to new malicious hacking attacks is changing from a response based on security technology for post-attack investigations to one based on security technology for early','',3,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 22:30:21','2025-02-19 22:30:21'),(1925,'611','App\\Models\\Section','Text','Tne concept Of T resources encompasses tne peopie, processes, sortware ana naraware used tO run anl business IT resources include IT support systems and IT management systems, of which the former are systems that support or manage IT businesses, such as ERP (Enterprise Resource Management) , SCM (Supply Chain Management)and PLMProduct Lifecycle Management) while the latter IT typically include information technology service management (ITSM): IT resources evolve continuously while maintaining a direct relationship with the IT business in question. They are changing in a direction that maximizes the results of an IT business with changing technologies ad the changing times. The system for managing IT resources is called an IT resource management system: Essentially, it manages and controls the solutions, products, and processes required to support IT businesses The IT resource management system manages resources (from planning and development through application, operation and management to disposal) using the IT resource lifecycle as a template It manages the specification list of IT resources as well as the gains in business performance achieved by utilizing IT resources','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 22:30:21','2025-02-19 22:30:21'),(1926,'800','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','companies are using their IT resources to improve their overall production efficiency: For example, most domestic hypermarkets in South Korea monitor customer purchasing patterns in realtime, and manage their Many inventory levels continuously based on information gleaned the customers\' purchasing data. The inventory data are sent to a process that analyzes real-time customer purchasing patterns This pursuit of production efficiency can maximize sales and contribute significantly to the building of competitive advantages Wal-Mart is a case in point: The company recorded sales of more than $28 per unit area of the store (which is more than double that of other retailers (sales of $12 per unit area on average) through the use of its RetaiLink system, which allows suppliers to access Wal-Mart\'s data warehouse directly: from','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 22:30:21','2025-02-19 22:30:21'),(1927,'801','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','Since the dawn of the twenty-first century, we have been seeing ever more examples of new business values being created through the application of IT resources. Apple completely changed the offline music distribution structure with its iTunes music store: The new online music distribution structure has created a new business value, and this is considered by many to have been the greatest driver of Apples growth as a company: E-commerce is also another example of a new business value created by IT resources. The virtual online market that emerged through IT is changing the traditional concept of commerce, spawning new concepts of commerce such as open markets and social commerce','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 22:30:21','2025-02-19 22:30:21'),(1928,'802','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','Many companies today are seeking new markets and global businesses to develop for the sake of their survival and prosperity: The global cooperative working environment enabled by IT resources has presented possibilities for exploring new markets to companies that otherwise would have kept their focus on local markets only: The global cooperative working environment has challenged traditional ideas about the costs, labor, ad time needed for developing global businesses For example, the establishment of videoconferencing systems has improved decision-making speed and efficiency in the rapidly changing business environment, while the ability to exchange information through Intranet systems without the constraints of time and space has given huge competitive advantages to global businesses','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 22:30:21','2025-02-19 22:30:21'),(1929,'612','App\\Models\\Section','Figures',NULL,'[Fig: 7] The role of IT resources',2,'67b65b8c925c6.png','/storage/figures/67b65b8c925c6.png','2025-02-19 22:30:21','2025-02-19 22:30:36'),(1930,'612','App\\Models\\Section','Text','One can identify the many benefits to be derived the use of IT resources for an IT business, but they can summarized into three main viewpoints from','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 22:30:21','2025-02-19 22:30:21'),(1931,'613','App\\Models\\Section','Figures',NULL,'8] The cyclical management of IT business [Fig',2,'67b65b8c9c178.png','/storage/figures/67b65b8c9c178.png','2025-02-19 22:30:21','2025-02-19 22:30:36'),(1932,'613','App\\Models\\Section','Figures',NULL,'[Fig 9] The management and control structure of an IT business',4,'67b65b8ca56b4.png','/storage/figures/67b65b8ca56b4.png','2025-02-19 22:30:21','2025-02-19 22:30:36'),(1933,'613','App\\Models\\Section','Text','The IT business\'s cyclical management activities follow the traditional PDCA management cycle of planning execution, checking, and corrective action: The Planning (P) phase identifies opportunities and issues, sets the and scope for IT business, and establishes an IT business plan for linking business with IT. In the Do (D) phase, the IT business is designed and implemented and the business operations data are collected: In theC (Check) phase, the results of IT business operations are analyzed, the business and IT performance indicators are monitored, and business & IT correlation verification is carried out. In the Action (A) phase, the improvements needed are identified and IT adjustmentslmodifications are made to support the IT business,after which the Planning (P) phase begins all over completing and continuing the cycle of reneat and renewal ad infinitum goals again,','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 22:30:21','2025-02-19 22:30:21'),(1934,'613','App\\Models\\Section','Text','The cyclical management structure of IT business is shown in [Fig: 8]. The IT service and IT infra provide operationa support amed at enablinga business (process) toachieve results in its IT business In IT business management, new IT business performance indicators are derived from the service quality of the IT operational support service (IT QoS) and the business performance results of the organization These indicators are then sent to the IT division The IT business management provides support for the making and adjusting of decisions, and investments, to the IT service and IT infra,thus ensuring that the target levels for the performance indicators can be met','',3,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 22:30:21','2025-02-19 22:30:21'),(1935,'803','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','Before the mid-2000s, IT-related activities or departments were seen as a category of back-office support activties, completely distinct the main activities of a company: However, since the 2000s, when IT companies began to emerge and existing companies accelerated the integration of IT, the perception of the role IT could play and the role of IT-related departments in the value chain model began to change In particular, since 2010, the perception of value chain models from the IT business perspective has changed dramatically, and this change can be seen from two main from perspectives.','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 22:30:21','2025-02-19 22:30:21'),(1936,'614','App\\Models\\Section','Figures',NULL,'',2,'67b65b8caf13b.png','/storage/figures/67b65b8caf13b.png','2025-02-19 22:30:21','2025-02-19 22:30:36'),(1937,'614','App\\Models\\Section','Figures',NULL,'',3,'67b65b8cb9ab9.png','/storage/figures/67b65b8cb9ab9.png','2025-02-19 22:30:21','2025-02-19 22:30:36'),(1938,'614','App\\Models\\Section','Text','The value chain model defines the ultimate direction of an enterprise organization in terms of the concept of value The model presents a structure designed to help an enterprise organization realize its value The value chain model has come to be recognized as a critical management theory for analyzing the business activities of an enterprise Furthermore, the value chain model not only provides a very useful framework for aalyzing and understanding a company s competitive advantage from its activties but also introduces the concepts of activities and support activities that have become important reference points for enterprises\' organizational structures key The concept of a business value chain can be approached from two different angles: a traditional manufacturing company ad a e-commerce company From the agle of a traditional manufacturing company a business value chain explains how activities (warehousing, operation [production], shipment, marketing and sales, customer service) and support activities (corporate infrastructure, HR management, technology development, purchasing activities) should be organized and implemented if the company is to reach both its financial and its non-financial objectives. The value chain of an e-commerce company can be used as a tool for increasing business efficiency and effectiveness by electronically handling business processes In this case, the key activities are procurement,, zero-inventory production, third-party logistics, network sales, and online services. The support activities include the deployment of an integrated information platform and network infrastructure, Internet recruitment, and the management of online sunnliers key','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 22:30:21','2025-02-19 22:30:21'),(1939,'615','App\\Models\\Section','Text','IT is applied throughout all the activities and support activities that constitute the elements of a companys value chain model. This signifies that the role of IT is no longer limited to back-office functions but that IT is integrated and utilized as a key factor in every aspect of a companys activities. For example, let\'s look at the typical example of a hypermarket: Without IT, would it be possible to pursue the five key activities of the value chain model normally or do it ina way that would be competitive? In an environment where managers working for a hypermarket can check inventory ad product information in realtime, place products on shelves in ways that reflect customer shopping behaviors and local characteristics, and collect customers\' purchasing histories in realtime, the answer to this question would be a resounding \'NO\'. In other words, today, when the operations of all key activities defined by the value chain model are based on IT, the above question suggests a new perception about the convergence of the value chain model and IT. Leaving aside the example of hypermarkets, the situation is pretty much the same in other industries referred to as \"smokestack industries\". being key - being key -','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 22:30:21','2025-02-19 22:30:21'),(1940,'616','App\\Models\\Section','Text','When a companys business model is e-business or Internet business, it is hard to explain its activities and support activities separately IT For example, Amazoncom is a leading example of a company that performs both its key activities and its supporting activities using IT: Likewise, Interpark in Korea is considered a similar case. In other words, companies that began their operations as IT-based entities cannot be understood if the activities and support activities defined in their value chain models are considered separately: In such situations, the traditional value chain model has to be approached from a new perspective key from key','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 22:30:21','2025-02-19 22:30:21'),(1941,'617','App\\Models\\Section','Text','The two perspectives explained above are related to the two angles mentioned when explaining the IT business Just as when one tries to understand the IT business, one must view it in terms of two different trends, that\'s to say one in which IT is integrated into the business processes across the whole company, and another in which IT is used as the main business, the value chain model can also be understood in two different ways. Therefore, since most companies today are pursuing their IT business in the hope of gaining a competitive edge from IT, our understanding of the traditional value chain model must also be expanded from the business perspective Such an expanded understanding of IT is raising several issues in academia and in the field Traditional job processes that have long been taken for granted are driving structural changes in companies following the company-wide integration of IT. Examples include the elimination of unnecessary processes in the decision-making process through the adoption of an intranet information system, and the transformation of a company into a more horizontal organization in which quality information is supplied to all employees information that otherwise would have been held by a privileged few: That is, the perception is spreading that the utilization of IT is not limited to just being integrated into the value chain model activities, but that it is a (new) concept of value chain model that could have & decisive impact on the structure of an entire organization and its competitive advantages','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 22:30:21','2025-02-19 22:30:21'),(1942,'618','App\\Models\\Section','Text','\"Strategy establishment\" is the process of defining strategies for fulfilling an organization s mission. Corporate strategies must incorporate explanations and analyses of the current status of a given company and suggest direction(s) for change The formulated strategies should be directly aligned with the strategies of each unit- level organization The output of strategic planning is a document that describes the top-level strategy and the environments or aims of the organization that could have a impact on the strategy: A strategic plan not only provides the basis for carrying out the specific action steps of the plan, but also provides the overall direction for the enterprise architecture (EA), process improvement, risk management, and portfolio management, and other types of company-wide activities. The subordinate goals and procedures for realizing a companys implementation strategies can be defined si as to reflect issues that are pertinent to each level of the organizations hierarchy: For instance, if the business manager establishes mid-level strategies and based on the corporate strategy, the production staff can then use the mid-level strategies to set their own goal sat their level. goals','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 22:30:22','2025-02-19 22:30:22'),(1943,'619','App\\Models\\Section','Tables',NULL,'<Table3 Elements of a strategy plan',2,'67b65b8cc5b87.png','/storage/tables/67b65b8cc5b87.png','2025-02-19 22:30:22','2025-02-19 22:30:36'),(1944,'619','App\\Models\\Section','Figures',NULL,'[Fig 11] The interdependence among the different elements of strategy development',4,'67b65b8cd3f35.png','/storage/figures/67b65b8cd3f35.png','2025-02-19 22:30:22','2025-02-19 22:30:36'),(1945,'619','App\\Models\\Section','Text','There are many different approaches to choose when developing a strategy. At a typical strategy developme stage, the current conditions of the subject company are evaluated, future goals are set, and implementati= strategies for realizing the companys target model are formulated from','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 22:30:22','2025-02-19 22:30:22'),(1946,'619','App\\Models\\Section','Text','In a typical strategy development process, the current (As-Is) model of a company is evaluated and a picture of the future (To-Be) model is presented, after which a set of strategies for transforming the company from one model to the other model is developed The interdependence among the different elements of strategy development is shown pclc','',3,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 22:30:22','2025-02-19 22:30:22'),(1947,'619','App\\Models\\Section','Text','A companys mission is typically either its objective or its main business A mission describes what an entity does for its own benefit and is not bound by time: A companys vision is the ideal future that it aspires to. A vision can only be obtained by the successful execution of the mission A company\'s vision is both a source of inspiration and an extension of its capabilities als must be measurable high-level, and support an entity in its efforts to achieve its mission ecific, quantifiable and low-level targets which signal that the objectives have been reached Principles state the constraints that a company must consider when selecting the method of achieving its targets. The basic ideology of a company represents its core values, and is used in shaping its strategy: Enablers Enablers are the external environments and corporate strengths that can boost a companys ability to achieve its and objectives. goals Barriers are the external environments and corporate weaknesses that impede an entitys ability to achieve its goals and objectives: Strategy Strategy is the approach a company takes to realize its mission, objectives, and goals. Strategy must support companys vision, but it is affected by enablers, barriers, and the basic ideology: Strategic plan 0 - A strategic plan is a document created through strategic plan setting activities A strategic plan explains the strategy of a company and the factors that affect the strategy: ves are a set of activities carried out to implement a strategy: Actions are specific procedures for achieving _ and objectives: Generally speaking: people are assigned to manage activities, and activities are subject to certain timetable constraints goals The performance index describes the performance target value for each go','',5,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 22:30:22','2025-02-19 22:30:22'),(1948,'804','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','The purpose of the strategy analysis is to collect the information required to make the business decisions of the company: The internal environment can be improved because it can be controlled by the company, whereas the external environment is generally difficult to control and requires an adaptive strategy: Exleltal eliviOreri alalysis This is an analysis of the environment surrounding a company and other external conditions (Macro-environment) This is the political, economic, social and technological environment surrounding a company: The boundaries of its influence can be expanded across several industries (Micro-environment) As the industrial environment to which a company belongs, the micro-environment is where the company faces competition when acquiring resources and its products/services, and is what we often call general competitive environment selling Internal environment analysis Tilentiai Eiiviiuniietil alialysis The analysis of a companys internal environment focuses on internal elements and processes, resources, organizations, etc, and also focuses on the interal changes taking place within a company: Consolidated environment analysis Cui ibuiualcu Ciiviuiiiciil aniaiysis A comprehensive analysis of the extemal and internal environmental factors of a company is carried out, and integrated interallexternal analysis results can be obtained: SWOT analysis is an important tool of consolidated environment analysis. A SWOT analysis examines the strengths (S) and weaknesses (W) of a companys internal environment and the opportunities (0) and threats (T) present in its external environment','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 22:30:22','2025-02-19 22:30:22'),(1949,'805','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','In the strategy selection phase, the best possible direction for the future of the company is selected based on the information collected in the strategy analysis phase If the information obtained the strategy analysis phase is incomplete or defective, it becomes impossible to determine whether the strategy chosen by an organization is the right one Therefore, strategy selection must begin with a thorough review of the results and inferences of the preceding strategy analysis phase during If this process is completed seamlessly, it will produce an optional list of alternatives to a set of strategic directions that a company can adopt It is common for each of these alternatives to have different resource requirements with unique solutions to key issues Each alternative is evaluated according to a reasonably established evaluation standard, and, ultimately, the most appropriate alterative is chosen as the strategic direction','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 22:30:22','2025-02-19 22:30:22'),(1950,'806','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','In the strategy implementation and management phase, the chosen strategic alternative is adopted and put into effect: During this phase, several managerial issues could emerge, such as the viability of a companys resources for executing a strategy the readiness of a companys culture and structure, the change management for realizing strategy, the of strategy realization and the development method decision, the strategy implementation readiness of the steering group within the company, and the level of influence over internallexternal stakeholders, etc The progress of the strategy is monitored continuously, and the status of the strategy is delivered from the implementation phase to the analysis phase via a feedback The progress of the strategy may influence the internal or external environment of the company: In addition, the internal or external environment may change due to the occurrence of unexpected events after completion of the strategy analysis Therefore,, a review of the strategy analysis should be conducted to ensure that the chosen strategic direction is still valid path path','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 22:30:22','2025-02-19 22:30:22'),(1951,'620','App\\Models\\Section','Figures',NULL,'12] Strategy setting process [Fig',2,'67b65b8cde4d3.png','/storage/figures/67b65b8cde4d3.png','2025-02-19 22:30:22','2025-02-19 22:30:36'),(1952,'620','App\\Models\\Section','Text','The strategy-setting process consists of strategy analysis, strategy selection, strategy implementation and management, and feedback First, in the strategy analysis phase, basic information regarding the company is investigated, and the As-Is model is studied. In the strategy selection phase, the future (To-Be) model and the strategy for realizing the To-Be model are established In the strategy implementation and management phase, the strategy is adopted and put into effect When necessary, adjustments can be made to a strategic plan during this phase.','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 22:30:22','2025-02-19 22:30:22'),(1953,'807','App\\Models\\Subsection','Tables',NULL,'<Table 4  PEST analysis and examples of items examined',2,'67b65b8cebf56.png','/storage/tables/67b65b8cebf56.png','2025-02-19 22:30:22','2025-02-19 22:30:36'),(1954,'807','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','PEST analysis, technique for analyzing the exteral macro-environment,, is used as a tool for analyzing the impact of political, economic, social, and technological opportunity and threat factors In PEST analysis, brainstorming is carried out to determine the characteristics of the country or region that is the target market for a companys products and business services The table below shows examples of items examined in PEST analysis','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 22:30:22','2025-02-19 22:30:22'),(1955,'807','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','When legal and environmental factors are included in addition to the four elements of PEST discussed above, PEST is called PESTLE or PESTEL.','',3,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 22:30:22','2025-02-19 22:30:22'),(1956,'808','App\\Models\\Subsection','Figures',NULL,'[Fig.13] Michael Porters 5 Force Analysis',2,'67b65b8d02bd7.png','/storage/figures/67b65b8d02bd7.png','2025-02-19 22:30:22','2025-02-19 22:30:37'),(1957,'808','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','Porter s Five Forces Framework, a micro-external environmental analysis technique is used to analyze the structure of the industry to which a company belongs It is used mainly in establishing a strategy for securing a competitive e