9 22:30:22','2025-02-19 22:30:22'),(1968,'812','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','The BCG matrix is used to evaluate a companys portfolio of products and business services, and also to evaluate single company or a single department within a company:','',3,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 22:30:22','2025-02-19 22:30:22'),(1969,'624','App\\Models\\Section','Tables',NULL,'<Table5 Definitions of IT governance',2,'67b65b8d2f7c3.png','/storage/tables/67b65b8d2f7c3.png','2025-02-19 22:30:22','2025-02-19 22:30:37'),(1970,'624','App\\Models\\Section','Text','The aim of IT governance is to implant a for controlling and managing a companys IT to the same degree as corporate governance In other words, IT governance can contribute to realizing business targets by aligning IT resources with a companys and strategies By defining the roles &nd responsibilities within an organization, goverance creates a control and management structure for handling the performance results ad risks of IT The table below gives some concrete descriptions of IT. system goals','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 22:30:22','2025-02-19 22:30:22'),(1971,'813','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','The governance area consists of 5 processes (evaluation (E), directive (D), monitoring (M), etc ), each of which comes with its own work procedures EDM 1. Establish the measurement standard with the governance framework EDM 2 Provide profits EDM 3. Minimize risks imize rickc','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 22:30:22','2025-02-19 22:30:22'),(1972,'814','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','The management are consists of 4 process phases: planning (APO), deployment (BAI), operation (DSS) , monitoring (MEA) The management are consists of 4 process phases: planning (APO), deployment (BAI), operation (DSS) , monitoring (MEA) Planning (APO) phase: planning Deplovment (BAI) phase: deploving acauiring configuring linking, (MEA) Planning (APO) phase: linking, planning Deployment (BAI) phase: deploying, acquiring, configuring Operation (DSS)phase: transferring, service, support Nonitorino AFAInhace- monitorino evaluationc raviiem The IT governance framework is linked to the international standard ISOJIEC 38500, which simultaneously provides the principles and frameworks required to evaluate, direct, ad monitor the utilization of IT by companies','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 22:30:22','2025-02-19 22:30:22'),(1973,'625','App\\Models\\Section','Figures',NULL,'[Fig.17] COBIT 5,a reference model for IT governance',2,'67b65b8d40241.png','/storage/figures/67b65b8d40241.png','2025-02-19 22:30:22','2025-02-19 22:30:37'),(1974,'625','App\\Models\\Section','Text','Due to the alignment of IT with the business of a company, in IT governance, the value of IT contributes to the attainment of business performance and results, Through the management of risks and core IT resources for the efficient operation of IT,the roles ad responsibilities related to IT resources are clearly defined. IT governance is structured to ensure reliability and transparency: The following figure shows the governance framework reference model of COBIT 5 (Control Objects for Information and Related Technology 5): This framework is widely known as the \"IT goverance framework\". In the reference model, the governance and management processes of a company are kept separate. goals good Business needs','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 22:30:22','2025-02-19 22:30:22'),(1975,'815','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','The planning stage involves linking business with IT, setting the of IT, establishing the structures, activities ad mechanisms regarding the rules on organizing IT related activities, using resources, managing risks, the governance structure, and measuring performance goals','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 22:30:22','2025-02-19 22:30:22'),(1976,'816','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','The monitoring of IT resources, IT risks ad IT management involves all the structures, activities and relatec mechanisms for helping companies to monitor their IT resources, IT risks and IT management The monitoring IT performance measurement involves the structures, activities and related mechanisms for helping companies to set target levels (for their performances related to IT resources, IT risks ad IT management) and measure their attainment of such targets','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 22:30:22','2025-02-19 22:30:22'),(1977,'817','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','IT value is evaluated through the earings ad costs of the future business opportunities delivered to the compar IT value includes strategic, economic, and risk management, as well as technical, social and quality benefits. To arri at the IT value, the costs of business risk ad other potential risk costs are subtracted from business opportunities','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 22:30:22','2025-02-19 22:30:22'),(1978,'818','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','ased on the results of the evaluation of the feedback information and the need to prioritize this information, during his stage a company takes corrective measures aimed at improving its IT governance activities Included in suct corrective measures are the structures, activities and procedures for improving the IT governance process and the related jobs','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 22:30:22','2025-02-19 22:30:22'),(1979,'626','App\\Models\\Section','Figures',NULL,'[Fig 18] IT governance process',2,'67b65b8d4b92e.png','/storage/figures/67b65b8d4b92e.png','2025-02-19 22:30:22','2025-02-19 22:30:37'),(1980,'626','App\\Models\\Section','Text','The IT governance process is composed of the planning stage, operations stage, evaluation stage, and feedback stage','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 22:30:22','2025-02-19 22:30:22'),(1981,'627','App\\Models\\Section','Tables',NULL,'<Table 6 Focus areas of IT governance',2,'67b65b8d58747.png','/storage/tables/67b65b8d58747.png','2025-02-19 22:30:22','2025-02-19 22:30:37'),(1982,'627','App\\Models\\Section','Text','IT governance has five key areas of focus, all of which are linked to the strategies of a company: IT governance looke at how a companys strategies are used in conjunction with IT value, and also includes the management of risk factor and the management of resources, as well as a performance evaluation system on activities','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 22:30:22','2025-02-19 22:30:22'),(1983,'819','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','EA stands for \"enterprise architecture\" It is a blueprint that explains the IT business of an enterprise in a way that is easy for the stakeholders to understand, so that the enterprise can achieve its strategic and the of its information resource management Enterprise architecture is a blueprint that defines the current state of the relationship between information technology and an enterpriselas well as the activities carried out by the enterprise) and the state that the enterprise must strive for in the future \"-United States Office of Management and Budget (OMB) goals goals','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 22:30:22','2025-02-19 22:30:22'),(1984,'820','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','Currently, enterprises ae enthusiastically introducing information systems to cope with the rapidly changing business environments but if information systems are deployed without proper planning at the macro level, enterprises will be confronted with a redundant system ad an inability to collaborate Such enterprises will fall into the so-called \"IT Productivity Paradox\"1 which can be described as the continuous adoption of information systems without seeing any benefits in the form of increased corporate profits There may be several causes of this paradox, but in most cases it is attributable to the lack of a system for clearly explaining companys business and IT operations to its stakeholders from an overall perspective For these reasons, enterprises need an EA, as it can provide a bird\'s eye view of the enterprises business while simultaneously creating close working relationships between different information resources','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 22:30:22','2025-02-19 22:30:22'),(1985,'821','App\\Models\\Subsection','Figures',NULL,'[Fig: 19] The concept diagram of EA',2,'67b65b8d63a44.png','/storage/figures/67b65b8d63a44.png','2025-02-19 22:30:22','2025-02-19 22:30:37'),(1986,'821','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','The deployment of an EA starts with the enterprise business strategy The enterprise business strategy is converged with the IT strategy, and the EA is the fruit of this convergence','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 22:30:22','2025-02-19 22:30:22'),(1987,'822','App\\Models\\Subsection','Tables',NULL,'',3,'67b65b8d75a4c.png','/storage/tables/67b65b8d75a4c.png','2025-02-19 22:30:22','2025-02-19 22:30:37'),(1988,'822','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','An EA is delegated or inherits the IT governance control system. To be more precise, the establishment of an EA itself is both an act of IT governance and an instrument of IT governance control. In addition to IT governance, the components of an EA are business architecture (BA), applied architecture (AA), data architecture (DA), and technology architecture (TA): The standard profile (SP) is a sub-structure of the technology architecture and can be understood as the detailed specifications of a list of technologies key','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 22:30:22','2025-02-19 22:30:22'),(1989,'822','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','There is a reference model for each individual architecture, namely the performance reference model (PRM) , service component reference model, data reference model, and technology reference model,, respectively: The reference model provides early reference cases in an identical business sector or similar industries that a company could use as a guide when it seeks to deploy an EA There is also a goverment EA reference model for government-wide EA which is used as a reference When EAs are deployed at the departmental level As a side note, the government-wide EA includes security architecture in addition to the four abovementioned architectures','',4,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 22:30:22','2025-02-19 22:30:22'),(1990,'630','App\\Models\\Section','Tables',NULL,'',3,'67b65b8d883ab.png','/storage/tables/67b65b8d883ab.png','2025-02-19 22:30:22','2025-02-19 22:30:37'),(1991,'630','App\\Models\\Section','Text','The Zachman Framework, TOGAF (The Open Group Architecture) , and FEAF (Federal Enterprise Architecture Framework) are some of the leading EA frameworks in use today: The Zachmann Framework is the one used most often when establishing a EA TOGAF,, created by The Open Group, is an open framework that focuses on interoperability between companies FEAF is also a framework developed in 1998 by the US. CIO Council with the help of the Jacquesman Framework and Spewak','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 22:30:22','2025-02-19 22:30:22'),(1992,'631','App\\Models\\Section','Text','The literal meaning of the acronym ISP is \"Information Strategy Plan\" . Generally, the term \"ISP establishment\" is used more frequently as an overarching concept: ISP can present a vision for the information system and information management structure that can support an enterprise or organization when it is developing its mid-to-long term vision and goals and business plan In other words, it can be understood as a plan that provides a rough sketch of the direction of information system deployment to aid the enterprise in realizing its term objectives long','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 22:30:22','2025-02-19 22:30:22'),(1993,'632','App\\Models\\Section','Tables',NULL,'<Table 9 Basic composition of ISPI',2,'67b65b8da59dd.png','/storage/tables/67b65b8da59dd.png','2025-02-19 22:30:22','2025-02-19 22:30:37'),(1994,'632','App\\Models\\Section','Text','In order to deploy an ISP, the externaljinternal environment of the company and the information environment must be analyzed first of all When analyzing the environment of a company, tools like SWOT, 5-Force,7S and 4C are commonly used. In addition, when analyzing the information environment, the technology requirements corresponding to the purpose and background of a project must be reviewed in detail by studying the technology trends and analyzing the application of new technologies The next step consists in analyzing the current operation of the company: The most important item that must be checked in this analysis is the business process. A careful study of the business process in its current state will reveal various factors at work in a company or an organization In addition, analyzing the information systems scattered throughout the company and drawing out the requirements of stakeholders and the improvement agenda are also important tasks to be undertaken at this stage. Also, through the benchmarking of earlier cases in the same or similar industries, missing or distorted information can be corrected to some extent','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 22:30:22','2025-02-19 22:30:22'),(1995,'632','App\\Models\\Section','Text','guide on information strategic planning (ISP) , National Information Society Agency, The results of the analysis of the enterprise environment and the current state of the enterprise constitute & important resource when determining directions for improvement,, developing improved job procedures, and creating an informatization plan in the last stage of ISP establishment:','',3,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 22:30:22','2025-02-19 22:30:22'),(1996,'633','App\\Models\\Section','Tables',NULL,'<Table 11  Comparison of ISP and EA concepts',4,'67b65b8dc9cde.png','/storage/tables/67b65b8dc9cde.png','2025-02-19 22:30:22','2025-02-19 22:30:37'),(1997,'633','App\\Models\\Section','Text','The ISP deployment process comprises a set of activities that must be performed at each stage, ad the results hese activities become the output of the deployment. An example of a list of typical outputs that could be used in ISP is shown below:','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 22:30:22','2025-02-19 22:30:22'),(1998,'633','App\\Models\\Section','Text','Although the actual implementation of ISP produces far more diverse and complex outputs, the most valuable output has to be a blueprint for a process for a future model and a set of activities for attaining a companys This content must feature sufficiently in the output When comparing ISP to the EA described earlier it can be said that ISP deals with plans that fall within the scope of EA but which are more microscopic than the EA An examination of the scope of ISP as described in the table below indicates that its scope, When compared to the EA, is more focused on the informatization strategy: goals','',3,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 22:30:22','2025-02-19 22:30:22'),(1999,'633','App\\Models\\Section','Text','In other words, the EA is deployed under a companys target architecture ad incorporates the latest information technology so that it can align the direction of its IT with its management strategy: Therefore, the EA must be managed in a way that allows a company to respond quickly to changes in the business management environment,, and must be flexible, so that the companys agenda can be implanted quickly through continuous updating, and in a way that ensures that the roadmap is shared with the rest of the organization','',5,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 22:30:22','2025-02-19 22:30:22'),(2000,'634','App\\Models\\Section','Tables',NULL,'<Table 12  Detailed description of examples of ordering processes',4,'67b65b8ddd366.png','/storage/tables/67b65b8ddd366.png','2025-02-19 22:30:23','2025-02-19 22:30:37'),(2001,'634','App\\Models\\Section','Figures',NULL,'20] IT business ordering process [Fig',2,'67b65b8de7080.png','/storage/figures/67b65b8de7080.png','2025-02-19 22:30:23','2025-02-19 22:30:37'),(2002,'634','App\\Models\\Section','Text','The IT business ordering process defines the activities and tasks of the orderer and describes a set of processes for deploying systems or software or services The process also includes such activities as concept definition and detailed specification of the requirements concerning the items ordered, preparation of the RFP, evaluation of the proposal, contracting, supplier management,, and acquisition of the end output,','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 22:30:23','2025-02-19 22:30:23'),(2003,'634','App\\Models\\Section','Text','By using the IT business ordering process, a company can define the activities of the contractor and supplier that must be performed when deploying a information system and also enhance the success rate of the information service business The ordering process provides a means of communication between the orderer and the supplier, and lends visibility to T business adoption, resulting in a predictable procedure','',3,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 22:30:23','2025-02-19 22:30:23'),(2004,'823','App\\Models\\Subsection','Tables',NULL,'',3,'67b65b8df1306.png','/storage/tables/67b65b8df1306.png','2025-02-19 22:30:23','2025-02-19 22:30:37'),(2005,'823','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','The basic life process consists of five sub-processes and provides support to the stakeholders participating the software lifecycle process. cycle','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 22:30:23','2025-02-19 22:30:23'),(2006,'824','App\\Models\\Subsection','Tables',NULL,'<Table14 Detailed process of the support lifecycle process',2,'67b65b8e0a965.png','/storage/tables/67b65b8e0a965.png','2025-02-19 22:30:23','2025-02-19 22:30:38'),(2007,'824','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','The support lifecycle process consists of eight sub-processes and plays the role of supporting other processes. It contributes to the quality and success of the outputs','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 22:30:23','2025-02-19 22:30:23'),(2008,'825','App\\Models\\Subsection','Tables',NULL,'<Table 15  Detailed description of the organization lifecycle process',2,'67b65b8e15b43.png','/storage/tables/67b65b8e15b43.png','2025-02-19 22:30:23','2025-02-19 22:30:38'),(2009,'825','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','The organization lifecycle process consists of four sub-processes which serve to configure the underlying structure of the organization lifecycle process for the business, without constrained by a specific project or informatior system deployment contract, being','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 22:30:23','2025-02-19 22:30:23'),(2010,'635','App\\Models\\Section','Text','ISOJIEC 12207 is an international standard for the software adoption lifecycle. It provides a standardized and systematic process for acquiring, supplying, developing, operating, and maintaining software ISOJIEC 12207 consists of three main processes and a detailed procedure for each process. ISOJIEC 12207 defines all the processes activities, and tasks that can be applied to the adoption and development of many different forms of software, but it contains no specifications regarding the naming, form, and contents of the output. Therefore, if ISOJIEC 12207 is used together with SPICE (Software Process Improvement and Capability Determination) or CMMI (Capability Maturity Model Integration), not just the WHAT but the HOW of the SW adoption process can be learned.','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 22:30:23','2025-02-19 22:30:23'),(2011,'636','App\\Models\\Section','Tables',NULL,'<Table 16  Important considerations for the tailoring process',2,'67b65b8e216eb.png','/storage/tables/67b65b8e216eb.png','2025-02-19 22:30:23','2025-02-19 22:30:38'),(2012,'636','App\\Models\\Section','Text','In addition to the main processes described above, there is also the tailoring2 process. The tailoring process defines the basic activities required for tailoring: It is the process of eliminating activities ad tasks that are not applied or perceived as unnecessary in the life cycle process Although the tailoring process is generally known as the optimization of the software development methodology, this section explains the part of tailoring that has to do with software adoption Before software is adopted, the adoption procedure, method, and outputs must be optimized to accommodate changes in the internal and external requirements. The need for tailoring becomes most acute for unit-level projects In these situations, the best software adoption environment can be created through tailoring','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 22:30:23','2025-02-19 22:30:23'),(2013,'826','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','This is a form of adoption that allows companies to set up and develop information systems their owr manpower resulting in a system that is faithful to the internal requirements of the company While know-how can be accumulated with this method, it involves relatively higher adoption costs, while success cannot be guaranteed. using','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 22:30:23','2025-02-19 22:30:23'),(2014,'827','App\\Models\\Subsection','Tables',NULL,'<Table 17  Comparison of in-house development and package purchase',2,'67b65b8e3071d.png','/storage/tables/67b65b8e3071d.png','2025-02-19 22:30:23','2025-02-19 22:30:38'),(2015,'827','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','This is a form of adoption under which a company can easily absorb the know-how gained from early cases of IT business adoption: By adopting a system that has undergone many tests and adoption verifications uncertainty about success can be eliminated. The adoption is short and the cost is relatively low, but the maintenance costs are likely to increase period','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 22:30:23','2025-02-19 22:30:23'),(2016,'827','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','From the perspectives of the IT business, in-house development and package purchase have their own distinct advantages and disadvantages. IT business used to be adopted using either one of the methods, but these days companies frequently opt for a hybrid approach to adoption In other words, the in-house development method is used for the overall approach while the packaged product method is chosen when acquiring the component technologies This method results in reduced costs and helps reduce risks when adopting IT businesses.','',3,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 22:30:23','2025-02-19 22:30:23'),(2017,'638','App\\Models\\Section','Text','A company can turn to several strategies when it has to respond quickly to changing internal and external environments For operational areas and processes where a company is certain that it holds a competitive edge, it will try to improve and develop further in order to strengthen its competitive advantage For non-strategic areas or processes where it is weak however, a company may tur to excellent outside resources For this reason, a company may seek to perform important activities (or those value chain activities where it enjoys competitive advantages) in-house, whereas for non-strategic areas and areas where it is weak, it will subcontract out the work to outside experts or third-party companies This is what is meant by \"outsourcing\" and, to be more exact, \"IT business outsourcing\" when IT resources are involved In IT business outsourcing, companies outsource IT resources, IT management, &d IT operations and usually focus on their core operational areas, thus enabling them to retain their competitive advantages','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 22:30:23','2025-02-19 22:30:23'),(2018,'639','App\\Models\\Section','Figures',NULL,'[Fig: 21] Conceptual diagram of IT business outsourcing adoption process',1,'67b65b8e3d3e2.png','/storage/figures/67b65b8e3d3e2.png','2025-02-19 22:30:23','2025-02-19 22:30:38'),(2019,'639','App\\Models\\Section','Text','When a company opts for IT outsourcing, it begins by identifying its core competencies and selecting the tasks to be outsourced. Once the target task has been selected, the vendor will be chosen, and negotiations will proceed until a contract is signed  The most important task is for the company and the vendor to reach a clear-cut agreement on how the index for service levels will be managed','',2,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 22:30:23','2025-02-19 22:30:23'),(2020,'640','App\\Models\\Section','Tables',NULL,'<Table 18  Forms of IT business outsourcing',2,'67b65b8e4db2a.png','/storage/tables/67b65b8e4db2a.png','2025-02-19 22:30:23','2025-02-19 22:30:38'),(2021,'640','App\\Models\\Section','Text','T business outsourcing can take one of four forms.','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 22:30:23','2025-02-19 22:30:23'),(2022,'641','App\\Models\\Section','Tables',NULL,'<Tablel9 Issues and considerations when adopting outsourcing',2,'67b65b8e5ca67.png','/storage/tables/67b65b8e5ca67.png','2025-02-19 22:30:23','2025-02-19 22:30:38'),(2023,'641','App\\Models\\Section','Text','In the course of outsourcing a IT business a company will come across many types of problems: To address these problems, the following steps could be considered: IT outsourcing requires continuous oversight of the outsource vendor (company) . Standards like eSCM and ISO/ IECZOOOO can be used for the oversight. It is necessary to establish a security system to prevent leakages of critical corporate information while managing the level of and continuously monitoring changes in, the service so as to secure optimal service quality When it is not a specific job category, but the whole or a part of the business process has to be outsourced, a company needs to adopt and operate business process outsourcing (BPO):','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 22:30:23','2025-02-19 22:30:23'),(2024,'642','App\\Models\\Section','Text','From 2010 to 2011,the Korea Workers Compensation & Welfare Service (COMWEL) built an advanced administration through a wide-scale process innovation (PI) project. Process innovation (PI) cannot be realized simply by setting up a system or with training alone: It can only be successful when there is a company-wide consensus the top management level to the working-level staff of the organization and when the best practices are applied to the organization process and fully interalized. For this reason, it is very difficult for conservative institutions to implement project innovations. However, with COMWEL\'s systematic project management ad utilization, it has so successfully implemented process innovation that it has become a benchmark for other institutions to follow: COMWEL pursued process innovation under the banner of \'job efficiencies through process innovation\' because it wanted to improve the quality of its public services despite having limited human resources It began the task of increasing job efficiency with interal discussions over those areas most in need of improvement Starting with AS-IS process diagnosis consulting, COMWEL next studied the end-to-end process of each job, and then selected the processes requiring process innovation (PI): The requirements at the working level were identified and extracted, and the information thus obtained was used in setting up the BPM, the process-based knowledge management (PKMS) , and the enterprise information display (EID) system. Among 50 core processes, systemization was completed for the 25 processes that were expected to produce the greatest effects once the process innovations were up ad running: COMWEL focused on improving its public service by eliminating unnecessary procedures and simplifying unnecessarily complex ones Process innovation (PI) was continuously performed around the framework of process establishment monitoring improvement activities- process establishment Through process innovation, when a user searches for reference data, the system provides to the user the information that is most relevant to the user\'s query: As the amount of information accumulates in this system,, the relevancy of the information multiplies In addition, the management was able to reduce risks by quickly modifying the management strategies after identifying the management plans and core information of all the business units at a glance In addition, management was able to a quick view of the business plans of all business divisions and the key information of the COMWEL ad make quick changes to its business management strategy so as to reduce risk system from public system top get','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 22:30:24','2025-02-19 22:30:24'),(2025,'643','App\\Models\\Section','Text','People participating in an enterprise as members of the organization, and the organization that carries out the function of dividing, consolidating, and connecting different jobs, are the elements of IT business execution: An organization is a activity or system consciously created by more than two people As such, it is important to maintain internal and external balance, effectiveness, and efficiency to fulfill their desires and common objectives of communication, volunteer work, and collaboration Through the division of functions and responsibilities, an organization allocates human resources so that it can fulfill the agreed-upon objectives more effectively: key','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 22:30:24','2025-02-19 22:30:24'),(2026,'644','App\\Models\\Section','Tables',NULL,'<Table 20  Relationships between the functions and business processes of an enterprise',2,'67b65b8e6a0c7.png','/storage/tables/67b65b8e6a0c7.png','2025-02-19 22:30:24','2025-02-19 22:30:38'),(2027,'644','App\\Models\\Section','Text','An enterprise is a formal organization whose objective is the pursuit of profits through the sale of or services at prices higher than the costs required to produce them: Furthermore, an enterprise can be viewed as a collection of interrelated business functions (or activities) defined by various business rules with the aim of realizing some objectives. Here, the term \"business rules\" refers to the rules that determine when, how, in what order, and which rules should be Business rules (e. processes) have a significant impact on an organization s management, performance, and value creation The of describing the method and the job of organizing work in a enterprise is called the \"business process\". Examples of common business processes by function (such as manufacturing and production, sales ad marketing, finance and HR management) are described in the table below goods applied step','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 22:30:24','2025-02-19 22:30:24'),(2028,'828','App\\Models\\Subsection','Tables',NULL,'<Table 21  BPM design stages',2,'67b65b8e7ac5f.png','/storage/tables/67b65b8e7ac5f.png','2025-02-19 22:30:24','2025-02-19 22:30:38'),(2029,'828','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','Business process management (BPM) is a technique for the consolidated management, optimization and automation of the flow of people, information resources, and tasks associated with IT business processes It is also an important means of implementing IT business processes: How well the overall process is managed can have direct repercussions for business performance Hence, it is essential to take a logical ad structured approach to managing the IT business process. BPM must be capable of handling changes in the management environment and should be designed to be capable of responding activelv to changes in business processes','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 22:30:24','2025-02-19 22:30:24'),(2030,'645','App\\Models\\Section','Figures',NULL,'[Fig: 23] Conceptual diagram of IT business process management',2,'67b65b8e83d6a.png','/storage/figures/67b65b8e83d6a.png','2025-02-19 22:30:24','2025-02-19 22:30:38'),(2031,'645','App\\Models\\Section','Text','BPM is a technique of IT business process management that consists in optimizing and automating business processes In addition, BAM is a technique for discovering and managing bottlenecks in business processes, while BRE is a business rule engine that sets and manages the flow of business processes key','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 22:30:24','2025-02-19 22:30:24'),(2032,'830','App\\Models\\Subsection','Tables',NULL,'<Table 23  Component elements of BRE',2,'67b65b8e8e828.png','/storage/tables/67b65b8e8e828.png','2025-02-19 22:30:24','2025-02-19 22:30:38'),(2033,'830','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','Business rule engine (BRE) is a technique for effectively managing, automating, and optimizing processes by formalizing the complex business rules and process flows of an enterprise: The ever increasing volume of information processed by IT business processes and the increasing complexity of process flows have led to the need for rule- based management. Rule-based management is also needed for service improvements and cost savings. For this reason, the adoption of BRE can help enterprises to proactively manage changes in, and reduce the operating costs of, business processes','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 22:30:24','2025-02-19 22:30:24'),(2034,'646','App\\Models\\Section','Tables',NULL,'<Table 22  Base technologies of BAM',2,'67b65b8e9ac27.png','/storage/tables/67b65b8e9ac27.png','2025-02-19 22:30:24','2025-02-19 22:30:38'),(2035,'646','App\\Models\\Section','Text','Business activity monitoring (BAM) is technique for optimizing IT business processes It detects ad controls process bottlenecks by monitoring processes in real time and recognizing risk factors in advance BAM also uses extended business intelligence (Bl) techniques for real-time analysis, and monitors and manages the process flow for business process monitoring (BPM):','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 22:30:24','2025-02-19 22:30:24'),(2036,'831','App\\Models\\Subsection','Tables',NULL,'<Table 24  Constituent elements of ILM',4,'67b65b8ea7f39.png','/storage/tables/67b65b8ea7f39.png','2025-02-19 22:30:24','2025-02-19 22:30:38'),(2037,'831','App\\Models\\Subsection','Figures',NULL,'[Fig: 24] Conceptual diagram of ILM',2,'67b65b8eb27c3.png','/storage/figures/67b65b8eb27c3.png','2025-02-19 22:30:24','2025-02-19 22:30:38'),(2038,'831','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','Information life cycle management (ILM) is a series of processes for separating and managing storage media, which is necessitated by ongoing changes in the value of data or information throughout its life cycle As the volume of data increases, so does the cost of managing data In contrast, the value of data changes as it goes through its life cycle: Thus, enterprises are turning to ILM in order to reduce their data management costs and manage data in a more systematic way:','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 22:30:24','2025-02-19 22:30:24'),(2039,'831','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','The constituent elements of ILM belong to one of two categories ie the management policy category or the technology element category:','',3,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 22:30:24','2025-02-19 22:30:24'),(2040,'832','App\\Models\\Subsection','Tables',NULL,'<Table 25  IRM process for EA',2,'67b65b8ec297d.png','/storage/tables/67b65b8ec297d.png','2025-02-19 22:30:24','2025-02-19 22:30:38'),(2041,'832','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','The purpose of information resource management (IRM) is the efficient and integrated management of IT resources Here, efficient and integrated management means preventing redundant investments in IT resources and increasing returns on investments It also means managing all types of IT resources HT resources to IT equipment, budgets and outputs from Ciilcipisc F Cuiccc DA: As one of the component elements of the EA, the DA describes the architecture of data Faced with the increasing complexity and scale of enterprise information systems and the growing need for the systemized management of information resources, enterprises have become dependent on IRM because it provides a common standard and management system for the entire range of informatization procedures (informatization planning, development, and performance evaluation): The IRM informs the EA of its framework for information resources, and the EA presents the IRM with guidelines for enterprise resource schemes and reference schemes That is, IRM and EA exist in a complementary relationship:','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 22:30:24','2025-02-19 22:30:24'),(2042,'647','App\\Models\\Section','Text','As IT business processes become ever more complex and have to respond rapidly to environmental (both external and internal) changes, there is a growing need for the systematized management of the data generated by such processes The data generated by IT business processes can be managed either by information life cycle management (ILM) or by information resource management (IRM):','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 22:30:24','2025-02-19 22:30:24'),(2043,'833','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','BPR is a technique for redesigning business processes in a fundamental way in order to bring about a radicz improvement in such performance indicators as cost, quality, service, and quickness. There are four attributes of BPF that should be mentioned here The first attribute is \'Basic: In BPR, activities are performed to address the basic problems of an enterprise Through BPR, answers are sought to such questions as \"For what purpose is a business task performed?\" \"What are the current problems?\" and What are the inefficient elements of an enterprise\'s operations?\" The second attribute is Zero Base\' BPR is all about designing a new way of performing business tasks by abandoning existing task procedures or processes The third attribute is \'Dramatic Improvement: BPR is used only when an absolute innovation is needed Thus, BPR signifies a radical improvement rather than a gradual improvement The fourth attribute is \'Process: The targets of BPR are mainly task processes BPR strives to resolve problems through process-centric thinking, without relying on jobs, workers, or organizational structures The aim is to','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 22:30:24','2025-02-19 22:30:24'),(2044,'834','App\\Models\\Subsection','Tables',NULL,'',2,'67b65b8ed2ae5.png','/storage/tables/67b65b8ed2ae5.png','2025-02-19 22:30:24','2025-02-19 22:30:38'),(2045,'648','App\\Models\\Section','Text','The concept of business process reengineering (BPR) was first introduced in a paper published by Professor Michael Hammer of MIT in 1990. As products from Asian countries began to penetrate the US market, US products began losing their competitiveness, so Professor Hammer sought to address the root causes of this problem in his paper After analyzing the causes of the decline in U.S competitiveness, Hammer found that U.S products were not actually lagging behind in terms of product competitiveness, but that were losing competitiveness in terms of price and quality: For American companies to provide the product values that customers were looking for Hammer felt that the solution lay in resolving the problems in the overall business process, and thus proposed the concept of BPR as a solution to those problems in his paper they','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 22:30:24','2025-02-19 22:30:24'),(2046,'835','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','Process innovation (PI) is the activity of improving the business environment to maximize corporate value. PI seeks to eliminate unnecessary elements (across all aspects of corporate activities ranging from business process to organization and IT) and rebuild effective business processes Pl is similar to BPR, but it was introduced in 1993 when David Port of the United States published his paper titled \'Process Innovation\' PI can be understood best as BPR, but with a greater emphasis on the integration of information technology The objective of Pl is to build a structure that can respond to changes in the business environment surrounding a enterprise by improving the current business processes and the flow of information logistics and values in a direction that is more customer-centric Internationally, the concept of BPR developed by Michael Hammer is used widely: But in South Korea, the concept of PI became more popular after it was first used by Samsung Electronics and after POSCO adopted a PI-based ERP as a strategy for improving its business processes. In South Korea, PI is used in a broader sense than BPR','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 22:30:24','2025-02-19 22:30:24'),(2047,'836','App\\Models\\Subsection','Figures',NULL,'',2,'67b65b8ee157d.png','/storage/figures/67b65b8ee157d.png','2025-02-19 22:30:24','2025-02-19 22:30:38'),(2048,'836','App\\Models\\Subsection','Figures',NULL,'',4,'67b65b8ef214f.png','/storage/figures/67b65b8ef214f.png','2025-02-19 22:30:24','2025-02-19 22:30:38'),(2049,'836','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','Generally, PI is implemented in conjunction with the deployment of information technology: typical situation is when an enterprise carries out sudden improvements of its business processes through integration with ERP The PI develops into a system that performs improvements to plans and processes, establishes an information service plan, and then realizes the planned items as a means of execution, whether ERP or CRM The implementation of PI begins with improving the processes and systems of an enterprise, after which an informatization plan is established through the improved systems and processes, followed by the deployment of a system that is capable of executing the plan through FRP or CRM','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 22:30:24','2025-02-19 22:30:24'),(2050,'836','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','The relationship between PI and ERP can be explained as follows. First, PI is implemented to bring abol improvements to an enterprise\'s systems, processes, and workforce and to lay the groundwork for the integration data and processes This is followed by the procedure for constructing the integrated system:','',3,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 22:30:24','2025-02-19 22:30:24'),(2051,'837','App\\Models\\Subsection','Figures',NULL,'27] Change management with PI [Fig',2,'67b65b8f0c2b2.png','/storage/figures/67b65b8f0c2b2.png','2025-02-19 22:30:24','2025-02-19 22:30:39'),(2052,'837','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','Once the process of an enterprise has been innovatively improved, the enterprise must grant itself sufficient time to adapt to the changed process In such a situation, the organization\' s productivity drops rapidly, and in order to ensure the success of PIl projects and mitigate the decline in productivity issues like expectations, resistance, insecurity, and motivation must be effectively managed at each stage of the project.','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 22:30:24','2025-02-19 22:30:24'),(2053,'837','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','For the efficient implementation of Pl, all executives and employees of the enterprise must be familiar with and share in the vision of change The activities and resources needed for implanting change must be organized and strategies must be developed. The CEO must display strong leadership and active participation. Leaders should encourage the completion of changes, take responsibility for activities, ad encourage active participation by the stakeholders Leaders must also turn the management vision into reality and increase the ability of individuals and teams to perform their jobs effectively in the new environment PI can be established stably only if change management with PI is successful. An organizations ability to adapt to change eventually determine the success or failure of the project will','',3,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 22:30:24','2025-02-19 22:30:24'),(2054,'650','App\\Models\\Section','Text','With PI, IT business innovation can be approached in two different ways: one method consists in adopting ERP through PI, while the other consists in using ERP to accelerate the implementation of PI. Irrespective of which approach is taken, an enterprise must strategically establish an adoption plan and a direction that reflect the circumstances of the enterprise','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 22:30:24','2025-02-19 22:30:24'),(2055,'838','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','\"Six Sigma\" is a quality innovation movement that was started by Motorola in 1987 with the aim of achieving a defect rate of less than three out of one million products and of reaching the so-called \"6 Sigma\" level of quality by analyzing and quantifying the causes of inefficiencies in management. Thus, the three main pillars of Six Sigma are statistical measurement, business strategy ad philosophy (transformation of the way work should be performed)','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 22:30:24','2025-02-19 22:30:24'),(2056,'839','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','The statistical measurement of process innovations IS critical. Quantitication and objective measurements are performed It is an enterprise-wide process innovation activity that is not limited to a specific department, team or area Its ultimate goal is to improve the value and satisfaction perceived by customers who are at the end of the value chain, \"Six Sigma\" strives for a passionate organizational culture in which all members of an organization participate in the rc continuouc imnrovementc','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 22:30:24','2025-02-19 22:30:24'),(2057,'840','App\\Models\\Subsection','Tables',NULL,'<Table 27  Six Sigma Hierarchy',1,'67b65b8f1ab4e.png','/storage/tables/67b65b8f1ab4e.png','2025-02-19 22:30:24','2025-02-19 22:30:39'),(2058,'841','App\\Models\\Subsection','Tables',NULL,'',4,'67b65b8f2da09.png','/storage/tables/67b65b8f2da09.png','2025-02-19 22:30:24','2025-02-19 22:30:39'),(2059,'841','App\\Models\\Subsection','Figures',NULL,'<Table 28  Six Sigma implementation methodolog',2,'67b65b8f3a204.png','/storage/figures/67b65b8f3a204.png','2025-02-19 22:30:24','2025-02-19 22:30:39'),(2060,'841','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','The Six Sigma implementation methodology can be separated into the design program and the manufacturing program: The design program uses the DMADV methodology, while the manufacturing program uses the DMAIC methodology Another characteristic is that the design program is focused on preventing errors and defects, whereas the manufacturing program is focused on reducing defects and preventing recurrences.','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 22:30:24','2025-02-19 22:30:24'),(2061,'841','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','The design program is for designing a process that surpasses the core requirements and the customers\' program expectations The design program is focused on preventing errors and defects It is suitable for MADV) developing new products or processes, and for redesigning existing products or processes. (Define) Establish the of design activities that satisfy the requirements put forth by users: (Measure) Select factors that impact quality in a critical way: (Analyze) Assess the feasibility of the design and conduct analysis for development of the best design (Design) Detailed agenda, optimize design, and plan for design verification (Verify) Activate testing of the design and verify the application of the product development process. goals','',3,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 22:30:24','2025-02-19 22:30:24'),(2062,'841','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','The manufacturing program makes repetitive improvements while focusing on reducing defects to the levels required by manufacturing, production and mass production The manufacturing program also nufacturing program improves existing products and processes (DMAIC) (Define) Define the problem, set the and estimate CTQ(Critical to Quality): (Measure) Select theitems for measurement, establish the method of measurement, and analyze the current status: (Analyze) Analyze the causal relationship of the identified problem and determine the root cause (Improve) Derive the optimal method for eliminating the root cause and improving manufacturing: (Control) Prevent recurrence, maintain the improved condition, and analyze the effects of imnrovemantc goals,','',5,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 22:30:24','2025-02-19 22:30:24'),(2063,'842','App\\Models\\Subsection','Tables',NULL,'',3,'67b65b8f43d75.png','/storage/tables/67b65b8f43d75.png','2025-02-19 22:30:24','2025-02-19 22:30:39'),(2064,'842','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','TRIZ is a systematic methodology for solving the problem of invention, which was developed in the Soviet Union by Genrich Altshuller5 In the 1940s, Genrich Altshuller worked for the Soviet Navy as a patent examiner He discovered that there were some common rules and patterns in inventions. Out of 1.5 million patents worldwide, 50,000 creative patents were extracted and analyzed, resulting in four important discoveries which are summarized in the table below:','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 22:30:24','2025-02-19 22:30:24'),(2065,'843','App\\Models\\Subsection','Tables',NULL,'<Table 30  Types of contradiction',2,'67b65b8f4df8b.png','/storage/tables/67b65b8f4df8b.png','2025-02-19 22:30:24','2025-02-19 22:30:39'),(2066,'843','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','In TRIZ, contradictions are classified as either a physical contradiction or a technical contradiction. Physical contradictions are mainly solved using the principle of separation, whereas technical contradictions are solved with 40 inventive principles, 76 standard solutions, 8 laws of technology evolution, and various effects of natural science','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 22:30:24','2025-02-19 22:30:24'),(2067,'844','App\\Models\\Subsection','Tables',NULL,'<Table 31  Management technique using TRIZ',2,'67b65b8f5a5dc.png','/storage/tables/67b65b8f5a5dc.png','2025-02-19 22:30:24','2025-02-19 22:30:39'),(2068,'844','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','TRIZ has been widely recognized for its effectiveness in management as well as in engineering Furthermore, many studies and cases of its application are being reported','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 22:30:24','2025-02-19 22:30:24'),(2069,'845','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','SERVQUAL is a technique for analyzing the gap between the level of service quality expected by users and the actual level of service quality provided by an enterprise Using the following five dimensions, SERVQUAL prioritizes the relative importance (as felt by the user) of service attributes, thus making it possible for an enterprise to provide a service based on its scale of priority: SERVQUAL was first proposed by Parasuraman, Zeithaml, and Berry in 1985.','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 22:30:24','2025-02-19 22:30:24'),(2070,'846','App\\Models\\Subsection','Tables',NULL,'<Table 32  5 dimensions of SERVQUAL',2,'67b65b8f656ff.png','/storage/tables/67b65b8f656ff.png','2025-02-19 22:30:24','2025-02-19 22:30:39'),(2071,'846','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','SERVQUAL consists of 5 dimensions: tangibles, reliability, responsiveness, assurance, and empathy','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 22:30:24','2025-02-19 22:30:24'),(2072,'846','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','The 5 dimensions of SERVQUAL are often subdivided into the following 10 categories ad utilized in investigations and evaluations: Tangibles: Physical facilities, equipment, employees, outward appearance of data. Reliability: Ability to perform a promised service in a manner that can be trusted and is accurate Responsiveness: Readiness to assist users and provide quick services Competence: Possession of the technology and knowledge required for the provision of services Courtesy: Courtesy, respect, consideration, and friendliness of front-line workers Credibility: Credibility and honesty of the service provider Safety: Absence of the likelihood of risks and doubt Accessibility: Accessibility and ease of access: Communication: Communication with users in a language that is easy to understand, listening to What users have to say: Customer understanding: Making the effort to understand what customers want and evaluations Tangibles: Physical facilities, equipment, employees, outward appearance of data. Reliability: to perform a promised service in a manner that can be trusted and is accurate Responsiveness: Readiness to assist users and provide quick services Competence: Possession of the technology and knowedge required for the provision of services Courtesy: Courtesy, respect, consideration, and friendliness of front-line workers Credibility: Credibility and honesty of the service provider Ability','',3,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 22:30:24','2025-02-19 22:30:24'),(2073,'847','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','SPC stands for \"Statistical Process Control\": This term contains the word \'statistical\' because it relies on statistical data and analysis techniques, the word \'process\' because it represents a given product quality specification and the capacity of the process, and \'control\' because the technique allows enterprises to control the condition of the product when it is produced: SPC is a management technique that allows enterprises to make repeated improvements to a process and maintain high rates of production of goods of satisfactory quality: SPC allows enterprises to conduct an engineering analysis of the causes of defects and establish the best way of rectifying the problem in a reasonable manner:','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 22:30:24','2025-02-19 22:30:24'),(2074,'848','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','The objective of using the SPC technique is to produce of uniform quality within a narrow range of quality distribution. Therefore, SPC-oriented management reduces process variations and ultimately stabilizes each goods processthus laying the foundations for the production of zero-defect goods With SPC, enterprises can produce high-quality goods and enhance their productivity to levels that will lead to significant cost reductions, thereby contributing to higher profits.','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 22:30:24','2025-02-19 22:30:24'),(2075,'849','App\\Models\\Subsection','Tables',NULL,'<Table 33  Constituent elements of SPC',1,'67b65b8f739a6.png','/storage/tables/67b65b8f739a6.png','2025-02-19 22:30:24','2025-02-19 22:30:39'),(2076,'849','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','Besides the component elements described above, statistical data must be collected for the variance analysis The instruments used in data collection include the work checklists,, and inspection device data among other The statistical techniques used in SPC analysis include the control chart, histogram, scatter plot, Pareto diagram, and cause-effect diagram: log\' things: 1s). e statistical techniques used in SPC analysis include the control chart, histogram, scatter plot, Pareto diagram, and use-effect diagram','',2,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 22:30:24','2025-02-19 22:30:24'),(2077,'655','App\\Models\\Section','Tables',NULL,'<Table 34  Key roles of enterprise solutions',2,'67b65b8f85e5b.png','/storage/tables/67b65b8f85e5b.png','2025-02-19 22:30:25','2025-02-19 22:30:39'),(2078,'655','App\\Models\\Section','Text','IT business is a enabler of enterprise competitiveness and continuous innovation In the past, it was simply a tool for supporting business activities, but today it plays an important role as a tool for survival within a highly competitive environment During the short 30-year period since the introduction of enterprise computing in the early 1980s, the power of computers has grown exponentially and enterprises have left many examples of how computers should be used in the business environment These examples have now evolved into formal solutions key An \"enterprise solution\" is a collective term for the information systems that support the management activities which an enterprise must perform in order to maximize business efficiency and competitive advantages in its business environment. The value ad utility of a enterprise solution will vary depending on the business processes ad activities to be defined, and not by the function provided by the information system Enterprise solutions are a broad concept encompassing advance IT planning, job specific solutions that will be configured together for building a business operation system using IT systems, and maintenance& repair for directly Ct Stinc LO ~foronontioned Cucton gain As such, enterprise solutions are focused on maximizing business efficiency: Work efficiency directly leads to productivity improvements and also plays an important role in strengthening the competitiveness of an enterprise The following table summarizes the role of these enterprise solutions. key','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 22:30:25','2025-02-19 22:30:25'),(2079,'656','App\\Models\\Section','Figures',NULL,'',2,'67b65b8f944b5.png','/storage/figures/67b65b8f944b5.png','2025-02-19 22:30:25','2025-02-19 22:30:39'),(2080,'656','App\\Models\\Section','Text','The various solutions needed for an enterprise\'s activities must be used in a way that is appropriate to the enterprise $ purpose and objectives Looking at some of the leading enterprise solutions, the first that comes to mind is enterprise resource management or ERP ERP provides enterprises with a means of optimizing, distributing and properlv deplovingloperating its entire resources, An information system that effectively aggregates management information','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 22:30:25','2025-02-19 22:30:25'),(2081,'656','App\\Models\\Section','Text','An integrated management system of enterprise functions for the optimal operation of enterprise-wide resources [Fig.28] Types of enterprise solutio There is the supply chain management (SCM) system, which integrates the entire supply chain from purchasing to production and eventual delivery to customers. With SCM, an enterprise can manage how many raw materials to purchase, sort them into product groups, and manufacture products in a timely manner ready for delivery when the customers need them. Because the analysis of customers is a critical factor of competition, the customer relationship management (CRM) system is a solution on which enterprises depend to properly analyze customer needs, enhance the service for customers, and strengthen customer relationships for additional value delivery:','',3,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 22:30:25','2025-02-19 22:30:25'),(2082,'657','App\\Models\\Section','Figures',NULL,'1 [',2,'67b65b8f9f97a.png','/storage/figures/67b65b8f9f97a.png','2025-02-19 22:30:25','2025-02-19 22:30:39'),(2083,'657','App\\Models\\Section','Text','In enterprise solutions, communication with customers, product management, and process integration should be organically linked. These aspects must be comprehensively managed so that enterprises can execute their business strategies efficiently and achieve their business The environment surrounding an enterprise changes fluidly every minute as such, enterprises are always faced with the challenge of responding nimbly in order to survive: Thus, companies have no other choice but to tailor and their strategies to fit the environmental changes The adoption of enterprise solutions that satisfy the strategic goals of an enterprise is an unavoidable choice: There are countless enterprise solutions required by businesses However the solutions that most enterprises absolutely need to deploy or need to develop on their own in one form or another can be defined using just a handful of solutions. There are also situations in which enterprises, as grow in scale, are forced to adopt a particular solution to meet the IT compliance requirements. goals change they','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 22:30:25','2025-02-19 22:30:25'),(2084,'658','App\\Models\\Section','Text','The figure above illustrates the interrelationship between a business strategy and various enterprise solutions For each application and purpose, an enterprise solution is tied to a particular strategy item: In other words, enterprise solutions are adopted in a manner befitting a particular strategy (as well as the sub-details of each strategy) of an enterprise','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 22:30:25','2025-02-19 22:30:25'),(2085,'850','App\\Models\\Subsection','Tables',NULL,'<Table 35  Characteristics of ERP',2,'67b65b8fac0d1.png','/storage/tables/67b65b8fac0d1.png','2025-02-19 22:30:25','2025-02-19 22:30:39'),(2086,'850','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','ERP (enterprise resource management) is a system that maximizes enterprise productivity by integrating the various management resources of an enterprise into a single system: The goal is to maximize enterprise-wide business efficiency by integrating the company\'s key business processes and sharing information Integrated work-related support for various aspects of business operation and the systematic of different aspects of business operation contribute to the efficient sharing of data and increased organizational flexibility: linking','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 22:30:25','2025-02-19 22:30:25'),(2087,'851','App\\Models\\Subsection','Figures',NULL,'[Fig.30] Configuration of ERP',2,'67b65b8fc226e.png','/storage/figures/67b65b8fc226e.png','2025-02-19 22:30:25','2025-02-19 22:30:39'),(2088,'851','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','Most operational functions of an enterprise, from purchasing to production, distribution, marketing, sales, service, finance, accounting and human resources, are organized in a way that ensures interdependencies between the functions and a balanced distribution of resources For example, when a customer places an order, the sales representative enters it into the ERP system and the finalized order data (how much, where and when the delivery must be made) are communicated to the department which requires the data. To meet the order the data concerning raw materials (when, how much and at what price were procured) are also sent to the relevant department in a similar fashion. The factory will produce the order on schedule, and the production data will be entered into the ERP and transmitted to the shipping department The shipping department will then deliver the goods to the customer on the desired date The ERP system provides an environment in which these operations can take place organically: they system','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 22:30:25','2025-02-19 22:30:25'),(2089,'852','App\\Models\\Subsection','Tables',NULL,'',3,'67b65b8fd415a.png','/storage/tables/67b65b8fd415a.png','2025-02-19 22:30:25','2025-02-19 22:30:39'),(2090,'852','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','The deployment of ERP should be approached as a concept of enterprise business innovation, and not just as the simple introduction of a system. The legacy operating procedures of the enterprise must be analyzed, and any problems and improvement points must be identified Through process innovation (PI) activities, the enterprise must undergo a radical transformation. Job activities must be innovated so that can be performed by employees from a common perspective and handled using standardized procedures that are integrated across the enterprise. To this end, the ERP implementation project must be wholeheartedly supported by the CEO and pursued at the company level in order for it to be successful. The typical ERP implementation process includes the following: they','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 22:30:25','2025-02-19 22:30:25'),(2091,'853','App\\Models\\Subsection','Tables',NULL,'<Table 37  ERP deployment strategy',2,'67b65b8fe252e.png','/storage/tables/67b65b8fe252e.png','2025-02-19 22:30:25','2025-02-19 22:30:39'),(2092,'853','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','There are three approaches to ERP deployment. With the Big Bang method, all modules and functions of the ERP system are deployed across the place of business at the same time: In the phased and function-based approach, the ERP system modules are separated by their functions and the ERP system is deployed only on some modules. In the phased and place of business approach, the ERP system is deployed in phases at each place of business. When the operation of ERP is shown to be stable, its deployment is then expanded horizontally through the remaining phases','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 22:30:25','2025-02-19 22:30:25'),(2093,'853','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','ERP solutions are supplied by both domestic vendors and foreign global vendors. Depending on the deployment strategy, the ERP solution could also be developed in-house. Leading foreign ERP solutions include SAP ERP and Oracle ERP while domestic ERP solutions include Younglimwon ERP and Douzone ERP Commercial ERP products offer the advantages of ERP deployment using standardized processes, however, customized development to match the environment of an enterprise is somewhat difficult, Another worth mentioning is that when adopting an ERP solution, an enterprise must check whether compliance with the IFRS (International Financial Reporting Standards)5 must be observed. leading thing','',3,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 22:30:25','2025-02-19 22:30:25'),(2094,'854','App\\Models\\Subsection','Figures',NULL,'[Fig 31] Bullwhip effect in supply chains',2,'67b65b8ff11f1.png','/storage/figures/67b65b8ff11f1.png','2025-02-19 22:30:25','2025-02-19 22:30:39'),(2095,'854','App\\Models\\Subsection','Figures',NULL,'[Fig 32] Conceptual diagram of supply chain management',4,'67b65b900c28e.png','/storage/figures/67b65b900c28e.png','2025-02-19 22:30:25','2025-02-19 22:30:40'),(2096,'854','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','Mrefers to supply chain management solutions To understand SCM, one has to understand the supply chain: The IFRS: The International Financial Reporting Standards (IFRS) published by the International Accounting Standards Board to ensure international acceptance of enterprise accounting standards. supply chain encompasses the entire process from order placement and the supplying of raw materials needed for the production of goods, to the production process, distribution network and final delivery to the customer The biggest problem with the supply chain is the whipping effect, a phenomenon in which decisions that are made further up the supply chain result in a sudden expansion of demand. What this means is that a small change in the end-consumer demand for a product will cause a chain reaction furtherup the supply chain, increasing the demand from retailers to wholesalers then to manufacturers and finallv to narts sunnliers','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 22:30:25','2025-02-19 22:30:25'),(2097,'854','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','As shown in Figure 31 above, if a consumer places an order for 10 goods to a wholesaler, the wholesaler will place an order for 12 just in case The manufacturer will in turn manufacture 15 goods just in case. In this way, the supply chain will become overstocked and resources will be wasted, with unnecessary investments in manpower and 6? goods _ If market demand is transmitted in this way to the upper level of the supply chain, the demand distorted a increases variance at each step In addition, the supplier who supplies the raw materials at the end of the val chain becomes exposed to huge risks, which seriously increases the inefficiency of the entire supply chain du to the imbalance in demand across the supply chain, ultimately resulting in surplus orders, excess inventory, overinvestment Therefore, supply chain management is a strategy that aims to maximize efficiency by rectifying whipping effect problem and by eliminating waste throughout the supply chain. gets To be more specific, in supply chain management the players in the supply chain cooperate with each in managing materials, funds and information, with the objective of linking and integrating the flow of all goods, services and values (purchasing, manufacture, allocation and distribution) from the suppliers to the end customers The effects of these activities manifest themselves as a shortened lead time and reduced uncertainties and variabilities It is the of supply chain management to support these activities and address the issues that arise in the supply chain goal It is a management technique that seeks to optimize inventory management ad other such supply chain decisions through the sharing of information and collaboration with suppliers throughout the entire process from production to distribution','',3,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 22:30:25','2025-02-19 22:30:25'),(2098,'854','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','To implement supply chain management (SCM), an enterprise must have in place some crucial functions in suppl chain planning (SCP) and supply chain execution (SCE):','',5,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 22:30:25','2025-02-19 22:30:25'),(2099,'855','App\\Models\\Subsection','Tables',NULL,'<Table38 Functions of supply chain management',2,'67b65b901a018.png','/storage/tables/67b65b901a018.png','2025-02-19 22:30:25','2025-02-19 22:30:40'),(2100,'855','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','SCM carries out the 3 functions of supply chain planning, supply chain execution, and supply chain visibility: These three functions form a positive feedback cycle, a structure in which their functions can be improved when the working environment changes','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 22:30:26','2025-02-19 22:30:26'),(2101,'856','App\\Models\\Subsection','Tables',NULL,'<Table 39  Comparison of SCM and ERP',2,'67b65b9029418.png','/storage/tables/67b65b9029418.png','2025-02-19 22:30:26','2025-02-19 22:30:40'),(2102,'856','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','CM and ERP are the parts of the work support system operated by enterprises Logistics and distribution nanagement are the critical areas of SCM that are intimately tied to ERP In recent some ERP have been mplemented with a part of the functionality of SCM, but the detailed flow is managed by SCM years,','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 22:30:26','2025-02-19 22:30:26'),(2103,'857','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','Dell Computer, the most successful company in introducing SCM, said that after adopting SCM it became possible to link information between customer, company, and component suppliers in real time, and reduced its inventory 8 weeks\' worth of supplies to 12 15 days\' worth of supplies. The introduction of supply chain management can improve customer satisfaction by increasing transportation delivery capacity ad reducing inventory, reduce logistics costs, and reducethe customer order processing time through strict adherence to delivery schedules It can also improve the efficiency of fund flow by standardizing work and by reducing the product delivery time and the order processing time from','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 22:30:26','2025-02-19 22:30:26'),(2104,'858','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','The CRM defined by Gartner is a strategy for optimizing corporate sales ad expanding the customer base by creating ad supporting relationships with profitable customers\'. In other words, CRM is a management technique that integrates and analyzes customer data across the enterprise and customer-related data inside and outside the enterprise, and then provides the findings to customer points of contact for use in interactions with the customers This is an integrated process that enables enterprises to continually deliver the products and services customers want, based on an accurate understanding of the customers, thereby maximizing customer lifetime value and increasing profitability:','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 22:30:26','2025-02-19 22:30:26'),(2105,'859','App\\Models\\Subsection','Figures',NULL,'',2,'67b65b9034de0.png','/storage/figures/67b65b9034de0.png','2025-02-19 22:30:26','2025-02-19 22:30:40'),(2106,'859','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','From a process perspective, CRM collects and analyzes the various data generated by the entity and provides it with meaningful information CRM can be classified as analysis CRM, operations CRM,, or collaboration CRM With analysis CRM, information generated through interactions with customers is gathered,, and meaningful insights are derived and then supplied to the enterprise With operations CRM, these insights form the backbone of marketing, servicing and sales activities Finally, with collaboration CRM, the enterprise engages in interactions with the customers through a diverse range of channelc','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 22:30:26','2025-02-19 22:30:26'),(2107,'661','App\\Models\\Section','Figures',NULL,'[Fig: 33] Life cycle of enterprise customers',2,'67b65b903f8f1.png','/storage/figures/67b65b903f8f1.png','2025-02-19 22:30:26','2025-02-19 22:30:40'),(2108,'661','App\\Models\\Section','Text','CRM stands tor customer relationship management It IS & management strategy system tor studying customers tendencies and requirements in advance in order to create the products that customers want and to develop marketing strategies Because todays customers\' knowledge of product and service information has vastly increased and customer expectations ad customer churn are higher than ever before, enterprises are compelled to establish new business management strategies, such as adopting a customer-centric corporate structure, establishing diverse customer interface channels, and implementing customer management that leads to better earnings To implement these strategies, enterprises must analyze customer behavior patterns and consumption patterns In recent years, enterprises have felt the need to consolidate internallexternal data and analyze markets and customers to derive insights Big Data analysis is a good example of this,','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 22:30:26','2025-02-19 22:30:26'),(2109,'661','App\\Models\\Section','Text','Enterprises can opportunities to acquire new customers through focused marketing or promotional activities that target responsive customers among potential customers in the target market who show interest in their products Enterprises should strategically manage customers who purchase their products as well as high-value (highly loyal) customers To this end, enterprises should have a in place that can sort their customers based on such criteria as personality, type, and interests, and provide their services and conduct their marketing accordingly: This requires a entity to establish a strategy for maximizing customer lifetime value, ie the total value generated throughout the customers lifecycle, rather than the temporary profitability generated by individual transactions: This is the goal of CRM gain system','',3,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 22:30:26','2025-02-19 22:30:26'),(2110,'860','App\\Models\\Subsection','Tables',NULL,'<Table41 Components of the CRM system',4,'67b65b904ef1d.png','/storage/tables/67b65b904ef1d.png','2025-02-19 22:30:26','2025-02-19 22:30:40'),(2111,'860','App\\Models\\Subsection','Figures',NULL,'[Fig 35] Configuration of the CRM system',2,'67b65b905e6d3.png','/storage/figures/67b65b905e6d3.png','2025-02-19 22:30:26','2025-02-19 22:30:40'),(2112,'860','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','n CRM, information begins to flow from the customer point of contact and ends at the customer point of contact Amid this flow of information,, the information generated by the work support system utilized and the operation of the work process occurs at the same time: gets','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 22:30:26','2025-02-19 22:30:26'),(2113,'860','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','In CRM, the customer point of contact has huge significance The customer of contact or channel collects the customer\'s VoC and communicates the results produced by the interal process to the customer Therefore, when the component elements of CRM must be identified, it is advisable to investigate the channel first of all, since this is the of contact with the customers. Also, if information analysis is conducted, followed by information utilization, it becomes very easy to understand the constituent elements of CRM point point','',3,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 22:30:26','2025-02-19 22:30:26'),(2114,'861','App\\Models\\Subsection','Tables',NULL,'<Table 42  Benefits of CRM deployment',2,'67b65b906c60a.png','/storage/tables/67b65b906c60a.png','2025-02-19 22:30:26','2025-02-19 22:30:40'),(2115,'861','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','With the introduction of CRM, enterprises can improve their relationships with their customers and prevent custome churn,, thereby increasing customer loyalty: Furthermore, enterprises can provide high-quality services by analyzin customers\' tastes, and can also induce linked sales and realize upstream sales. Furthermore, they can build competitive edge in terms of customers through differentiated policies in products and services','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 22:30:26','2025-02-19 22:30:26'),(2116,'662','App\\Models\\Section','Tables',NULL,'<Table 40  Comparison of CRM classifications',2,'67b65b907d32d.png','/storage/tables/67b65b907d32d.png','2025-02-19 22:30:26','2025-02-19 22:30:40'),(2117,'662','App\\Models\\Section','Text','Categorizing CRM in this way is only done for the purpose of increasing peoples understanding of CRM: In fact, the ultimate target of CRM is to inside the minds of the customers. In order to accurately read the customers\' minds, data analysis has to be performed,, while assistance from a business support system is also helpful. A diverse set of customer points of contact (channels) for interacting with customers has to be secured as well: get','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 22:30:26','2025-02-19 22:30:26'),(2118,'862','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','PLM can be defined as a support system that integrates and manages information related to products such as drawings, documents, CADICAM information, basic parts information, design changes, and process information These forms of information are generated throughout the entire product life cyclesof the products that are developed and manufactured by an enterprise','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 22:30:26','2025-02-19 22:30:26'),(2119,'863','App\\Models\\Subsection','Tables',NULL,'<Table 43  PLM components',4,'67b65b908c559.png','/storage/tables/67b65b908c559.png','2025-02-19 22:30:26','2025-02-19 22:30:40'),(2120,'863','App\\Models\\Subsection','Figures',NULL,'[Fig: 36] Diagram of the configuration of PLM',2,'67b65b90993bc.png','/storage/figures/67b65b90993bc.png','2025-02-19 22:30:26','2025-02-19 22:30:40'),(2121,'863','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','Recently, PLM has come to be understood as a concept that includes not only product planning, but also the post- sales services provided to customers Managing the entire cycle of an individual product from the planning stage until it is sold is the role of PLM However, organic support from other work support systems is a prerequisite for fulfiling this role To understand the components of PLM, it is sometimes helpful to visualize the flow of a product s entire life key cycle,','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 22:30:26','2025-02-19 22:30:26'),(2122,'863','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','The main components of the process presented in the PLM configuration diagram shown above are derived and described in the table below:','',3,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 22:30:26','2025-02-19 22:30:26'),(2123,'864','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','Product development was always a collaboration-centered effort To more effectively manage product developmen activities, beginning in the 1990s, enterprises began to operate storages in which kept the system desigr information of their engineering teams. they As the number of projects and products in need of development increased and became more difficult to manage, it became necessary to consolidate the scattered information Included in the centralized system were a number of items that served as important reference data when designing items and products, such as BOM (bill of materials) management,, development process standardization, and the workflow-based change management function, etc, The inclusion of these items made it possible to maximize the efficiency of product development Recently, the trend among companies has gravitated towards consolidating the PLM through the integration of ERP and MDM solutions for the purpose of managing the reference data from the enterprise-wide perspective: In the future, PLM will be expanded to include the social PLM area by linking it with external data.','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 22:30:26','2025-02-19 22:30:26'),(2124,'663','App\\Models\\Section','Text','Product lifecycle management (PLM) is a product life cycle management solution It is a production/design process that increases a product\'s added value and reduces costs by uniformly managing the entire process creation of the product design drawings to production of the final product. PLM provides product information data management server system, both of which are related to the product life cycle and the network of multiple client systems. from','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 22:30:26','2025-02-19 22:30:26'),(2125,'865','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','The enterprise data warehouse (EDW) is a system that can address, by subject matter information analysis requests by users, through the integration of internal and external data. The EDW requires the construction of infrastructure that serves as the backbone of enterprise data. This infrastructure touches every area and aspect of an enterprise\'s pucinocc Tne enterprise aata warenouse (ELW) IS a system tnat can adaress, Dy subject matter, Intormation analysis requests by users, through the integration of internal and external data. The EDW requires the construction of infrastructure that serves as the backbone of enterprise data This infrastructure touches every area and aspect of an enterprises business: In the beginning, the EDW mostly encompassed the internal data of an enterprise Today, however, it is evolving into a forecasting system that integrates both the internal and external information of an enterprise business: In the beginning the EDW mostly encompassed the internal data of an enterprise: Today, however, it is evolving into a forecasting system that integrates both the interal and external information of an enterprise','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 22:30:26','2025-02-19 22:30:26'),(2126,'866','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','II an enterprise wisnes tO maintain unliormity Or viewpoint across ItS entre Organization, IC must consolldale lne information that it possesses and any external information it needs from an enterprise-wide perspective and keep it as the master information In today\'s rapidly changing business environment, enterprises have to extract enterprise-perspective data by conducting diverse data analyses for users in diverse sectors. This is because enterprises need to have sufficient forecasting capability for making strategic choices and responding to changing user requirements brought about by changes in the business environment Enterprises also have to integrate their information resources and reorganize their management system as part of redesigning their to prevent data duplication: system','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 22:30:26','2025-02-19 22:30:26'),(2127,'867','App\\Models\\Subsection','Tables',NULL,'<Table 44  Characteristics of the EDW',2,'67b65b90a613d.png','/storage/tables/67b65b90a613d.png','2025-02-19 22:30:26','2025-02-19 22:30:40'),(2128,'867','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','The EDW was created with a clear purpose for its use The concept explains a very import characteristic of the EDW, namely, that of being topic-centered. Upon adopting the EDW, critical data within and outside the company become concentrated and consolidated in one place, and data are loaded and used in a time-based order Once stored, data will not be destroyed or changed unless there is a particular reason for doing so These characteristics of the EDW are described in detail as follows.','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 22:30:26','2025-02-19 22:30:26'),(2129,'868','App\\Models\\Subsection','Figures',NULL,'[Fig: 37] Concept diagram of the EDW',2,'67b65b90b3102.png','/storage/figures/67b65b90b3102.png','2025-02-19 22:30:26','2025-02-19 22:30:40'),(2130,'868','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','The EDW is configured so that the work support system collects, transforms and loads data during operations, analyzes data that meet the given requirements, and visualizes them in such a way that will be of assistance when making decisions From a macro perspective, all these processes are referred to as the EDW, and from a microscopic point of view, the repository for storing data is referred to as the EDW. they','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 22:30:26','2025-02-19 22:30:26'),(2131,'868','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','As shown in the figure above, transaction data are acquired from the legacy system of the enterprise and stored in the data warehouse. The analyzed data carry considerable value as information and are made visually presentable by using Bl solutions.','',3,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 22:30:26','2025-02-19 22:30:26'),(2132,'869','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','As a system that supports decision making, the Decision Support System (DSS) provides interactive dialogue support to decision makers during the decision-making process This is an interactive dialogue-based system that assists decision-makers with solving semi-structural and non structural problems using data and analytical models. The core elements of the DSS are the enterprise data (both internal and external) and the analytical model for processing quantitative data. These perform a critical role in decision making:','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 22:30:26','2025-02-19 22:30:26'),(2133,'870','App\\Models\\Subsection','Tables',NULL,'',3,'67b65b90c4b3d.png','/storage/tables/67b65b90c4b3d.png','2025-02-19 22:30:26','2025-02-19 22:30:40'),(2134,'870','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','The key feature of the DSS is its ability to solve non-structural problems through interactive dialogue Here, \"interactive means that issues can be explained or expressed from many different angles as desired by the user The focus of the DSS is on how analyzed data should be represented','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 22:30:26','2025-02-19 22:30:26'),(2135,'871','App\\Models\\Subsection','Tables',NULL,'',5,'67b65b90d6687.png','/storage/tables/67b65b90d6687.png','2025-02-19 22:30:26','2025-02-19 22:30:40'),(2136,'871','App\\Models\\Subsection','Figures',NULL,'[Fig: 38] Configuration of the DSS',2,'67b65b90e2ba4.png','/storage/figures/67b65b90e2ba4.png','2025-02-19 22:30:26','2025-02-19 22:30:40'),(2137,'871','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','The configuration diagram below shows how the DSS is made up of a document system, a model system, ad a knowledge system These components interact with each other to deliver the necessary information to the user:','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 22:30:26','2025-02-19 22:30:26'),(2138,'871','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','The user obtains the information required to make decisions by accessing the knowledge system through th user interface In addition, for model system management and database management,, the user must access th respective system to perform necessary tasks','',3,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 22:30:26','2025-02-19 22:30:26'),(2139,'872','App\\Models\\Subsection','Tables',NULL,'<Table 47  Types of DSS data models',2,'67b65b90ef14a.png','/storage/tables/67b65b90ef14a.png','2025-02-19 22:30:26','2025-02-19 22:30:40'),(2140,'872','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','The data model in the DSS provides a framework for analyzing data, with the data with which decision makers can make rational decisions Different types of data models are generated from different types of algorithms and are continuously being developed and improved: In recent years, the DSS has been evolving in the direction of actively employing Al for better forecasting, ad the types of models are also diversifying: along','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 22:30:26','2025-02-19 22:30:26'),(2141,'873','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','Business intelligence (Bl) is a set of processes that seeks to improve the quality of business decisions and business performance through the summarization, analysis and use of enterprise data and information. If the DSS is the system for decision makers, and the traditional concept is support system for decision-making, then Bl is the decision support system that can be adopted for use by regular employees In the narrow sense of the term, Bl is a system that improves the quality of decision-making in business management ad improves the performance of a business by summarizing and analyzing enterprise data and information Intelligence is the ability to understand the interrelationships between given facts, which could produce guidance for achieving a desired goal. (Hans Luhn, IBM, 1958) The general consensus is that todays Bl evolved from the DSS. Analysis technologies such as data warehouses, OLAPs, and BIl began to be developed in the late 1980s based on the DSS.','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 22:30:26','2025-02-19 22:30:26'),(2142,'874','App\\Models\\Subsection','Figures',NULL,'[Fig: 39] Configuration of Bl',1,'67b65b910889c.png','/storage/figures/67b65b910889c.png','2025-02-19 22:30:26','2025-02-19 22:30:41'),(2143,'874','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','Bl provides ETL (Extraction, Transformation, Load) operations on data with which enterprises can maintain the consistency and compatibility of OLTP (Online Transaction Processing) data: These features, naturally enough, are also included in the EDW described earlier, and, as indicated by the component elements, it needs to be understood that the set of processes for collecting, analyzing and visualizing data, as well as the functions for supporting decision-making are in an organic relationship with each other Bl consists of a data warehouse that stores data, a data mart where different perspectives can be applied a analyzed in multi-dimensions, analysis tools, and dashboards that generate charts, simulations, statistical analys and predictions for visualization In addition,, for decision makers, Bl can supply them with a visual presentation of an analysis of key management metrics that would normally be released as a standardized summary report. For managers in the field, Bl provides multidimensional analytical tool called OLAP with which can perform expert-level analyses they','',2,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 22:30:26','2025-02-19 22:30:26'),(2144,'875','App\\Models\\Subsection','Tables',NULL,'<Table 48  Types of Bl',2,'67b65b911544c.png','/storage/tables/67b65b911544c.png','2025-02-19 22:30:26','2025-02-19 22:30:41'),(2145,'875','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','The types of Bl can be explained by separating them into 3 following areas are Bl, which represents the and strategies of an enterprise, analysis Bl, which is about data-driven analysis Bl, and operational Bl, which is centered on the day-to-day operations of the personnel in charge of a specific operation: These types of Bl are summarized in detail as follows They goals','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 22:30:26','2025-02-19 22:30:26'),(2146,'876','App\\Models\\Subsection','Figures',NULL,'[Fig: 40] Example of Bl dashboard',2,'67b65b9120142.png','/storage/figures/67b65b9120142.png','2025-02-19 22:30:26','2025-02-19 22:30:41'),(2147,'876','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','The Bl dashboard is one of the most important elements of the Bl functions because it permits users to make intuitive judgments. This is a data visualization tool that displays in one glance the status of quantified metrics and performance metrics for an enterprise Through dashboards, metrics such as sales, costs, profits, and risk levels in various areas are presented on a single screen so as to help decision makers make quick decisions by making it easier for them to idontf  Lc arocc  LoCLCudpa clocc 3 tontion to key','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 22:30:26','2025-02-19 22:30:26'),(2148,'876','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','In general, the screen configuration of dashboards is easy to customize as it supports easy customization and easi integration with tools such as spreadsheets and real-time data analysis.','',3,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 22:30:26','2025-02-19 22:30:26'),(2149,'667','App\\Models\\Section','Figures',NULL,'[Fig: 41] Interrelationships of IT service management technologies',2,'67b65b912a16c.png','/storage/figures/67b65b912a16c.png','2025-02-19 22:30:26','2025-02-19 22:30:41'),(2150,'667','App\\Models\\Section','Text','IT service management is commonly referred to as ITSM ITSM is used as a systemized method of managing IT services and the quality of such services,','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 22:30:26','2025-02-19 22:30:26'),(2151,'667','App\\Models\\Section','Text','ITSM uses ITIL (IT infrastructure library) , which is the standard model (best practice) of the IT service Depending on the form of trade between companies, ITSM could be outsourced. An IT service can only be realized when a service level agreement (SLA) has been signed. The signed SLA becomes the standard for measuring the quality of the IT service, and systematic management of the IT service can be pursued SLM The customer service reauest (CSR) process is for reauesting an T service using ITSM uses the ITIL (IT infrastructure library), which is the standard model (best practice) of the IT service: Depending on the form of trade between companies, ITSM could be outsourced: In addition, an IT service can be only realized when a service level agreement (SLA) has been signed. The signed SLA becomes the standard and the baseline for measuring the quality of the IT service Therefore, it is important to establish and manage these standards Once the level of a service has been decided between the user and service supplier, the IT service is delivered at thae level User requests for IT senvices will be handled bv the CSR (Customer Service Request) nrocess level. User requests for IT services will be handled by the CSR (Customer Service Request) process. Some of the leading standards associated with IT service management include eSCM and ISOJIEC 20000. These standards are all rooted in ITIL, The eSCM (eSourcing Capability Model) is an international quality assessment model used by service providers to objectively evaluate quality ad capabilities in order to provide IT services to customers. It provides guidance on imnlomonting ITconiicoc at allnbacoc Of tho bucinocc ISOJIEC 20000 is an international standard which clearly defines the requirements for IT service managemen activities It was developed by modifying the BSISO00 certification of the BSI (British Standard Institute), the facto international standard and certification specification on IT service management','',3,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 22:30:26','2025-02-19 22:30:26'),(2152,'877','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','The IT Infrastructure Library (ITIL) is a guideline for IT management developed by the Central Computer & Telecommunications Agency (CCTA) of the UK for public agency users in the late 1980s. ITIL is an IT service management framework which is a compilation of the best practices in IT service management, and which provides standard guidelines for IT service management It also provides a process for clearly and transparently identifying the complex IT service framework so that enterprises can realize their business objectives','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 22:30:26','2025-02-19 22:30:26'),(2153,'878','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','ITIL is an intellectual property ad a registered trademark managed by the British government, but it is effectively used as a de-facto global standard for managing IT services Version 1: In the 1980s, the British government\'s CCTA developed a standard reference document to address its reliance on IT In this version, several books on the specialized field of IT services were collected and published: Version 2: the period 2000~2001, ITIL version 2 was announced and an ITIL v2 glossary was published. Version 3: Version 3 was anounced in 2007 by the OGC, an organization under Her Majestys Treasury, and is known as the ITIL 2007 edition In July 2011, ITIL 2011 was published as an improved version of ITIL 2007. Cinco  bon  ko Wnonbin Cf bachelonced   ko Dritick CTOonanao During','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 22:30:26','2025-02-19 22:30:26'),(2154,'879','App\\Models\\Subsection','Tables',NULL,'',3,'67b65b9138469.png','/storage/tables/67b65b9138469.png','2025-02-19 22:30:26','2025-02-19 22:30:41'),(2155,'879','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','The component elements of ITIL v2 are service delivery and service support key','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 22:30:26','2025-02-19 22:30:26'),(2156,'879','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','Besides the two areas mentioned above, there is also the Business Perspective area, which deals with business continuity management and partnership outsourcing, and ICT Infrastructure Management, which deals with network service management and operations management, computer installation and accessibility, and system management','',4,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 22:30:26','2025-02-19 22:30:26'),(2157,'880','App\\Models\\Subsection','Tables',NULL,'<Table 50  ITIL v3 process',4,'67b65b9152843.png','/storage/tables/67b65b9152843.png','2025-02-19 22:30:26','2025-02-19 22:30:41'),(2158,'880','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','ITIL v3 was born as a business value model from ITIL v2. It supports IT governance (lacking in ITIL v2), and extend service management to all areas of a business. (NOTE: In the box above, capitalization of names is inconsistent, eg Carnegie Mellon University)','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 22:30:26','2025-02-19 22:30:26'),(2159,'880','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','ITIL v3 strengthens the service support area and service delivery area of v2 and includes the Requirement Process of ISOJIECZOOOO. The of v3 are to formulate strategies for alignment with business through a lifecycle perspective goals , and to improve the IT service life cycle','',3,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 22:30:26','2025-02-19 22:30:26'),(2160,'880','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','ITIL v3 consists of 5 process areas This 5-step process of continuous service improvement (Service Strategy Service Design Service Implementation Service Operations) is a continuous, repeated cycle. In particular the performance evaluation (ROI) area was strengthened in ITIL v3 because it was deficient in v2 By reflecting the performance results back into service strategy, ITIL v3 further strengthens the IT service capabilities of an enterprise','',5,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 22:30:26','2025-02-19 22:30:26'),(2161,'881','App\\Models\\Subsection','Tables',NULL,'<Table 51  Comparison of ITIL v2 and v3',1,'67b65b91671bb.png','/storage/tables/67b65b91671bb.png','2025-02-19 22:30:26','2025-02-19 22:30:41'),(2162,'669','App\\Models\\Section','Figures',NULL,'',2,'67b65b9173069.png','/storage/figures/67b65b9173069.png','2025-02-19 22:30:26','2025-02-19 22:30:41'),(2163,'669','App\\Models\\Section','Figures',NULL,'[Fig: 43] Chart showing the flow between SLA and SLM',3,'67b65b917b513.png','/storage/figures/67b65b917b513.png','2025-02-19 22:30:26','2025-02-19 22:30:41'),(2164,'669','App\\Models\\Section','Text','The quality-of-service issue between a company that supplies IT services and its customers can become a sensitive subject during the servicing Therefore, there is a need for clear guidelines on the level of service between the party supplying an IT service and the party using that service The agreement between a IT service provider and its customers on the scope, item, form, performance, measurement methods, and price of the provided service is called the SLA The framework for continuously monitoring ad changinglmanaging the SLA (Service Level Agreement) is called SLM (Service Level Management): period,','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 22:30:26','2025-02-19 22:30:26'),(2165,'882','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','Seamless communication: Used as a communication tool between consumers and of services Prevention of conflicts: Narrows the expectation gap (vs reality) for service levels ad the foundation for resolving the gap. Objective evaluation: An objective and quantitative evaluation of service quality is possible Continuous control: Provides a control system for managing services suppliers lays','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 22:30:26','2025-02-19 22:30:26'),(2166,'883','App\\Models\\Subsection','Tables',NULL,'<Table 53  Examples of SLA metrics',4,'67b65b918d4b5.png','/storage/tables/67b65b918d4b5.png','2025-02-19 22:30:26','2025-02-19 22:30:41'),(2167,'883','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','An SLA sets the service target levels for service level management metrics, provides performance measureme standards for the objectives of the service, and has a for reporting service levels. system','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 22:30:26','2025-02-19 22:30:26'),(2168,'883','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','ome examples of metrics defined in the SLA are shown in the table below In particular the items described usir netrics are also called \"service level items\" or \"configuration items\" (Cl):','',3,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 22:30:26','2025-02-19 22:30:26'),(2169,'670','App\\Models\\Section','Text','Statement of Work (SOW) is a work statement that specifies the details of a service or the work described in the SLA that must be performed. It is also used in project management as a work statement that describes the requirements of the project','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 22:30:26','2025-02-19 22:30:26'),(2170,'671','App\\Models\\Section','Figures',NULL,'',2,'67b65b919fcd9.png','/storage/figures/67b65b919fcd9.png','2025-02-19 22:30:26','2025-02-19 22:30:41'),(2171,'671','App\\Models\\Section','Text','SLM (Service Level Management) is one of the core processes of ITIL, The use of SLM ensures that the level of service quality agreed upon with the customers can be delivered and that the process for increasing customer confidence and improving service levels can be managed','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 22:30:26','2025-02-19 22:30:26'),(2172,'672','App\\Models\\Section','Tables',NULL,'<Table 54  Component elements of SLM',2,'67b65b91ac8c9.png','/storage/tables/67b65b91ac8c9.png','2025-02-19 22:30:26','2025-02-19 22:30:41'),(2173,'672','App\\Models\\Section','Text','SLM provides the ability to manage service level objectives (SLO) , which are the contents of an SLA and to notify an enterprise of any infringements of the SLA  Therefore, the implementation of SLM is essential for managing the IT service levels:','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 22:30:26','2025-02-19 22:30:26'),(2174,'672','App\\Models\\Section','Text','When operating SLAs and SLMs, the evaluation criteria for established service levels must be specific, quantitative, and objective The evaluation criteria must be verified, and seamless setting of the baseline and smooth management of any changes must be ensured . In addition, the responsibilities under each item should be clearly specified in anticipation of potential disputes. In this regard, the use of a automated and reliable management tool for managing the service level can be of great assistance when executing tasks.','',3,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 22:30:26','2025-02-19 22:30:26'),(2175,'673','App\\Models\\Section','Text','Financial performance evaluations are done using financial indicators the traditional performance evaluation metrics_ They are also called \"quantitative performance evaluations\" because use a common unit called \"currency\" , and can evaluate products or services with different characteristics in quantitative terms. they The reason why financial performance evaluations are used is because the shareholders and managers of companies are more interested in the financial results than in the specific production process involved in producing the results, and, with the financial indicators, it is easy to understand the management situation in one glance Financial indicators have a strong result-oriented nature and tend to ignore the process involved in attaining the results For this reason, financial indicators are not great boosters of employees\' motivation. Because financial indicators are abstract accounting figures it is difficult to accurately convey their meanings to all the members of an organization','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 22:30:27','2025-02-19 22:30:27'),(2176,'674','App\\Models\\Section','Tables',NULL,'Table 55  Types of financial performance evaluation techniques',2,'67b65b91bbaa7.png','/storage/tables/67b65b91bbaa7.png','2025-02-19 22:30:27','2025-02-19 22:30:41'),(2177,'674','App\\Models\\Section','Text','Some of the most well-known techniques for evaluating the financial performance of an enterprise include return on investments (ROI), net present value (NPV)  internal rate of retumn (IRR), and payback period (PP): These financial performance evaluations can be used to evaluate performance for both a specific period of time ad a specific point in time','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 22:30:27','2025-02-19 22:30:27'),(2178,'675','App\\Models\\Section','Tables',NULL,'',3,'67b65b91cd16d.png','/storage/tables/67b65b91cd16d.png','2025-02-19 22:30:27','2025-02-19 22:30:41'),(2179,'675','App\\Models\\Section','Text','The balanced performance evaluation technique is referred to as BSC (Balanced Score Card) BSC is a technique for managing balanced performance by evaluating not only financial performances but also non-financial performances It was introduced to the world by Harvard Business School Professor Robert Kaplan and consultant David Norton in 1992 in the Harvard Business Review: The traditional performance management system is so restricted to financial indicators that enterprises experience difficulties in executing their strategies in a systematic manner This has raised the need to consider non-financial evaluations BSC is utilized as a tool for maintaining  a balance between indicators, for the concretization and of strategies, and for communication within the organization. linking','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 22:30:27','2025-02-19 22:30:27'),(2180,'676','App\\Models\\Section','Tables',NULL,'<Table 57  Component elements of BSC',2,'67b65b91d8db6.png','/storage/tables/67b65b91d8db6.png','2025-02-19 22:30:27','2025-02-19 22:30:41'),(2181,'676','App\\Models\\Section','Text','In BSC, performance is evaluated from four different perspectives It contains elements for managing enterprise goals and elements for ensuring that the are met. A balanced performance evaluation is possible with BSC goals','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 22:30:27','2025-02-19 22:30:27'),(2182,'677','App\\Models\\Section','Tables',NULL,'<Table 58  Description of the 4 BSC perspectives',4,'67b65b91e4546.png','/storage/tables/67b65b91e4546.png','2025-02-19 22:30:27','2025-02-19 22:30:41'),(2183,'677','App\\Models\\Section','Figures',NULL,'[Fig: 45] Four perspectives of BSC',2,'67b65b91ee7c4.png','/storage/figures/67b65b91ee7c4.png','2025-02-19 22:30:27','2025-02-19 22:30:41'),(2184,'677','App\\Models\\Section','Text','The BSC is composed of four perspectives: Financial, Customer, Process, and Learing & Growth The BSC manages hotb financial and non-financialviowic','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 22:30:27','2025-02-19 22:30:27'),(2185,'677','App\\Models\\Section','Text','The four perspectives are managed in organically interconnected relationships. For example, i) new product development is managed from a learning and growth perspective, () product quality and production efficiency improvements are managed from an internal process perspective, (i) customer satisfaction and delivery time compliance are managed from a customer perspective, and (iv) shareholder dividend income is managed from a financial perspective','',3,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 22:30:27','2025-02-19 22:30:27'),(2186,'678','App\\Models\\Section','Text','IT-BSC (IT-Balanced Score Card) is a performance management tool that helps enterprises to achieve their goals by introducing the concept of BSC in the evaluation of investment performance in the IT sector The growing importance of IT in corporate activities has led enterprises to recognize the need for a method of systematically evaluating IT investments. With the traditional finance-based investment evaluation technique, it is difficult to quantify intangible IT investments, and hence enterprises have rushed to adopt IT-BSC','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 22:30:27','2025-02-19 22:30:27'),(2187,'679','App\\Models\\Section','Tables',NULL,'<Table 59  BSC link structure of IT-BASC as seen from different perspective',3,'67b65b9205014.png','/storage/tables/67b65b9205014.png','2025-02-19 22:30:27','2025-02-19 22:30:42'),(2188,'679','App\\Models\\Section','Figures',NULL,'[Fig: 46] 4 perspectives of IT-BSC',1,'67b65b920ef8a.png','/storage/figures/67b65b920ef8a.png','2025-02-19 22:30:27','2025-02-19 22:30:42'),(2189,'679','App\\Models\\Section','Text','IT-BSC has four perspectives as its constituent elements, and are linked to the enterprise BSC. That is, causal they relationships exist among the indicators within a structure where results are shared. IT-BSC and BSC not only hel managers to make decisions, but also provide a balanced view of performance evaluation in the IT sector because are ultimately linked to the financial indicators they','',2,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 22:30:27','2025-02-19 22:30:27'),(2190,'680','App\\Models\\Section','Text','KPI stands for performance indicator and is a quantifiable indicator that contains the critical success factor (CSF) of an organization The KPI is used to measure the achievement of a goal. Therefore, KPIs must accurately reflect the of the organization and must be selected from among the elements that are critical to realizing those goals. KPIs are the factors (means or determinants) that could determine victory in competition as well as the factors (ends or results) related to the success of the selected strategy: Generally set by the organization and its employees, KPIs are important indicators that are widely used in performance evaluations Therefore, depending on which KPIs are selected, the emplovees could start behaving differently at work key  goals they','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 22:30:27','2025-02-19 22:30:27'),(2191,'681','App\\Models\\Section','Tables',NULL,'<Table 60  KPI establishment procedure',2,'67b65b921f6a4.png','/storage/tables/67b65b921f6a4.png','2025-02-19 22:30:27','2025-02-19 22:30:42'),(2192,'681','App\\Models\\Section','Text','The right KPIs should be compatible with the vision and objectives of the organization, should function as strategic drivers, and should allow the members of the organization to move forward in accordance with the same purpose and strategy: Therefore, KPIs should be able to provide guidance for the entire organization, and should not be limited to specific areas. The derived KPIs should be made to match the strategy and of the organization after undergoing validation process goals','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 22:30:27','2025-02-19 22:30:27'),(2193,'884','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','KPIs should be kept separate from legacy processes ad instituted as an internal process that could lead to the bes performance from the organization as a whole The task of managing the KPIs should not be delegated to a tas force composed of middle-level managers, rather, it should be the responsibility of the top management, who mus make sure the strategic vision of the organization, is reflected in the KPIs.','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 22:30:27','2025-02-19 22:30:27'),(2194,'885','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','Even a set of KPIs from a great company is of no use to aother enterprise because the and strategies are different for each enterprise Therefore, an enterprise must develop its own KPI which matches its strategies goals','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 22:30:27','2025-02-19 22:30:27'),(2195,'886','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','Starting with a balanced set of KPIs, the KPIs should be derived in gradual steps so as to allow them to evolve a mature set of KPIs. It must be possible to modify a set of KPIs in order to allow enterprises to respond promptly to changes in the business environment into','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 22:30:27','2025-02-19 22:30:27'),(2196,'683','App\\Models\\Section','Text','BO (Management by Objective) is a system for managing the of an organization MBO is also a busines= anagement technique for setting and controllinglmanaging the to meeting those for the purpos improving individual performances and capabilities goals goals path goals MBO sets goals whose levels can be measured quantitatively by the employees through their own decision Because, in MBO, achievable goals are set in a bottom-up fashion, employee are not necessarily in full alignment with the enterprise goals. However, employees finalize their through discussions with their supervisors Therefore, when individual employees do meet their individual goals, this can have a sufficiently positive effect on how close the enterprise comes to reaching its corporate goals goals goals','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 22:30:27','2025-02-19 22:30:27'),(2197,'684','App\\Models\\Section','Tables',NULL,'<Table 61  Main reasons why enterprises are adopting MBO',2,'67b65b922d1cc.png','/storage/tables/67b65b922d1cc.png','2025-02-19 22:30:27','2025-02-19 22:30:42'),(2198,'684','App\\Models\\Section','Text','MBO begins with a clear understanding of an enterprise s objectives and makes each individual responsible fc meeting their own individual goals Also, under the MBO system, efficient organization management can be secure since the members of the organization work hard to achieve their respective _ goals.','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 22:30:27','2025-02-19 22:30:27'),(2199,'684','App\\Models\\Section','Text','However, the goals set by MBO will likely not align with the goals of the enterprise if the enterprise does not set the of MBO or provide ay guidelines Consequently, the have to be revised through a separate discussion process In addition, special care must be taken when adopting MBO, because if the goals of individual employees conflict with each other, it could lead to serious disputes goals goals','',3,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 22:30:27','2025-02-19 22:30:27'),(2200,'685','App\\Models\\Section','Tables',NULL,'',3,'67b65b92391ef.png','/storage/tables/67b65b92391ef.png','2025-02-19 22:30:27','2025-02-19 22:30:42'),(2201,'685','App\\Models\\Section','Text','From the very goal setting stage, MBO encourages the participation of supervisors and subordinates. Therefore, the MBO approach works interactively to align the goals with the enterprise strategies In addition, continuous feedback in the form of evaluations and encouragement is needed to align the MBO of employees to the of the enterprise goals','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 22:30:27','2025-02-19 22:30:27'),(2202,'887','App\\Models\\Subsection','Figures',NULL,'',1,'67b65b924466a.png','/storage/figures/67b65b924466a.png','2025-02-19 22:30:28','2025-02-19 22:30:42'),(2203,'887','App\\Models\\Subsection','Figures',NULL,'',2,'67b65b924e6c2.png','/storage/figures/67b65b924e6c2.png','2025-02-19 22:30:28','2025-02-19 22:30:42'),(2204,'888','App\\Models\\Subsection','Figures',NULL,'48] Business environment transformations and trends [Fig',2,'67b65b925dbdd.png','/storage/figures/67b65b925dbdd.png','2025-02-19 22:30:28','2025-02-19 22:30:42'),(2205,'888','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','To respond to the ongoing transformation of the business environment, companies are diversifying their businesses to a competitive advantage in the market through new business models. Among the approaches that companies employ to develop new business models are specialization, modularization, scaling up, interationalization, and networking The rapid development of IT technology and the advent of the smart era are also driving the latest shifts gain To respond to the ongoing transformation of the business environment, companies are diversifying their businesses to gain & competitive advantage in the market through new business models. Among the approaches that companies employ to develop new business models are specialization, modularization, scaling up, interationalization, and networking The rapid development of IT technology and the advent of the smart era are also driving the latest shifts in the business paradigm. Changes in the internal and external environments surrounding corporate business activities are accelerating, manifesting themselves in the form of endlessly evolving IT, changes in consumption patterns, diversification of platforms, and increasing calls for innovation from companies The gradual blurring ad disappearance of business boundaries (occasioned by offline companies\' entry into the online market, the growth of mobile businesses, and the emergence of convergent businesses, etc )which previously guarded different areas of competition, have diversified business channels by, for instance, paving the way for the rise of the online market. Through the online market, enterprises have the opportunity to meet diverse customers and create new synergies In addition, new business concepts have emerged that reflect the latest consumption trends, such as SNS-based smart shopping ad the growth of one-person Internet companies and crowd sourcing: gained Customer-oriented marketing is becoming more popular and more free services are being offered to customers Furthermore, value-oriented businesses such as social work businesses that could support the sustainable busines= activities of companies are also growing','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 22:30:28','2025-02-19 22:30:28'),(2206,'888','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','The trend in business transformation brought about by the smart society is progressing rapidly: As such, enterprise should react proactively to this trend and work hard on strengthening their IT business capabilities s0 that cal provide a broader range of products and services they','',3,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 22:30:28','2025-02-19 22:30:28'),(2207,'687','App\\Models\\Section','Text','Many companies that have entered the global market are now experiencing difficulties because of the global economic downturn and low growth. As domestic growth slows and direct overseas investments increase, the costs that companies have to bear are increasing, while the corporate business environment is becoming ever more complicated due to the opening of markets and fluctuations in currency exchange rates. To overcome this situation, large companies are implementing a number of different strategies such as expanding global sourcing and entering the service industry in the case of manufacturing companies. long','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 22:30:28','2025-02-19 22:30:28'),(2208,'889','App\\Models\\Subsection','Tables',NULL,'',6,'67b65b9277c44.png','/storage/tables/67b65b9277c44.png','2025-02-19 22:30:28','2025-02-19 22:30:42'),(2209,'889','App\\Models\\Subsection','Figures',NULL,'[Fig: 49] Relationship between disruptive innovation and sustaining innovation',2,'67b65b9288fc6.png','/storage/figures/67b65b9288fc6.png','2025-02-19 22:30:28','2025-02-19 22:30:42'),(2210,'889','App\\Models\\Subsection','Code',NULL,'[Fig: 50] Disruptive innovation method',3,'67b65b9295672.png','/storage/code/67b65b9295672.png','2025-02-19 22:30:28','2025-02-19 22:30:42'),(2211,'889','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','Disruptive innovation is receiving a lot of attention as the solution to the persistent problem of slow growth and depression in the business market. Disruptive innovation is a technique for destroying existing markets ad creating new marketsIn essence, it consists in dominating the market with technological innovation/price destruction or in pursuing a business strategy aimed at beating the market leaders: Disruptive innovation is a innovation technology that can alter the hierarchy of competition in existing industries, have impacts on other industries, and produce new markets and businesses by changing consumer behaviors and ways of thinking, Disruptive innovation has the potential to surpass the performance of existing technologies in an instant, just like smartphones did when appeared in the late 2000s ad quickly revamped the existing mobile they pho JUI To understand disruptive innovation, one also has to understand the meaning of \"sustaining innovation\" . Sustaining innovation is the strategy of continuously improving existing products to satisfy and retain key customers in the market, with the of providing high value at a high price through gradual improvement: In contrast, disruptive innovation is the strategy of targeting niche markets by creating low-priced but good-quality products through simplified functions and enhanced convenience goal In other words, the market targeted by disruptive innovation is the overshot customer7 base. This market has emerged from the argument that there is a limit to the performance that customers are willing to use or accept. Overshot customers are not in favor of paying for high-end features that they do not need. There are two approaches to introducing disruptive innovation: low-end disruption and new market disruption: Low- end disruption is the strategy of entering the low-end market by resolving the product complaints of overshot customers and entering the market through low-priced products that perfectly match the satisfaction levels of the','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 22:30:28','2025-02-19 22:30:28'),(2212,'889','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','In new market disruption, enterprises target non-customers who consciously reject the products in the market or customers who are dissatisfied with existing products. By launching innovative new products that utilize new technologies, the enterprises try to build a presence in niche segments of the market dominated by existing leading e= In low-end disruptive innovation, enterprises target customers who have been overserved by leveraging a new process and by employing a financial approach By a combination of low margin and high utilization of resources, enterprises provide customers with discounted prices that are critical to succeeding in the business. In new market disruptive innovation, enterprises target non-consumers who previously could not afford to purchase a product or who had no access to the technology with low-feature products that are simple and convenient to use This is business model in which enterprises make money with loW-priced products that are mass produced in small volumes. The total takeover of the mobile phone market by smartphones is a great illustration of disruptive innovation at work The traditional industry shifted from a voice-centered industry to a data-serviced industry and hardware centered (i.e mobile terminal) industry to a platform-based market structure: In addition, if one examines the impact on other industry sectors, the high-performance functions installed in smartphones have obliterated the markets for conventional MP3, digital cameras, game consoles car navigation equipment, and tablet PCs Smartphones also created a variety of new markets and business models, including app stores, location-based using from Smartphones also created a variety of new markets and business models, including app stores, location-basec services, SNS, social commerce, social games, Big Data, and smart services Naturally, there have to be some core technologies for such disruptive innovations to occur Some of the latest technologies driving disruptive innovations that racantl attncted attontion include bave','',4,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 22:30:28','2025-02-19 22:30:28'),(2213,'889','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','Disruptive innovation can be leveraged as a strategy for overcoming the barriers to technological innovation and reshape future industries. Enterprises that are planning disruptive innovations must clearly specify the target technology and its area of application, and seek outside resources in order to lay the foundations for dominating market opportunities','',7,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 22:30:28','2025-02-19 22:30:28'),(2214,'890','App\\Models\\Subsection','Figures',NULL,'[Fig: 51] Crowdsourcing business model',2,'67b65b929efd1.png','/storage/figures/67b65b929efd1.png','2025-02-19 22:30:28','2025-02-19 22:30:42'),(2215,'890','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','As a composite word coined py combining crowa and outsourcing , crowasourcing IS the concept of opening up phases of an enterprise\'s operations to the participation of consumers and the general public alike If the activitie of an enterprise or its revenues improve, the revenue is shared with the participants With the recent developmer of SNS, companies have been using social networks a lot more, and crowdsourcing has traction as an activit that can generate ideas by exploiting the power of the masses using these new channels of communication with public Dell Computers succeeded in collecting 10,000 ideas during an 18-month period after starting a wher consumers could exchange business-related technologies directly: Like Dell, crowdsourcing allows an enterprise present some very creative ideas for solving a enterprise issue to a group of specialists. The enterprise can the receive help from the specialists, which can then translate into time or labor cost savings In recent years crowdsourcing services have begun to partner up with professional technology brokerage firms successfully complete diverse types of crowdsourcing, and, in the process, have begun to build an ecosyster with a positive virtuous cycling structure: gained blog they','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 22:30:28','2025-02-19 22:30:28'),(2216,'890','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','Furthermore, because it is so well coupled with information technology (IT), the rapid advancements in IT have made crowdsourcing one of the elements for success in business. By allowing consumers or the public to directly key participate in the manufacturing of products or the service delivery process, enterprises are creating better products and services The profits generated in this way are shared with the participants, while the enterprises themselves are able to obtain creative ideas potential future consumers at very little or no cost at all Therefore, through crowdsourcing, enterprises are able to acquire insights about consumers in a rapidly changing market, and, through the success of early adopters, can also ascertain the need for their products or services: For this reason, the utilization of crowdsourcing bv companies is expected to increase in the future from they','',3,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 22:30:28','2025-02-19 22:30:28'),(2217,'891','App\\Models\\Subsection','Tables',NULL,'',2,'67b65b92aad6b.png','/storage/tables/67b65b92aad6b.png','2025-02-19 22:30:28','2025-02-19 22:30:42'),(2218,'891','App\\Models\\Subsection','Figures',NULL,'',3,'67b65b92b72fa.png','/storage/figures/67b65b92b72fa.png','2025-02-19 22:30:28','2025-02-19 22:30:42'),(2219,'891','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','Open innovation is a method of enterprise innovation. During the research and development and productizatior processes, an enterprise can open up the whole process and invite outside experts to share their ideas anc knowledge: Through this form of sharing enterprises hope to reduce costs and increase the likelihood of success the past, enterprises approached R&D activities more as a opportunity to augment and boost the efficiencies their R&D manpower and their technological prowess, rather than as a chance to cooperate with outside parties fact, enterprises kept the lid on the output of their development activities firmly sealed This kind of corporate activity had its limitations when it came to responding to the rapidly changing marke environment, and it became more difficult to launch products on time and satisfy the changing needs of consumers In traditional R&D, the size of investments grew year by year but the chance of succeeding was small and the risk borne by enterprises wereon an upward trend. In order to address these problems, enterprises began to activel explore the option of developing new products or services in collaboration with outside experts, institutions anc organizations that held the required core capabilities Today, the sources of technology development (venture companies, SMEs, research institutes, and universities) have become even more diverse and the scope of potential technologies has expanded, and the development of networ) infrastructures has led to an era in which business connections with the outside world can create ever greater value Thus, enterprise improvements triggered from the outside are accelerating more than ever before:','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 22:30:28','2025-02-19 22:30:28'),(2220,'689','App\\Models\\Section','Text','Open innovation can be divided into inward open innovation and outward open innovation: In inward open innovation, an enterprise obtains know-how or ideas an outside company, research center or university during the course of researching, developing  and commercializing a specific item. In outward open innovation, a company sends its knowledge or ideas to the outside world in order to commercialize them through other business models. There are six main forms of inward open innovation: technology purchase joint research, sub-contracted research, establishment of a joint venture, venture investment, and acquisition As for outward open innovation, technology sale and spin-off are its two main forms, With the rapid advances made in IT technology, convergence as a trend is gaining momentum and the pace of development of new products through convergence has become much faster than before, making it difficult for companies to keep up with the pace of market changes simply by dint of their own R&D efforts. Open innovation capability as a means of strengthening innovation capability in the face of structural transformation of technology and business management is expected to have a huge impact on the growth of companies in the coming years. from','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 22:30:28','2025-02-19 22:30:28'),(2221,'892','App\\Models\\Subsection','Tables',NULL,'',4,'67b65b92cf445.png','/storage/tables/67b65b92cf445.png','2025-02-19 22:30:28','2025-02-19 22:30:42'),(2222,'892','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','A platform is a basic structure commonly used to produce or sell various products. as competition among corporate ecosystems in the business market intensifies the platform is increasingly viewed as a strategy for securing a competitive edge using one s enterprise ecosystem. This signifies that as and services become ever more complex and the network effects between suppliers and consumers increase, the pattern of competition is changing from competition between companies to competition between corporate ecosystems The platform is the foundation for creating and delivering values to the participating companies, ad its role as a medium can determine the fate of the enterprise eco-system. The main functions of a business platform are described below: Today, being key goods','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 22:30:28','2025-02-19 22:30:28'),(2223,'892','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','The importance of the platform is clearly illustrated by the examples of Apple and Nokia. Although Nokia entered the smartphone market earlier than Apple, its platform was edged out of the market by competition with Apple Symbian, Nokia\'s operating system, had a very complex development environment because it was geared for the enterprise market and focused on enterprise application It failed to become a standard because the entry barriers to developers were too high: However, in the case of Apple, it emphasized the entertainment functions of the iOS and built an online contents-centered ecosystem (App Store) which attracted the participation of numerous developers In other words, the platform became a medium that connected and complemented the values produced by stakeholders As shown in the figure below, the business platforms that companies build to a business competitive edge can be classified into three categories: product platforms, customer platforms,, and trading platforms, gain','',3,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 22:30:28','2025-02-19 22:30:28'),(2224,'892','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','The product platform is a platform of the common parts used in the production of a final product  The purpose of such a platform is to reduce costs The customer platform is the core customer group targeted by a company from which more can be made: Finally, the trading platform is an infrastructure that supports a trading relationship with external suppliers. Through customer entrenchment ad cooperative relationships, an enterprise can become leading player in the market by leveragingits trading platform Many companies try to create various business models and build a stable business ecosystem based on their own platforms. As a result, it is reasonable to predict that the business model will expand and the size of the platform market continue to grow in the future, and that it could in fact see accelerated growth profits','',5,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 22:30:28','2025-02-19 22:30:28'),(2225,'893','App\\Models\\Subsection','Figures',NULL,'[Fig 54] API value chain',2,'67b65b92e10e5.png','/storage/figures/67b65b92e10e5.png','2025-02-19 22:30:28','2025-02-19 22:30:42'),(2226,'893','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','A company may disclose its internal business assets or services to a third party in the form of an application programming interface or API and create additional business values through the production of new assets and consumptions The series of activities involved in this effort are collectively called \"the API economy\" . In an age when API open data constitute a new form of business, if companies wish to respond effectively to market demands, must be able to apply assemblable business models in all channels and improve their operational and business agility This means that the APIs can provide an environment (platform-neutral environment) where various they applications can be connected As the characteristics ad purchasing patterns of customers who seek and pay goods using their smartphones are accumulated, are released through the API and all the member companie get to jointly use the marketing data collected by each of the other members they App developers will also be able to utilize the API open data as a business asset to build new applications and provide variety of customized services to consumers Since 2010, E Trade has been providing its stock trading service to partner companies through an API. Its partner companies have been able to sell, order or view a portfolio on behalf of itc Cuctomerc In addition, E Trade has made it possible for its customers to use the companys service without requiring them to visit its website. Through this strategy, E Trade has elevated the quality of its service and is providing it very stably: In the United States, IT companies such as Amazon, Twitter and Google are also generating revenue by releasing their data and services through APIs. By sharing their APIs (their core assets) through their respective business ecosystems, these companies are able to maximize their internallexternal efficiencies and raise expectations of new revenue generation But the task of developing and managing APIs is not easy and even after APIs are released, essential management tasks such as account management, authentication, and security management have to be taken care of Since the number and diversity of APIs released by companies are increasing every year, systemized management of APIs is something that companies are being called upon to commit to.','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 22:30:28','2025-02-19 22:30:28'),(2227,'893','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','The API value chain must be understood before API can be used as a business model. In other words, enterprise dat and services are released through APIs, and third-party developers create innovative applications by using the ope API. Companies that provide APIs must also understand the requirements of third-party developers who use APE directly and the even the needs of the application users Internally, an enterprise must have a system in place for monitoring and managing the released APIAn enterprise should also be able to provide formal documents or websites where developers can contact each other s0 that exteral developers can easily understand and use the APIs. In an era when mobile devices ranging from smartphones to tablets and smart watches are deeply embedded in daily lives, companies should be able to manage different forms of customer contact points through strategic A management','',3,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 22:30:28','2025-02-19 22:30:28'),(2228,'894','App\\Models\\Subsection','Tables',NULL,'<Table 66 Examples of convergent products and services of major companies8',4,'67b65b92f0b87.png','/storage/tables/67b65b92f0b87.png','2025-02-19 22:30:28','2025-02-19 22:30:42'),(2229,'894','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','The term \'servitization\" refers to a fundamental transformation of the business model in which a product evolves into a service bundle that continues to deliver value throughout the lifecycle of a customer experience. This means that the system of competition has shifted to around service whose revenue generation potential is intimately tied to the availability, reliability ad performance of the companys assets. In particular, this phenomenon is expected to accelerate in the traditional manufacturing sector where revenues are generated from the sales of As the traditional product sales model gives way to a service model and as companies find it increasingly difficult to differentiate themselves on the merits of their products alone, many are striving to differentiate themselves through servitization, ie by combining their products with software The software model for the servitization of a product can be one of three types,as shown below: goods','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 22:30:28','2025-02-19 22:30:28'),(2230,'894','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','Many companies are strengthening their software convergence capabilities so as to be able to respond flexibly to the changing environment and secure a competitive edge in the market through servitization. Software convergence capabilities are becoming a factor in determining the value of products and corporate performance Many companies are converging their products &d software to optimize their business models ad respond to the rapidly changing consumer environment key','',3,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 22:30:28','2025-02-19 22:30:28'),(2231,'894','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','Source: KIET, New Growth Strategies of Major Industries in Korea through Servitization, 2008 Built a service ecosystem using iTunes, App Store Transformed itself from a facsimile manufacturer into a supplier of document management systems Acquired Health Watch in 2006 to venture into the healthcare service market Acquired 5.5 million customers through OnStar its subsidiary company which telematics services Through a GPS-based remote management system, Caterpillar provides a service for analyzing the status and history of excavator equipment, replacing parts, improving fuel efficiency, and monitoring illegal use Airport/road/parking operation services account for 56% of operating profits although only bring in 14% of the total revenues: supplies they','',5,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 22:30:28','2025-02-19 22:30:28'),(2232,'895','App\\Models\\Subsection','Tables',NULL,'',4,'67b65b930f26a.png','/storage/tables/67b65b930f26a.png','2025-02-19 22:30:30','2025-02-19 22:30:43'),(2233,'895','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','AlphaGo, the Al that beat one thousand years of human learning','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 22:30:30','2025-02-19 22:30:30'),(2234,'895','App\\Models\\Subsection','Header','Preview for practical business','',2,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 22:30:30','2025-02-19 22:30:30'),(2235,'895','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','The match pitting Lee Sedol (a Go player with the 9 \'dan\' rank) against AlphaGo\'s Deep Mind Challenge,, held from March 9 to 15,2016, was shocking event that showed how artificial intelligence could far surpass human learning ability The fact that AlphaGo defeated Lee Sedol, the world s No 1 player for more than a decade and also one of the strongest players in the world of Go since 2014, was a clear sign that artificial intelligence can overcome human learning skills that have evolved over many thousands of years.','',3,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 22:30:30','2025-02-19 22:30:30'),(2236,'896','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','Typically, a separate program must be installed when a person wants to use a particular service or program on a smartphone or PC. Kakao Talk is a messenger program that is widely used in South Korea and exists in different versions for PC, Android and iOS. As such, a separate program must be installed for each type of OS in order to use Kakao Talk However if HTML5 is used, there is no need to install a separate program, and Kakao Talk can be accessed directly through the web browser Furthermore, word processors and games can be used without having to inctall witb the heln of HtM 5 leading The HTMLS standard is a next generation HTML standard that overcomes the limitations of previous HTML standards, allowing rich web applications such as video, voice, and 2D graphics, without requiring a separate plug-in and Active X control were very popular as solutions for overcoming the limitations of the previous HTML: However, each came with its own set of problems, which could only be overcome through functional expansion and combination through the advanced CSS3 and JavaScript APIs. Plug-! -ins HTML5 was designed around the principles of compatibility, practicality, interoperability, and universal access. The contents of the HTML standard cover the document structure, markup standards, and API standards When the semantic markup part and the API part of the HTML 5 standard are examined separately, 26 new markups have been added to the semantic markup to enable much clearer semantic representation than conventional HTML4. HTMLS allows various services or applications based on web content, such as search engines, to provide improved functionality In the case of APIs, new functions such as web form, canvas, and web socket were added to support the development of web-based applications. HTML5 uses much less JavaScript code than HTML4 to support the same functionality, making it easier to use in mobile environments where network speed is a sensitive factor Recently, a growing number of cases have arisen in which corporate business solutions are transitioning to an HTML5-based environment so as to maximize scalability and efficiency: part','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 22:30:30','2025-02-19 22:30:30'),(2237,'897','App\\Models\\Subsection','Figures',NULL,'[Fig 55] The responsive web can configure the same contents in different ways.',2,'67b65b9319e65.png','/storage/figures/67b65b9319e65.png','2025-02-19 22:30:30','2025-02-19 22:30:43');
INSERT INTO `contents` VALUES (2238,'897','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','With the growing use of mobile devices such as tablet PCs and smartphones, interest in the mobile web is also increasing Users want to enjoy the same web contents at the same level of quality, irrespective of the type of mobile device or PC being used. However, it was not easy to provide the same quality of service for different environments resulting from different mobile phone specifications and the restrictions that come with different mobile phone screen sizes It is also impossible to develop a web that is optimized for all types of mobile devices The responsive web emerged as one approach to solving this conundrum, The responsive web is an approach to web design that results in the most optimal user environment, i.e. one that meets the requirements of many different devices from desktops through monitors to mobile phones In other words it is a web whose size changes to fit ay device environment, making it easy for users to read the contents With the recent trend towards carrying mobile devices as the primary or first device, the number of mobile wel users has grown to exceed the number of regular Internet web users Web designers have responded by minimizing unnecessary elements of regular web pages for the sake of improving the screen size, network speed and quality, and the user mode of the mobile devices (the common limitations of the mobile environment), that is, have begun to focus more on the functions that should be provided on the mobile web. While responsive webs typically focus on how changes in layout ad style take place from one device to another, there also exist responsive webs that reconfigure web contents strictly from a mobile first perspective. they','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 22:30:30','2025-02-19 22:30:30'),(2239,'897','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','In addition to the responsive web, adaptive web technology is attracting a lot of interest as a technology that enables websites to provide a seamless transition of information for different screen sizes The adaptive web is a server- based or client-based technology that checks the device that is trying to access the web By using images tailored for the device of the user, the adaptive web allows website access on a mobile device at high speeds','',3,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 22:30:30','2025-02-19 22:30:30'),(2240,'898','App\\Models\\Subsection','Tables',NULL,'Table 67 Application areas of semantic web',2,'67b65b932349e.png','/storage/tables/67b65b932349e.png','2025-02-19 22:30:30','2025-02-19 22:30:43'),(2241,'898','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','Web that enables intelligent data processing and the accumulation of knowledge through the defining ad building of structured data (ontology) and data among the structured data is called semantic web: The web, which only displays web documents in HTML language, has severe limitations in expressing resources, and the relationship between web documents is defined. Hence computers cannot understand semantic. Since there are problems in recognizing all objects with just URL alone, semantic web was developed as a way to efficiently use information from distributed webs, extract meaningful data from flood of information,, and as a means for structuring and interpreting the amounts of data produced on the web linking huge','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 22:30:30','2025-02-19 22:30:30'),(2242,'899','App\\Models\\Subsection','Tables',NULL,'<Table68  Main functions of SNS',2,'67b65b933204a.png','/storage/tables/67b65b933204a.png','2025-02-19 22:30:30','2025-02-19 22:30:43'),(2243,'899','App\\Models\\Subsection','Code',NULL,'',4,'67b65b933ca64.png','/storage/code/67b65b933ca64.png','2025-02-19 22:30:30','2025-02-19 22:30:43'),(2244,'899','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','Social Network Service (SNS) refers to a service that helps people continue their personal relationships online or tc establish new relationships Early SNSs began in the form of online communities on websites, such as The Well which began in 1985, and \"Theglobcom,\" which started in 1994. These are the first examples of SNS that provide services in the form of early communities','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 22:30:30','2025-02-19 22:30:30'),(2245,'899','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','Facebook, the global SNS site with the largest number of users, has about 2 billion (September, 2017) monthly users_ WhatsApp,, another global SNS site, has acquired about 1.3 billion users.','',3,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 22:30:30','2025-02-19 22:30:30'),(2246,'899','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','[Fig 56] Number SNS users each month (as of September 2017, units: million peop igures for the sites marked with  were not updated for the past 1 ye','',5,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 22:30:30','2025-02-19 22:30:30'),(2247,'900','App\\Models\\Subsection','Tables',NULL,'<Table 70  Examples of REST API Method',4,'67b65b9345de2.png','/storage/tables/67b65b9345de2.png','2025-02-19 22:30:30','2025-02-19 22:30:43'),(2248,'900','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','Open API is a free public API that is free for use by anyone including users and developers By using the API providec to the free of charge by websites, users are no longer confined to receiving ad consuming services. car now develop their own service and use them: public They Cllal aclenislcs ui Open AFi Using the open API, people can gain access to the functions of a website New service can be designed by connecting several APIs. factor in the emergence of mashup sites? People who were just users of a service can become service providers Key','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 22:30:30','2025-02-19 22:30:30'),(2249,'900','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','(cpesciluliuniui OluCC cnsic / REST API is currently the most widely used Open API. REST API is a network-based architecture published in 2000 by Fielding, one of HTTPs leading authors, to properly utilize the superiority of the Web (HTTP) REST is a web service architecture based on the Resource Oriented Architecture (ROA) and it is composed of HTTP URI HTTP Method. HTTP URI is used to specify the target resource, and the designation of actions for that resource utilizes the HTTP Method Roy','',3,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 22:30:30','2025-02-19 22:30:30'),(2250,'901','App\\Models\\Subsection','Tables',NULL,'<Table71  Network based location determination technolog)',2,'67b65b9352ca2.png','/storage/tables/67b65b9352ca2.png','2025-02-19 22:30:30','2025-02-19 22:30:43'),(2251,'901','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','Location-based services are growing together with the smartphone market, which has seen exponential growth since 2010, and are evolving into a broad category of services by merging location information, commerce, and entertainment Due to the mobile Big Bang, the availability of location detection capable devices greatly increased and the location determination platform became open: This led to the rapid evolution of location-based services (LBS) In the case of location detection mechanism used in smartphones location detection technologies like base stations Cell-ID, GPS, and Wi-Fi were combined with motion sensor-based precision navigation. Furthermore, by adopting maps like Google Map and Apple location-based services began to be used for many general purposes guess Map, 9 Mashup site ~Websites that use APIs for product information, map information, etc from Microsoft, Google, Yahoo, Amazon, ad others and combines them with their own user interfaces to come up with new services These technologies in combination with services such as social network services, augmented reality, mobile games, and advertising, are boosting the utilization of the services Network-based location detection technologies include the following:','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 22:30:30','2025-02-19 22:30:30'),(2252,'901','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','With the advancements in IT technology ad mobile communication technology, the technique of location determination has also evolved. In the 2G era, location determination was based on the principle of simple cell-based positioning But for 3G location determination, the Global Positioning System (GPS) was adopted In the 4G era, location determination has become highly precise with very narrow error margins because the technology has greatly improved the high error margins that had been the weakness of base stations and the difficulty of determining positions in indoor areas and areas with many impediments to GPS. And wherever an access (AP) exists, location determination has become possible with Wi-Fi, point','',3,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 22:30:30','2025-02-19 22:30:30'),(2253,'902','App\\Models\\Subsection','Tables',NULL,'<Table73  Key technologies of mobile commerce',3,'67b65b9364f98.png','/storage/tables/67b65b9364f98.png','2025-02-19 22:30:30','2025-02-19 22:30:43'),(2254,'902','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','Mobile technology can be characterized by 3 words: \"Anytime\", \"Anywhere\", and Device\". It is these characteristics which has made mobile technology the essential backbone of mobile businesses from mobile based commerce to mobile based entertainment, communication, search, and location information Mobile commerce is mobile business that utilizes mobile devices like smartphones, tablets, and smart for trading goods, services, and information \'Any pads','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 22:30:30','2025-02-19 22:30:30'),(2255,'903','App\\Models\\Subsection','Tables',NULL,'<Table 74  Component elements of MEAP',4,'67b65b93750fd.png','/storage/tables/67b65b93750fd.png','2025-02-19 22:30:30','2025-02-19 22:30:43'),(2256,'903','App\\Models\\Subsection','Figures',NULL,'',2,'67b65b9383059.png','/storage/figures/67b65b9383059.png','2025-02-19 22:30:30','2025-02-19 22:30:43'),(2257,'903','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','Mobile Enterprise Application Platform (MEAP) is a platform that can support a wide range of different device environments and permit the sharing and the reuse of applications The main reasons behind the need for MEAP are reuse and cost savings. Allows the same code to be reused for different smartphone OS/smartphone HWIservice provider environments Through the sharing of a common platform, companies can save money that would others have to be spent on duplicate infrastructure and middleware required for services Support for developing the mobile screens for different types of devices.','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 22:30:30','2025-02-19 22:30:30'),(2258,'903','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','comporiells ui IVICAF MEAP covers the entire life cycle from mobile development to execution and operation: It is composed of a integrated development environment (IDE), an execution environment framework that acts a middleware, standard interface for integrating with legacy system, and a mobile device management (MDM) for device management and security:','',3,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 22:30:30','2025-02-19 22:30:30'),(2259,'904','App\\Models\\Subsection','Tables',NULL,'<Table76  Component elements of MDM and roles',4,'67b65b9394151.png','/storage/tables/67b65b9394151.png','2025-02-19 22:30:30','2025-02-19 22:30:43'),(2260,'904','App\\Models\\Subsection','Figures',NULL,'58] Configuration of MDM [Fig',3,'67b65b93a1223.png','/storage/figures/67b65b93a1223.png','2025-02-19 22:30:30','2025-02-19 22:30:43'),(2261,'904','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','IDM is a solution for efficiently managing all the diverse mobile devices and applications used in enterpris perations It is a system that can be used to manage mobile devices anytime, anywhere through over-the-air (OT, ansmissions (although the device must be in the power on state):','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 22:30:30','2025-02-19 22:30:30'),(2262,'904','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','MDM aeployment ettects By deploying MDM, enterprises will gain flexibility &nd expandability They will able to connect to diverse services, manage devices at PC level, ensure consistency in security, provide remote support easily, trouble shoot issues and provide OS/languagelsystem support','',5,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 22:30:30','2025-02-19 22:30:30'),(2263,'905','App\\Models\\Subsection','Figures',NULL,'[Fig: 59] Types of machine-to-machine services and market status',2,'67b65b93adba5.png','/storage/figures/67b65b93adba5.png','2025-02-19 22:30:30','2025-02-19 22:30:43'),(2264,'905','App\\Models\\Subsection','Figures',NULL,'[Fig.60] Component elements of MZM',4,'67b65b93bb27a.png','/storage/figures/67b65b93bb27a.png','2025-02-19 22:30:30','2025-02-19 22:30:43'),(2265,'905','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','Machine-to-Machine (MZM) refers to machine to machine communication MZM integrates information to network and platform to provide a service that monitors the status of objects, controls the situation and sends information about the status of objects to users Network communication networks are used to provide people or intelligent devices with information about objects or to let them control the objects Typical types of MZM services are described below:','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 22:30:30','2025-02-19 22:30:30'),(2266,'905','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','There are three reasons driving the spread of the infrastructure for MZM communication: The first reason is the expanding wireless networks The coverage of wireless networks and the guaranteed service stability greatly facilitated the growth of MZM communication The second reason is the declining prices and increasing availability of telecommunication modules. The telecommunication module market is growing at more than 30% per year but are gradually decreasing, ad market penetration is rapidly increasing: The third reason is the declining price of sensors As the market expands, sensor technology is getting more sophisticated, but prices are falling, allowing companies that provide sensing-based services at low cost: These sensors are expanding from simple monitoring to fault and accident detection, asset management, and customer usage management information. Furthermore, the applications of these sensors are becoming increasingly diverse Starting first with simple monitoring, sensors are now being used to detect malfunctions and accidents, manage assets, and extract data about customer usage levels Typically, the process of developing a MZM device first begins with developing a module that contains a mobile chipset: Then the device is developed using the module. An MZM device can be roughly designed as an object consisting of a chipset and a module and largely divided into three parts: a sensor/input&output unit, a data processing unit, and a communication module, prices','',3,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 22:30:30','2025-02-19 22:30:30'),(2267,'905','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','The data acquired through the input&output uniit is processed by the data processing unit before it is sent to the communication module RS-232 or USB is used when sending the data from the processing unit to the communication module The technology used in MZM communication defines the technology needed for services at the service layer and takes a typical top-down approach to design the the lower layer to follow the definition set by the service layer: However, this approach can disrupt the standardization and public sharing of the technology ad hinder the growth of the market Therefore, standardization of the MZM environment is a critical task for stimulating the growth of the market','',5,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 22:30:30','2025-02-19 22:30:30'),(2268,'906','App\\Models\\Subsection','Code',NULL,'',2,'67b65b93ca03b.png','/storage/code/67b65b93ca03b.png','2025-02-19 22:30:30','2025-02-19 22:30:43'),(2269,'906','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','The diffusion of MZM technology has opened wide the era of loT which creates an environment where communication takes place not only between objects but everything from people to objects, spaces are connected to the Internet to create, collect, share, and utilize information about everything: Unlike the recent explosion of public interest in loT,, the idea of loT was already commercialized a time agolts just that loT has been spreadinglevolving gradually long due to a combination of factors at play such as the technology development levels and the economic conditions. In recent years, buzzwords describing a completedly connected world (MZM, loT and Internet of Everything) are being discussed so much that it has become rather diffcult to distinguish the difference between such words The difference between the approaches taken by MZM and loT is in how connections are made As mentioned earlier, as MZM evolved in each industry sector, it became specialized to the particular sector it served. loT is the effort to connect these disparate MZM technologies under the universal communication network umbrella we call the Internet so that businesses could offer more diverse and dynamic services. There are many different perspectives to MZM, but if are grouped by different types of services, some of the typical examples can be listed as follows. they\'','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 22:30:30','2025-02-19 22:30:30'),(2270,'695','App\\Models\\Section','Text','Internet of Things(loT)','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 22:30:30','2025-02-19 22:30:30'),(2271,'907','App\\Models\\Subsection','Tables',NULL,'',4,'67b65b93df92b.png','/storage/tables/67b65b93df92b.png','2025-02-19 22:30:30','2025-02-19 22:30:43'),(2272,'907','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','Cloud computing is a technology that lets people user IT resources (networks, servers, storage, ad sE applications) through the Interet as a service whenever need them,, without ever having to own them implies the IT services could be provided better ad cheaper aytime ad anywhere  Different organizations define the concept of cloud computing in their own different ways Gartner defines cloud computers as a fo computing that leverages Internet technology to provide high-level, scalable resources to many customers service Forest Research defines cloud computing as computing that provides standardized IT based func through IP, access to computing at ay time, computing power that varies based on the level of demand, prc billing model based on the usage level or advertising and provides web or programmable interface Cloud computing is not a new technology, but it existed as a concept for a long time in the IT community it emerged as a market issue as companies began to show interest in cloud computing to reduce costs wake of the global economic recession Cloud computing can be seen as a form of rental business With virtualization technology, it became possible to integrate the IT resources located in different spaces into a system for service Tho cbanctaricticc cloud COmn aro Jmmarizadintho tahlo naloia they impi of Itina Cloud computing is not a new technology, but it existed as a concept for a time in the IT community: But it emerged as a market issue as companies began to show interest in cloud computing to reduce costs in the wake of the global economic recession. Cloud computing can be seen as a form of rental business With improving virtualization technology, it became possible to integrate the IT resources located in different spaces into a single svstem for service long','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 22:30:30','2025-02-19 22:30:30'),(2273,'907','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','Cloud computing has a direct and interactive relationship with the IT sector, which encompasses networks, hardware, solutions, and applications The stakeholders of cloud computing can be divided into three main groups. In the first group are vendors who provide hardware, solutions, and applications to cloud service providers. In the second group are providers that provide cloud services to users and some global leading companies are Amazon, sales force dotcom, and Google. Third, there are various users such as individual users or corporate users, those that actually use cloud services. Users can rent as much services as need and can scale up their services in real-time in response to increased service loads, support real-time scalability based on service load. And only have to pay as  L they they they . 10 Cloud services are made up of the following technologies. Cloud client is a technology for utilizing cloud computing services like cloud lightweight terminal platform technology, cloud-mobile technology, and cloud agents Cloud service and applications are technologies for providing the many types of cloud computing services in SW or application format Cloud platform is a cloud computing technology for providing in service format, the platform of basic functions for easily developing services Cloud infrastructure is a cloud technology that provides resources such as servers, storage, ad networks as services to users. push','',3,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 22:30:30','2025-02-19 22:30:30'),(2274,'696','App\\Models\\Section','Text','Global loT is presently in the introduction phase or early growth phase of its technology life cycle But it is expected to grow more than 20% annually to reach $1.2 trillion by 2022,and it will create new value by reducing the transaction costs between the physical world and the digital world. Ultimately loT eventually improve productivity and give birth to new markets Due to the market\'s desire to value connectivity and technological innovation, the market will loT to transform itself into a mobile centric network where information can be accessed anytime and anywhere: The increasing of network connectivity and the market penetration of different types of mobile devices and connection technologies have triggered the generation and sharing of much more data than before Consequently, loT is being even to the process ad analysis of Big Data. In addition, the accumulation of product knowledge in the market, increased use, and the process of connecting are encouraging the market to change itself a supplier market to a buyers market This trend will have a significant impact on the development direction of future Ci will push speed applied from The functions expected to drive the growth of the loT industry include optimization function, function for integrating with other social infrastructures that transcends industries, and function for managing social infrastructures These functions may contribute to greater social benefits, such as improving the efficiency of social infrastructure or responding to echoes, rather than improving personal convenience','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 22:30:30','2025-02-19 22:30:30'),(2275,'908','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','Cloud service model can be put into 3 classifications, based on the nature of the IT resources_ IO Source: TTA ICT Standardization Strategy 2011 I1 Source: TTA ICT Standardization Strategy Map, 2011 Map, Faasirialiui as a OCi viCC) laaS(Infrastructure as a Service) SaaS is service that lets people use applications through the Internet ad web browser Saas is one of the tier services that cloud service companies can provide and leading services include Google s Gmail and MS Office 365. PaaS is a service that lets companies provide as a service, an environment for developing and running web applications In order to provide this kind of service, the technologies for app development must be modularized and standardized. Leading Paa include Salesforce com s Forcecom and Google\'s Google App Engine: laaS is principally an enterprise service that provides a virtualized environment of resources like servers, storages, ad networks to companies who are permitted to use the resources whenever needed laaS service requires the ability to build and operate servers for large data centers, capital, and a very electrical environment: Examples of laaS include Amazon EC2 and S3,as well as Gabia\'s cloud hosting service top good grid Cloud service can be divided into one of the following categories, depending on how it is configured Public Cloud public cloud is a service shared by multiple users over the Internet, and a cloud service provider provides the services and has management responsibilities A private cloud is an IT environment that is exclusively deployed on a companys or an organization s intranet It is controlled by the company or organization Hybrid cloud is a form of cloud service that has scalability and combines the best of public cloud services and private cloud services It can be used in parallel for special purpose applications With cloud computing, users can directly purchase, design and install without the need for intervention by an IT manager By sharing IT resources that could be used by everybody, cloud computing improves efficiency and the cost associated with owning IT resources could be avoided Due to these advantages, cloud computing can be merged with different types of services and evolve into new business models','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 22:30:30','2025-02-19 22:30:30'),(2276,'909','App\\Models\\Subsection','Tables',NULL,'<Table78 Virtualization functions',2,'67b65b93f368f.png','/storage/tables/67b65b93f368f.png','2025-02-19 22:30:30','2025-02-19 22:30:44'),(2277,'909','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','Virtualization is the abstraction of computer resources on a computer and it could be defined as a technique for hiding the characteristics of physical computer resources the method other systems, applications, and end users use when interact with the resources\". It is a technology that can create multiple logical resources from a single physical resource or create a single logical resource from multiple physical resources from they Application virtualization Through the virtualization of applications installed in individual PCs, users immediate access to needed applications without to install them on their PCs every time Desktop virtualization Server-side desktop virtualization allows users to virtually own another heterogeneous desktop, such as Windows Vista and Windows 7. Client-side desktop virtualization enables heterogeneous virtual desktops in PCs Desktop virtualization allows the separation of personal and corporate workspaces. gain having Server virtualization By consolidating dozens of physical server workloads within the data center on to several virtual servers, the utilization of server resources can be improved (physical rack costs, administrative costs, and green IT): Storage virtualization In place of the physical storage space required, a technology called Thin-Provisioning virtually allocates only the initial minimum required space to enable service implementation It also provides an environment where heterogeneous storage systems can be integrated and used: Network virtualization 13 | 7 switches network firewalls and securitv equinment that had existed in the form of hardiware annliances ietwork virtuaiilzation L2, L3, L7 switches, network firewalls, and security equipment that had existed in the form of hardiware appliances are implemented as virtual machines. This allows network resources to operate internally through virtualization even in a single shared physical environment Functionc Of ictualization','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 22:30:30','2025-02-19 22:30:30'),(2278,'698','App\\Models\\Section','Figures',NULL,'',2,'67b65b940b561.png','/storage/figures/67b65b940b561.png','2025-02-19 22:30:30','2025-02-19 22:30:44'),(2279,'698','App\\Models\\Section','Text','The surge in the use of cryptocurrency Bitcoin in recent years has led to growing interest in blockchain, the core technology behind Bitcoin: Using the concept of distributive network-based decentralization, Blockchain is a distributed ledger network technology in which PZP data blocks that are stored on a distributive network form chains with each other hdi aclcislicd Ui DiocnchaI| Unlike traditional trading methods, transaction ledger data are recorded and managed and verified in block units on all nodes in the network','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 22:30:30','2025-02-19 22:30:30'),(2280,'911','App\\Models\\S