:30'),(2287,'912','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','Technologies that make up smart can be largely grouped under smart platforms and smart applications. The platform has intelligent devices, bi-directional communication and sophisticated control system for managing distributed and intelligent power The platform is configured to operate renewable energy applications, intelligent electric vehicle charging stations, smart metering applications power grid monitoring applications, demand response applications. Intelligent storage devices have electronic sensor ad meters that monitor the current state of the smart and has digital intelligent devices that can make basic decisions on their own. grids grid grid grid, grid The IT infrastructure attached to the power act as the IT elements that are critical to the operation of the smart It optimizes energy efficiency and people to consume energy through bi-directional exchange of real time information (about the supply and demand for electricity). Therefore, the smart must be equipped with open system networks and protocols so that its value-added services could create new products, services, and markets and not limited to just providing power The communication infrastructure should provide end-to-end services between intelligent devices and maintain a reliable and steady supply of electric power: Furthermore, development must abide by standards to support interoperability for various interfaces. grid grid, gets grid','',5,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 22:30:30','2025-02-19 22:30:30'),(2288,'913','App\\Models\\Subsection','Figures',NULL,'66] Concept diagram of Korea Electrical Safety Corporation\'s micro system\' [Fig grid',2,'67b65b9453388.png','/storage/figures/67b65b9453388.png','2025-02-19 22:30:30','2025-02-19 22:30:44'),(2289,'913','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','Microgrid is an extension of a smart The US Department of Energy (DOE) defines a microgrid as \"a group of interconnected consumers and distributed energy resources (