ide shall be connected to the back-end server of the traffic control center and transmit and receive status, location, and operation information that it receives from vehicles. The center system collects and analyzes information received from a multitude of vehicles and base stations, and then sends information about the traffic, road traffic conditions, and others to the base stations, and the base stations will them to vehicles. Examples of V2I services include real-time traffic information collection and provision services, toll collection service, roadside information and obstacle notification service, and road construction notification service and protected zone relay','',5,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 22:30:30','2025-02-19 22:30:30'),(2299,'915','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','VZN service is a service that lets a vehicle communicate through a network with a server or mobile device in the cloud or on the Internet The TCU (Telecommunication Control Unit) is installed in the vehicle and communicates with the backend server, which communicates with the mobile device to provide information to the user and controls the vehicle','',7,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 22:30:30','2025-02-19 22:30:30'),(2300,'915','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','COlecleu Cal Seivice Connected car is a core technology of self-driving cars whose development has been driven by advances made in telematics technology made possible by the development of mobile communication and cloud services. Connected cars can provide services like transportation information services, music services in cars, and information services to car riders based on their connectivity to other cars, surroundings, and infrastructure Examples of services that connected cars can provide include information services using augmented reality, services that help drivers by recognizing and notifying them about road conditions ahead, and fully autonomous driving and automatic parking that do not require any driver response.','',9,NULL,NULL,'