nal structures by stacking layers of materials that could be in powder liquid, or solid (threads, wires, pellets) state The reason why manufacturers are paying attention to 3D printing is that 3D printing is suitable for customized production of small batches of diverse range of products 3D printing improves the manufacturing environment to satisfy consumers\' diverse needs, making it easy to customize the product quickly ad easily to the needs of consumers, and providing a one-person manufacturing environment where consumers can make their own products In addition, as the principal of product manufacturing becomes diverse and the share of the manufacturing/ distribution businesses generated by individuals and small manufacturers increases, the reprocessing industry for product commercialization will also develop. Until now, manufacturing and consumption were separate domains, but 3D printing has allowed the boundaries between consumption and manufacturing to collapse and meet the small needs for manufacturing in everyday life The next example case is a product called Button 2.0,which is an improved button that can be printed with a 3D printer It has grooves on the side for clamping earphone wires and was an idea borne from the inventors frustrating experience of getting his earphones frequently tangled with the buttons on his chirt 21','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 22:30:30','2025-02-19 22:30:30'),(2343,'924','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','onsumers who are living in an era where can easily access 3D printing products will exhibit a different onsumption behavior than the previous generation Instead of simply purchasing products made by companies, will actively demand their own requirements and sometimes will resort to marking the product themselves, xpanding their involvement in the production process they hey ` they As mentioned earlier, 3D printing is an industry for producing small quantities of a wide variety of products and is alsc suited for personalized manufacturing 3D printing is creating a new form of productionkdistribution/consumption tha is markedly different from traditional manufacturing with its strengths in economies of scale and low labor costs While existing manufacturing processes are advantageous for mass production and is perfected suited for especiall simple-shaped products, 3D printing manufacturing processes are advantageous for small-volume, large variety production. A single equipment can produce many different types of products. The process of modeling the product The process of printing the stereoscopic shape by stack printing the layers that makes up the digitized model. Post-processing process for polishing or dyeing the surface of the printed object The 3D model data required for 3D printing can be generated by a 3D scanner when it scans the shape of objects or the developer can create the 3D model using a 3D modeling program: Prior to printing, the 3D model data is converted to thin layers of data by a program called slicer: When the data converted by the slicer is sent to a 3D printer a solid output is created through the process of stacking thin layers of material by stacking or hardening: The final product is produced through -processing processes, such as removing the temporary supports that had been inserted to support the 3D output, shaking off the hot powder on the surface, or dipping it in an adhesive I,diS post-[ Various technologies are needed at each process of 3D printing, and the critical component technologies for each process are as follows: the modeling process requires a technology for scanning or designing objects and for converting the design into data The printing process requires the highly complex technology for spraying the raw material in the right location and controlling the energy source needed for hardening the raw material: In materials, work must be done on developing a material that is compatible with the technology used in the printing process while also meeting the product requirements dictated by the customer materials research for 3d printing is focused on alloys and bio-materials due to the fact that they are materials that create high values Today, urrently, the 3D printing technology is showing limited performance on several technological fronts. But rap levelopment is expected in the years to come because of positive factors like the effort being put into developin iew technologies, advancements being made in new materials, &d critical patents whose rights are scheduled xpire','',4,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 22:30:30','2025-02-19 22:30:30'),(2344,'925','App\\Models\\Subsection','Tables',NULL,'<Table 93  Types of wearable devices?2',2,'67b65b95ae107.png','/storage/tables/67b65b95ae107.png','2025-02-19 22:30:30','2025-02-19 22:30:45'),(2345,'925','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','The smartphone market, which was on an explosive growth trajectory since the introduction of the iPhone in 2009, is now in its maturing stage At this point in time, the next-generation mobile technology that is expected to replace the smartphone is the wearable device. Wearable devices are devices of various form factors that are designed to be attached to the human body to improve the convenience of use: Wearable devices are electronic devices that are just worn on the body like an accessory, but are electronic devices that can communicate with users from the closest location to the user\'s body: provide functions that are clearly differentiable from existing devices in terms of portability, ease of use, and environmental adaptability: From fitness and well-being to healthcare, medical care, manufacturing, military, and infotainment, wearable devices are used in increasing number of applications Wearable devices began as an accessory type device But are evolving into many different forms, including body attachment type which is attached to the human body, apparel-integrated type which is integrated into textiles, and body transplants, which are devices that are actually inserted into the human body: TKo Jifforon f Noaraklo JoI rizodin  kc  klo polc they They being today, they Jico','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 22:30:30','2025-02-19 22:30:30'),(2346,'925','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','In recent years, the growth of loT has greatly expanded the scope and the range of objects (people, objects, devices, etc ) that could be interconnected. This development has led to the growing importance of wearable devices because such devices are always connected to the users network Because can free up the 2 hands of users and are always located close to the user\'s view and the user\'s position, the role of wearables will become increasingly more they 22 Source: Directions and Challenging Tasks of Smart Grid, Park Chan-guk, NIPA 2009 important ad the collection of data that was previously difficult to collect will become possible. Consequently, the production of customized personal contents will become possible, opening the floodgates to new types of services The problems wearable devices are short battery life which severely restricts the users ability to appreciate the value of always wearing the device, limited content that can be implemented in a small screen, and the lack of killer content or services and the lack of a game changing function: However, wearable devices will be able to create core values if converge with loT, cloud computing, Big Data, and mobile devices. The sensing functions in wearable devices can be used for gathering Big Data, Big Data (cloud) analysis can be carried out on the gathered data,, the implications from the analysis results could be used in customized services for users. Also, new business models like smart home service based on loT, 020 commerce, and smart car service will create new markets and expand existing markets facing they','',3,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 22:30:30','2025-02-19 22:30:30'),(2347,'926','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','Self-driving cars are defined as automobiles that can drive safely on their own by recognizing the surrounding environment on their own without the drivers intervention, and can drive safely by recognizing risks To be more precise, self-driving cars incorporate ICT technologies like software, Al, communication and sensor technologies to minimize human control while it is being driven safely: The emergence of self-driving cars IS due to the tollowing developments: IT companies and car makers are accelerating their cooperation to bring latest ICT technologies to cars The growth of the electrical parts and telematics market in response to demand for better safety an convenience Improvements in network ad Internet technology allow cars to be recognized as new mobile space and offer nev UXs to drivers rapid','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 22:30:30','2025-02-19 22:30:30'),(2348,'927','App\\Models\\Subsection','Figures',NULL,'[Fig: 78] Concept diagram of smart machine',2,'67b65b95baf44.png','/storage/figures/67b65b95baf44.png','2025-02-19 22:30:30','2025-02-19 22:30:45'),(2349,'927','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','Smart machines that can be tound in our surroundings today are machines that recognize human voice and provide answers to questions by users, eg Apple Siri or Google Home: Medical advisors that provide guidance on medical diagnosis or use, and robots that assemble on behalf of people in factories are also example of smart machines Smart machines are defined as a machine that acts autonomously, has intelligence and self-learning abilities, and is able to judge ad adapt itself to different situations and performs tasks that have been thought to be impossible 23 except for humans, posed drug things','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 22:30:30','2025-02-19 22:30:30'),(2350,'927','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','Direction of developments in smart machines Smart machines are evolving in a direction where it can learn by itself and make its own rules, create and validate hypothesis and become situational aware and discover the optimal solution, in tandem with advances made in cloud computing, Big Data and artificial intelligence (AI): In other words, it is approaching the real concept of a smart machine being In other words, the age is dawning when machines could do things that could not be accomplished by humans because of the lack of human ability Machines will be able to study vast medical records or judicial records to come up with the best interpretation of the data and recommend the best decision to make. It will be able to perform the role of improving our daily lives, for instance by supplementing the muscles or cognitive abilities of the elderly and the weak','',3,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 22:30:30','2025-02-19 22:30:30'),(2351,'928','App\\Models\\Subsection','Tables',NULL,'<Table 95  Applications of drones',2,'67b65b95cc32d.png','/storage/tables/67b65b95cc32d.png','2025-02-19 22:30:30','2025-02-19 22:30:45'),(2352,'928','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','A drone is defined as an aircraft or helicopter-shaped unmanned aerial vehicle that is flown by the radio signals Drones were first developed for military purposes. After the Second World War, drones were developed to be reused as target aircrafts military exercises Drones are gradually beginning to be used in the private sector Once they are equipped with GPS or video devices, drones can be used in many applications during Auval ilages ui ululie Drones can go to places that are impossible for humans to reach, such as the underworld or used for exploring the deepest parts of the oceans. can approach places that are too hazardous for humans to go, such as places where hazardous gases or radioactivity may be present Drones can also be operated in autonomous mode without a human operator in which it can recognize its surrounding environment and fly by itself Because there are no restrictions to where drones can g0, can be used in various sectors They they','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 22:30:30','2025-02-19 22:30:30'),(2353,'706','App\\Models\\Section','Tables',NULL,'',2,'67b65b95df04a.png','/storage/tables/67b65b95df04a.png','2025-02-19 22:30:30','2025-02-19 22:30:45'),(2354,'706','App\\Models\\Section','Text','AC} LCC 1010s-\"#i DC 4i 76 Cu 0 The job of a self-driving car is acquiring information and using this information to drive the car safely: It requires technologies of recognition, judgement, and manipulation. These technologies become integrated with other technologies like AUTOSAR, RTOS, and functional safety technologies.','',3,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 22:30:30','2025-02-19 22:30:30'),(2355,'929','App\\Models\\Subsection','Tables',NULL,'',2,'67b65b95ed927.png','/storage/tables/67b65b95ed927.png','2025-02-19 22:30:32','2025-02-19 22:30:45'),(2356,'929','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','job. Many people in modern society engage in vocational activities while belonging to a specific organization called the workplace, not only attaining self-realization but also forming relationships and interacting with others while participating in the common life of society: At this time, the norms and standards that can be applied to individuals\' mindsets, attitudes and related behaviors toward jobs and work, and mutual relations required in a specific setting of a job can be called professional ethics In the normative aspect, professional ethics consists of ethical norms that must be observed among people in their professional life, norms made up of rules of common behavior, and norms that limit harmful behaviors that should not be performed, that is, unethical behaviors','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 22:30:32','2025-02-19 22:30:32'),(2357,'930','App\\Models\\Subsection','Tables',NULL,'',4,'67b65b960e505.png','/storage/tables/67b65b960e505.png','2025-02-19 22:30:32','2025-02-19 22:30:46'),(2358,'930','App\\Models\\Subsection','Tables',NULL,'<Table 97  Answer Checklist',6,'67b65b961baff.png','/storage/tables/67b65b961baff.png','2025-02-19 22:30:32','2025-02-19 22:30:46'),(2359,'930','App\\Models\\Subsection','