ublic enterprises The government provides a manual in relation to this, and diagnoses the personal information protection management and infringement prevention activities of institutions at the national level, reflects them in the institutional evaluation to induce the improvement of the level of personal information protection If you look at the \"Checklist for Diagnosis of Personal Information Protection Management Levels of Public Institutions presented in the manual published in 2018, you can see What the most important factors in personal information protection are public system','',6,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 22:30:33','2025-02-19 22:30:33'),(2387,'940','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','Sensitive information: a wider range of personal information such as ideas, beliefs, membership or withdrawal trade unions and political parties, political opinions, health information, genetic information, criminal history, etc Unique identification information: Identification information that enables the subject of information to be identifiec by means of resident registration number, passport number, driver\'s license number alien registration number, etc Personal information impact assessment: An evaluation system conducted to analyze risk factors and derive improvements in cases where there is concern about personal information infringement due to new introduction modification of personal information files Image information processing device: It refers to a device as specified by Presidential Decree that stays installec in a certain space to shoot images of people or objects or transmit them through wired or wireless networks. The image information processing device operator must prepare and disclose a policy for image information processing device operation and management that includes the following contents (Article 25 of the Act, Article 25 of the Enforcement Decree): <Required items for personal image information management register   Classification of use, provision, reading, destruction Date and time Name/type of file Person charge Purpose/reason Third party for data use provision/ reading Grounds for use and provision Tvne of use and nrovision (0 Period','',10,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 22:30:33','2025-02-19 22:30:33'),(2388,'712','App\\Models\\Section','Tables',NULL,'<Table 101  Related laws related to personal information protection in Korea',2,'67b65b96e8a8b.png','/storage/tables/67b65b96e8a8b.png','2025-02-19 22:30:33','2025-02-19 22:30:46'),(2389,'712','App\\Models\\Section','Text','relation to personal information protection, the comparison of personal information processing by laws and gulations is as follows','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 22:30:33','2025-02-19 22:30:33'),(2390,'941','App\\Models\\Subsection','Tables',NULL,'',4,'67b65b970dcd3.png','/storage/tables/67b65b970dcd3.png','2025-02-19 22:30:33','2025-02-19 22:30:47'),(2391,'941','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','The OECD Privacy Guidelines is named the Recommendation Concerning Guidelines Governing the Protection of Privacy and Transborder Flows of Personal Data, which were established in 1980 as guidelines for the cross- border transfer of personal data in 1980. Since then, it has been revised to reflect the opinions of the intemational community on the collection and management of personal information, and is currently used as basic data for the development of laws and guidelines related to personal information in countries around the world,','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 22:30:33','2025-02-19 22:30:33'),(2392,'941','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','32 Officially named \"Recommendation Concerning Guidelines Governing the Protection of Privacy and Transborder Flows of Personal Data','',3,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 22:30:33','2025-02-19 22:30:33'),(2393,'942','App\\Models\\Subsection','Tables',NULL,'',4,'67b65b97240ef.png','/storage/tables/67b65b97240ef.png','2025-02-19 22:30:33','2025-02-19 22:30:47'),(2394,'942','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','The GDPR is a unified rule created by the European Parliament to strengthen the privacy of European citizens. It was promulgated by the European Parliament in 2016 (Regulation (EU) 2016/679) , and after a grace period of about two years, it took effect in each EU member state from 25,2018. When data of EU citizens, you must comply with the GDPR For example, even if there is no business establishment in Europe, any company that provides goods and services to residents of the European Union (EU) must comply with the regulations of the GDPR In addition, when a company violates the right of personal information, it is required to notify the supervisory authority within 72 hours, The main contents of the GDPR are the expansion of the application of personal information processing (for all companies that process personal information), enhancing the rights of data subjects, strengthening the responsibility of data controllers prohibiting the transfer of personal information abroad in principle, and taking measures to protect information the processing design stage when processing personal information In GDPR, the three entities involved in the process of processing personal information are defined as the data subject,, the controller and the processor Data Subject: Refers to a natural person\" who creates personal information and has the right to the personal information created by himher Controller: As a subject responsible for processing personal information, it controls personal information according to the type thereof determines the purpose of processing, and is in charge of processing means: Even if the data is the same, the controllers can be differentiated if the purpose of processing is different: Processor: Refers to an individual, corporation, or institution entrusted with processing personal information on behalf of the controller, and processes personal information as directed by the controller May using from \"living public','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 22:30:33','2025-02-19 22:30:33'),(2395,'942','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','The EUs GDPR reinforces the rights of data subjects compared to existing data protection guidelines by newly guaranteeing the right to be forgotten and the right to transfer data, and strictly restricts the transfer of data of EU citizens abroad The main items to guarantee the rights of data subjects in GDPR are as follows. the right to be informed the right of access the right to rectification the right to erasure the right to restrict processing the right to data portability the right to object The right to erasure (right to request erasure) has been renamed the right to forgotten in the previous GDPR draft, and the right to erasure and the right to data portability are items that reinforce the rights of data subjects. The rights in relation to automated decision making and profiling refer to the right to notify the user who is the data subject and to let them decide whether their information will be used or not, when an individuals occupation, hobbies, and location are automaticallv collected and used as nart of marketino from 3 Korea Internet & Security Agency, Guidance on \"General Data Protection Regulation\" for Korean Enterprises, 2017','',3,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 22:30:33','2025-02-19 22:30:33'),(2396,'943','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','Individual Control: The right of the data subject to control personal information Transparency: Transparency in access to information Respect for Context: The right to know the context and reason for the act of collecting, using, and disclosir information Security: Strengthen the security of personal information Access and Accuracy: The right to access personal information as the data subject and to its accuracy Focused Collection: The right of the data subject to personal information collected and held by businesses Accountability: Data collecting agencys compliance with legislation and actions taken accordingly','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 22:30:33','2025-02-19 22:30:33'),(2397,'944','App\\Models\\Subsection','Tables',NULL,'',3,'67b65b973bb47.png','/storage/tables/67b65b973bb47.png','2025-02-19 22:30:33','2025-02-19 22:30:47'),(2398,'944','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','34 Korea Internet & Security Agency, EU Privacy Policy Status, 2018. 35 US White House(wwwwhitehousegov), \"Consumer Privacy Bill of Rights','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 22:30:33','2025-02-19 22:30:33'),(2399,'945','App\\Models\\Subsection','Tables',NULL,'',4,'67b65b974fc95.png','/storage/tables/67b65b974fc95.png','2025-02-19 22:30:33','2025-02-19 22:30:47'),(2400,'945','App\\Models\\Subsection','Figures',NULL,'[Figure 85] De-identification Process of Personal Information',2,'67b65b975ba7e.png','/storage/figures/67b65b975ba7e.png','2025-02-19 22:30:33','2025-02-19 22:30:47'),(2401,'945','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','Businesses, who want to process information for data analysis, etc, should de-identify and manage the information if it is personal information De-identification refers to de-identifying elements that can identify an individual so that a specific individual cannot be identified by processing personal information with alternative methods such as pseudonymization, aggregate processing deletion, categorization, and data masking 36 US White House(wwwwhitehousegov), \"Consumer Privacy Bill of Rights\"','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 22:30:33','2025-02-19 22:30:33'),(2402,'945','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','De-identification Standards for Identifiers: As a rule, an identifier included in datasets should be deleted. However, an identifier that is absolutely needed for a purpose of the use of data can be utilized after de-identification De-identification Standards for Attribute Values: As a rule, an attribute value included in datasets should be also removed if it is irrelevant to a purpose of the use of data. Attribute values like rare disease or unique professional experiences need strict de-identification as are highly likely to identify an individual under certain circumctancec they','',3,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 22:30:33','2025-02-19 22:30:33'),(2403,'715','App\\Models\\Section','Tables',NULL,'',3,'67b65b976b0f5.png','/storage/tables/67b65b976b0f5.png','2025-02-19 22:30:33','2025-02-19 22:30:47'),(2404,'715','App\\Models\\Section','Text','Unique identification information (resident registration number passport number alien registration number driver s license number) Name (including Chinese/English name, pen name, etc ) Detailed address (address included up to the district(gu) unit) Date information: birthday (yangllunar calendar), anniversary (marriage, first birthday, sixtieth birthday, etc ) , date of certificate, etc, Phone number (mobile phone number, home phone number, company phone number, fax number) Medical record number, health insurance number welfare recipient number Account number, credit card number Various qualifications and license numbers Vehicle number, registration number & serial number of various devices Photos (still photos, videos, CCTV footage, etc ) Body identification information (fingerprint, voice, iris, etc) Email address, IP address, Mac address, homepage URL, etc Identification code (ID, employee number, customer number, etc ) Other unique identification number: serial number business registration number of sole military = Methods of De-identification: A range of methods including pseudonymization, aggregation, data suppression and data masking can be used individually or in combination. There are various kinds of technology in place to realize each method. The most suitable methods and specific techniques need to be chosen and utilized based on the purpose of data usage, and strengths and weaknesses of each method.','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 22:30:33','2025-02-19 22:30:33'),(2405,'716','App\\Models\\Section','Figures',NULL,'',2,'67b65b977706f.png','/storage/figures/67b65b977706f.png','2025-02-19 22:30:33','2025-02-19 22:30:47'),(2406,'716','App\\Models\\Section','Figures',NULL,'',3,'67b65b97826e8.png','/storage/figures/67b65b97826e8.png','2025-02-19 22:30:33','2025-02-19 22:30:47'),(2407,'716','App\\Models\\Section','Text','<Example  Application of non-identification measure','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 22:30:33','2025-02-19 22:30:33'),(2408,'947','App\\Models\\Subsection','Tables',NULL,'',4,'67b65b97a7929.png','/storage/tables/67b65b97a7929.png','2025-02-19 22:30:33','2025-02-19 22:30:47'),(2409,'947','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','There is the ISMS-P certification system which establishes a personal information protection management system,, examine whether systematic and continuous protection is performed, and grant certification if the standards are met, in order to protect personal information All persons under the following < Table 7  among \"telecommunications business operators\" and \"persons who provide information or mediate the provision of information using telecommunications services of telecommunications business operators\" (Article 47, Paragraph 2 of the Information and Communication Network Act) are the subject of the obligations, falling','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 22:30:33','2025-02-19 22:30:33'),(2410,'947','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','In addition, companies and institutions that do not meet the criteria, but voluntarily establish and operate a information protection and personal information protection management system are classified as voluntary applicant and can apply for certification and receive certification examination. Whether institutions and companies have a personal information protection management and systematically and continuously perform protection tasks, ad grant certification when the standards are satisfied, are objectively eyamined system','',3,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 22:30:33','2025-02-19 22:30:33'),(2411,'948','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','If personal information is leaked (mandatory obligation in case of more than one thousand data subjects Article 34 of the Personal Information Protection Act, Article 39 of the Enforcement Decree of the same Act), the data subjects must be notified immediately and actions such as confirmation of facts, blocking of the website, notification of password change, etc. must be promptly initiated. In addition, victims of leakage may file collective dispute mediation with the Dispute Mediation Committee or file a lawsuit against the infringement of rights to the court, which requires thorough preparation','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 22:30:33','2025-02-19 22:30:33'),(2412,'949','App\\Models\\Subsection','Tables',NULL,'',3,'67b65b97b9bb1.png','/storage/tables/67b65b97b9bb1.png','2025-02-19 22:30:33','2025-02-19 22:30:47'),(2413,'949','App\\Models\\Subsection','Tables',NULL,'',4,'67b65b97c7711.png','/storage/tables/67b65b97c7711.png','2025-02-19 22:30:33','2025-02-19 22:30:47'),(2414,'949','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','If personal information over a certain scale is leaked, it is required to report to specialized agencies such as the Ministry of Security and Public Administration and the Korea Internet & Security Agency (KISA) to provide support for damage prevention and recovery technology:','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 22:30:33','2025-02-19 22:30:33'),(2415,'950','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','c and private services in which personal information is used in combination with informatic technology: Personal information is not just information but becomes an asset of a company such as electronic civl service for public institutions, education, finance, information and communication, medical care, entertainment, etc If personal information is leaked, it can be abused for crime and fraud through illegal trafficking and impersonation Increasing personal information infringement accidents and class action lawsuits by victims of leakage cause loss of corporate management. Protection of personal information becomes an essential element of national and social safety and corporate development Personal information and privacy protection, which has become a global trend, serves as a growth engine of Korea Personal information protection becomes an important issue in industries. The signing of FTAs with countries around the world has increased cross-border exchange of personal information Personal information issues affect public administration credibility and national brand','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 22:30:33','2025-02-19 22:30:33'),(2416,'719','App\\Models\\Section','Text','Intellectual property rights mean rights to intellectual property recognized or protected by laws or treaties include knowledge, information and technology created or discovered by human creative activities or experiences, expressions of ideas or emotions, representations of business or objects, varieties or genetic resources of living organisms, and other intangibles of realizable property value They','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 22:30:34','2025-02-19 22:30:34'),(2417,'720','App\\Models\\Section','Text','Intellectual property rights are largely divided into the following three types Copyright: Exclusive rights recognized for academic research findings or literary creations Industrial property rights: Industrial property rights are rights recognized for new industrial inventions, practical inventions, product forms or trademarks New intellectual property rights: New intellectual property rights are rights to intellectual property that emerges in new fields due to economic, social, or cultural changes or development of science and technology:','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 22:30:34','2025-02-19 22:30:34'),(2418,'951','App\\Models\\Subsection','Tables',NULL,'',2,'67b65b97d5347.png','/storage/tables/67b65b97d5347.png','2025-02-19 22:30:34','2025-02-19 22:30:47'),(2419,'951','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','Copyright is a right arising to a person who created a work, and generally refers to an exclusive right granted tc the author of a work by law The copyright applies the time the work is created, and follows the non-formality principle, meaning that it is automatically generated even without formal requirements or registration procedures for from copyngii 15 a ng\'i 015ing IU a peisuii Wiio Cicalcu WvuiK aru gericraiy iCicis IU al exciusive \"griL gralileu lu the author of a work by law The copyright applies the time the work is created, and follows the non-formality principle, meaning that it is automatically generated even without formal requirements or registration procedures for the work Copyright is largely divided into moral rights, authors economic rights, and neighboring rights. Copyrights which are the rights of authors, can be classified into moral rights and authors economic rights. In the case of moral rights, it is a non-monetary right to protect the author\'s honor ad character and is non- transferable (the right under exclusive belongingness of oneself). The moral rights include the right of attribution, the right to have a work published anonymously or pseudonymously, and the right to the integrity of the work Authors\' economic rights are related to the property of the author, are monetary rights and are transferable Authors economic rights include the right of reproduction, performance, broadcasting, transmission rights, exhibition, distribution, production of derivative works. The copyright holder may allow other people to use the work, and a person who has obtained permission to use the work may freely use the work within the scope of the permitted use methods and conditions. In addition, even if a work has been licensed for use, it cannot be transferred to another person without the consent of the copyright holder, so it is necessary to pay attention to the use of the work Meanwhile, neighboring rights refer to the rights of neighbors such as performers, record producers, and broadcasters Neighboring rights are given differently to each neighboring right holder ad since it is usually a secondary right to from create added value by using the work, more restrictive rights are given to the copyright holder','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 22:30:34','2025-02-19 22:30:34'),(2420,'952','App\\Models\\Subsection','Tables',NULL,'<Table 106  Types of Recognized Works',2,'67b65b97e9ba5.png','/storage/tables/67b65b97e9ba5.png','2025-02-19 22:30:34','2025-02-19 22:30:47'),(2421,'952','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','The term \'\"work\" means a creative production that expresses human thoughts and emotions Copyright is established only when a work with originality and externality is created, and the types of works recognized are as follows','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 22:30:34','2025-02-19 22:30:34'),(2422,'722','App\\Models\\Section','Text','If it is difficult to know who actually created the work, any person who falls under any of the following subparagraphs shall be presumed to have the copyright for his or her works as an author: (Copyright Acty Article 8 (1) A person whose real name or well-known pseudonym (referring to the stage name, pen name, abbreviated name, etc , hereinafter the same shall apply) is indicated as the name of the author in a usual manner on the original or copies of a work, A person whose real name or well-known pseudonym is indicated as the name of the author in the public If the name of the author is not indicated as prescribed under any of the subparagraphs of paragraph (1), the perso who is indicated as a publisher, public performer or a person making the work shall be presumed to have th copyright: (Copyright Acty Article 8 (2)) public PPj\"6\' Public performance\" means to present to the public works performances, phonograms or broadcasts by acting, musical playing, singing, narrating reciting, screening, playback or other means. \"Public transmission\" means transmitting works, stage performances, phonograms, broadcasts or database by making such available to the public by wire or wireless means so that the public may receive them or have access to them: \"Publication\" means a reproduction and distribution of the works or phonograms to meet public demand \"Making works public\" means to make the works open to the public by means of public performance, public transmission, or exhibit and bv other means and to publish the works','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 22:30:34','2025-02-19 22:30:34'),(2423,'953','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','The term work made for hire\" means a work made by an employee of a legal person, organization or other employe (hereinafter referred to as \"legal person, etc\" the course of his or her duties and on the initiative of leg person, etc\"7 The authorship of a work made for hire which is made under the name f such a legal person, etc. as the auth 38 shall be attributed to that legal person,, etc, unless otherwise stipulated in the contract or work regulation, etc In order for a legal person, etc: to become the author of a work made for hire, it must meet all of the followi requirements (Korea Copyright Commission\'s Consultation Case Book) The work must be initiated by a legal person or the like It must be written by a person who is engaged in business such as a legal person: It must be a work written for business. It must be publicized in the name of a legal person, etc, during public 37 Copyright Act, subparagraph 31 of Article 38 Convrioht Act Article','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 22:30:34','2025-02-19 22:30:34'),(2424,'954','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','According to Article 2 of the Software Industry Promotion Act, the term software means collection of instructions and commands (including audio or visual information, etc) that enables equipment,, such as computers, communications apparatuses and automation equipment and peripheral equipment to command, control, input, process, save, output and interact, and descriptions used to prepare them and other related data. A computer program work is a generic term for a computer program and a work of descriptive language of a program: A computer program work includes programming language (C, Java, etc )  protocol, algorithm, source code and object code (compiled source code), and structure and arrangement method of the program. Here, the source code, object code, program structure and arrangement are protected by copyright, but programming languages, protocols, algorithms, etc, for programming are excluded from the protection In other words, the product of writing software is protected by copyright, but programming languages, protocols, and algorithms for writing programs are excluded copyright protection: Software is copyrighted so that only the software author has the right to use, copy, distribute, and modify the software: If the software author gives someone the right to perform certain actions, this is called & \"license\" The software license agreement contains detailed regulations based on the basic contents of the purpose of the contract, the definition clause, the establishment of the license, the term of the contract, the storage of records, and royalties, in order to clearly set forth the criteria for settlement in case of dispute. from','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 22:30:34','2025-02-19 22:30:34'),(2425,'955','App\\Models\\Subsection','Tables',NULL,'<Table 108  Comparison of open source licenses by features',4,'67b65b980d110.png','/storage/tables/67b65b980d110.png','2025-02-19 22:30:34','2025-02-19 22:30:48'),(2426,'955','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','Open source software (OSS, Open Source Software) refers to software in which anyone can freely use/copyldistribut odify its source code Representative examples include Apache web server, FireFox Web Browser, and Linux Kerne','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 22:30:34','2025-02-19 22:30:34'),(2427,'955','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','Most open source licenses require the following basic requirements Indicate or include matters about the developer or contributor and matters about copyright on the product If the source code is modified, information on the modification, such as who modified the code and when, should be included