 to detection of pedestrians and obstacles in the vehicle pa occupant protection and safety) Remote control attack and availability threat due to hacking Threat of life and property loss due to hacking, real-time exposure of user information Privacy invasion due to leakage of personal information collected by in-vehicle sensors and computers such as trai Ati 6\" \"6 Co CAC_ ID C TCj# 4o9u JCCC C Li I The ethical dilemma of -driving cars (controversy on how to deal with accidents and who is the cause of the accident) Safety issues of autonomous vehicles (reaction to detection of pedestrians and obstacles in the vehicle occupant protection and safety) Remote control attack ad availability threat due to hacking Threat of life ad property loss due to hacking, real-time exposure of user information self-c path, route and address The possibility that self-driving cars will be abused as unmanned vehicles that monitor others and invade the privacy of others','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 22:30:35','2025-02-19 22:30:35'),(2452,'973','App\\Models\\Subsection','Tables',NULL,'<Table 113  Comparison of domestic and foreign drone operation policies',4,'67b65b9887104.png','/storage/tables/67b65b9887104.png','2025-02-19 22:30:35','2025-02-19 22:30:48'),(2453,'973','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','As the drone-related industry has recently emerged as a representative field of the 4th industrial revolution, the investment and research on drones are actively being conducted. Drones are becoming an issue in the education filed, with the rise of education using drones and training for professional drone pilots Recently, drones are not limited to a hobby or mere filming, but are also used for industrial purposes such as delivery, forest fire monitoring, and distribution of pesticides. As drones can be used for real-time command systems, surveillance systems, high-definition video recording and sharing, and autonomous driving, its use is expected to spread to all industries with the increased use of drones, various accidents such as drone crashes, collisions with buildings, and flying in no-flv zones are also increasing Along On May 10, 201.2,a drone crashed in Songdo, Incheon due to a cyber-attack presumably from North Korea In August 2013,a drone appeared above the submarine manufacturing plant of the British On October 5, 2014 a drone crashed at 7 nuclear power plants in France On January 26, 2015,a drone crashed into the White House On April 22, 201,5,a drone carrying radioactive material crashes at the Japanese Prime Ministers office On June 23,2015,a drone crashed into Duomo in Italy On July 10, 2015,a student at the Department of Mechanical Engineering at Central Connecticut State University in the US. made a shooting drone On July 26,2015,a drone appeared at the nudist beach in Studland, England On July 26, 2015,a drone dropped drugs over Mansfield Correctional Institution On July 29,2015,a drone for monitoring the beach in Busan crashed over the sea On April 17,2016,a British Airways A320 plane collided with a drone Navy As drones are becoming more popular, the number of drone accidents continues to increase. Drone hacking and privacy invasion accidents as well as crashes are frequently occurring: There have also been incidents of hacking drones to disrupt remote control or steal the imagery captured in drones For example, data of US. combat drones was leaked to hackers and traded on the black market, ad there were cases in which a video footage of a country\'s key intelligence data stored in the drone was leaked due to the hacking: The number of personal information infringement cases is increasing as videos related to personal life are illegally filmed and collected/transmitted by drones. Therefore, it is necessary to understand drone-related regulations and ethical guidelines before operating drones to 6 Source: Weekly Chosun article, \"[News in News] It is to deregulate drones for accidents 2016.06.06. good','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 22: