nd detailed content.\"','[\"Key components include a subject line, summary, and detailed content.\", \"Emails should be informal and concise.\", \"Only the summary is necessary for effective emails.\", \"Attachments are more important than the email content.\"]',NULL,'2025-02-26 14:53:46','2025-02-26 14:53:46'),(1794,'Multiple Choice - Single','\"Top-down communication can lead to a lack of engagement, while bottom-up encourages participation.\"','[\"Top-down communication can lead to a lack of engagement, while bottom-up encourages participation.\", \"Bottom-up communication is always more effective than top-down.\", \"Both styles have the same impact on employee morale.\", \"Top-down communication is preferred in all situations.\"]',NULL,'2025-02-26 14:53:46','2025-02-26 14:53:46'),(1795,'Multiple Choice - Single','\"PMS focuses on overall project progress, while RMS focuses on identifying and mitigating risks.\"','[\"PMS focuses on overall project progress, while RMS focuses on identifying and mitigating risks.\", \"PMS is primarily for financial tracking, while RMS is for team management.\", \"PMS deals only with scheduling, while RMS handles quality control.\", \"PMS and RMS serve the same purpose but use different software.\"]',NULL,'2025-02-26 14:53:46','2025-02-26 14:53:46'),(1796,'Multiple Choice - Many','[\"Financial perspective evaluates ROI\", \"Management perspective assesses project progress\"]','[\"Financial perspective evaluates ROI\", \"Management perspective assesses project progress\", \"Technical perspective focuses solely on coding standards\", \"Management perspective is only concerned with budget overruns\"]',NULL,'2025-02-26 14:53:46','2025-02-26 14:53:46'),(1797,'Multiple Choice - Single','\"Inadequate training can lead to confusion and errors.\"','[\"Inadequate training can lead to confusion and errors.\", \"Increased communication always resolves challenges.\", \"CMS implementation requires no prior planning.\", \"All team members will ada