dentities before certificate issuance.\", \"The RA issues certificates directly to users.\", \"The CA manages the revocation list, while the RA handles certificate renewals.\", \"Both the CA and RA are responsible for generating keys.\"]','2025-03-28 01:40:51','2025-03-28 01:40:51'),(2435,4,'Test','Categorize the different access control policies, such as Mandatory Access Control (MAC), Discretionary Access Control (DAC), and Role-Based Access Control (RBAC). How do the principles behind each policy affect the management of access rights in an organization? Examine their strengths and weaknesses in various operational scenarios.',0.8,1.2,'Hard','C4-FVVj5Y6uTXSeC9dMo0LwMw','Multiple Choice - Many','[\"Mandatory Access Control (MAC)\", \"Role-Based Access Control (RBAC)\"]','[\"Mandatory Access Control (MAC)\", \"Discretionary Access Control (DAC)\", \"Role-Based Access Control (RBAC)\", \"Network Access Control (NAC)\"]','2025-03-28 01:40:51','2025-03-28 01:40:51'),(2436,4,'Test','Examine the significance of salting in hash functions for password security. How does the addition of a salt value enhance the security of stored passwords against attacks such as rainbow table attacks? Analyze the implications of using insufficiently random or short salt values.',0.8,1.8,'Hard','C4-r3cL5/J/TMy6y/XbrkJWvA','Multiple Choice - Single','\"Salting adds randomness to passwords, making pre-computed attacks like rainbow tables ineffective.\"','[\"Salting adds randomness to passwords, making pre-computed attacks like rainbow tables ineffective.\", \"Salting reduces the storage size of hash values.\", \"Salting requires the use of a key.\", \"Salting can be used to reverse-engineer passwords.\"]','2025-03-28 01:40:51','2025-03-28 01:40:51'),(2437,4,'Test','Differentiate between user authentication and message authentication. How do these two concepts interact in a secure communication environment? Analyze the importance of both in preventing unauthorized access and ensuring data integrity.',0.8,1.1,'Hard','C4-Y+2K00EDTa+jr4UoRIy15Q','Multiple Choice - Single','\"User authentication verifies the identity of users, while message authentication ensures the integrity of the message.\"','[\"User authentication verifies the identity of users, while message authentication ensures the integrity of the message.\", \"User authentication is less important than message authentication.\", \"Message authentication relies on user credentials.\", \"User authentication is only needed for sensitive data.\"]','2025-03-28 01:40:51','2025-03-28 01:40:51'),(2438,4,'Test','Investigate the complexities involved in implementing a secure electronic signature system using public key cryptography. What are the critical requirements for ensuring non-repudiation and integrity of signed documents? Compare the effectiveness of electronic signatures against traditional handwritten signatures in digital transactions.',0.8,1.1,'Hard','C4-HpK24ThZQiybozSFGB16SA','Multiple Choice - Many','[\"Non-repudiation\", \"Integrity\"]','[\"Non-repudiation\", \"Integrity\", \"Speed\", \"Ease of use\"]','2025-03-28 01:40:51','2025-03-28 01:40:51'),(2439,4,'Test','Analyze the Bell-LaPadula and Biba models in terms of their focus on confidentiality and integrity respectively. How do these models address the security requirements of different types of information systems? Discuss the implications of applying these models in real-world scenarios.',0.8,1.3,'Hard','C4-qAIHy19sRZ6PwGQ1/5ey3A','Multiple Choice - Single','\"The Bell-LaPadula model emphasizes confidentiality, while the Biba model emphasizes integrity.\"','[\"The Bell-LaPadula model emphasizes confidentiality, while the Biba model emphasizes integrity.\", \"The Biba model is more widely used than the Bell-LaPadula model.\", \"Both models prioritize user access over data protection.\", \"The Bell-LaPadula model is designed for commercial use.\"]','2025-03-28 01:40:51','2025-03-28 01:40:51'),(2440,4,'Test','Examine the relationship between cryptographic protocols and their underlying cryptographic techniques. How do protocols ensure secure communication by leveraging cryptographic methods? Analyze how the effectiveness of a protocol can be compromised if the underlying cryptographic technique is flawed.',0.8,1.1,'Hard','C4-bS7QErNaSaGA0jNsWx6xhw','Multiple Choice - Single','\"Protocols utilize cryptographic techniques to ensure secure communication, but flaws in techniques can compromise security.\"','[\"Protocols utilize cryptographic techniques to ensure secure communication, but flaws in techniques can compromise security.\", \"Protocols operate independently of cryptographic techniques.\", \"All cryptographic techniques are equally secure.\", \"Protocols only focus on data integrity.\"]','2025-03-28 01:40:51','2025-03-28 01:40:51'),(2441,4,'Test','Categorize the various attack techniques against password authentication systems, such as brute force and social engineering. How do these attacks exploit weaknesses in user authentication methods? Analyze the effectiveness of countermeasures like intrusion detection systems and password policies in mitigating these risks.',0.8,1.4,'Hard','C4-gLj37e0/TO+6vWPotkHWXA','Multiple Choice - Many','[\"Brute force attacks\", \"Social engineering\"]','[\"Brute force attacks\", \"Social engineering\", \"Phishing\", \"Denial of Service attacks\"]','2025-03-28 01:40:51','2025-03-28 01:40:51'),(2442,4,'Test','Investigate the role of access control mechanisms, such as access control lists (ACLs) and capability lists (CLs), in managing user permissions. How do these mechanisms interact within an access control matrix? Analyze their effectiveness in different organizational contexts and identify potential limitations.',0.8,1.1,'Hard','C4-MZMknrZTQMCcJDPmQXCD7g','Multiple Choice - Single','\"ACLs manage permissions based on objects, while CLs manage permissions based on subjects.\"','[\"ACLs manage permissions based on objects, while CLs manage permissions based on su